text: A coworker took me to lunch here; this was my first time visiting a Firehouse Subs restaurant. The restaurant was clean, and the servers were very friendly and attentive. My sandwich (meatball) was served promptly and was very fresh and hot. The wheat bread was awesome. They have one of the new pop machines that lets you pick from several dozen flavors. The variety of subs leans to the healthy side. They have only white and wheat bread. There is a slight bit of uniqueness to their subs, but mostly they are pretty standard (more like Subway than like Which Wich). I think the price for a medium sub and drink is a bit high: $9. A great place to eat for a change up on sandwiches.

categories: Food, Delis, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New)
text:
So they enticed me w/ a coupon for a free sub w/ drink purchase. Heard about how they steamed their meats so let's go ahead and try it.

Have to admit first impression wasn't great. When I walked back to the car I noticed there was water dripping from the bag! That must have come from the steaming of the meat. Luckily I caught it before I made a mess of myself.

I ordered the Firehouse Hero (Roast Beef/Turkey/Ham) which was one of the Specialty subs. There was a substantial amount of meat and the sub roll wasn't soggy like I expected to be. If you are hungry get a sub at Firehouse. I was feeling lethargic after finishing the sandwich.

Also interesting was the Coke Freestyle machine they used to serve soft drinks. You can choose from 100+ selections. I always get bored w/ the standard fountain drinks so the Freestyle machine worked great. Ended up getting a Diet Vanilla Root Beer.

Final Verdict: Steaming of the meats did bring out more flavor, and it didn't make a mess of the sub. And I might go back just to get a special soft drink.

text:
YUM! 


I was undecided between this place & penn station, but I decided to give them a try. As soon as I walked in the door I was greeted by the staff. I ordered the pull pork on King's Hawaiian bread. It had cheese pulled pork, cabbage, & was on a King's Hawaiian bun.  Honestly when I got it home I was hesitant b/c it didn't have any barbecue sauce. But I decided to try it as is. It was one of the best sandwiches I have eaten in a long time. It's very filling I couldn't eat the entire sandwich. 

My taste buds recommend you try fire house subs.

text: Just ordered from here this evening. The young blonde lady working there with a tattoo on her right arm was behind the register. As I walked up she completely ignored me after I say hello. I stand there waiting to order for a few minutes with no one asking me if was ready to order. She finally does, say No. 1 please. She proceeds to do nothing and I was very confused. A couple them walks in and she asks them what they would like. Dumbfounded at this point I ask what the deal is. Her response " oh I thought you weren't ready" I just told her No.1 less than a minute before. She is either really ignorant or just dumb. Sandwich was good but I won't be going to that location again.

categories: Food, Delis, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New)
text:
To lead off, for anyone originally from the East Coast, when you order an 'Italian Combo' you are not ordering a sandwich made from a combination of classic Italian deli meats.  You are ordering an Italian combo combo with fries and a drink.  Furthermore, you are ordering a sub - not a hero, a hoagie or a grinder.  All sandwiches seem to be modeled on the subway franchise, a derogatory form of sandwich, from which the term derives.  

Firehouse is a kitschy place.  Everything is themed out with menu items and additional offerings being related to firehouses, firefighters, fire or heat.  The collection of hot sauces for your use earns this place a star all on it's own.  That doesn't leave much for their sandwiches though.  

All I can say is my sandwich, which should have had a bit of spice, was somehow sweet.  It was also soggy, lacking meat, and made with the inferior bread that seems so popular in the area.  It's such a shame the sandwiches aren't worth eating, they made it easy to donate to a good cause.  At least if I want to make a donation I can go to the website and by pass the aftertaste.

text:
So my first time going in, I only went because I'd gotten a coupon for a free medium sub from work. I heard they were really good so I went in to try. 
Walking in the door I was surprised with how big it was inside and how friendly the staff was. There were three employees behind the counter and each one of them said "welcome to firehouse!" With a big smile as soon as I walked in. So that was nice. I told the girl at the counter that it was my first time there and she was super helpful. I ordered a Club on a Sub(bacon, turkey, etc) in the medium size. The sub alone with no drink or side was $6.29(but free for me because of my coupon). I sat down and waited probably five minutes when my name was called. The sandwich came with a pickle spear, and oh my goodness it was good. It was a delicious and good sized sandwich and service was prompt and friendly. I'll be back!

text:
I have eaten here twice in the past week. One experience was terrible, one was great. So it averages out to a decent review. Just be warned, your experience may vary.

The first time, my food was delivered and it was incorrect. I called the store and was informed my name would be put on a list for a free sub the next time I came in - a problem since I was traveling and didn't have a car at the time. I accepted their 'apology'.

I convinced my coworker to go the next night. We stopped in to get dinner, and I brought it up to the manager who was working. They said my name had NOT been written down, but were able to verify my info and proceeded to get me the replacement sub free of charge, and even made it a combo due to all of the hassle. That was a much better experience, though I don't like being basically lied to by the first manager - at least the second one made up for it.

text: Typically I love firehouse but this time the food was not worth the money spent! Ordered subs for our whole office and the lettuce was wilted, meat tasted like lettuce on sandwiches that had no lettuce, bread was soggy and everything was put together sloppy. Called to complain to manager and he really didn't care as he already gave us a free coupon due to food being ready 20 minutes late. Will never order food from here again, will drive to another firehouse for better food and hopefully management

text: Love the food here, but my experience at this location was very sub-par. I came in during the week at lunch. Service was extremely slow and there were several people waiting in front of me. I ordered my usual Hook and Ladder and sat down to wait for my lunch. 10 minutes...nothing. 15 minutes...still nothing and I notice people who came in after me have gotten their food. 20 minutes...okay so I need to say something. I went to the front and asked how much longer it would be for my meal -- and they looked at me like I was crazy. The person who took my order at the register acted like he didn't know what I was talking about. I took out my receipt and showed it to them. However it happened, my order got "lost." One of the staff members even commented that I had been waiting for awhile - ummm, you think? I appreciated that they made my sandwich in record time, but just was not impressed with the customer service here. Very slow for everyone all around, not good when you have a lot of people coming in for their lunch break.

When I ask for suggestions you can best believe they will explain each sandwich and tell you about any likes or even dislikes.  (No lies). Never had a bad meal yet. My only  is they don't have coupons. Lol. I love deals and feed quite a few people.

text:
Since I'm working "from home", I decided to "Uber Eats" an Engine Company speciality sub. Since this sandwich is no longer on the menu, but's it's the only sandwich I've ever eaten, for years, mind you, I decided to call prior to placing my Uber Eats order. 

When I called, I spoke with a very kind, informative and thorough employee named Manuela. She is awesome!

Manuela told me exactly what I needed to do to order the Engine Company speciality sub, which, for all intents and purposes, is technically on their "secret menu". 

Clearly, I'm super, duper (sometimes ridiculously) picky, so, naturally, I called after following Manuela's instructions "to a T". She answered, confirmed my order, and it's on its way. 

There's a first time for everything. I've never written a Yelp review based off phone service, alone. However, I am a Pranic Energy Healer, and the Queen of Manifestation. Given the former and latter, coupled with the awesome A-One service Manuela provided, I am confident that my 5-star rating will be exactly that! Actually, bc of Manuela's customer service, I'd go so far as to say that 1. She should DEF, if not already, be the manager/get a promotion. Period. So many people who are employed in the service industry are rude. They don't like their job(s), and it shows. Manuela has great energy, and was happy to help me. That's what matters most. Yes, we sign up for Firehouse bc of the way it tastes. However, personally, if I call and the employees are rude, it's a wrap. I'm good, and on to my next choice. 

Any who, excited to receive my "secret menu" sub!

text:
I have enjoyed Firehouse subs on three separate occasions now.  All three sandwiches were delicious.  What I like about Firehouse is the understandning that a 6" sub is too small and 12" is a bit much.  Sandwiches are available in an 8" or larger size.  A large assortment of sauces (BBQ and hot) are available to dress your sandwich.  

Please note Firehouse Subs was started by Firemen and staff may ask you to round up your bill to the nearest dollar to donate to their foundation. 

From the website: "The Firehouse Subs Public Safety Foundation is dedicated to improving the life-saving capabilities of first responders and public safety organizations in communities served by Firehouse Subs by providing funding, resources and support"

Also note this place has a Coca Cola Freestyle machine and you may wait in line for a bit while kids play with every flavor combination possible.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Sub's is a chain, so this location is much like every other store. Place your order at the counter, pay, and wait for your sandwich to be made and your name called out. While waiting you can grab a seat at a table and get your beverage, there is a Coca-Cola Freestyle machine here so can customize your soda to fit your personality. 

The food here is pretty good, a step up from Subway. The sandwiches are served on steamed bread. I usually prefer the Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket, its more than enough to fill even the biggest of appetites, if not you can always get a larger sandwich. Prices are reasonable, and service is usually pretty good. Good food, fast service, decent location, and plenty of seating make Firehouse Subs a great place for a quick bite to eat.

text:
I have not been here before.  Ordered the Firehouse Pub steak that was a limited sub.  When we got home and opened it, it looked like there was mass amounts of steak.  When you pick it up, its very light though.  The middle of the sandwich is actually filled with pub cheese, and they sprinkle the steak on top of that, then put the fried onions on.  Obviously disappointing.  The pub cheese was not melted, so it was this thick spread that was not appetizing.  It was also expensive, a medium was $6.99.
Might give it another try, if someone else is paying.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Nice surprise out in West County.  I was looking for something different and this had opened recently.  

It was a odd time of the day so I didn't expect a crowd.  There were a few folks in eating.  The place was bright and spotless.  I was greeted right away.  I asked the sandwich chef what to try in order to have a good first opinion.  I ordered a Smokehouse Beef and Cheddar Brisket.  Made it a combo with Sun Chips and a drink.

The drink machine was interesting.  Only one spot to get drinks and ice.  The touch screen allowed me to choose whatever flavors I wanted and how much of each.

The sandwich was brought out to my table rather quick.  And it was good.  I had to take smaller bites in order to make the sandwich last.  It wasn't as filling as a Subway or Quiznos but then again the bread wasn't the star of this sandwich - the cheese and brisket was.

When I was done and went in to store for my last refill and drop off my trash one of the employees reminded me that completing a survey would get me a free 32 oz drink next time.  Not a bad deal since (A) I had good things to say and (b) I knew I would be back.

text: The manager at this location, Shannon, is awesome. Her attention to detail and commitment to service is impressive. A lot of fast food places I go to have marginal service...she goes above and beyond! text:
Our family loves firehouse and this location keeps up their good reputation.
Anytime we don't know what we want for dinner, or are craving a warm sub, we come here.

They have health options and.. not so healthy options. They make their own pickle spears and they're delicious. They are famous for their meatball sub and it's easy to see why.
They also have a coke freestyle machine which is really great.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
This is a drive thru review. Ordering was painless, their menu was a little hard to see from passenger sides. The lane splits into two probably to prevent long lines but it bottlenecks at a weird spot so people got stuck in the single line anyway, since everyone here has trucks or SUVs.

It took them three minutes to take our payment. No one came to the window in that duration. Doesn't seem that long? Well it's a drive thru! People go through because they probably came for their lunch break and needed something quick. The minutes add up! Then after the payment it took them another 18 minutes to give us our sandwiches. We were the only one in the drive thru, by the time we got the three sandwiches we ordered, a whole line gathered behind us. From what I could see, there were plenty of staff but they didn't seem to be in any particular rush. They didn't even try to address the wait time. No apologies. Not to mention the person who handed us the bag still had the gloves they were wearing to presumably make sandwiches! The whole top half of the bag was covered in... I don't even know! I saw them hiring far before opening day. There's a bit of an expectation for them to be working harder for at least the first *week* of opening.

I was excited because not a lot of sandwich places have drive thrus but for a quick meal meal I should have stuck to Cane's. Pretty sure I could have ordered a sandwich at Subway and gotten it way faster. At least then I would have gotten what I paid for. Fast, inexpensive and mediocre at Subway vs slow, expensive and slightly better than lunch meat from a deli at Firehouse Subs. 

This might be a better place to enter in lobby to eat.

text:
They have GOOD sweet tea. (I'm from Georgia so it's sweet!) the sandwiches are fresh and full of flavor. Even the simplest sandwich will make you want to come back for more.
They are ALOT more expensive  than most subs shops but they are worth the price.
Soup, salad, chips, or cookie, or brownie as a side item.

I got the club and it was not soggy even with everything on it.
We came at lunch time so they were slammed. Not a single table to sit at so our order took almost 30 minutes to get.

MILITARY DISCOUNT available here. 10% is what I got.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
2nd time visiting this place. The first time was amazingly good, food was done well, tables clean, etc. 
This time, not so much. Arrived there right before lunch time (11:50am). About 6 people in line to order and 1 person taking orders. We kinda felt bad for him cuz he was really overwhelmed. Then he started snapping at people... "get it together" or "you should know what you want" or "everything is listed on the board, don't ask so many questions"... Hey, this oughta be fun! We placed our order and looked for a table. Customers had their order numbers on each table, leaving nowhere to sit. After counting heads, we realized they weren't cleaning or clearing tables. We cleaned up a 2 seat table and went to get our drinks. BOTH MACHINES WERE OUT OF ICE! We were told that they "hadn't had a chance to fill them this morning".
Received cold soup, a meatball sub. Meatballs were so over cooked that the texture had turned to mush. Oh yeah, you also owe me a pickle!
We'll be back to try again...

text:
Update 8/29/19:

Back again for my Dr. appointment.

I had already packed the hubby's chips in his lunch, with no sandwich! Told him I'd drop off a surprise.

Finished early at the Dr., so I went thru the drive thru with no cars in front of me!

I ordered two small steam rollers(?), and two chili's.

I was kidding when I asked if they were opening a shop in south Reno... but he said "yes we are"!!!!!

I had them bag the sandwich and chili into two separate bags and dropped off the hubby's lunch (curbside) to his office.

I get a call that it was the perfect lunch! Perfect not stringy or fatty meat!

The chili was good, but next time I'll skip the onions on top of the chili.

text: I am so happy that they opened a location in the Reno/Sparks area! Their sandwiches are DELICIOUS! Seriously. I'm also a big fan of their rewards apps. It's super easy and fast to get a free sandwich. I've gotten 3 free sandwiches in the course of 8 months with the average purchase of 3 sandwiches once a month. They not only give you a free sandwich option, you can choose to do double meat, a free drink, a free medium sandwich, a salad, a Large sandwich, and even rack up enough points for a free catering. Their prices are affordable and a medium sandwich is plenty of food to fill up a hungry adult. Every sandwich comes with a pickle spear.

text:
Been wanting to come here for quite some time. My son came here with a few of his school buddies and said that the sub sandwiches were really really good.

I went with the hero sub. It had roast beef ham and turkey on it. The sauce they used was a little on the Sweetside, almost like they used miracle whip instead of mayonnaise. It was quite tasty. The only thing I could say is for $13, wish it had more meat on it. $13 for sandwiches quite a bit. It tasted really good for sure. 

The service was definitely friendly. And I do like them having a drive-through for convenience. I would have to say it's probably one of the best subs around, just a little pricey.

I will come back, however it will probably take me finding a coupon for buy one get one free or 50% off or something.

text:
Pros: Clean, fresh, cute firehouse atmosphere, friendly staff, not busy.

Cons: Small portions, just average sub sandwich (nothing special), upper end of price scale, slow service, salad had too much toppings and very little lettuce.

I like that this company supports our local community, but their food was not good enough for me to go back again.

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
Perfect timing after seeing my physiatrist.

I miss going to Firehouse. 

It's been  two years since my last visit  (back in California)!

I parked off to the side, because I noticed there was a sign for a drive-thru. I noticed three or four cars pull up.

I couldn't remember what sandwich I liked, but took a chance and pulled up.

Luckily they have a very nice clear menu, and when I saw my sandwich "the steamer", I knew it was mine.

Perfect offering of sizes, so I just got the small, with chips and a medium drink. The medium was really big.

Service was a little slow, but hey it's lunch time and three cars ahead of me, so no problem. I can take more pics!

I'm not sure why, but I really like how they make their sandwiches! Perfect bread and not stringy corn beef/pastrami. 

Plus I don't mind rounding up my bill to help their organization.

I'll be back in three weeks for my next appointment and I will plan on stopping for lunch. 

I hope maybe in the future they open one up down in my area!

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
My husband and I LOVE Firehouse.

The locations a little goofy since the building used to be a bank so the parking situation is odd but that's not a problem.

The place is always clean and super bright. Fun decor throughout and the staff is always smiling and jolly. Never a long wait.

A special huge shout out to Nikki. When we were there today it was crazy busy and the soda machine went down. Nikki has to deal with two very rude customers while she ran around delivering food and her smile. I would have punched those rude customers but Nikki handled it very well. Kudos!

Now for the best part. The fooooood! Awesome sandwiches each and every time. You can get soup, chili or chips for the side instead of chips.

If you haven't tried Firehouse yet you need to. There are tons of sandwich places in this city and they are definitely in my top 10.

text:
Been waiting for them to open ever since the sign on the corner of Prater and McCarran came up. I have enjoyed the Carson City location a number of times during my lunch hour but living in Reno haven't had the opportunity until now. 

Came here with my brother for a dinner on a random weekday night. The place was for the most part empty and maybe had 6 other ppl sitting. I normally stick with the Meatball (sweet and spicy) or the BBQ Brisket but this time walking in I noticed that they had just released a new sandwich the Spicy Cajun Chicken and deuces to give that a chance while by brother stuck with the consistent Meatball. The service for how empty the place was wayyy to long (especially compared to The Carson location) but the Spicy Cajun Chicken made up for the wait and then some as it was absolutely delicious. I enjoyed my with a small amount of Datil Pepper hot sauce. Try it if you can handle a lil spice well worth the change. 

Will absolutely continue to come back.

text:
Big Firehouse Subs fan here. I have had Firehouse Subs in Carson in the past, but some how must have slipped my memory. We ordered online and I loved that you could select your time. I got the Meatball sub and it was so fantastic. The bread was perfect and not too soggy, the sauce had great flavor without being spicy, and the meatballs are some of the best I have ever had!! The sprinkle of Italian seasoning on the top of the cheese is a great touch. 

Our order was ready when we arrived with no issues! This was a great quick dinner on these crazy nights.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: Ok ate here a few times now, a couple deliveries and a couple pick up orders and as far as the sandwiches go, great job. They were made carefully so that they weren't falling apart and they didn't fall apart at any time so already that's good compared to some sandwich places. I've had a few different sandwiches and all of them tasted great. The only complaint I have with the food is with the pickle. Although the pickle tasted alright it didn't seem as fresh as it should have been. It comes wrapped up in a small plastic bag and it seems to me like they wrap a bunch of them up all at once and they are stored for a period of time individually wrapped. Not that big of a deal but it's the only complaint I could think of regarding the food. The delivery's were placed through Door Dash so I can't fault them in any way for the delivery time and as far as the pick up order situation goes, they were very professional and clean. They practiced 'social distancing' and required a mask while waiting for the food so that was a plus for me. All in all a great place for sandwiches especially if your hungry because their large is quite big. It could be slightly more inexpensive but it was worth the money. Would definitely recommend this place to anyone looking for a great big sandwich.

text: This was our first time trying their subs. Holy Cow they were AMAZING! I had the Brisket and Cheddar my honey had the Hero. The brisket was smokey and hot with melted cheddar and just the right amount of BBQ sauce. The bread is nice and soft and obviously fresh. The Hero was meaty, veggies were fresh and the onions were sweet. It was ridiculously good warm. My honey is the sandwich king in our family and has always sworn by Jersey Mike's. But today he has a new love. I wish we had taken pictures....next time. We can't wait to go back and try other sandwiches. Way to go FIREHOUSE SUBS!!!! See you soon!

text:
While I wouldn't normally write a review for a sub shop, Firehouse Subs is the exception to the rule. 

After our third visit, the consistent service and delicious food it was time for a review. The staff are super helpful, very upbeat and ready to help. We typically order ahead for take away, our subs are always ready and delicious. An added bonus is a portion of each the sales goes to support firefighters and first responders. 

These subs are above the normal sandwich shops and well worth a try.

text: WARNING!  WARNING!  STAY AWAY!!  I went to the drive-thru and sorry I did, because if I would have been in the restaurant and served this scrawny brisket sandwich, looking NOTHING like the sub in the photo, I certainly would have brought it to the manager's attention.  With such a rip-off, the best advice is stay away...there are certainly dozens of other sub places to choose from.

text:
The Turkey Bacon Ranch is probably one of the best sandwiches I have ever eaten. The ranch sauce was super creamy, the bread perfectly toasted and it was made with excellently portioned toppings. There wasn't too much or too little of anything. I ordered a small, but I definitely wish I would have ordered a larger one. 

However, the macaroni and cheese was some of the worse macaroni and cheese I have ever had in my life. It was watery and bland and I was super disappointed, taking one bite, and throwing it away. 

Overall, I would definitely come back, I've heard amazing things about the potato soup and I have dreams about that turkey bacon ranch sandwich. The drive through staff was quick and efficient and super friendly. I would just never order the Mac and cheese again and I highly suggest no one else does either.

I cannot say enough great things about Firehouse Subs.  I went in on Black Friday, needing two catering boxes for Saturday's UNR/UNLV game.  Joel was so accommodating - took the order and when I told him I needed to pick up the order at 8:30 a.m. (they don't open til 10) he said "not a problem - they will be ready for you". Everything was included and everyone loved the subs.  Thank you so much for great food - but even more for the great customer service.  We will be back!!!

text:
We discovered Firehouse in Carson a couple years ago, so we were excited to see them coming to Sparks. 

I was super impressed with how smoothly everything was operating within their first few days being open. Everyone was confidently operating as a well oiled machine. The first visit involved an overwhelming pressure to fill out the survey, which we heard from multiple people while we were eating. Aside from that pressure to evaluate when we just took a bite, the food was good and service was great.

Subsequent visits have been through drive through or ordered to-go, so the evaluation pressure may have dwindled since opening week.  The food is consistent and service is always friendly! I also love the freshness of their salads! 

Their prices are a little steep but they have a GREAT reward program that's easy to use, and all of their sandwiches are easily splitable. They will even split it for you!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: First of all, my hubby and I are former volunteer firefighters, so that was the motivation to try out their subs. They make donations to local fire departments and public safety for equipment. I chose the Firehouse Salad- trying to eat fewer carbs these days. WOW! it was huge! And the presentation was well done for a "fast food" restaurant. However, I felt it could have used olives or pickles or pepperoncini. As you can see from the before and after, I enjoyed it anyway lol. The balsamic dressing was good- not the best ever, but tasty. The hubs had the Steak and Cheese sub combo with chips and drink. It arrived piping hot and full of gooey goodness. They also have Firehouse chili, which I'd like to try on a future visit. Oh- the salad bowl was a paper composite, so that, along with the community donations gives it a solid 4.

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: I am thoroughly impressed by this business. Their sandwiches are good...it's hard to mess up a sandwich, but their customer service is outstanding. I wish more local chain restaurants would go in and see what I'm talking about. Their employees are always genuinely friendly, courteous, and seem to enjoy their jobs. I also love the business model this company has. They give back SO much to the community. It makes sense. Firefighters are always risking their own lives to save others...they're usually pretty good cooks since they eat at the firehouse when they're on shift. Why not make a sandwich shop? Check them out! You won't be disappointed, and if you are, you're mean.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
Always looking for a good sandwich and if there is any support for firefighters, we want to be able to help whenever we can.
I decided to create an online account and order through there.  I ordered two  sandwiches (see menu below).  I received a confirmation email that my order went through and that the payment was accepted.  However, when I arrived, my order was nowhere to be found.  The manager found that my card did not go through, which contradicted the email.  I used the same card and paid for the order (I could have typed it in wrong, but either the email or the manager made a mistake).  Within 7-10 minutes my order was brought out to me.
The sandwiches were filled with very fresh and tasty ingredients.  Our only complaint would be for the "limp" pickle spears that were on the side.   

Menu:
Pastrami, served Fully Involved with provolone on a toasted sub roll.
Fully Involved - Loaded complete with mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a kosher dill pickle on the side. Add black pepper, jalapeno and balsamic vinegar

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: There are a lot of choices to patronize. Jersey Mikes,Port of Subs, Yellow Submarine and others. I was anxious for this business to open. I took the time to fill out the rewards card. I received an email today that the receipt I submitted had a cut off image and would not be used.I don't cheat and the inference was that I was being devious. They go out of their way to build their business on the backs of first responders. More attention should be spent connecting with your customer base. Food was adequate and I probably would have been a customer down the road. Never again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: Have only had the privilege of enjoying a Firehouse sandwich twice. Once in Kern County California just off the Grapevine and the second time was this afternoon in Sparks, NV. Both times I had the large Firehouse Steak and Cheese. If there were only a location closer to my home, this would become my go to for sandwiches. Seriously....this sandwich is that good. The Sparks location was immaculate which was kind of surprising considering how busy it was and the fact the humans tend to be a sloppy species when eating food at a fast food place.  The staff was friendly, courteous, and fast without sacrificing quality. When you combine that with the fact that Firehouse was founded by retired firefighters and well know for their never relenting support for first responders, I can't think of a reason not to enjoy a Firehouse Sub when you  have a chance. Thank you for your service and the great food choices.

text:
Almost my favorite food on earth is the meatball sub. I had wanted to try a meatball sub since forever. I love meatballs so much! 

When my husband brought one home it was life changing. I am so thankful he chose firehouse subs as theirs comes with the most delicious cheese and herb combination it looked so good I immediately got so excited! Then I took a bite. The meatballs were so big and had the most amazing flavor and the melty cheese and herbs all combined into the best sandwich experience I have ever had! 

Please try the meatball sub as it's more then a sandwich it's just so good and the size was enough to fill me up but I still rejoiced sadly over my last bite since I knew my tummy experience was coming to an end. 

For my birthday everyone had whatever was catered and I specifically had someone get me a meatball sub! I have had about five or six and I would like a thousand more!

text:
I first found Firehouse subs when I was living in Vegas and it quickly became a favorite place to pick up a quick meal. The Turkey Bacon Ranch is to die for but I have had friends that have ordered other things and have never gotten a bad review of any of their sandwiches. I love the hot sauce bar (open in non-covid times) and the Firehouse BBQ sauce is so good I had to buy some for my house. 
This location especially is great. I don't know where they find their employees but every time I go in there, the MOST friendly people I have ever met are there to meet me and take my order. They are quick, friendly and aim to please- always. I would highly recommend Firehouse Subs to anyone looking for a great sandwich.

text: I've been wanting to try Firehouse Subs and wished I tried it sooner...the sandwich was excellent.  I had the medium size Hook and Ladder and asked for the mustard and mayonnaise on the side.  The turkey and ham was perfectly thinly sliced and had a great flavor to it.  I don't usually like ham since it tends to be salty but this ham had a sweet taste to it which I've never experienced before with ham.  There are plenty of tables to dine-in and it was very clean.  Packages of mustard and mayonnaise was available so I could use just the amount I needed.  My reason for the 4 stars is the price.  $10 for a sandwich is more than I would like to spend.

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
This place was pretty good! I dropped by here to pick up a free sub that I got for my birthday. Go sign up for their loyalty program - free medium sub! I have never been here before and was excited to hear it open since I've passed by it in Vegas.

I tried ordering online and mobile, but my order didn't go through, no biggie. I'll just order when I get there - it was the lunch rush, nooooo. I wouldn't recommend coming here during the lunch rush since it took around 20 minutes to get my sandwich from when I ordered. Most of the tables were taken too! Anyways, I got a medium Hook & Ladder on wheat.

While waiting I helped myself to their sauce selection, definitely try their Datil Pepper Sauce! It was sweet and slightly spicy, but not too much. It complimented my sub well~

I didn't get to eat it until I drove back to work, but the hot sub held up well on the ~20 minute drive back. I devoured my half of the medium and was pretty satisfied. Will definitely be back to try their current special of a $5.55 medium Spicy Cajun Chicken!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
I had high hopes for Firehouse Subs. The building looks cool and new; inside was bigger than I expected and quite clean. The cashier was very nice and I overheard her tell another customer that they don't take tips. Instead, all "tips" are donated to a charity, which is a nice touch. Lastly, my sandwich was neatly placed in a cardboard to-go box, which is so much better than a styrofoam. I wish every restaurant did this!
Alas, this is where my compliments end. 
They made so many mistakes on my sub that it's unforgivable and have permanently lost a customer. I would like to note that I ordered my sub during the lunch rush, so some of the mistakes are undertstable. 

Below are the list of mistakes Firehouse subs made, beginning with the worst: 

1. They forgot to include the steak in my "Steak & Cheese" sub!?!
Just let that sink in...
I didn't confirm this until I started to eat the second half for two reasons: (a) I was famished so I inhaled the first half. (b) The sandwich was filled with so so many veggies - pepperoncinis, bell peppers, mushrooms, olives, and onions - to the point where I could taste nothing else. It was even difficult to taste the cheese!
2. There were so many veggies the sandwich became too messy for comfort. I had to wash my hand after eating this. 
3. I asked for no mushrooms and lo & behold, there were mushrooms. 
4. I asked for my sub on white bread and... you guessed it (or looked at my photo)! My sub came with wheat bread. 

Individually these mistakes (except for #1) are forgivable, but all together I cannot be convinced to come back.

text: I was in the mood for something a bit different from our usual take-out food rotation. My husband and I had discussed getting Firehouse Subs the night before, but then our plans changed. I stopped by about 6:30pm on a Wednesday night after work. There was one car in the drive thru ahead of me, but I'm not sure how many people might have been inside. I don't feel I had to wait too long to order, but it did seem to take awhile for the person ahead of me to get their order. Maybe it was a large order? The gentleman working the drive thru was very friendly. It did take a little while to get my order as well. I ordered an Engineer (Smoked turkey breast, melted Swiss, and sauted mushrooms), a Firehouse Hero (USDA Choice roast beef, smoked turkey breast, Virginia honey ham, and melted provolone), a bowl of chili (our favorite!), and two large drinks. I did request no pickle spear, but they were served with the sandwiches anyway. My husband is not normally a pickle eater, but he enjoyed his spear. I normally love pickles, but thought it tasted a bit off. Maybe it was just me. Both my husband and I enjoyed our sandwiches (which can be ordered small, medium or large - we got the large). I could only finish half of my sandwich, but my husband ate all of his. The sandwiches were fresh, tasty, and satisfying. Definitely recommend Firehouse Subs for a change from the usual sub shops and highly recommend the chili!

The wait of 25 minutes in the drive thru for 4 cars was quite long but acceptable at this time. 

The gross thing was watching the worker that took my card wearing gloves turn around with the same gloves and help with the food prep. Touching the bread and unwrapped sandwiches. 

Not sanitary at all.  Protect the worker just not protecting the customers at all. 

Do better.

Unfortunately failing to meet clean sanitary food prep conditions doesn't allow for a second chance.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: We love Firehouse! We eat it at least once a week and it is usually amazing. They have a great rewards program where we often get a free sandwich. They even gave me a free sandwich on my birthday. Last night was not the case. I tried to order through the app and it would not work. I kept getting an error message so I called the store to order. After I got home and went to eat my sandwich there were no hot peppers (this had happened before), no Italian dressing, no balsamic, and a pickle spear on the side (I had said no pickle spear). My sandwich was basically dry. One of the things I love about Firehouse is the sandwiches literally drip with tasty deliciousness. I was disappointed. Doesn't mean we won't be back, but now I guess I'll have to check our sandwiches when I pick them up.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: I got the Engineer. Turkey, mushrooms, lettuce,  tomato and onion. I ordered the small and boy was it small. Even though the sandwich was tasty I feel for 6 bucks it was a poor value. 5.95 with tax but rounded up to donate. I admire the % that goes to firefighters but just can't justify the size/value for the price.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text:
My husband, daughter, and I decided to try here for lunch today. This was our first time coming to Firehouse Subs so we decided to order three different subs and share them so we could sample more of their menu. I ended up getting their special which was the medium cajun chicken sandwich my daughter decided on the medium meatball subs and my husband had the steak and mushroom sub. We also signed in on their app so we were able to get a free large drink with the purchase of a sub.
 The staff member was really helpful and told us what came on our sandwiches. The service was really quick and we were able to get our sandwiches delivered to our table in under 10 minutes. The Cajun chicken sub had really good spicy flavor with the Cajun seasoning and pepper jack cheese. The steak and mushroom was really good but the next time I get this sandwich I would like it a little more spicy and probably order it with pepper jack cheese. The meatball sub was cheesy, gooey, and delicious. For our drinks we decided to get there cherry limeade. We tried it both sparkling and original and we decided that we liked the sparkling better. Overall I would say my visit at Firehouse Subs will have me coming back for another time!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: It's hard to find the type of customer service anymore that I received today at Firehouse.  I called this morning to make a catering order and the were very busy and had to put me on hold.  As I was on hold I'm pretty sure my bad service cell phone dropped the call so I gave it a few and called back.  They were so happy to hear from me!! I came in about ten minutes later than I had scheduled to pick up and they weren't quite ready but it was no biggie.  To them though it was and they were amazing!!! They offered me chips and deserts and gave me ten percent off my order.  This was above and beyond in my opinion.  Extremely nice team and amazingly good sandwiches to boot!!!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'DogsAllowed': 'False'}
text: Before I ever tried Firehouse subs I thought I only liked Port of Subs for a sub sandwich.  But now since I've had Firehouse subs, I have a new favorite sub shop.  These subs are like nothing else, they come warmed and with the perfect amount of fixings on them. All subs come with a pickle and you can also add chips and a drink for a combo meal. The freshness of the meat, bread and cheeses is what makes these subs extra good. Average price for a medium sub is about $10. I especially like that this company gives discounts for all first responders.  I will continue to get my subs from Firehouse !

text:
Been wanting to try it for a long time and to be honest I was disappointed. I had a turkey sandwich with mushrooms melted Swiss. There's not a lot of meat and it really reminded me of just another Subway sandwich. How to mac and cheese fanatic I really wanted to try it. It was watery and taste like the Kraft mac and cheese out of the box. It wasn't bad but it wasn't great.
Just so so. On the other hand, the service was very good!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: Hands down favorite sub place around. The atmosphere is fun with the fire fighter theme- they totally roll with It from the table decor to the names of the subs. Who doesn't love a hot sub!? They are by far more unique than subway or jimmy johns or any other sub place. They don't have many bread options but the toppings and wide selection of hot sauces makes up for that- talk about flavor! I love the sub machine with the over 120 drink options but with only one machine it takes forever to get your drink.... But at least you can make it special! Every time I go here it's packed! The customer service is great, I love that they walk your meal to you, it's better than standing around or having a pager. They also do boxed lunches or catering which is always a great addition to any party.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: It's Firehouse. Always consistent throughout the chain. I like the subs here. My only complaint is with their ice tea. Its way too weak, always. This particular location also seems to be least enthusiastic about the  "Welcome to Firehouse" greeting , always but that's ok, gives hubby and I something to joke about when we eat here and we've been coming here since they opened.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
If I had only gotten the pastrami sandwich, I'd probably give them 2 stars.

If I had only gotten the chicken bacon ranch sandwich, I'd have given them 4 stars. 

But I've had both, so 3 stars seemed right.

The pastrami is not to be ordered here, it's just not good quality pastrami, period. Rubbery and fatty are words that come to mind.

However, the chicken bacon ranch sandwich was excellent. The sauce and the cheese made it, and, of course, it had the bacon in it.

If you've never eaten here before, prepare to possibly be yelled at when entering the store. They're shouters here, like at Moe's, and usually belt out a big welcome (entire staff) every time the door opens. It's startling enough when you walk in, but then picture eating in the store while the staff is screaming every 3 minutes.

text: My daughter had the beef and cheddar brisket and I got the NY brisket. The cheddar brisket taste just like a bbq sandwich nothing special about it and my NY brisket felt like ham w/ melted cheese sandwich. I gotta say though the bread is really soft. The services was good can't complain. Would I go there again meh, I mean I would choose them over subway but if I'm on a budget, subway lol.

text: This particular firehouse has taken at least 15 minutes every single time I have gone. The past three times I went they messed up my sandwich and instead of making a new one, just scraped off what they messed up. Would not recommend.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
Very clean and well decorated firehouse theme upon entering. It wasn't busy at all so the service was incredibly fast. It definitely has a Subway feel to the ordering process, but what sub shop doesn't right? They had a lot of different chips to choose from and I LOVE the customizable coca cola machine they had there. There's so many different combinations and flavors you could make - I usually never ever drink soda but I couldn't resist because it was so awesome. 

The food came out pretty fast and the staff was very polite. I wish they had more bread choices than white or wheat but the white bread was nice and crispy from being heated but still soft on the inside - my favorite. The sandwich was a good size, longer than a 6 inch but smaller than a footlong - however you could go bigger if you wanted. 

Overall, the sub shop chain had a really nice feel to it and with speedy services and delicious sandwiches, who wouldn't enjoy it :)

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: I am from Maryland. We have great sub shops there. Firehouse is not that but it's better than any chain store sub I've ever had. I love the hot italian, can't get enough of it. The crew is great at the Brandon location. I waited too long to try this place. They blow all the others out of the water. They will make gluten free bowls if is needed.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
My three stars are for the food. Definitely not the customer service. This firehouse is next door to a burger place that I've been wanting to try, but my fianc wanted a sub, so we decided to come here. 

When we first arrived, I told the girl I hadn't been to a firehouse before and I needed a few minutes to look. There weren't any other customers trying to order, so I expected at least a smile or something- but she just rudely turned around like I was a bother. Then I told my fianc that I'm going to try to steak and cheese. Anyways a polite guy behind the counter overheard and started making my sub. The girl was like "no- you order here" um hey. You work at Firehouse in customer service. Act like it. 

Anyways, the entire ordering process was painful. The food arrived, and the pain of dealing with Ms Attitude disappeared when I tried my sandwich. That was a good damn sandwich! The brownie was fine, nothing to write home about. 

I'll give them another shot at some point, but I would have a talk with my employees about how to treat customers. There are plenty of places to eat in Brandon, I won't go out of my way for poor customer service.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: Always delicious, hot, fast, and easy to order. In the Subosphere its one of my favorites. Cons would be limited choices for sure, but that's what makes it easy order and fast movement (as opposed to subway where it takes 10 minutes to order and make a sub it seems). Good choice for picking up multiple subs so you don't have to bring a 10 page document to get a group of subs. Also love the fresh and hot choices, and large portions of meat you get with your sub (not just paying for bread and veggies and a little meat like some sub shops). Always a good lunch stop when in the area.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
OK I'll give them the fact that they have decent subs and they have a cool drink machine but i don't get the hype..

First off the bread is horrible, and the sauce that they put on everything is not good. but the sandwiches do have a good amount of meats and are tasty in that respect. they toast the bread which I like sometimes, i just think the bread could be alot better.

And maybe its just me but i find it annoying when i walk into a place of business and every single employee turns to you and yells "welcome to Firehouse" then when you leave they all have to yell goodbye. I understand being friendly but come on, the only thing worse is when you go to eat and the waiter or waitress sits at your table to take your order.

it is overall a good shop but there are better choices out there. (Jimmy John's, Jersey Mike's, or even Lenny's)

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: Came by to use by bonus points for free large sandwich. The guy at the register said I had to make drink purchase to use. No I have used before so I put in my phone number and it rang up free. He did not apologize. Waited about 5 minutes for my turkey and bacon. The guy who made it handed it to me upright. The sandwich is served in a styrofoam package so serving upright everything slides. The sandwich was good but they need work on customer service.

text:
I've been here a handful of times and the service is pretty consistent. The sandwiches are really good (better than subway, not as good as publix) and they have a Coca-Cola freestyle machine. 

The staff is hit or miss, but I've gotten more friendly service than unfriendly.

name: Firehouse Subs

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: This location is disgusting!! I should have listened to the previous reviews. Once we walked in we were greeted by a homeless man sleeping at one of the dining tables next to the door with his pants to his thighs. Yes, you read that correctly. He had his naked butt on the chair that customers sit on. Highly doubt that chair was cleaned once he woke from his nap and left. So I suggest not siting at the table by the window. Actually I suggest not eating here at all if I'm being completely honest. Anyways, I got my drink at the poorly lit drink station. There were no straws and I made a comment how there were no straws as a worker walked by but they didn't care. Whatever just get me out of here. Also, the firehouse sauce was empty which really disappointed me as I like to put it on my sandwich. I took my food to go because I couldn't be there any longer. When I got home I noticed that I did not get extra pickles after I asked for it. Worst of all, the sandwich was hard as a rock! Was this bread from 2018??? It was stale bread on a dry sandwich. Thank god I have my sparkling cherry limeade to help me get down this dry old sandwich right? NO! As I take a sip of my drink it's all syrup!! How do you mess up a sandwich and cherry limeade!?? Lord!! I am never coming back to this location ever again! Do yourself a favor and go to a different location. The one on Bloomingdale is decent.

attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text: I absolutely love Firehouse Subs, one of my favorite sub places to eat at! I went here for lunch and the food was great, sandwich was delicious, pretty good selection of chips, and a great selection of drinks, and the workers were polite. It was slightly pricy but nothing way over the top. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
I have seen Firehouse Subs around for a few years and always wanted to try them out. I love subs. Jimmy Johns, Jersey Mike's (NOT SUBWAY)... all decent.
Today the timing was right. I was going to stop, grab a sub to take home and watch some football.
I drove the ten minutes home and... they had put so much mayo, wet lettuce and vinegar on the sub the bottom slice of bread was completely soaked through. I couldn't even pick it up out of the box.
The service wasn't great either. They person taking my order simply assumed i wanted EVERYTHING on it and never asked me what I wanted on it. I luckily asked if I had to tell the sandwich makers what I wanted on it like at Jersey Mike's... that's when he told me no, I had to tell him (I had already paid by this time).
Wouldn't you simply point to all the toppings and confirm "Hey is everything here ok on your sub?" Maybe that's just me tho.
But yah, ruined my afternoon and I probably will not go back to any Firehouse Subs as there are so many other, better, non-soaked options out there.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
I love Firehouse. Let's be honest, turkey sandwiches are my 2nd favorite food, and as long as the meat is not nasty quality (I'm looking at you, Subway), I'm game. Quizno's, Which Wich, and Firehouse rank in my top 3, not in any particular order. Around here, we have more Firehouse than the rest, so I get to indulge often. 

Pros: steaming hot, super fresh. The turkey is smoked, which is usually not my fave but I love it here. They donate a portion of sales to local fire/police/EMS (for example, over $2.5 million to Florida first responders and public safety in April of 2015). I think they also give a discount to uniformed public safety workers (although most places do).  You can call ahead or order by app to save time. There is a wide assortment of hot sauces (like 50+) to use. Also salads, chips, cookies, and a Coke Freestyle machine. Generally friendly service. Never a mistake on my order.

Cons: And these honestly only pertain to this location. Every time I come in here, the place is a mess. Dirty floors, tables, and counters. The Coke machine seems to be perpetually out of whatever I have a taste for that day. Price is a tad high for serving size. And SLOW. I realize that some of this is the nature of the beast - they don't drop the meat for your sandwich into the steamer until you order it - but I have waited over 15 minutes for a sandwich here at lunch time. Firemen ain't got no time for that! 

I have not experienced the same degree of slowness at my other 2 regular locations in North Lakeland and West Bradenton. This store, however, is always pretty busy and they always seem shorthanded, so that may account for things.

But always yummy. I put up with the wait.
