name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
Came in at 3pm and over half the chairs in the dining room were up on the table.  Assuming so they didn't have to clean this area?  Not a great first impression. Almost walked out bc we thought they were closing.  They wouldn't heat up the cookie we ordered (every other firehouse does so regularly).  They were out of medium cups for our combo but they were happy to give us a small instead at the same price as a medium.  Ice machine didn't have ice in it and wasn't refilled at any time during our visit.  The sandwiches took 23 minutes to come out. Did I mention that there were only two customers who ordered before us and six total customers (including us) in the restaurant?  

Our family are firehouse fans overall, we'll just have to steer clear of this one.

I'm not impressed. A simple takeout order with two sandwiches took almost 15 minutes to make. 

The drink selection at the soda fountain was extensive and good. 

Since when do sandwich preparers not wear a hat? That alone earned one star. 

Also, no American cheese? Really? I'm sure I'm in the minority when I say that, but c'mon.

Late add: I wanted only the cheese on my ham sandwich. She kept saying a plain ham. I told her FOUR times I wanted only ham and cheese. I got only ham. 

Incompetent.

text: I have finally concluded that ordering over the internet is slower that ordering in the store. attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'"}
text:
There's cold subs, there's fast subs and there's hot subs. When you want a hot sandwich, Firehouse  is the place. The Bbq cheddar brisket is already amazing. The service  is always fast and friendly at this location. The sweet tea here is A+ as well. 

For me they miss the last star for just a few reason. 1- a little dirty sometimes. 2- a little expensive IMO. 3- I absolutely hate the gimmick of having the entire crew yell "welcome to firehouse" when I walk in the door! This does not constitute good service to me. How about you train the staff to be friendly and nice instead of yelling me at me. 1 I know where I am and 2 being yelled at doesn't make me feel welcome.

text:
If I could give less than 1 star I would. I dislike leaving bad reviews but this was horrible customer service and food. We always love firehouse but the crew you've got working in there today on 8/2/20 is about as incompetent as any I've seen. We ordered 2 sandwiches at 3:12 according to our receipt and specifically asked for no cheese. It took 45 minutes to get our sandwiches!!! And they both had melted cheese. No one started making the sandwiches for about 35 minutes. The employees were standing in the back doing anything but working. Then when we took them back they offered to make new sandwiches but we ran out of time so she gave us a tiny slip of paper, not our receipt and told us to call in 25 hours if we didn't get a refund   

The air conditioning was out so I understand things happen but there was no one else in the store and they seemed more concerned with not working than working. We'll see if our money gets refunded or I'll be calling tomorrow. This used to be a good store, don't know what happened.

text:
Yes, I know it is unorthodox to give a "lowly" sandwich shop five whole stars, but I feel the staff here deserves it. I can't remember when I have received friendlier service. 

All three employees working greeted everyone as they came in the door. With genuine smiles, no less. They remained courteous through the entire visit. 

I tried three different sandwiches; the smokehouse brisket, the turkey cranberry and the Italian. All were delicious and filling. 

I have been to many a casual sandwich shop, and I have to say that for now, Firehouse is my favorite.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': 'None', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
First time here last year, I ordered a sub to go.  Worst decision ever.  The bread was soggy and the sandwich was just horrible.  I vowed never to go here again.  Fast forward to yesterday, I went again.  Order a sub to eat in the store.  Perfection!

I was greeted immediately when I walked in, the cashier was ready for me to place my order right away, I didn't feel pressured to "super size" my sub or to add the combo.  The sandwiches can be ordered fully loaded with lettuce, tomato, mayo, mustard... or you can pick and choose what toppings to add.  The sub was then steamed and served directly to my table with perfectly melted cheese.  If you opt for the drink, there is one of those newer Coca-Cola machines that allows you to pick and choose any drink/syrup combination known to man.

While I was eating, a lady stopped in to place a large order for pick up this weekend.  The manager was super polite and explained the options in detail.  She was even able to customize the order by having the lettuce on the side instead of the sandwiches being prepared with the lettuce on them.  Mustard and mayo packets come on the side.

Moral of the story: don't order the hot sub to go, eat in the store.

text: These guys deserve a raise! Fast, efficient, and friendly service. The gentlemen delivered our food and another gentlemen took the trays away while we were chatting at the table. The New York Steamer is by far the best sub I have ever had. Very succulent corn beef brisket with a fantastic mayo and mustard. A medium sub runs $6 but is in a whole separate league from Subway and significantly worth the little bit of extra cost. Don't forget your $2 pickle bucket. These are cheaper than any hardware store bucket and come with the lid. This place is top notch and very clean. Will recommend whenever I can.

text:
Solid joint. First of all the restaurant is very clean and orderly. The drink station was clean, that's one of my pet peeves and I was pleasantly surprised. 
I ordered the medium sized spicy meatball sub with a drink and oatmeal raisin cookie. 
The meatballs were large and moist and nicely seasoned. They were mildly spicy in my opinion, but I like it hot so my viewpoint might be biased. 
Anyway, I can't wait to try more of the menu. 
Did I mention the subs come with a pickle spear?! Well done Firehouse, well done.

text:

I was a bit disappointed that there wasn't a big grand opening, or even a soft opening. 

Having to find out they had been open for three weeks prior, I am  still happy they are situated close to me.

It's clean and spacious, even without a drive-thru.

I liked the soda machine, and able to get caffeine free drinks.

Can't wait to try it!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: My new favorite sub place!! They put so much meat in each sandwich! And they're served warm. Service was great both times I have been and so was the food! Affordable and delicious!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
So I'm VERY picky with my sandwiches. Several other places in town have disappointed me. 

I only got one sub so far, but i got the Italian and it was DELICIOUS. I got whatever it normally comes with (except mustard), got it toasted and it was perfection. Best Italian in town; and my favorite sandwich spot so far.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: They are great here. Friendly and helpful. The sandwiches were just as ordered, perfect

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I think the first and last time I had a firehouse sub was somewhere circa 2005 on the east coast. So it has been a while! I was in the mood for a good sandwich and being gluten free, my options are limited. After a quick yelp search, I learned of this new location and their gluten free bread options. Sold! Not 15 mins later, I was in the store placing my order. I like firehouse because they serve their sandwiches warmed with melted cheese and they have a great array of toppings to choose from. I went with the GF medium club and it did not disappoint. I added hot peppers, cherry peppers, peperocinis, and pickles to spice it up. The sandwich was about $9, gluten free bread +$2 (a little steep, but whatever), and add a combo with chips and drink +$3.50, all amounted to about $15 for lunch. It was definitely on the pricier end of lunch options but it hit the spot. The store was large and clean with plenty of employees working to move people through fast at the lunch hour. Nice addition to south Reno!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I love this place! They are so friendly and make some of the best sandwiches in town.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Just ordered for the first time today after hearing about you guys some time ago. We can't say enough good things!!! Your food SMELLED delicious before it even came out of the bag! Everyone was more than happy and satisfied with their sandwiches.  Thank you! This family will be back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This is a good sandwich shop. I went in around 12:30. They had several people making sandwiches. The line moved quickly. The sandwiches came out fast. I tried a sandwich that was being featured on a poster. It had cream cheese, a sweet mustard and several types of meat. 
I don't love the shredded lettuce approach to sandwiches. It always seems like more of it ends up on the floor than in the sandwich. 
But the ingredients are fresh and high quality. I'm not sure this would be my first choice of sandwich shops, but it's worth a visit.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Great sandwiches! Oh and you can't forget to get a cookie, sooooo good. Glad there is a location in Reno now.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: After returning to this Firehouse location several more times since my first review I'm happy to give them another five stars. They have been great every time. This last trip there we ordered and ate in the restaurant and it was even better. Hot and fresh and perfect. The staff is really friendly and helpful as always. I'd give them more stars if I could.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I just had the best sandwich in South Reno! Turkey ranch bacon club on wheat was BOMB!  Thanks Joel for doing a great job!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This review pertains to the new store at Damonte Ranch.  I understand new restaurant growing pains and right now your pains are evident.  I ordered yesterday, and made two special request, light mayo and to put the chopped pickle on the side, what I received instead is a sandwich with chopped pickle on the sandwich, no dill spear and a thick coating of mayonnaise.  My spouse asked for extra tomatoes and he has a picture show 3/4 slice of tomato on his sandwich, what part of this fulfills the request of extra tomato?

The bread was tough, obviously you need to have your sub prepared as hot so they steam the bun otherwise it is not that good.  I ordered the sandwich cold purposely  as I do not like the soggy condition of a steamed sub.  

By the way there is no way to let Corporate know how disappointed with the product as the Reno store is not listed, so really this is the only way to let you know that the sub was "MEH" and you have a long way to go.  In a town that has good alternatives, I urge your staff to PAY ATTENTION to the order and make it right or risk future patronage.  My visit was at 6:15 PM on Wednesday, May 20, 2020.  The store was empty and hardly busy so your staff cannot claim they were "rushed" to make my order.  I plan to order again,  everyplace can have a bad day, but when you are new in Reno and you want to make a good impression, the impression you left was MEH!  

On the corporate side, your app is poor and buggy, we tried to order this past Saturday and I could,  but my spouse who actually likes you and has had the app for awhile could not, so there was a lost business opportunity.  I lost my first user reward for signing up as well because I was not going to a place where I could order but my spouse could not.  These are easy errors to fix why did you make it so difficult?  Maybe it was warning sign to expect disappointment.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I normally love Firehouse Subs but I don't know what's the deal with this location. Last time I ordered from here, both my breads were soaked. It was not appetizing at all. The first time was awesome but this time it wasn't so I'll just with in the middle of the road rating until next time. Oh by the way, hot subs is the only way to go here.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I would highly recommend this place I have lived here in Reno (67) years, and have eaten at most of the sub shops here, no doubt in my opinion this Firehouse Is the BEST ONE,

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Was very satisfying! Had the italian, good sized, great bread, fresh toppings and all melted
together. I love it when you eat a sandwich and your mouth waters while you eat it. They have a freestyle soda machine, lots of choices. Friend had the cheesesteak and was not left wanting or hungry. Plus, part of the proceeds support our Fire Fighters!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The sandwiches are amazing especially the Cajun Chicken but the service is spectacular. There's a young man there that's so nice, caring, and very considerate. Just wanted to do a shout out .

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I had this sandwich bought for me, and thats why i am rating it a 3. It was just ok. I dont even know if its a good deal for the price, as i dont know the price. I am glad i tried them, been wanting to! I received the roast beef sandwich box, which included a sandwich (lettuce, onion and tomato), a bag of BBQ chips, a pickle spear, a packet of mayonnaise, a packet of deli mustard, and a giant chocolate chip cookie. The sub: alot of bread to meat ratio, however, everything was fresh and tasted decent. Nothing special really, but im a huge fan of Jimmy Johns and Pub N Sub. The chips were great, crunchy and delicious. I forgot what brand they were, but i took a pic of the entire lunch box. Pickle spear was fresh and seedless? A little strange. The packets of mayo and mustard added flavor to an otherwise dry sandwich. I bet the sandwiches would have been better with vinegar, oil and spices, more meat too, but that wasnt the option we had. The best part was the cookie! It was quite large, and great! Great texture and crunch and the chips were fresh!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The subs here are freakin delicious. I can't believe I ever ate at a different sub shop with this place in my neighborhood. Never again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Varied menu. I like the option of getting double meat. It's nice to have a sub sandwich at least warmed, although they're cold if we take them home to eat.

A couple of annoyances: We always tell them we don't want pickle spears with our sandwiches, and we always get them. The other is being asked if we want to donate to their fund. Who knows if it's legit?

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
What a great experience! 
I was a first time customer and stopped in because I saw they offer a gluten free sub. I have celiac, and it's VERY hard for me to find a good sandwich, let alone a sub! The experience didn't disappoint. The staff was knowledgeable, helpful and went the extra mile to make sure my food remained gluten free and safe for me to consume. Quality service, excellent sub!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Just did an online order from the Damonte ranch store. I didn't even know they had opened but glad they did. Their website sucks but their app actually works well. Got two sandwiches and they were both great. On the cart waiting for me just inside the doorway. Hot and ready to go. Keep up the good work guys. I'll definitely be a regular.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:

It's so convenient, less than two miles from my house, and another two miles to drop off at his office... actually we are dining in the car today.

To my surprise, they took off one of the small sandwiches, because of my frequent buying (using my points).

Place online, walk in the store, and pick up on the right side  Rapid Rescue!

We are already regulars and it only opened a couple of months ago.

My husband has his favorite here but the only thing I ever order is the meatball sub; it is outstanding! 

The meatballs are super tender and not dense like most meatball subs. The Mariana sauce is better than some Italian restaurants I've been to!

As a bonus, a percentage of all their profits go to support your local fire departments

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text: I have to admit that I truly love this place! I'm not a huge sandwich fan to begin with, but I love that Firehouse always has warm deli meat on a lightly toasted French bread. The condiments and vegetables are nice and crisp, but the meat is always warm and juicy. The bread holds up perfectly but it's not overly crusty and it's only served with a pickle spear that just hits the spot. They also give back to our local community by providing millions of dollars in donations annually to our local fire houses. What a great way to have lunch and put back into the community.

I've gotta not ordered food from here twice.
1st visit:
Ordered a Steak n Cheese add mushroom. The only thing that was on it was steak, cheese and mushroom. No onion or peppers. 

2nd visit:
Ordered Steak n Cheese, Meatball, Salad and chicken & Dumplings.
Sandwiches were good
Soup was literally just broth. Not even exaggerating. It was the end of the day so maybe I got the last bit but it was terrible. 
Salad I ordered with the intentions of taking it to lunch the next day - lettuce was bad by the next morning. I ordered it at 8pm the previous evening so it's not like it was that old. The lettuce should of not gone bad overnight.

text: This is a newly opened sandwich shop and we decided to give it a try.  So glad we did!  The decor is like a firehouse and the tables are red with a Dalmatian white with black spots top!  So cute!  Everyone was very friendly.  We went at an odd time so there wasn't a line.  I love how you can get a small, medium or large sub.  I'm not a big eater so the small is perfect for me.  Hubby got the medium size; you can compare them in my photos.  Hubby got the hero and I got the turkey bacon ranch. They have the usual chips and pickle.  What makes these subs outstanding is they come warm with a toasted bun so the cheese is melted!  Yummy!  The price is very reasonable too.  Great sub sandwich and fast, friendly service, what's not to love?!  We'll be back and I highly suggest you give them a try! One of the best subs I've had in a long time!

text: I have eaten here twice and I don't think I will be back. The subs are no better or worse than any other sub place. The wait is unacceptably long. text:
I ate at one of these near Tucson, AZ a couple of weeks ago and feel in love. I had a Corned Beef on honey wheat! Wow was it good. The day I flew back to Indy, I took my wife to the location in front of Wal Mart on Emerson near I-465.

She loved it too! It isn't that expensive and really, really good. The meat is hot and the bread is fresh. This is a great change of pace to Subway and so much better! 

Plus, they have this super cook coke machine that mixes you soft drink anyway you want it. Almost takes a week long course to figure out how to operate it. 

Wonderful for quick lunches or supper with one or a dozen!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Went with my husband for lunch today- he's been dying to try this place after hearing their radio ads! He had the beef brisket & cheddar and I had the Italian. Two options for bread, white or wheat, and two options for sizes - 8 inch or 12 inch. My husband had the 12 inch and said if he did it again, he'd get double meat on the 8 inch - the meat was great, there just wasn't enough for him. I had a taste- very tender & flavorful! I liked mine, I kept it with the same toppings that come on it but said no to the spicy mustard - I figured Italian dressing & mayo was enough. My mistake. It was little too sweet for my liking so I went to get the banana peppers to add to it after I took a couple bites. That did the trick. 

Two things I liked: you get a pickle with every sandwich and they have one of the fancy "Freestyle" computerized coke machines. I've never used one before and it was kind of fun! You can add a flavor to any kind of drink, so you can have Strawberry Sprite Zero for example. Or Cherry Vanilla Coke Zero. I would definitely return for the drinks, I loved the strawberry lemonade! 

The only negative for us was the chip selection. They had Sunships, some Lays and Mrs Vickers but no BBQ flavored chips for my husband and no salt & vinegar chips for me. :( But we were full without chips so not that big of a deal I guess... I will just go to Jimmy John's when I need delicious chips to go with my sandwich! :)

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This was my first visit and I'm glad I finally made it over here.  I ordered the spicy meatball sub and it came with a drink and potato chips. 

I didn't think the sub would actually be spicy as most sub sandwich shops advertise spicy, but just don't deliver.  Well, this spicy meatball sub certainly delivered the tangy taste and I really enjoyed it.  If you want extra heat, the restaurant offers several bottles of hot sauce from mild to oh my god, that is burning my tongue hot.  I'm looking forward to trying some of those sauces on future visits.  

The service was okay and I agree with earlier posts that it could be better.  It seemed as if we were bothering the staff by ordering food.

text: This could be my favorite sub place in Indy. They usually fix the subs in a quick manner. The employees are always courteous and polite. Its a clean atmosphere. Only complaint? The restroom sink water pressure is weak. Great place to eat and fair prices.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
My parents suggested that we try Beech Grove's newest sub shop.  Firehouse Subs has great selection of hot, submarine style sandwiches featuring an array of meats, cheese, and condiments.  They have combos available with your choice of chip flavors and a freestyle coke machine (I suggest vanilla-cherry Dr. Pepper).

The place is very clean with a great firehouse theme and the staff is exceptionally friendly.  If you're looking for a quick, tasty meal, then look no further.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Hand down best sub shop.  Fresh meats and bread and a long line of hot sauces.  Being a first responder myself I like the fact that they donate part of their profits to various first responders organizations.  The best sub in my book is the Hook N Ladder.  The inside of each location is decorated like a fire house and there is memorabilia to the local fire department that is in the area of the shop.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The food is really good but the employees are not. I came in last night and tried to pay $30 cash for my order and the rest ($2 and some change) on my card. The cashier messed it up and put $60 in the computer instead of $30. 2 other employees were trying to help and it took forever for the 3 of them to figure out how to refund and re ring the order. Finally 1 employee tried to refund me $29 instead of $30. At that point I was feeling very uncomfortable and I was really  wanting to just get my $30 and get out of there but they got it figured out eventually. As I waited for the food it looked like other people were having issues too at the register. I don't think I'll be going back to that location again though. Seems like no one knows what's going on.

text:
We are from out of town here and arrived at our hotel late, yelped places nearby to eat and the Firehouse Subs popped up. We checked their web site and decided to give it a try. 
The service was very nice and courteous, very rear to find at other places. They accommodated me with a smile, literally a couple minutes before the closing time. Thank you! Ordered a classic tuna and brisket subs for our family and everyone lived it. Really tasty, beautifully packaged, priced right and with a warm service. Overall a great deal!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I wasn't really impressed. My mom loves it, but it's nothing to go crazy about. The first time I got a vegetarian. It was good. My sister got chicken. She said it was only okay. The second time and probably one of the last I got the vegetarian again. It was soggy and mediocre. The second time my sister order a chicken again but they didn't have any so she got turkey. She ordered  it with no mayonnaise and cheese, but they gave her everything on it.  My mom got a steak and cheese and she enjoyed it. She always keeps asking us if we want to go back, but we prefer not to.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text:
The review is for the restaurant not the food. The food is amazing and the quality is great. The restaurant is ok as far as cleanliness but it's COLD! OMG, it's soooo cold in here I'm shaking! It's always like this and if you are cold natured get take out! I am going to bring a thermometer next time but guessing 58ish in here. The soap dispenser in the restroom doesn't work unless you work for it, hope the employees have another place to wash hands......... Second time I've been here that the soap has been sketchy.
Had the chicken with verde sauce, it was terrific. Again, eat here, bring a parka! Would be four stars if it were comfortable in here but trying to eat with teeth chattering sucks!

text: My first visit to Firehouse was terrific.  I samples four different subs and each one was excellent. I was impressed at the high quality meats and cheeses. The staff was super friendly and really catered to my children, which was nice. I will be going back for sure.

text: I love Firehouse, but I have always had issues at this location. Today was no different. Twenty five minutes to get my food. Sandwich bread wasn't toasted. Tea containers were empty. When employees have down times they do not clean or check on drink machines, containers, etc. Tables were dirty. It is worth the drive to go to the Dunedin location where service is important, and I've always had a great meal and experience.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text:
The way they "steam" (or whatever) their sandwiches sets this chain apart IMO. I don't eat here frequently, but when I want a really dope sandwich, I choose Firehouse. The meat, cheese and bread are always fresh. It's not overloaded with veggies. The sauces are great.

Far superior to the other fast casual chains, Subway, Quizno's, Jersey Mike's, Jimmy John's, etc. Not that these places are bad, but if I'm going for a sandwich, I'm going to Firehouse. The Italian and the club are my two favorites.

text: I love this place.  At least once a week i come here for an Italian.    The food is still amazing. Staff still friendly. text: Usually have pretty decent service here but today was lacking. After 15 mins of placing my order the staff were having a debate over my order and who was suppose to make it, then blaming each other. It took 18 mins to get my sub which only left me 12 mins to eat ajd get back to work when there were only 6 people in front of me. Quality was on par with what I come to expect. Wait time was the only issue.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text: Firehouse sub is a cross between Potbelly's and subway sandwiches in my book. You know they have a great idea going for themselves with a firehouse theme with naming their sandwiches like " engineer" that comes with mushrooms and swiss cheese, with hardly any actual mushrooms. I had the Italian and the kid's shared a large Firehouse meatball sub. The kids loved their meatball sub sandwich, I liked the Italian but I didn't love it takes too much like  a wreck sandwich from Potbellies. My husband late his engineer but for someone who loves mushrooms he didn't get much of it. Would I return to firehouse for sub sandwiches I would but with reservations on trying something different possibly asking them to not heat up my sandwich. Possibly, but this is their MO so I might have to go with it. They aren't cheap but they aren't incredibly expensive for a fast food sub place. Just be aware it's a nicer franchise chain sub shop. It's a level up from Jimmy John's and Subways.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text:
I absolutely love the food that firehouse has, I've had issues at a previous Firehouse because it would take 30 minutes to order my food and I would have no time to eat before returning to work. 

 This location on the other hand is close to my parents house and is what they requested for dinner. I got a total of 4 sandwiches and 2 of them had the toppings switched with the meats which is unfortunate because my mother's sandwich was one that was affected and she cannot eat Mayonnaise.

 This truly saddens me. Can the staff not read? I literally had no time restrictions and thought this was going to be a good visit. I really suppose this chain restaurant is not for me.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text:
I had originally ordered the tuna sub but when the girl went to check the container holding the tuna, and I asked if it was fresh because it didn't look fresh, she said "yes I made it yesterday" which I'm sorry; but that isn't what fresh means.

Instead I ordered a steak sub with no mayo, paid and began my wait.

After 15 minutes of listening to the workers loudly complain about management and other coworkers which is super unprofessional and awkward at best, a grumpy employee called my name, barely smiled and walked away after setting down my food on the counter.

The sandwich does not smell good, I tried it but it didn't taste good either (very dry, soggy bread and they forgot the deli mustard) so I wasted my time and my money.

I'll never come back to this location.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True'}
text: Sandwiches were good, but half of our order was missing when Uber Eats delivered it. Missing 5 items - 2 sides and 3 deserts. Manager was useless and should be fired after blaming it on her employee who had been working there for his second day, and then wanting us to call the Uber delivery guy and see if he could come back and get the rest of the order(which he couldn't). $18 in delivery fees and tip which wasn't worth it for just the sandwiches. Don't trust delivery from Firehouse Subs!

text:
I felt compelled to write this review because I really enjoy their Italian sub.

Jersey Mike's used to have my favorite Italian, but after receiving one really substandard sandwich there and their steep price increase, I now prefer Firehouse.

The steamed bread, piles of Italian cold cuts, veggies and dressing combine to make an Italian sub I crave.

A bit pricey at $10 and change, but the taste and quality makes it worth it for me.

This location has always offered excellent and speedy service too!

text:
Stephanie is miserable. She doesn't  belong there. Today a customer asked for an italian pepper to be cut in two pieces. He simply asked for one half to be bigger than the other.... In front of me and the customer she snapped at the prep girl...."we don't do fancy things like that here..."

I'd have to say one of the best sub sandwich shops around, not to mention they have one of the coolest soda machines I've ever seen.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
text:
I walk into the place and are met with 3 very smiling faces and 2 people with the look of, crap, we have to do it again. "1012, (unison) Welcome to Firehouse." Which at the time made me feel special and warm and fuzzy inside. That is untill the next people got the same welcome and I started to understand after 5 minutes of being in there why those other 2 people looked like they hated the thought of anyone else walking in.

 Now, we got past the welcome committee so let's get the on to the food. I know that a sandwich is just a sadwich but his my friends is a sub and it's a sub that's done well. I had the turkey and mushroom with everything except olives cause, i hate olives. This is way up on the fast food scale. As of right now I am hooked on this place. The wheat bread is awesome and the sandwich just has a flavor that's just freaking good.

 So all in all if you even remotely like subs give this place a chance. They will great in a chours of 3 part harmony and make you feel special and give you a great sub. All in all I higly reckomend this place, and let's face it. I'm always right about good food!

text: This used to be a once a week or more lunch stop for me, but not anymore. I LOVE the food, but I only get a 30 minute lunch break so I have to call in my order. I've called 15 times over the past 3 days with no answer. It either goes to voicemail or someone picks up the phone and immediately hangs up. I called the corporate number to see what was going on and was told because it is a franchise they would have to let the owner know and have them call me back. No response from the owner thus far. Hate to say it, but if my business doesn't warrant picking up a phone, then I'm done calling and done with Firehouse.

text: October 26th we chose to order lunch from Firehouse vs Subway which was closer to where we were meeting - 19 people. Ordered direct at the restaurant. Staff was nice and helpful. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Subs is trying to break through as a legitimate competitor to Subway.  They do a pretty good job, and they've got a good schtick, with decent sandwiches, a great soda choices, and a nice gimmick of lots of hot sauces.

I've been, going to try their meatball sub, and in my own opinion, they oversold the darn thing.  It wasn't bad; but it wasn't any kind of reincarnation of the standard meatball sub.  It wasn't even very cheesy, and I like my red sauce sandwiches to have some cheesiness to them.

I also found the service to be a little slow.  I was almost the only person there, and I felt it was kind of slow.  I like Firehouse, but I don't love it.

text: Subway has lost its appeal, now that I've tried Firehouse Subs.  Their hot subs are really good.  When we were there, they were featuring a Sweet Thai Chili Pork Sub that was simply awesome.  It was very flavorful and very filling.  It was a limited-time sandwich, so I'm interested in finding out what their next special will be.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True'}
text:
What is the deal with the employees being forced to yell, "WELCOME TO FIREHOUSE SUBS!!!!!!!" every friggin time someone enters the store?????

It was happening every 10-20 seconds. I feel sorry for the employees.

I asked one employee, "Do they force you guys to do that?" She said, "Yeah. We don't have a choice. I don't like it but what can I do?" and after we complained TO THE OWNER, because they were shouting every 30 seconds... she started yelling to them, "I CAN'T HEAR YOU!!!" so they would shout it even louder. I said to my mother, "WTH!!! Is she doing that to spite us now??? 

The management seems like horrible psycho bosses from Hell. 

I'll never be back.

text:
SMOKED TURKEY BREASTS...

We just ate here and the food was delicious.  The dining area was very well maintained.  The staff was very helpful and greeted us as we entered the dining room.  I will put his on the top of my list for eateries in Boise.

The price was also reasonable.

text: I am a sucker for a good sandwich. It's one of my favorite things to eat. I'm pretty excited to try new sandwich places when they open and get a taste of all the different places out there. I have to say firehouse subs is by far my favorite sandwich place! The meat is sooo extremely flavorful and juicy! The hook n ladder is to die for! But all of their sandwiches that I have had (almost all of them!) are delicious! I have not had one bad sandwich from there and I've been there MANY times! I highly recommend this place!!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
2nd time here and we still love it!

Atmosphere= clean& adorable! Dalmatian spotted table tops, actual fire men's jackets/gear hanging on the walls, large mural of fire truck, accented with red!
Also there are 2 flat screens that are on with the nba finals so husband likes that :)

Drinks= those cool coke dispensers that have 120+ flavor choices! And they have fresh lemons and limes cut so I made myself a cherry limeade!

Food= awesome! I USUALLY do not like hot subs but I love firehouse subs!

Smokehouse cheddar brisket filled with flavor and it melts in your mouth!

Turkey bacon ranch also great flavor!

Service= friendly & received food quickly!

attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The subs were good, a better alternative to Quiznos for a hot sub. I had the Smokehouse Beef and Cheddar and my wife had the Turkey Bacon Ranch. The amount a meat on both was a bit disappointing for the price but there was plenty of flavor. We went right before the dinner rush and the tables and chairs were filthy and there were flies everywhere. Overall, it was a decent experience, especially since we used coupons but not somewhere we would frequent.

text: So I love this place I've been here twice but I have to say I came in got the beef and cheddar brisket it was amazing but 2 hours later I got food poisoning I was out for about 3 days so please just cook it better or wash your hands honestly idk what my food contained but it was a terrible experience

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: First of all, I LOVE Firehouse Subs. I was excited to see one on a recent visit to Boise and stopped by for an early dinner. The subs were amazing as always but what I wasn't impressed with was the cleanliness of the place and the drink station. I was the only customer in the place when I walked in  and still had a hard time finding a clean table that had been wiped down. I can understand this during busy hours but this was 4:30 in the afternoon and I was the only customer. The fountain drink station had fresh limes cut up but they were covered in brown spots and very unappetizing. And the drinks had a funky taste to them too. Almost like they had a bad water supply. Maybe a filter would help the taste? Little improvements could be made to make this a great franchise location.

text: If i had to put them all in order. 1. Jimmy Johns 2. Quiznos 3.Firehouse. 4.Subway. I didn't think there was anything special about the sub. It wasn't bad but not as good as the above order.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Had a fantastic first experience. The smokehouse beef and cheddar was amazing. The brisket was very flavorful and moist. My wife had the turkey bacon ranch and loved it. 

Price was well-suited to the portions. My large sub was the same size and price as a premium footlong at that "other" sub place but 10 times better. The signature pepper sauce was delicious. 

The service was fantastic. Despite the fact that nearly every table was full, we had our order within just a few minutes. And when I went up a couple minutes later to ask a question, my server remembered and called me by name from when I had ordered 10 minutes earlier. Service was very friendly and helpful. I will definitely come back soon. 

And they have one of those freestyle coke machines with a hundred different flavors. LOVE!

Zero complaints.   HIGHLY recommend.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Heard about this place from a lot of people. You know it's going to be good when lots of people are talking about it. The staff was amazing. Since it was our first time they were really nice to explain the menu to us. I ended up getting the hooks and ladders sub. It was amazing. This place blows Quiznos out of the water. Everything was super fresh, the bread was light, and it was a great portion. Filled me up and I can eat! The other thing they had that was super amazing was this drink machine. It would allow you to mix flavoring a with soft drinks, there were over 120 different flavor combinations. We tried diet coke with raspberry, it was amazing. My son got a fire hat. Best place ever. I highly highly recommend it! You won't be disappointed!

attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
The first time I went to the Firehouse, I was curious to see if they were just another "Subway" Boy was I WRONG! 

It's way better than Subway by a landslide! And not that much more expensive. I'll sub Firehouse for Subway any day. It is a chain, but it tastes like an amazing "hole in the wall sandwhich shop"

GO there if you haven't. If you have gone there, GO THERE AGAIN!

text:
This is the best sub sandwich and soup shop in Boise. All sandwiches are served warm. The Staff is extremely attentive and the quality of the sandwiches is excellent. Value for money is awesome and I always round up to support our local Fire Department.

If you haven't tried them yet now is the day, you will not regret that you did.

text: Caitylynn... (hope I spelled it right) just made me a sub like no other!  I had to ask if she measured everything out properly.  I'm a restaurant manager myself and like things uniform.   While I am a fan of firehouse and have had them from Florida to Idaho, the sub I just got (and it's always the same one) was at a whole mother level!  Not only was Cat courteous and professional but she made a sub I believe the owner would be proud of.  Well done miss!

text: Oh firehouse, I came in after hearing from many of my friends that the food was great. Well for me the first thing I noticed was the meat to bread ratio which was about 3 parts bread to 1 part meat... OK I can live with that if the flavor is there, which it wasn't I ordered the number 10 meal no mustard with BBQ sauce almost no BBQ sauce what was there was good but not enough to save the fact that it was mostly bread. My wife had a number 5, the turkey bacon ranch, and was not impressed with her sandwich either. While being filling, as it was mostly bread, there was no flavor. The bacon was bland and scarce, the cheese was flavorless. Tue best thing about the place was the coke freestyle machine and the chips.

text:
Was it the best sandwich of my life, no. Was it the best sub chain, ABSOLUTELY!!!

I feel like the competition(Subway, Jimmy John's, Blimpie) are what you end up eating when you want something that's not greasy, but isn't good...

I got the Italian and it was delicious. I would totally get it again because I want it, not just it's convenience

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I frequent some stores at the other end of this strip mall, and one of my friends working at one told me about this place.  I have never heard anyone so enthusiastic about a sandwich before.   My Dad and I tried it today (and took home a meatball sub for hubby).  She was right!

Upon entering, we explained that we hadn't been in before and they let us have a little taste of the brisket and the corned beef so we could decide what to get.   As much as we love corned beef, there was something about the moist, smoky brisket that I just had to have.   We got a large combo and split it.   It was more than enough sandwich for the both of us for lunch.

I can't say enough good things about the friendly, helpful staff.   Chris, the cashier, was awesome, as was the Assistant Manager with the cute pixie haircut.   They let me pay for hubby's meatball sub with our sit-down meal  (so I didn't have to wait in line again) and then make it when we were ready to leave so it arrived at home fresher.

We were surprised how busy they were today -- but everyone got greeted and the tables were kept clean.   We had a really nice experience and we'll continue to get sandwiches here for sure.     BTW -- for anyone with kids, they have great little kids meals and adorable fire hats for them to wear.   I know my nephew would love that!

text:
Gonna keep this review short and simple:

First trip to Firehouse Subs; thought I'd try something different.  Ordered the Hook n' Ladder and The Hero.  Was asked if I wanted the pickle on the side (that it's supposed to come with).  Paid my money.  Sat down and waited for my to-go order.

I supposed Jimmy Johns has spoiled me because I waited longer than I expected with the three employees working.  While waiting, I noticed the place had a hot sauce selection for customer use.  For those who don't know, I'm a HUGE sucker for hot sauce.  Because my order was to-go, I passed but I love me some hot sauce.

Received my two subs and bailed as planned.  When I got home, to my dismay, we had no pickles!!!  WTF!?!?!?  Don't tell me I'm getting pickles when you don't include them.  That was Strike One.

Still upset, I began eating my sub.  My overall impression was that the employee who made my sub put all the ingredients in a blender and once all combined, dumped the concoction onto some sub sandwich bread and gave it to me.

I really want to give this place a second chance but when a place asks me if I want something, I say yes, then the place neglects to give me what I ask for, I have a really hard time with the second chance.  We'll see........

text:
Pretty good sub. I ordered the Reuben and it was okay. Not a ton of flavor like I would expect from a Reuben, but it was okay. The bread is kind of blah. But the meat is good. Not fatty or gristly at all. Finding a really good Reuben is very difficult nowadays but this one is definitely passable. I'm for sure going to try a different sandwich next time so I have a better idea of firehouse's menu.

The service is nice and friendly. It's quick in quick out so if you're in a hurry there are definitely no worries on that score. The only complaint I have is the prices are kind of high for what you're getting. Especially when you line Firehouse up next to other sub chains.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Came here late one Wednesday in need of fast, kid-friendly eats.  

Firehouse had exactly what I was looking for.  

They are definitely a fast-food, large chain style sub sandwich joint--that said, I think they are one of the better fast-food, large-chain sub sandwich joints.  I ordered their medium "engineer" sub combo.  The sub had smoked turkey, swiss, and sauteed mushrooms.  It came with a soda and a bag of chips. Our sandwiches were brought to our table piping hot and they have the self-serve Coca-Cola freestyle fountain beverage machine (which is just plain cool--I got a diet cherry coke--which isn't that unusual but, for some reason, still reminded me of childhood trips to 7-11 where I would get a coke slurpee with just a touch of cherry slurpee added--it's the little things that tend to delight me).  The service was quite friendly and efficient.  The atmosphere is a little visually loud but seemed to be appreciated by the kiddo in our group. 

Overall, a solid choice if you're in need of quick sammys with broad appeal (ie--you need to feed a finicky kid).

Get to it!

text: I enjoy the sandwiches at Firehouse, and in my opinion they would be the best in Boise if their sandwiches were a bit lower in price. Firehouse has good quality, and the pickles served with the meal are very good. It is an excellent place to go if you have a coupon. I have had several of their sandwiches and they are all quality. attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse subs is certainly a local favorite for a really good sandwich. I tend to go in the fall winter and spring for a good warm sandwich that fills you up. I love that all the sandwiches have names related to a fire house and I think the atmosphere inside makes it a lot of fun for families. They have plenty of options for both adults and kids.

I get a medium smoked turkey and cheese sandwich and the Italian salad.  The Italian salad isn't just any boring salad. This salad packs a punch with flavor and dressing.

My niece and nephew get a half sandwich with the mac & cheese. They absolutely love this new option. The mac & cheese has a breading on top to give it a little bit of crunch and additional flavor and it is super tasty!

The team inside working is always really friendly and happy to greet you when you walk in. They tend to also be really great with kids.

text:
Been here 3X - 3rd times the charm.

Two Stars:
1) Good Food
2) Nice Atmosphere

No Star for really poor service. Don't go in when Monday night football is on. The entire staff was way more into the game than my business. I was literally asked three times what size of sandwich I wanted. 

No Star for LOOOONNNNNGGG wait time. Again, TAKE the tv down. I'd rather go to a sports bar for that. This is (or so I thought a family sit down restaurant)

No Star for LACK of MEAT in sandwiches - then, they have the gall to ask me for "an additional charge, would I like more meat"?... Please!! Have you ever been to Togo's? They PILE the meat on - same price tag.

Sorry Firehouse. Great idea and concept. But I've definitely had better.

text:
After a morning of activities, we were just driving around and looking for the nearest food we could all agree on. We were going down Milwaukee and saw a sign for Firehouse subs. Subway was just up the block but we decided to turn around and try something new. Boy, are we glad we did!! Walking in, the place smelled AMAZING!! We were greeted by the people behind the counter "welcome to firehouse!" Looking at the menu, that has great pictures and calorie content, it was very hard to decide! There are a lot of great options and even a low calorie section. We placed our order, the price was very reasonable. They asked if we wanted to round up to support the fire stations.. Of course! We went to grab our drinks from the soda fountain (which has every option you can imagine) and by the time we sat down the guy was coming to our table with hot sandwiches! My son says "mom, they're faster than Jimmy Johns!!" The meat was freshly cut, hot, and very flavorful. We were shocked at how good these things looked and smelled. There were 3 people working in there. They were all working hard but looked and acted like they loved their jobs! The place is very clean and well taken care of. My only negative on this place is that there's not one near my house. Although that could make me go broke! 
My family and I are new fans!!

categories: Hot Dogs, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis
text: I love Firehouse Subs, but the experience at this location was  completely unacceptable. There were 18 people waiting patiently as only two employees tasked with making sandwiches for a lot of hungry people. I don't blame the poor folks who were making the sandwiches because there's only so much two people can do in such a situation, but  management is a completely different story. I don't know if employees called in sick or what, but  management should have brought more people in to help or at least came in to work themselves. We waited 30+ minutes for our sandwiches and were late to the Indianapolis Indians game for which we had purchased 6 tickets to see. Completely unacceptable and I will never eat at this location again prior to attending an event in downtown Indianapolis.

text: Another sub place downtown, yay?  I had the spicy meatball sandwich and the meatballs are really good. They were creamy and flavorful The spicy marinara had a great flavor without being too spicy. And always fun for me is the 100 choice soda fountain. To avoid being hurried they have two of the self serve machines. I tried Orange Sprite. The price is decent and the portions tend to the large size. I'll definitely go back since I work nearby.

Excellent hot steamed subs.  One of the best sandwich shops: great variety, good service, good value and unique decor in the dining area.  Always spotlessly clean.

There are new sandwiches and salads on the menu with healthy options as well.

I would give five stars if they had fries or other sides besides chips.  Although I appreciate the good variety of chips available I would prefer other side options to choose from.

text:
This was my first time trying out Firehouse Subs. However, I didn't try out their subs instead I tried one of their sandwiches. I ordered the Momma's Homemade Chicken Salad sandwich. It was very good. My wife ordered the Capt. Sorensen's Datil Pepper Grilled Chicken sandwich. She liked it, as well. We both ordered ours as combos, which came with chips and a drink. The total price was $17.89. That was the only thing I didn't like about this place. Quite pricey for the type of food you're getting. 
Other than that the food is good, the service was great, and the restaurant was clean. Besides the price, it's worthy of another visit.

text: Went here first time. Menu isn't very easy to read, sizes aren't anywhere to be found, any of course a bunch of lazy teenagers working, but that is to be expected. With that being said, this place is just ok. I had a large brisket, it was a little over 8 dollars with tax. It was a decent sandwich but would of been a better value around the 5-6 dollars range(where jimmy johns is) The main problem here is price, they price their sandwiches like they are an elite sub shop(diebellas,jersey mikes) but aren't in that league. Probably wont go again.

categories: Delis, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches, Fast Food
text: This was my first time ever visiting a Firehouse Subs, and it will certainly not be my last. You're greeted the second you walk through the door. They have a lot of space around the counter so you can take your time decided on what you'd like without worrying about being in someone's way. I decided to get my order to go so I wasn't inside the location long. From what I saw its really cute and very clean. My order took maybe 5 minutes to make and get into my hands. I was thinking that $10 for a large was a bit extreme but omg was it worth every penny. It was loaded with meat and cheese and had just the right amount of mayo and other delicious add-ons. There was even a dill sliver which I was not expecting. Totally worth the money and with all the meat that was actually on the sandwich makes it worth the cost as well. They will see me again...and again...and again.

text: Went to the store to have the issue with their points and app resolved, boy was the store manager a rude, unfriendly and unprofessional man! He was argumentative, condescending and unhelpful. This was the third attempt with this to store fix not receiving points onto the app. First time was at the time of purchase. The manager on duty said there was nothing  she could do and to just wait to see if it would fix itself. The second I called a few days later another manager on duty took may name and number and said he would have a manager prepared to help me when I came in. The third time I went in the store manger was a complete waste of time. He flat out would not do anything and refused to listen to the problem. He kept insisting that i follow he to the office so he could get a number. He was not in control of himself, I was not going to a small room with him. On top of it all 3 mangers didn't know anything about their own companies app. As a was leaving in complete frustration he yelled half way down the store if I wanted to go back to the office with him. I called their costumer service line I was told that all of their management staff was required to know their app and how to correct problems. Come to find out that the first manager could have just refund and did the trans action again.

categories: Delis, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches, Fast Food
text:
There are justifiable reasons why this Firehouse Subs location doesn't have a very good rating: inconsistency and flippant staff. 

Whenever we go INSIDE this location to eat,  the food is always great quality. Whenever we DoorDash (which is how we have ordered the last few times), it's like the staff doesn't even read the order and we end up with sammies that are nothing like we ordered. 

Today I went in to talk to someone about our latest DoorDash order and the 50's/60's man I spoke to became somewhat rude pretty quickly. I started to show him photos of the sandwiches we received two nights ago and he stopped me cold saying he didn't need to see the photos, that he was only interested in fixing the problem. He also made a comment about not understanding why the orders are right when we come in but not when we DoorDash.  I agreed that I don't know why either.  I get that he wanted to move forward from an order gone wrong but he had no interest at all in seeing the proof of the poor quality food we received. If it was my place of business, I would be interested in the quality of the product going out the door even when I'm not there. 

He gave us coupons for free medium subs for future visits but he could use some lessons in showing interest in customer complaints. I am not someone to go into a place of business ranting and making a scene or being rude and I did not do it this time either but that is how I was treated. I was not impressed with the way I was treated by this employee/manager/owner or whoever it was I spoke with.

The sammies posted below are a Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar and a Veggie with Mushroom. They were made nothing like we ordered.

categories: Delis, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches, Fast Food
text:
I went to the Firehouse Sub in Franklin last year (you get a free meal on your birthday) I had no problem. They FS in Franklin closed. So, I went to one in Greenwood. Again on the day of my birthday. I walk in  there, they were not busy that much. I ask the employee "Does some one get a free meal on the day of their birthday" He did not know what I was talking about. Another employee told me "It's really simple, you need to download the app on your cell phone. come back a few days later to get the free meal" I said "  I have no cell phone. SO how am I suppose to download the app?" At the point the guy became mad, All because I don't have a cell phone to download the app. I ordered a bbq brisket. The sandwich hardly had any sauce on it...Iwaited patiently for them to make the sandwich. 
They put the sandwich in a large paper back. (Like you would see in a grocery store) I thought that was odd.  I picked up a diet coke that was in a cool/ warm fridge. That was the first and last place I will go in.

text:
A sandwich is a sandwich is not true!  The service was good and the sandwich was excellent.  I was impressed with the amount of meat and toppings.  I was also impressed with the amount of money people will pay for these sandwiches!!!! Are you crazy!? 

The prices are too much and the quality of meat isn't comparable to a true deli sandwich.  I hate the rating I gave them but the sandwich was good, but not good enough for me two spend a little over $20 for me an my wife to eat two sandwiches!  

At the end of the day - it's just a sandwich :-) Go get a real meal and be healthier.
