I ate there during lunch with a local friend  and though my sandwich had good flavor, the bread in my "hot" sub was barely lukewarm, bordering on cold.  We had to wait a bit so don't know if they just forget to send it out to the table.  The last time we ate there they totally forgot our order and when it finally came out mine was the wrong sandwich.

The sandwiches are tasty  and the staff welcoming and friendly and based on how busy they always are, others agree,.  But after two strikes out,  we probably will try another place next time we want a sub.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text:
I liked them when they first opened in Avon, but once they got their fancy Coke fountain, I told them their mixture was off, and while they swear it isn't, there just isn't enough syrup to make it taste right. I hate it when places screw with the mixture to save a couple of pennies here and there. I guess if you like the flavors mixed into your pop, you will think their fountain is pretty cool, but it just isn't my thing. I would rather buy a bottle of Coke down at the gas station and BYOC.

On the other hand, the subs are awesome... they rival and beat some of the popular places like Penn Station and Jimmy Johns. My favorite is the #10, with two kinds of brisket... combined with mayo and their barbecue sauce, this thing is like crack cocaine on a bun. Seriously. I find myself having a difficult time stopping.

Great firehouse decor, and last time we were there, Wayne Township firefighters came in to eat, so that was kind of cool for our kids. The kids fare is actually pretty sparse, but if there was one closer to where I worked, I would be here all the time. Two TVs tuned to NFL Network also guarantee that you will have trouble listening to what your wife just said.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text: These guys are pretty good. I'd rank them somewhere below Penn Station and Jimmy Johns, but above Subway. They have the usual variety of deli sandwiches and a good amount of optional toppings for them. Everything tastes fresh and the service we've had here has always been friendly, albeit a bit on the slower side. The prices are also pretty typical of this type of place, so no worries there. I don't really have any complaints, but also don't think the world of them. It's a good place to get a solid sandwich, but I won't go out of my way to visit here.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text: This is easily my favorite chain sandwich place that I have tried. Staff is always friendly, warm delicious subs delivered quickly and there is of course the fun drink machine. This applies to both the Avon and Plainfield locations. I have tried a handful of the sandwiches but my favorites are Club on a Sub and New York Steamer. My boyfriend really likes the meatball sub and the beef brisket.  We go here pretty frequently. Now I am craving it again...need to go soon...

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text:
Tonight was my first visit to Firehouse, it will not be my last!

When I first walked in I was greeted by 2 employees with a very nice welcome. There is no rush to order and everyone is willing to answer questions.

The menu is better than other sub shops. I ordered the meatball sub. The size options are 8 or  12 inches. Bread options are white or wheat. The subs are all toasted which I like.  

Their options are pretty interesting, good mix of ingredients and the flavors are pretty bold.

My favorite part of this shop is all the hot sauces at the end if the bar!! 30 plus different hot sauces that you can put in your sub!  

They also collect spare change, donations, and sell their old pickle buckets in support of local first responders. A very cool place.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text:
Where to begin...ok...the food is amazing! The service is always friendly (but sometimes in the slower periods of the day it can get slow when the staff is cut). 

Last night was her first night ever eating Firehouse...she loved it!

We were just there Monday night after a disappointing dinner at Fogo on Sunday, and she says, "If I would have known how good these subs are, I would have rather had dinner here." And she said, "I don't know if I can ever have Jimmy John's again..." - and that's coming from a sprout eating, lentil soup making, food snob !

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'Ambience': 'None'}
text: Bland & tasteless. It's almost uncanny how little flavor these subs have. And the bread is never fresh. I have absolutely no problems  with the service here or the preparation of the subs. attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: They generously provided me with a free birthday sub.  I ordered steak and cheese but discovered they had given me turkey and mushrooms and since I was home and 7 miles away I removed mushrooms and ate it.  It was ok.  I called and a manager said come back we'll give you a 2nd free sandwich. So yesterday I went back.  The place was empty so no big crowd thus time.  They make my sandwich which I confirm once in the car is steak and cheese with peppers and onion (mostly onion).  I am hungry so I am eating as I drive home.  The peppers were hot but crunchy as though completely uncooked - odd.  The onion seemed more cooked but they had used that first layer of onion which is tough and not edible.  So I kept pulling strings of onion out and throwing them.  While the staff is nice and the place was very clean and they even gave me a free beverage for my inconvenience....when 2for 2 you can't get it right that's a problem.  Glad I did not have to pay.

text:
This Firehouse subs location really impressed me. They are known for upholding respect for first responders. As I ordered I was given the opportunity to round up to donate to first responders and the woman taking my order asked for my name and used my name again when delivering my order to the table, this made me feel welcome. As each order was ready the sandwich makers would tell "dispatch" which I thought was such a cute touch for their restaurant.
When I walked in I noticed there were Marines eating here today... and as I started typing this to yelp (already impressed) the man behind the counter came around to shake their hands and thank them for their service... 
unfortunately, I am not in the area frequently... but I will be back.

text: This place is located near the abandoned ghost town of a former blockbuster video... Tucked away in the corner... Outstanding subs. text: I came in today to get subs for me and two other of my colleagues and put everything on one order. When it came to us paying, I payed with $20 cash and wanted to split the rest 50/50 on two cards. The cashier said she wasn't sure how to do that but she wanted to "try" to learn how by herself. She ended up putting the entire rest of the bill on my credit card and nothing on my colleague's credit card. I know this may be not a common issue but as a worker if you don't know how to do something, please ask others. Also I've never gone in this location and felt like the employees enjoy their jobs. Other than that problem the subs tasted ok.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text:
If only I hadn't become sensitive to gluten!  My husband & I stopped in for lunch - he had a sandwich & I tried a salad.  Firehouse Subs is definitely good at sandwiches...my husband liked his turkey cranberry sub. I was not quite as impressed with my "chopped" salad.  While all of the salad toppings were chopped, the lettuce was not.  Of course it was during this visit that I realized how much I like having spinach and dark lettuces in my salad! 
The staff and restaurant are an important part of the equation - and they did great here!   The staff was very friendly and professional and the restaurant was clean...we even got to witness a new employee being trained in the virtues of customer service and cleanliness!  Bravo Firehouse!  Next time I may have to ditch the gluten free diet for a minute so I can try one of those subs!

text: Greatest subs in town!just a little advice for future customers that come in,don't talk on the phone while putting your order in cause it causes confusion with the people taking your order and it's very DISRESPECTFUL!it sounds like the person that gave it one star was having a bad day and or is trying to get free food!it's sad that people have to use the excuse "racial" whenever something doesn't go somebodies way!anyway this location is very professional and goes outta their way to make your stay as comfortable and entertaining as possible.i encourage everybody to come in when you have a chance!

text: These subs are really tasty! I've had two of the hot ones and they are so filling and satisfying! When I first looked into this place and looked at their menu online, I admit the subs didn't look very tasty, just kind of simple. But I think the simplicity is what makes them so good!! The meat is sliced very thin which I find very delicious on a sub sandwich. You can also tell that the quality of the ingredients is good, much much better than the sub chains around here. Customer service was superb and they even gave my little boy a cute little plastic fire hat which made his day!

text:
Who doesn't love a good sub?

When we moved, we moved further away from the original FHS we would go to but we were happy to see that shortly after, they built one in the strip mall not too far from our new place.

They are always welcoming when you walk in, you are greeted no matter how crowded they are.  On busy days you will have to wait a bit for your food but it still arrives in the state of matter it should be.  You order at the front and can modify whatever you need.  One of the best parts of FHS is their coke machine - the one where you can pick so many different options its insane!  This is one of my husbands favorite parts of our visits.

text:
I really like Firehouse Subs and have been to many other locations.  The Tesson Ferry location is very disappointing and after reading other reviews I am not the only one with these feelings.  To say they worked at a snails pace would be giving them to much credit.  I ordered a NY Steamer sandwich, the two small pieces of meat did not even cover the bread.  Did they forget to put all the meat on my sandwich because they were so busy talking or getting themself a soda while 7 customers waited.  There were 5 employees so the excuse of short staffed due to Covid does not apply in this case. 
Good Luck to the owner because I would hate to see another small business go by the wayside.

text: If you like watching science fiction movies as well as debating movies and actors while getting paid to do so, you should seriously apply for a job at Firehouse Subs on Tesson Ferry Rd. Don't worry about the customers, they're a minor inconvenience as you can watch two movies at the same time, on the two dining room televisions! Take all the time you need talk about actors and actresses, their movie performances, box office earning and more while you're slapping together three smokehouse cheddars for a family that has nothing better to do than wait on you for 21 minutes during their 40 minute break in-between baseball games to eat lunch. Customers enjoying the Pickle Ball Championships on tv during their excruciatingly long wait for a Hook & Ladder Sub and a side of Mac-n-Cheese are of no concern... just change the channels to not one, but TWO different TNT channels and watch two different Marvel movies for the 14th and 18th time! So come on down to Firehouse Subs on Tesson Ferry and join our day shift for movie aficionado's!

text: This has got to be one of the slowest and worst experiences I've had at firehouse in the last 15 years. There are currently 9 employees here during the lunch rush and there is no line, but every table is full and 75% don't even have there food yet, I ordered a small sub 20mins ago and still waiting. There are three employees wandering around with a clueless look on their face. Won't stop at this one again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text:
Once again, and now, three times in a row, disappointed.
Call in order for two sandwiches.  Arrived to pick them up about 5 minutes later.  Cashier said it would be a few minutes, shouted out that I was there and had paid.  Response from maker was that he was working on them now.
I stood there for about ten minutes.  My name was never called and no one asked if I was waiting for something, until finally the owner(?), or one of the employees, asked what I was waiting for.  Told them my name and they turned around to find a bag with my sandwiches (no longer hot) in it.  No offer of $$ off the almost $15 charge, no real apology, not the least bit interested in trying to keep me as a customer.
Last, but not least, the sandwich bread sucks.  Close to what you would get with day old rolls.  No crispiness to the crust, dry, tasteless and yuck!
You've lost another customer, for good!  Way too much competition in the area doing a much better job.

text: This store in particular is tiny. attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text: Beyond disappointed. Ordered from the riverview location and paid $4.99 for delivery plus $3 tip only to receive part of my order. I ordered a sub and chips.....not difficult. When my uber driver called to let them know I did not receive full order, while I was standing there on speaker phone, was told I could drive there to pick up chips today or a different day. My response ,"I just paid $5 for my order and a tip to drive and pick up the rest of my order?". At that point I sent the order back and expect a full refund. I call the store directly to speak with the store manager and she offers no help or solution. Sad to say I wanted to support this company, however I will nvr order again. Manager was argumentative with no solution. This place is a joke.

text:
I was one of the first customers at this new location on the day they opened.  As a longtime Firehouse customer, I was very impressed/excited to see that this location held the same high standards I received at their other franchise stores.  

However, I went to Firehouse Subs today and received substandard service at best.   I arrived at the Hwy 301 location at 3:58 pm and was warmly greeted by the staff....after that everything went downhill.  I ordered 2 Lg Subs at 4:01 pm.....there was another couple in front of me......other than that, there was no other customers.  Please note, there was 9 Firehouse workers on duty, one woman did get off between the time I ordered and when I received my sandwiches 17 mins later!  

During my 17 minute wait I began to record the lack of motivation of this staff, all of  which was being done in front of the Manager on duty named Kesha.  

I absolutely love Firehouse and hope the service I received today will not be the norm.

text:
New Store first time I've seen it..have a sub sandwich variety all in the general area. I have a singular desire I seek out once or twice a month "The Meatball Sub"
Generally it's made to order or ur asked what u would like on it, okay that's like making it at home and you've been raised to to detail a peanut butter and jelly sandwich giving your parental unit details of everything that you want on it. No it's time for you to make it urself & clean up after urself ect... Back to Meatball Sub as is Please ! Likely it's made all reasonably nice and neat then rolled up in paper and off you go to consume. Now u unwrap ur sub and it's become globb a mushy soggy mess that the normal presentation result. This is not the result I had in presentation at Firehouse Subs there presentation was a paper fiber box with it laying nice and neat inside unable to become all mushy and Soggy mess the blends of flavors that came together on it were surprisingly different from any meatball I've had elsewhere in this area so in short "I'll be back" seriously if they can get the meatball so this right what can they do with others like a cheesesteak that's not a big glob when you open it up I've got to feel that the flavors would all be less than a glob..

text:
This is one of the few franchises that I like.    First time at this location and not disappointed.   The staff was very friendly and took my order and had food ready in a timely manner.   I had the brisket with cheese and it was very good.  The bread was fresh and the ingredients had great flavor.  Do I wish the small was just a tad bigger?   Yes!

There is a nice variety of sandwiches from which to choose, or you can create your own sub.  For only $2.99 you can make it a combo and have chips and a pretty large drink.  The subs are toasted which in my mind makes them perfect.

Will definitely return.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text: I love these subs. The food did not disappoint. The service however did. I was so excited that this location opened up. I ordered one sub online ahead of time. I arrived exactly when the sub was supposed to be ready. I signed for it and the cashier said she'd tell me when it was ready. I waited. Watched other people get their orders. Finally after 20 mins I decided to ask what was going on. The person behind the register found my order immediately and handed it to me. I asked "how long has it been sitting there?" "I dunno look at the check". According to the check it was sitting there for 19 minutes. I consider myself to be a pretty patient person (my husband was sitting in the car the whole time). And the place was busy which is why I waited so long to ask. But no apology was given. In fact the person I dealt with didn't seem to care at all.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text:
An earlier reviewer says you should rate a place by what you are getting.
If I went along with that opinion, this Firehouse would rate a one star!

My visit yesterday was not at all up to expectations and I certainly did not get what I expected.  It was my second visit in two weeks.  The first time, my Italian sub tasted fantastic, though I was a little surprised that it was just barely warm.  Yesterday, I asked for it to be cold.  Note:  for those not familiar with Firehouse;  they only have one cold sub, the tuna salad.  All others are hot, but you can ask that they make any of them cold.
While my Italian sub two weeks ago tasted great, with a pronounced Italian flavor and beautifully made, with the meats and cheese nicely layered and spread out over the bread, today's was completely different.  It was on stale bread, the meat kind of thrown on it, with the ham balled up into pieces.  No Italian taste whatsoever.  Couldn't really tell if it was just a ham sub or what, but definitely not Italian.  I had ordered an Italian, and the receipt says it was, but no.  It wasn't.  A big disappointment, and at $19.99 for it and another sandwich, way overpriced.  Subway, at $4.99 each, for they're specials...a much better deal.
The second sandwich, meatball, was ok, by my wife's comments, though at almost ten dollars, way short of equal to it's price/value.

One other note; her meatball sub was wrapped and put in it's accompanying box.  For some reason, they put a pickle spear, in a little plastic baggy, under the sandwich??!!  Why?  Warm pickle spear anyone?!  And secondly, they bagged the hot meatball sub in with the cold, supposedly Italian sub.  Not a good idea.  The hot sub cools faster while the cold sub doesn't stay cold.

The place was clean, the service fairly quick and friendly.  Too bad the food did not live up to expectations.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text:
How do you rate a franchise like this that is so well known...well since you pretty much know what you're getting, I rate it compared to other Firehouse locations I've visited.

I walked in and was greeted with more than one smile and the first and most important thing I noticed was how clean it was. There was no straws or napkins or any trash on the floor. Every single chair was pushed in and lined up and even every napkin dispenser on the tables were lined up and looked orderly. The drink station was wiped down and didn't have any drops of soda on the counter and there wasn't a single straw wrapper laying around. Pretty impressed.

I ordered my sub, it came out fast and exactly as I ordered it...can't complain. While I was eating I noticed 3 different employees simultaneously cleaning and wiping down tables and seats.

It doesn't get 5 stars because the subs were phenomenal, although they are very good in my opinion, it's gets 5 stars because of how I was treated, how timely & accurate my food came out and their obvious commitment to cleanliness.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}"}
text: I am absolutely sick to my stomach. I picked up a sandwich and a cup of soup for lunch. Just got home and ate half of my sandwich then took a bite of soup. Next bite of soup I stirred it and noticed something white on the surface. Then proceeded to scoop out dozens of white bag clips. I thought I was seeing things at first, but nope, they're all bent and clearly used. What on earth? This is disgusting. I literally ate from what I can only understand would be a discard cup that dozens of employees have touched bag clips and thrown them in. I want to throw up. So disgusting there is no way this was not seen when putting soup in there. How could you feed this to someone? No regard for the health (given the current pandemic) or safety of others? What if this soup was meant to be eaten by a child? I will never be back and I will dissuade others from visiting as well. I'm literally stunned.

text: Great sub , actually donates back to the community - WOW!!! Emergency personal actually get upgraded to a combo for free. Coke machine is cool with 240 different favors. Would definitely return again and again. Try it - you'll like it.

name: Firehouse Subs
categories: Delis, Restaurants, American (New), Fast Food, Sandwiches
text: This place is great! The sandwiches are delicious, the choice of soda is fantastic, and the service is tremendous.  You can keep Subway, give me the Firehouse!

name: Firehouse Subs
categories: Delis, Restaurants, American (New), Fast Food, Sandwiches
text: I really liked the toasted sub. Beyond that, I visited the day after Hurricane Sandy. Firehouse Subs was one of the few places with electricity and there were long lines. Only two workers could get in to work, but those two guys worked hard to make everyone happy. It was an oasis for most of us without heat or kight or food at home. And even though they must have been pretty tired, they kept the quality of the food they served up to the usual great standards. Kudos to those guys. We will be back.

name: Firehouse Subs
categories: Delis, Restaurants, American (New), Fast Food, Sandwiches
text: Nice place, friendly staff and delicious sandwich until... I found a long blonde hair. I had the Italian sandwich and I don't think I saw hair listed on the ingredients for the sandwich, but i was in a hurry so maybe I missed it. I guess if you like hair on your sandwiches this is the place for you. I prefer my sandwich without hair, although I do like mayo. BTW, I called the hotline to let the know that they were serving hair subs and it took the guy 10 minutes to establish that they had a Fire House on route 1 in  Langhorne. The guy on the hot line did confirm that hair is not one of their standard condiments.

attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text: This Firehouse has fast service and great food. I order the meatball sub (pictured). The meatballs are large and homemade tasting. It is smothered in spices and cheese and then baked for perfection. I recommend getting a fountain soda as well. They have the soda machines that have hundreds of choices. There are about 20 soda brands to choose from (Coke, Diet Coke, Mellow Yellow, Dasani, Minute Maid Lemonade, Sprite, etc). Then you can add different flavors to the main soda choice. I like grape or orange Mellow Yellow or Sprite.

text: Didnt know what we were gonna get since there were no other reviews to steer us in the right direction. But we were pleasantly surprised! Delicious sandwiches! I had the steamer. Yum! text: Ok so I tried it half a year ago when I moved right behind it. Boy was I glad I did. It is a two minute walk from me and I eat it weekly to the point that the staff know me. If you want a fast sandwich place, then this place certainly beats subway by 2.89 miles. I always order a turkey bacon ranch and it has never disappointed. Although the ordering online system times could use a little work, the place definitely deserves 6 stars if I could.

text:
4 stars for the delicious food and friendly service. 

I love the Hook n Ladder so much that I rarely try anything else. Though the engineer is a tasty sub too. Always hot and melty cheese...yum! Their selection of hot sauces is awesome and the house hot sauce is really great. Add in the fact that they have a CocaCola freestyle machine and this place is in a different league than Subway. The only issue I have is with the parking. Not much up front but there is some in the back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
I have always loved Firehouse and definitely more than Subway or any other sub places. I recommend it to everyone hungry. This location, first, had a guy that looked high and was REALLY SLOW. Other people that came in after me were all getting their subs made by someone quicker and were done and out. He then had to throw it away because he used the wrong bread and then the other person made it because I asked him if he was new. The other girl working kept asking him "did they even train you?!" I haven't seen him there since but once so I am guessing maybe he got fired? I, however, never see the same people so it is always hit or miss with the quality of the food. 

I still go there though because I love Firehouse and because it is literally 2 minutes from my house. 

Last night I went there with a friend and they took a little longer than usual to make two subs. We even called it in. We waited for it to finish and went straight home (reminder - 2 minutes) when it was done. The subs were hard and cold. I bought 5 of the lemon macadamia nut cookies which are usually totally amazing. They were hard and tasted bad; almost as if they had an old freezer burnt taste. I threw them away. Then today, my partner and I have had some serious upset stomachs. 

I'm really sad about it because Firehouse to me is like going to a families restaurant. I get even sadder when they forget to put my pickle in the bag (every time). Knowing me I am still going to go there, though, mainly because I love their subs.

Before I go in next time, I'm going to get down on my knees and pray to Jesus that they're having a good day today.

Diamond XP

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'very_loud'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text: This was my first time going to a Firehouse. Overall the aesthetic is that typical American type, similar to five guys or so. Let's start with the sandwich. I got a club on a sub, but they forgot the bacon. We all know that a club is nothing without the bacon, so that was pretty disappointing, but overall the sandwich was just alright. The bread didn't have a satisfying toasted crunch, nor did it melt together in an untoasted fashion. The flavors were all just meh. Not bad, but not great either, just ok. The pepper sauce that you can get on the side was just super sweet and nothing else really. It was good, but again, not great. The Mac and cheese... Came out of a plastic baggie. I know that that's just a reality of fast food, but it's still jarring to see. The worst part though, was that it was Mac and cheese soup. It was so funny and relatively flavorless. Off you're looking for a similar flavor, I definitely recommend Panera bread's Mac. I also tried the cherry limeade that's a Firehouse special. Again, way to sweet, where is the lime part? I certainly couldn't taste it. A pretty mediocre trip overall, I probably wouldn't go out of my way to get it again.

name: Firehouse Subs

text: This is the place to go if you want slow food and your order incorrect. One of the worst firehouse subs I have ever been to. text:
We were in there about 6:30 PM on Friday 8/27.  I remember Firehouse employees used to shout "welcome to Firehouse" when you walk in.  Ok they don't do that any more, it was neat, but not necessary.  But now we don't even get "be with you in a minute" or something like that.  They just keep working and talking to each other while you wait at the counter.  Then they proceeded to mess up my wife's sandwich, including things she specifically asked them to exclude.  On top of that they sold us fountain drinks not telling us there was a service person working in their drink dispenser.  My wife wanted soda and had to settle for tea because they didn't say anything.

I appreciate the fact that they're working at a time when many aren't working, but the appreciation has to go both ways.  We always tip, we expect good service in return.

text: This location never has its open sign on, I usually only come here at night so I don't know if it is broken or they purposely turn it off to make it seem like they are closed but it has been off for weeks now. attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text:
Slow service and very sloppy sandwich.

There isn't a veggie sub on the menu, but they made me one. The cashier had a hard time entering all the items into the ordering system, but she got it eventually with a little help from somebody else. After ordering I sat down to wait, and I realized that there were 5 or 6 other tables with people and none of them had their food. I could tell this might take a while and it did. I waited about 15 minutes before getting my sandwich and the employee actually apologized for the wait.

It was nice that he recognized that it took a long time. But still, waiting that long for a fast food sandwich is kind of bad.

As far as the sandwich goes, I don't understand why it is was so wet. Everything was falling out of the bread, and it was just a mess. I did ask for some dressing but why so much? Publix takes forever to make your sandwich too, but at least you are rewarded with a very good sandwich at the end.

I ate it and moved on with my life. I guess that about says it all. I'll stick with Jersey Mike's or Publix.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text:
Fly in the sub.

First time trying this place. Got home opened styrofoam box and fly was crawling on top of meatball sandwich. I hit it with finger and it didn't fly away, just kept walking around on sandwich. Must have liked it a lot.

Okay, so it happens but I'm not about to eat the sandwich. I was in my kitchen when I opened it so I know it wasn't mine, I don't have flies. Back to the place to return it, but not getting another cause I lost my appetite.

I politely asked who manager was and took him to the side cause I didn't want everyone in the place who was eating to start throwing up. I told him I just wanted my money back. Said Okay, gave me money and said Sorry about that. That's it.

He said it so matter-of-factly that I figured it happens all the time. As I was leaving I saw another fly and there were some outside when I went out. Don't know what they can do about it, maybe pay more attention when they pack up the food that they're not rapping bugs with it.  

Wouldn't usually post something like this if the manager was a little more apologetic but he wasn't so...

text:
I think they have it down when it comes to hot subs. The one thing I don't like is the amount of meat that they put on a sub. They are a little light and stingy.

I usually go with the Engineer or Hook and ladder, you can't go wrong with either of these sandwiches.

This restaurant is always clean and has easy to read menu boards. You are greeted with a "Welcome to firehouse" when you walk in the door. Ordering is quick and easy and the subs come out relatively quick. They ask for your name to call out when you sub is ready, give them a fake one and have fun with it.

They have the uber expensive coke machine that does 250 flavors, or something like that, but not one of them taste right in my opinion. They should just go back to the old fountain machine, it's better.

They have a couple of TVs with sound if your alone at lunch and want to catch up on news or sports. Usually running bay news 9 or ESPN. 

Bathrooms are well kept.

text: My husband says I'm addicted to Firehouse subs. Perhaps I am. I started coming to Firehouse when I was pregnant with our twins. They steam their meat so it's safe eat while pregnant. I always opted for extra meat (2oz is $1) to get extra protein. Morgan (one of the managers) is great. She always smiles and greets us like family. We've always had positive experiences at this location. I'd even say it's the best Firehouse in the area. Yum!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text:
Always greeted when you come in and out. They have a Firehouse Rewards app you can use to gain points after purchases for free subs, sandwich upgrades (double meat) etc. The sandwiches are always prepared fresh so after a short wait (usually 5-10 min max) your delicious sandwich is served to your table after you order it from the counter.
Love the detailed Firehouse and Dalmatian decor, makes it fun for the kids - free plastic Firehouse hats for the kiddos as well.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text: I had been a big fan of Firehouse Subs, and have been to the East Lake Rd location many times. But a few months ago I got a NY Steamer and it had very little meat on it. I decided to give them another try, and this time was even worse. Barely any meat on the sandwich, with no more than 2 layers of meat on most, some with only one layer, and even some parts of the sandwich with no meat at all. And to make matters worse, the bun was stale. I wish I would have checked it before I left, as I would have either asked for another sandwich, or my money back. Probably one of the worst subs I've ever had. The 2 things that I always liked about Firehouse Subs were the stacks of meat and on a soft sub roll. I rarely write negative reviews, but I'm very disappointed and probably won't return to this location.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text: I'm not trying to exaggerate, but I have never but never had a sub as good as this one! When I first walked-in i was disappointed that they didn't offer fries with the meal. But guess what?! You don't need fries! You don't need anything else other than the sub! Because it is ridiculous delicious!!!! As I was walking out I had a thought, the guys in the kitchen are not just regular employees that learned in 2 hrs how to flip a burger and got them selves a job. Those people back there are real chef! So for everyone, "Firehouse" is the real deal! Trust me, go there take your family members, friends and I guarantee you will have a awesome time and meal! And just for the record, my name is Pedro and I'm not getting paid to advertise they restaurant, I'm simply a happy customer and they deserve my compliment and review! Customer service 5 stars*****

text: I was hot tired and emotionally drained. I went to the Firehouse sub shop on E  Lake Woodlands,  it was 901pm  . They had just locked up . attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text:
First time at this location - because I went to the wrong store after placing a phone order.  I thought I was calling & going to my usual Tarpon Springs location. When the phone was answered, I didn't hear him say, "East Lake."  No worries. This was an easy to find store, and both gentlemen inside were friendly and accommodating.  Our order was ready, and it smelled delicious on the ride home. 

We split a large hot pastrami & delivered a kids meal to the kid next door - hot ham, drink, dessert & hat. I had to ask for the hat before leaving. It wasn't in the bag. He was thrilled with it! But he didn't know that he was supposed to get dessert - marshmallow treat. So he wasn't disappointed. But I was. No treat! I didn't call to complain because it's a 15 drive back to get it. Not worth it. Our sandwich was good. I hope he enjoyed his sandwich and his drink. 

I'll be returning to Tarpon next time I order. It's closer & they've never gotten my order wrong. I should have checked my order before leaving. Then it would be a 5 star review. But I didn't. Do check your order before you leave here, and you won't be disappointed.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False'}
text:
TLDR: the new York steamer is where it's at. Quick quality sandwiches decent options for those with food allergies.
We were running errands today and decided to stop in for a bite to eat. The kids ordered grilled cheese which they of course didn't eat. I had the engineer which was huge and pretty good. My husband got the New York steamer and man, that was a yummy sandwich! 
Our family does have some food allergies and although, they had a hard time finding the allergy guide in stores, I was able to easily locate it online. Most of the sandwiches are soy free which is a great sign for fresh food as most processed items contain soy. 
The bathrooms were clean and the service was good. My kids really loved all of the drink options available from the touch screen kiosk.

text:
I like this place and have been here 3 times.

For a chain, I think that the sandwiches are tasty. I didn't think that I liked brisket until I started eating here. They don't skimp on the meat and I've never had to wait long.

Close to work, it is convenient to pop in and grab a hot lunch. Now I'm also a WaWa gal but the one next door gets crowded plus I like a little variety. This is a nice option for me in the neighborhood.

I very much enjoyed the free birthday sub today and will keep coming back. (Sign up for their rewards to get your own!).

text: My husband and I LOVE firehouse - but this location is beyond terrible. Sandwich orders are ALWAYS wrong, the staff moves slower than molasses, over 30 minute wait for a sandwich?!?! Are the ingredients grown in that time as well? It's just so bad. Never experienced a firehouse this slow and the customer service is just awful. Where are they getting these employees? They all look miserable, never a smile in sight, and it's like you are interrupting their leisurely day by ordering something. Terrible terrible location.

text:
This place is hilarious. This has got to be one of the saddest experience of customer service I've ever experienced. First, there was another person inside already eating and then there was me. Walked in, and for the first 5 minutes no one even acknowledged my existence. Then I ordered and it took 20 minutes..... I mean I'd understand if they were busy, but there was like no one inside. So I get my order and I asked for Wheat Bread and they put white. lol. Slow and messing up the order is just bad. 

I get it sometimes it's a slow, but the lack of customer service is why I'll probably never return here again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: American (New), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
First ever visit and my order was wrong. Decided on a whim to try this place for lunch - 1:30 Wednesday afternoon. Wasn't busy, and the guy at the counter was very friendly. I ordered a medium Engineer on wheat,  and added banana peppers.  Guy told me right off they were out of tomatoes, so there wouldn't be any of those. OK, I can live with that - but unfortunate for a sub restaurant to run out of one of the most popular toppings ever. They only serve salads and subs, very limited menu, and can't keep tomatoes? Tons of grocery stores around, they should have picked some up.  Come on, guys! 

Got it to go - waited at a nearby table that had sticky pink soda or some kind of drink on it - yuck. Took a little less than 10 minutes for them to call my name, so I grabbed my sub and headed back to work in Maryland Farms.  Sat to eat when I got back to work - and there were zero mushrooms on my sub. Not a single one.  Though after reading another reviewer mention the mushrooms they use are canned and not fresh, well, heck, not as disappointing as I may have initially thought. Supposed to also be served with a pickle - didn't get one of those, either.  So, no tomato, no pickle, no mushrooms.  I paid more for an Engineer sub, when I could have just paid for a turkey sub, cause that's all I got. 

Also, feel it's worth mentioning that it was served in a little closeable carboard box.  IMO, just a waste of resources. What's wrong with wrapping the sub in paper? Cardboard sub box, then in a paper bag as well.  Not very eco-friendly. 

Well, since this was my first ever visit to Firehouse Subs, and they basically cannot even do their job, this was also my last visit to Firehouse Subs.  Way too many excellent places in Brentwood and Maryland Farms to grab lunch where you actually get what you order and pay for.

text: Poor customer service.  Took more than 10 minutes to get food, and we were the only ones there.  Ice machine was not working, but did give some ice.  The only drinks available in the machine were either diet or "Free".  No regular drinks of any kind.  My wife's sandwich contained lettuce, tomato etc., which she specifically asked to leave off.  My grandson never did get the cookie that was supposed to accompany his grilled cheese sandwich.  Staff was very inattentive and did not act like they wanted to be there.  Much better service available at other paces.

text:
This is based entirely on the wait time for the food.  On Saturday 2/27, we finished a sporting event and decided to stop by to grab some sandwiches and head out for the remainder of our day.

Was a good size lunch crowd this day and waited for a couple of minutes to place our order.  Upon placing our order, the cashier stated it would be 30 minutes.  I thought maybe she was just overestimating, but came to find out it was true.

Places like Firehouse need to have a faster production line and move food to the customers quickly.  I like their sandwiches but there is no way anyone should be waiting more than 10 - 15 minutes, even on a busy day. 

Probably will not be coming back here when I think it is a busy time of day.

text: Friendly staff, fantastic subs - makes a great combination.  I have ordered three or four different sandwiches and so far, none have disappointed. This is a nice area and a great place to stop for a quick meal. I recommend the Italian sub or the beef and cheddar brisket. 

The staff are very friendly and the food is to die for! You really have to make sure to try the different hot sauces that they offer. The best for the Italian sub is the Melinda's Garlic hot sauce (they run out of this quite frequently).

text: Went there on an invitation to come back for a complementary meal for two due to our order not being correct on a previous visit. Everything was perfect! I'm a retired over the road truck driver and have eaten at many fast food places spending many $$$, so I take store surveys and reviews very seriously. Firehouse responded to my survey the next day with an apology and explained what steps had been taken to prevent the same from happening in the future. I'm impressed with Firehouse both with their service and product. 5 stars Firehouse!!!

attributes: {'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: American (New), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
Food is always delicious here. Never not enjoyed what I had, but the employees at this location are a joke. My wife and I dined here today at 6:15pm and got two sandwiches. We and one other person were the only ones in the restaurant. Took 15 minutes to get our two subs. Not only did it take a long time but they got the orders wrong, and we got the wrong sandwiches all together. The young lady at the register was short and rude and the other young lady working didn't move at all when the sandwiches were ordered. She was on her phone hiding behind the hot sauce tray. 

In the time we have been here (25 minutes) two other customers have come in and they have yet to get their food. A group of young kids came in halfway through our meal and the two ladies are hanging out with these boys instead of actually making food. It's unbelievable. I feel awful for the customers still waiting, and I'm terribly upset with my experience. As paying customers, we expected much more. We don't just pay for good food, we pay for good service... And tonight that was severely lacking.

attributes: {'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}

text:
Second time at Firehouse Subs...as restaurants deserve 2 visits before conclusions are made. Service was poor at best, as the restaurant was populated mostly by people who had waited over 20 minutes for a simple sandwich...and it wasn't busy!
On to the abomination that was to have passed for a sub sandwich...please picture the movie "Falling Down" where Michael Douglas goes nuts comparing the burger he received with the burger pictured...it was dreadful...and whomever put the sandwich together actually missed the bun with the meat...as it was half on and half off the bun.
Waited over 15 minutes, sandwich was not good...I'm done.
Pathetic excuse for food and service...maybe less should be spent on advertising with more spent on staff and product development.
Just my thoughts.

text: I wish that I could give a better review for this location as it is very close to my work but the last 3 times I have gone have been progressively worse. Pretty underwhelming. Got a meatball sub.
Meatballs were super hot, so I almost got my tongue burned which is never a fun feeling.
The meatballs were kinda bland, but other than that, its a decent place for a somewhat good quick bite during work.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: American (New), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis, Burgers, Restaurants
text: I don't know how many stars to give this place because I walked out before I could try the food.  Which sucks, because I bet you that the sammies are good here.  But I walked in on a Wednesday evening and the place is empty.  I look up at the menu board and all the prices are missing.  I ask for a menu with prices and they say they have none.  I asked them what the prices are and the lady behind the counter looked at me like it was the first time anyone had ever asked such a thing.  Finally, she said that you have to order your sandwich, they make it, and then when you are ready to pay, they ring it up and that's when you find out what the price is.  Seriously.  Who orders stuff without knowing what it costs?  Not me.  So, its in the neighborhood (walking distance from the house), so maybe I will try it again sometime.  I expect that they were just raising their prices and that's why everything was blacked out on the menu board.  But seriously, how can the employees not be able to tell you what anything costs until after they make it for you?  No thanks.

categories: American (New), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
I have stopped and ate at this Firehouse Subs location on several occasions over the past 18 months and and have not ever experienced poor service, order issues or long waits as I have read in other reviews. 

On my last visit last week the store was busy but the line moved as quickly or faster than most other places during the lunch crowd. The longest wait I had was waiting for other customers to get their drinks at the drink station and my food was being brought out as I searched for a table. As I sat and ate I observed many customers names being called as food was being brought out while they were still getting their drink. 

On all of my visits the store was clean, well stocked and staffed and the food has been very good for a sandwich shop. For a quick lunch stop this is a good place to give a try. I will be back as my travels take me to Brentwood during a meal time.

text: I'm writing this review assuming you've been to a firehouse subs and like the sandwiches. I like to eat at firehouse back in Colorado and was in Nashville driving by the restaurant. I decided to try out a Nashville firehouse. Upon entering I was welcomed with a friendly greeting. The cashier took my order quickly and was very polite. The sandwich came out fast and the team member addressed me by name and asked if I needed anything. The sandwich was well prepared with plenty of meats. I stopped it off with a couple hot sauces each with a little variation on heat. Overall this is one of the best firehouse experiences I've had!!

text: So I went to this overpriced dump of a restaurant expecting little but wanting a quick sandwich. They sold me a combo, which included a drink. Then after paying I learned that they only had "diet" drinks (which I really don't like) and they had no ice. No mention of that situation when I ordered. When I complained about it, they simply said, "Sorry about that." But nothing was done to correct the situation. Then I sat down to eat my sandwich and was crawled all over by flies all through the meal. Even if you want something quick there must be better options than this place. Avoid it if you can.

text:
I got the hungries for a beef brisket sandwich, so my wife and I went to the nearby Firehouse subs and their beef brisket sub. When we first read the news that Firehouse intended to locate here we were thrilled , because that meant good sandwiches. This store did not disappoint.

I ordered their Smokehouse Beef  & Cheese Brisket sub. It looked as good as the one pictured on their website!! It would have been nice had the cheddar cheese been allowed to melt to embrace the meat, but it didn't.  I would have liked to have had a lot more brisket, but this is not a deli. All in all, it was a tasty, filling sandwich. My wife picked my old fav, their Pastrami sub. She seemed to enjoy it down to the last bite.

I was really impressed with the level of service today. That, and the food, are the reasons that we are long time customers. My sandwich, their Smokehouse Beef & Cheese Brisket sub, was a good deli-style sandwich, but a deli sandwich it isn't. In my opinion,Firehouse Subs is the best sub shop Nashville, but it's still just a chain sandwich shop, nothing more, nothing less. Three stars for Firehouse.

categories: American (New), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis, Burgers, Restaurants
text:
I KNOW THAT YOU CAN DO BETTER!

I am not a fan of purchased sandwiches simply because they just don't live up to my standards and that is not arrogance it just reflects my specific preference.  My husband decided that he wanted a sandwich and I specifically told him that I did not. He bought me one anyway.  It was a turkey sandwich with canned mushrooms, scant lettuce, scant tomatoes mayo and turkey.  Boring!!

I like my sandwiches hot and fully dressed.  This means that the bread needs to be toasted, the meat needs to be grilled, there should be a double serving of fresh vegetables added to include leafy greens such as spinach, or green lettuce, a sharp cheddar and a shot of balsamic vinegar.  I also will occasionally add mixed peppers, cucumbers or guacamole.  I would never have canned mushrooms added to my sandwich as they are frankly disgusting.  Of course my husband is aware of my mushroom rule but simply forgot to ask if the mushrooms are fresh.  Also, as far as I know, he has only eaten two Firehouse subs over the past 20 years and is not really familiar with their practices.

Unfortunately, I am away from home and cannot access my own kitchen to make my own sandwich so I appreciated my husband's thoughtfulness.  I removed the mushrooms from the sandwich and tried it.  I found it lacking in flavor and in need of additional vegetables and seasoning.   Firehouse needs to step it way up and commit to a better quality product.  

Choose carefully!

text:
Giving them the benefit of doubt( 2-stars) only because it was Memorial Day and I wouldn't want to be at work either...

Walk up to the register where there is an employee who makes eye contact with me and then quickly goes "heads down" staring into the register without saying anything for 1-2 minutes. A simple "Hi, can you give me one second" or any kind of acknowledgment would have been appreciated. Finally, she asks what I would like, to which I order the New York Steamer( meat, cheese, mayo, mustard, and Italian dressing). Specifically, I said I'd like the New York Steamer with no mayo or mustard. While looking at the screen on my end I see New York Steamer and then an indented minus or no mayo and no mustard pop up. While I'm reading/reviewing my order it changes to New York Steamer and the line below that is indented switches to "plain". I then clarify with the lady taking my order " The screen just switched to plain and I just want to clarify that I DO want Italian dressing on my sandwich just no mayo and no mustard". Oh yes, yep it will have Italian dressing on it... Got home to a plain sandwich with no Italian dressing. 

I love Firehouse but this location/experience literally left a bad taste in my mouth. Had the employees been friendly or remotely seemed like they had tried I would not be leaving this review but the overall lack of caring caused me to want to share. You're better than this, Firehouse!

text:
I chose Firehouse Subs after an intense workout at the CycleBar next door. I was feeling lightheaded and just needed a small bite. 

We were greeted as soon as we walked in the door by an employee sitting at a table by the door (likely the manager). The gal at the register seemed to be new, as aforementioned employee/manager helped her with my questions, but she was sweet and trying- good enough for me. 

The 4inch sub is a great option for a quick, small bite. It comes with a free pickle spear, which is always a plus. Service to the table was quick and the sandwich was tasty. 

The dining area and restrooms were clean, but the fluorescent lighting was harsh and unwelcoming. I certainly wouldn't want to spend more time in there than it takes to eat a 4in sub, but I'll definitely return for a to-go sandwich!

text: My gf already wrote a review for this place. By far the best sandwich 'chain' you will go to. I wouldn't even classify it as a chain tho. Way better than jersey mike's, and whatever else you may consider to be the best. Nortons and South Coast deli are more specialty sandwiches that taste no better than here and cost more. Plus, i can finish their sandwiches no problem. But at firehouse, my girlfriend and i always split. And we are stuffed after. Today we had a smoky spicy pork sandwich with bbq and holy crap. Excellent. If you're familiar with sb sandwiches, it's just as good if not better than plaza deli as well. So come here. Now. Do it.

text:
My boyfriend and I have made it our mission to try every new place opening up in IV. I wasn't particularly excited about another sandwich shop here because theres already about ten million of them in IV. However, this place really did prove me wrong...
First off, the decor is spot on. The tables are spotted like dalmatians and the walls have murals reppin' UCSB. Theres also firemen costumes that customers can wear and take pictures with. 
The service was also great. Everyone was friendly and attentive. All smiles.
We shared number 10: beef brisket (smoked for 16+ hours), melted cheddar, mayo, and sweet baby ray's bbq sauce. This was seriously sandwich heaven. The brisket (to my surprise) tasted superrr fresh and the thinly cut slices made it taste even better. Seriously though, just the meat alone got me to rate this place 5 stars. To top it off, the melted cheddar with bbq sauce really blew this place away...
They also have tons have different sauce bottles to try, my fav being the jalepeno hot sauce ones!
I can't wait to come back again to try their other subs!

text:
This place opened up in the bottom of my apartment building, and it's amazing! I've been here a handful of times now, but I've found myself dreaming of their subs every time I'm hungry. I'm not even someone who loves sandwiches that much, but something about this place really gets it right. The staff is always very friendly, and sometimes the order does take a while to come out, but they are heating up all the meat and everything, so I guess it's worth it.

I recommend the Club on the Sub (turkey, bacon, ham, Monterey Jack cheese) with everything (ask for oil, vinegar, salt/pepper). It's so good! I get a large and then save the second half for lunch the next day. I just finished this sandwich a few minutes ago, and I'm already wanting more!

text: I tried their veggie sandwich here and the cashier informed me that the mushrooms included in the sandwich were not vegetarian. I don't know why it wasn't but I excluded it from my order. First the sandwich did taste really good, it had lots of mayonnaise, cheese, onions and bell peppers which made an interesting tasty combo. The downside to this meal, was that when I went home I had a terrible stomach ache. With some further thinking, I conclude that this veggie sandwich was made sloppy and fatty with way too much mayonnaise and cheese, which tasted yummy, but was incredibly unhealthy. My friend's other meat sandwiches looked fine but mine was not as composed. Their toppings and the way they slathered on the fatty ingredients in my sandwich was immature, compared to better places like South Coast Deli. I would not come here again to avoid a stomach ache, but I guess if you had to eat here as vegetarian, the sandwich does not taste terrible.

text:
Update.  Closed in IV. Sad. 


More proof that this is the best food era, EVER for IV. Sure I miss Serranitos and the NY Hero House --but we now have more variety, price-points, and range of elegance than ever. Folks who don't live in IV ought to come here just for the dining. It's starting to remind me of the district in Paris around the Sorbonne. 

I am taking advantage of the spring break to get into IV to try out some of our newer spots. I was VERY impressed with Firehouse Subs. The place feels a little overly adorned, but it'll age well into the Isla Vista culture. 

But it is all about the food. At the suggestion of an employee, I tried the #10. I'm not an expert on brisket. But I doubt it could get much better than this. I enjoyed every bit of my seven dollar and one cent sandwich. 

I tried one of the salsas from their rack of sauces from around the world and I believe that the sun had broken it down -- it tasted a little like petroleum and vinegar. Maybe they ought to pull back on the salsa museum and further feature their own sauce--which is very, very good. 

What an excellent first experience. I'll be back to the firehouse. My message to their management--well done! Now ease up and enjoy yourself. You're getting an A.
