text: After coming home from my morning classes, I was starving. I had a coupon for Firehouse subs, which just recently opened and was founded by firemen. Since it was my first time there, I was given a walk through of the menu which included a turkey bacon sub ranch sub! Yum! I got the fully involved (fully loaded-mayo, mustard, lettuce, tomatoes, pickles..) engineer sub. It had smoked turkey, Swiss cheese, and sauted mushrooms. It was delicious and the portions were really generous. The service was fast and friendly. I will definitely be back soon.

text:
Firehouse Subs is as good as fast-casual gets. The restaurant is clean and smells great. Like many new restaurants in IV there's a theme, and you can guess what it is from the name. The theme permeates the restaurant in a way reminiscent of Disneyland, and it helps create a unique atmosphere inside without being obnoxious.

The franchise owner is often working on site, and he and his employees are always very friendly and accommodating. I don't expect I'll ever have an issue with bad service at Firehouse Subs.

Finally, the food - let me tell you it is GOOD. This is no Subway, Firehouse uses some really high quality meat in their subs. Seriously, like LA deli good. I've had four of their specialty subs and they were all fantastic and filling. If you're looking for the best sandwich joint in IV, Firehouse is it.

text: Well, Serena M. is obviously affiliated in some way with this restaurant (no random person goes in and takes a bunch of pictures) so I wouldn't trust that review. But you can trust mine! I went to Firehouse today because a girl gave me a coupon for a free sandwich at the pardall tunnel. This review is to thank them for that sub. Everything on the menu looked good. All the medium subs are 8" long and cost about $6.50 before tax. I just tried the turkey bacon sub and it was bomb. The firehouse setting is cool. Nice interior. I tried the "captains firehouse" on pardall last quarter and the sandwich tasted good but it was super soggy and cost $2 more. Fuck that place. If I had money to eat out, I would buy all my sandwiches at firehouse subs tho. I haven't tried sams to go though (yeah I know I am pathetic).

text:
First time here, and first time at any Firehouse Subs. Our medium subs (ham & cheese and Italian) were excellent: fresh bread, lightly toasted, and tasty ingredients. Our cashier was friendly and efficient. Whoever made the sandwiches did a superb job. A young man brought our sandwiches to our table with a big smile, and wanted to know if we needed anything else. Nope. We were quite content! 

The place is clean and bright. Lots of places to sit and eat. When you get your drink cup, you can choose from way too many selections. It's a newer drink machine than the one at AMC Woodlands & easier you use. 

Before we left we bought a 5 gallon pickle bucket without the pickles. All the money from the sale of these buckets goes to Tarpon Springs Fire Department. We also signed a Christmas greeting for firefighters from Firehouse Subs and their customers.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
text:
Awful, awful, awful!!! I just ordered from here and had it delivered through Uber Eats. The delivery service was great.... the food and even ordering process was TERRIBLE!!! When ordering, I read the descriptions for the sandwiches as my husband HATES and will not eat anything with mayonnaise on it. I was sure to pick a sandwich that had no mayonnaise on it. I also created my own sandwich for him for leftovers, obviously did not ask for mayo. In the comment section of both, I requested that they put jalapeos, salt & pepper, & vinegar & oil on the sandwiches...... NONE of those things were added to my sandwiches, I was given the wrong meat in the sandwich that I "created", and they REQUIRE you to order $1.99 drink with each sandwich. I tried to unclick the drink option but it even says next to it, REQUIRED. 
As a long time citizen of Tarpon Springs, I truly want to see these businesses succeed. However, after having to throw away all but $6.00 in drinks - which I didn't want in the first place- and 1 sandwich that was mediocre at best, I will certainly not be going back here!!! In fact, I'd give them a lower rating if it were possible!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
text:
I love leaving positive reviews and I really don't like leaving negative ones but sometimes you gotta do what you gotta do, I guess.  I have ordered from them through GrubHub two times this week both a little before 8 PM.  Both times they have said they'd gotten the order and they'd have my food to me within the hour.  Both times, two minutes later this Firehouse Subs location would cancel the order and the email explanation I got both times from GrubHub was that they are no longer accepting delivery orders?  I get when it's fifteen minutes before closing time, but over an hour before closing time?  I am curious if they lock the doors an hour before closing time.  Either way as someone who worked in food service for years and never stopped taking delivery orders until fifteen minutes (or 30 minutes at the most), I just don't understand why they can't make one sandwich for delivery with over an hour to go... I'm not saying it's a bunch of lazy teenagers just waiting to clock out and so they stop doing their job an hour before closing, but it is sure what it feels like.

Anyways, it is what it is, but I just had to put it out there because it's happened twice in a week and three times overall.  I mean, if you don't want to make money, why run a business?

text: Great subs. Way better than subway. Staff very friendly and fast. You get a free sub on your birthday which is awesome.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'"}
text:
When I first tried Firehouse I knew that I would never look at a Subway sandwich the same way. That still stands today. I will take Firehouse over any other sub. Their subs are delicious and made to order. I have two that I switch between 1) Firehouse Meatball sub and 2) Smokehouse Beef & Chedder Brisket.

The biggest difference between Firehouse and Subway is that Firehouse uses REAL MEAT. Not crappy, cheap processed packaged meat. Their meatballs are homemade. The meatball sub is smothered in melted cheese and seasonings. So good! The Beef & Cheddar Brisket has brisket, liquid cheddar, mayo and bbq sauce and will leave you craving this sandwich combination. 

Firehouse was also the first place to have the Coca-Cola Freestyle machines were you can mix your soda with different flavors (I like Grape Mellow Yellow or Orange Lemonade). 

This is definitely one of my favorite "fast food" places. I would definitely recommend trying them.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'"}
text:
This location always greets you with a cheery welcome to Firehouse. The dining room is clean and spacious.  The staff is always very friendly. On this particular visit I had just left the doctor (woke up and could not hear in my right ear) and they were very patient with me while trying to communicate as I did not know how loud I was talking and felt very awkward.   They also accommodated me when I told them that I was going to dash to the Starbucks next door while the prepared my sandwich. 

The good thing about Firehouse is their subs.  My two favorites are the Hook & Ladder and the Steak & Cheese.   Today I had the Steak & Cheese which is a lot like a Philly.  The Steak & Cheese has that meaty, sink your teeth in it sensation, topped with sauted onions and bell peppers.  This is a hearty sandwich that I find very satisfying.  This time, which I did not try perhaps next visit, they offered mushrooms which sounds like a wonderful combination. One addition I like to do with this sandwich is add A-1 Steak Sauce which really adds a nice zing. 

One thing that Firehouse offers that is kind of an "in your face" secret is they have a multitude of sauces (hot sauces, steak sauces, etc.) that are readily available for your selection.  If you are doing a carry-out they offer "to go" sauce cups for your convenience (they are sturdy and do not seem to come part easily which protects against those accident explosions that can happen).

Definitely give this place a try.  I think it is good for families and kids.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'"}
text:
For a chain sandwich shop, the food was pretty good.
When you ask for double meat here, you better be prepared for it, I am used to other chains were they skimp on the meat but when I doubled my meat at Firehouse i could barely fit the sandwich in my mouth!

The food was good, better than other chain subs I've had, the menu didn't have anything really inspiring and the layout had that generic chain feel to it.

all in all, if your in the mood for something quick and decent, there not half bad, just don't expect to be wow'd.

text: I like some of the sandwiches here, however, they really need to work on customer service.  Ordering was akin to being interrogated...many questions asked in rapid-fire succession while the cashier was also attempting to hold a conversation with her co-worker.  Once I'd paid, I was lucky enough to have a front row seat to hear the employees griping about their working conditions/management.  As for the finished product, my sandwich was assembled nicely but lacked any distinctive flavor.  There is definitely a lot of room for improvement.

text: I had the beef brisket cheddar sub today, which I've had several times before. It was the fattiest worst sub I've ever had in my entire life. text: This was my preferred Firehouse location however not anymore.  The food is standard Firehouse but since what I presume is new management and new employees I will no longer visit this location.  The staff have had inappropriate conversations in the presence of customers discussing labor laws they believe are being violated by the company.  The kicker for me is you can't walk in the front door without walking through a cloud of smoke from an employee smoking outside the front door.  I've seen the employees doing this on several occasions which has lead me to find another location even though this one is closest to me.

text: Just swung by on our way from South Florida back home to North Tampa and my husband and son said it was the best service they've had in a long time at any restaurant. Not going to lie but it was a really good sandwich; it was also a pretty basic sandwich, by no fault of theirs. 

My only draw back was for meat, cheese and lettuce the combo came out to a little over $10 -- something about the price seemed way too high for everything to had been so simple. 

I was also given spicy brown mustard which I don't care for not did I ask. I asked for yellow mustard (this is me just being detailed, not complaining lol)... 

I was short on time and the service was really quick and efficient. Sandwich was hot and neat. So no real complaints.

text:
Stopped in for a quick lunch. I'm low carb (depending on the day) and appreciate the option to get a salad.

I got the grilled chicken Italian salad with extra chicken and peppercorn ranch. HUGE SALAD, fresh ingredients and great taste.

The main reason for my rating, is the service. Both women working were so nice, so helpful. They walked us through our options and even walked around to the tables and asked us how we liked everything. They were genuinely happy to help. You just don't come across workers like that anymore, else during these times. 

If we are ever over in the area again, I will definitely go back!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
This location deserves 5 stars for the food quality, taste, and service.

But the price?  1 star at best!

For years now, I enjoyed the FH Italian sub.  It is unique and very tasty.

Their posted menu sizes/prices are a bit deceptive here?  If you order a sub, you get a "regular" size at the posted price.  Hungry?  Want a "large?"

Then make SURE you notice and read the fine print on the menu wall for the $2.50 markup for a LARGE, 12-inch size sub!  This markup used to be just $2, but it increased along with all their other prices.

To conclude, I ordered just 1 large 12-inch Hero sub and 1 large 12-inch Italian sub...

No chips, no drink, no combo - just 2 large subs.  All cold-cut subs, NO fancy grilled cheese-steak stuff, no special "sub-of-the-month" and still...  My total was $19.24?  Really?

I know you offer better quality than Subway and other sub joints, that is why I used to enjoy coming here and gladly paid a bit more.  But now?

Geez, I can get a monster Italian sub from Jersey Mike's just minutes SE of here, and for about $5 less than this order.  Plus, JMS always slices their deli meats fresh-to-order, and their mini/regular/giant sub prices are clearly posted!

I used to love FH, but there are many nearby offerings, both local and chain, that make FH's current sandwich size/pricing gimmick seem silly now.

Calling Capt. Sorensen!  This joint almost set my wallet on fire!!

(Thankfully, I was able to put it out and will now forever seek my submarine fix elsewhere...)

text:
I love an Italian sub, and Firehouse has my absolute favorite. They don't have a ton of toppings, but you really don't need it because the sub has so much flavor already. I always get their wheat bread, it's tasty.

No matter what deli meat you choose, it is always moist. Many other chain sub shops have dry lunch meat. That's what makes Firehouse standout in my opinion.

If you have room for a sweet snack, their chocolate chip cookies are delicious!

text: I am a big fan of Firehouse and was looking for a quick lunch option after a movie.  This location was great - clean dining area, friendly and fast staff, and the same great tasting options I've come to love.  I love the Coke Freestyle machine and often go for Firehouse's own cherry limeade blend but felt more like a Diet Coke with Lime.  My Turkey Bacon Ranch sub was hot and delicious.  Like every Firehouse, there was a tv going in the dining area, but the volume was low enough that I wasn't distracted from my book.  Good food and fast, thanks Firehouse!

text:
First time here. Ordered an Italian sub with extra onions. Take out. By the time I arrived home the mushy sub was soggy. Being from NJ, I have never had a sub that was heated.Except a meatball one. No extra onion. The only evidence of cheese was indistinguishable from the gob of mayo on the roll.
My wife and I split it and am sorry to say we both had "the green apple trots" next day. Can't wait till Jersey Mikes opens later this month across the street. They know how to make a proper sub. Bread made in house, meat sliced fresh in front of you and the sub made before your eyes.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
I have been to this store several times for pick up, there're couple of times while I was there, the employees were arguing in front of customers, once I walked in there  an employee was arguing with her coworkers and not doing her job, I was there for almost an half hour and almost the whole time they were arguing, I wondered why the orders has been taken so long, and no manager could stepped up to take care the f the situation. Friday right afternoon time I walked in the store for a pick up, seemed a little busy, few customers waiting, and there's an order on the pick up shelf that was ready for customer, so I approached and tried to look at the bag on the shelf and see if that's my pick up, the label on the bag was not flat so I used one finger to flatten the label so I could see the name on the bag, (I was wearing a clean glove and mask), this blonde girl worker yelled loudly "Don't touch the food"! I applied " I wasn't touching the food in the bag, I used one finger flattened the label so I could see the name for it", she acted aggressively angry and said " Don't touch the food, I have to protect my customers" again, I said "I did not touch the food, just verify the name on the label" and I asked what is her name, she yelled " what is your name and I told her, she could never told me her name, instead she said" I will make sure you don't ever come in this store again"!!! Seriously??? What a ridiculous and obnoxious act toward customer!!! Accusing and insulting the customer, is this allowed in the customer service? I have been in the hospitality industry for many years and have never seen one treated customers like this, what a terrible act to treat a human being! Wonder how many customers she had ran away and how many more will be?! Of course I walked and never look back! Sounded like the delivery drivers can't pick up the food from this store and deliver to their customers then, because all the drivers have to "touch" the bag to be able to deliver to their customers! 
Totally nonsense act!!!

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
I am underwhelmed by my experience here at Firehouse.  I entered and when normally the staff shouts welcome, it quiet. Not that I need fanfare, but if that is the business' welcoming, then it should be done everytime (ok off the soapbox).

I asked about a few menu items and got stale answers from the young man at the register. I ordered my medium sub, and he just gives me a blank look and asks, "Is that it?" I'm sorry, I was giving you a chance to type that in. He never tried to upsell me, he was over it. I got a drink and bag of chips and my total was just shy of $11.

So the young lady starts to make the sub, and a known person to the staff comes in and everything stops and everyone of the staff congregate to this person. I'm being selfish, but I'm on my lunch break and you all have received my $11 for the food. Please make it so I can go back to work...

Ugh...I could have ran to the border, gone to where they got the meat, seen the little red headed girl or should have gone to Publix for better tasting food and service.

Just hate spending money with apathetic people making and serving the food.

I haven't been in awhile and my last visit was definitely my LAST visit. They have incredibly rude employees who act like you are invisible.  I must have stood at the register for a good 2 minutes while the employees finished their conversation. The gentleman with the glasses was the only one concerned with actually trying to help customers. The shorter-haired mouthy girl making sandwiches needs to calm down and relax. She has a very poor attitude and you can tell that it sets the tone for everyone else. 
The order I was given was incorrect, the food was poorly made, and the customer service is a joke. I would definitely recommend taking your business elsewhere.

text: So to start off my experience while walking in to the store at 5:45 I was greeted outside by someone chaining up the chairs. He informed me due to New Years they were closing in just a few minutes and without saying so told me to go eat somewhere else. I decided they were still open for the next 15 minutes so I would still order but get it to go. After ordering my three sandwiches to go an employee by the name of Joanne walked out, looked at the order screen, loudly sighed and rolled her eyes. I called her out on it and. Said wow you don't look happy. Her response was she was tired. The other employee that took the order said it had been a long day. Honestly the store closing at 6 means you take customers until 6. If you don't want people coming in and giving you business I can easily get a sandwich elsewhere in the future. Food from my experience here is good but the service tonight was terrible

text: The experience here is more attributed to the staff on duty.  They had a gal working the counter that appeared to have a disability but did a fantastic job.  The females there were very mean to her and even laughed about it a few times.  I had to leave before I made a scene.  The subs were not good.  My husband ordered the steak and beer cheese sub and it had about 2 ounces of meat on it.  I ordered the italian sub and it was ham and a piece of pepperoni, I think.  The gal slammed it down in front of me, I said thank you and she just walked off, said nothing.  We will not be back and I hope the owners check up on these employees.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}"}
text: I'm not really sure what it is that the other comments left here are really talking about let me tell you one thing this place is great if you're just looking for a tiny snack super overpriced the sandwiches themselves are tasty but super over price you're paying about 9 to $11 depending on the sandwich to get what you see on the picture if you decide to get double meat it's $3 more which to me it's outrageous when you should be already giving while you portray on your menu the place is very cool to go look at if you're looking for a change of scenery but given the other options that you have around being way more affordable and tastier I go with Peter Piper Red Lobster or even subway because at least at Subway you'll be full once you eat your meal something they truly need to work on its being faster at making the sandwiches when we were there and there was literally three other couples in the joint two of them already had their food and it still took over 30 minutes for us together subs... subs for goodness sakes not a steak meal tops we shouldn't wait more than 15 minutes for something to come out plus the people that take your order act like you should know what you're getting excuse me but this is a new restaurant and I'm not even sure what I'm going to get please don't rush me when I'm trying to place my order oh yeah and then they offer you to change your side without telling you that an extra charge to change them you go to subway and you choose a soup over your chips there might be iffy but they let you know going here was the worst experience I would change my review if I have a better experience 6 months from now when I decide to go again and waste yet again $30 to feed a family of 3 at a fast food restaurant!!!!

text:
2 adults, friday night, 6 pm, not busy, ordering slow, only one cashier, tables were not clean, doing maintenance on the coke machine, only medium prices posted, yet cashier tried to upsell to a large. Cashier asked if we wanted a pickle, feels like cost saving, other store just gave us a pickle spear. Wife thought the woman cashier was kind of rude.

One combo, one just the sandwich,

Have been to other Firehouse around town, positive experiences. Been waiting for this one cause it is close to where we live. The amount of meat is much less here than we had at another Firehouse. After eating a whole sub, did not feel full.

No compelling reason to come back.

text:
This is a great addition to Spectrum.  There hasn't been many choices here for a quick bite.
I was impressed with Firehouse Subs!  The store has fun items to look at & the kids get a fire hat!  It was clean, too! 
Contrary to other reviews, the service was great! The cashier was very attentive, explained the menu & told us about their loyalty program.  She checked in on us later to see if everything was okay. 
We ordered the Turkey/Bacon Ranch and the New York  Steamer.  We opted for the meals so we got chips & a soda.  The total was around $20.  The prices are more than Subway,  but it is defiantly worth it! The New York Steamer was great - highly recommended!

text:
The only thing that was good on our visit is the coke machine. 

Subs were all made wrong even after the staff remade one of them. Still made wrong. If I am spending 4o bucks for my family of 4 to eat. I would like to have at least 1 person leave feeling happy and satisfied. Yet, that didn't occur this evening for us. SAVE YOUR MONEY & AVOID this place.

  I never complain however, our food was so bad I will be personally emailing the businness. Please have your staff understand the subs they are making. One sub was the New York steamer. It had zero dressing tons of mayo :( and no mustard. In fact even sandwiches ordered with no mayo had mayo on both sides. 

The smokehouse brisket meat has good flavor the sub came with next to no BBQ sauce. 

The salad lettuce is wilted. Very very nasty. As if the side salad had been sitting pre-made for a week.

text: I had an awful experience here tonight. When I arrived at firehouse subs there was about 5 people sitting down eating and maybe one customer in line. My friend and I ordered our food and waited almost 20 minutes for it to arrive and when the food arrived it was not what I had ordered. When I brought the sandwich back to the counter I told them why it was wrong and explained exactly what I wanted. they said it was unintentional and was someone else's food and mine would be out shortly. At this point we were going to be late to our destination and had the sandwiches wrapped Togo so we could eat them in the car. Upon opening our sandwiches not ONLY was my sandwhich wrong again, but my friends was as well. My friend asked for all the dressings for her Italian sandwhich on the side and it was completely drenched. In addition to this the bread on both sandwhiches was so unappetizingly soggy we ended up not even eating our meal. Overall a horrible experience and will not be going back.

text: We happened on this place while running some errands on the south side of town.  We were starving and decided to have lunch here.  Hubby and I both loved it!  The dcor is so cute.  The mural on the wall was very Tucson-centric with one firefighter with a sombrero on!  We shared the Virginia  -baked ham sub - fantastic!  The bread was especially good - it was so soft, and lightly toasted - just perfect!  You can get the sub with what it comes with or add your own toppings.  We also got the mac and cheese side - that was just ok - I wasn't a fan of the bread crumbs on top. There are a lot of good side options, next time, I think we'll go for the chili since it is a firehouse!  They also had plastic fire hats for the kids!  It was fun!

text: We took our grandsons for a last day of school lunch to Firehouse subs. This is our favorite sandwich place, by far. Fantastic subs that can be customized with many ingredients. Prices are great, food is fresh and tasty, service is always friendly ! Hook and Ladder is probably my favorite, but all of the sandwiches are great. Make sure to sign up for the "club" and they have a great App to install on your phone. Firehouse beats all the "usual" sub sandwich fast food outlets. Once you try it - you'll be "hooked" too !

text:
My first try at a Firehouse Subs and I was not disappointed.  Sure, I like the veggie sandwich at Subway and I've been known to eat an Italian hero at Port o Subs, bit neither compadre to the Pastrami Reuben I had today.  For a sub shop, I really enjoyed it.  (Of course, it's not a "real deli" sandwich, but it was good. The pastrami was lean and tender and the slaw was pretty tender.  My friend enjoyed her steak sandwich. 

The cater and have salad options and a kids menu

Plus they donate and collect to provide emergency equipment to our first responders ... firefighters & ENTs

Want a quick sandwich... check them out

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}"}
text: I went in yesterday for a late lunch, mid afternoon.  I was the only customer in there.  When I went to the counter, I noticed no plexiglas shield LIKE EVERY OTHER RETAIL ESTABLISHMENT IN TOWN at the cash register, the woman at the counter had no mask and no gloves LIKE EVERY OTHER FOOD PLACE IN TOWN.  That made me realize that, even though they make a good sandwich, and I go there probably once a month, I would not be ordering any food there until that changes.  Oh, and on my way out, even though there were NO CUSTOMERS in the place, I saw that there were at least two tables with scraps of shredded lettuce on them which tells me they had  NOT cleaned and sanitized them which in this time of protecting the customer and themselves, it wasn't high on the priority list.   Come on, you can do better than that.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}"}
text: I had a great experience at this location. I was honestly a little discouraged by the negative reviews but I decided to stop in anyways and I'm glad I did. I went on a Monday afternoon and the first thing I noticed was the greeting as soon as I walked in :) friendly staff. The guy making the sandwiches even greeted a couple people by name which is always nice. I got the turkey, bacon, ranch and it was delicious. The bread was nice and soft and the sandwich was perfectly put together. I love that you get a pickle on the side! Also they have a pretty nice selection of chips which is awesome. Nice clean tables, the outside patio was also clean. Only thing I would say is that for the size of the subs it's a tiny but pricey but not too crazy. Would definitely be back.

text: These guys have the best subs of any chain! The bread is nice and moist and it won't fall apart. The meats are always juicy and tender and the service is fenomenal! Best part of this location is that if you also want a more substantial dessert than the cookie they offer you can walk a short distance to Coldstone creamery. We enjoy coming here after a movie. Best part is that they'll ask you to round up to the dollar and will donate that money to local fire departments.

text:
I normally have really good experiences at different fire houses that I've gone to across the country; today was a little bit different there was only one person ahead of me that was getting two sandwiches the cashier waited on me and she was actually very friendly and helpful; but once my order was placed and they were supposed to make my sandwich I couldn't understand why it would take 20 minutes for one sandwich when the place was not that busy, as I mentioned only one person was ahead of me and he had two sandwiches.
I should've known better and checked my bag before I got home because I didn't even get my pickle spear, what a bummer and I really like their pickles.
Hopefully next time I go it won't be a trainee making the sandwiches because that could be the reason why it took so long and the reason why I didn't get my pickle.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}"}
text: We were greeted 30 minutes before closing time with rolled eyes from a spunky little girl who couldn't get customer service right if it hit her in the face.  The second teeny bop, maybe the shift manager, came to take our order. She got the job done but again with an attitude.  Food done...spunky Brewster handed it to me in a paper bag as if we were taking it to go.  Already told the lady that took the order we'd be dining in.  Spunky made it clear that we should leave as they close in 15 minutes.  I said no, we're eating here and we won't keep you a second beyond your closing time.  An audible millennial ugh from her and rolled her eyes again.  We sat, ate our cold food that should have been hot and left five minutes before closing time.  The teenagers at the table with me were more respectable than the three girls manning the restaurant that evening.  Horrible display of Firehouse taste and Firehouse virtues.

text:
Love Firehouse Subs! So happy they opened one up closer to home. Bar none better than Subway, Quizno's, Jimmy John's or Jason's Deli sandwiches! 

Brand new location near the Harkins Theater in the Calle Santa Cruz plaza off the I-19. Great place to meet before or after a movie for a bite. Very spacious, great for groups...The staff was very nice & friendly, and welcomed everyone that came through the doors! 

Loved the decor too! A tribute to firemen & policemen & first responders, the interior design is cool & fun to see! 

Now if you haven't had a Firehouse sub or salad before, you'll absolutely enjoy one! So much flavor, and they don't skimp on the toppings!

Definitely gonna continue coming back for more....

text:
Firehouse has become my favorite sub place for the ease of look-n-point-by-picture ordering. Even at busy times, the food quality is consistently good, consistently hot, and consistently moving at a fast pace. They have enough variety to keep me trying me things despite my favorites. The staff are attentive, knowledgeable, and darn near psychic.

Just be warned that their largest sub is one of those meals that lasts you all day.

Bring back the turkey and cranberry sub!

text:
This is by far the best sandwich chain in Tucson. The ingredients are absolutely amazing and all of the meat is cooked much better than one could find at Eegees, Subway or Quiznos. The caveat is that the better ingredients have a little of a premium and are slightly more expensive, but you absolutely get what you pay for and it is worth it.
This place does brisket better than many expensive restaurants, and their proprietary cherry limeade drink is incredible. 
This location is pretty new and very clean with good service. Go check it out now!

text: The place was really clean and new, which is nice. Everyone working there was really friendly, too. Had the turkey & cranberry "lighter fare" sandwich which was super tasty. They do a "steam heat" thing, so the turkey was very moist and yummy. I think there was too much meat on the sandwich compared to cranberry sauce, but otherwise a good lunch. The cups were HUGE and the combo meal cost about $10 total. A bit expensive for a sandwhich, bag of chips, and soda, but really tasty.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Restaurants, American (Traditional), Sandwiches, Fast Food, Delis
text:
Its my first time here... I thought another deli sandwich shop...  But it was like being in the twilight zone and i into a New York deli.   The place was vast and clean.   The variety of sandwiches seemed endless with make your own option.   They had a few suggested sandwiches on the menu,  the usual club, tuna turkey.   Then they have their specials like hook and ladder and the engineer...  U have to go there to find out what they are.  They gave me a sample of their corned beef deli and it was freshly cut and delicious.    The club sandwich I had was amazing!   A nice fresh baked it seemed bread with a warm core.  The contrast in temperature gave a curious and inviting flavor to everything....   Hard to describe.   The sauce was sweet yet tangy with a heaping pile of meats nestled between the lettuce and tomatoes.   Just the right ratio of sub bread meet sauce and veggies.   It was truly delicious 
Highly recommend for a new York in Tucson sandwich shop.

text:
The single best FHS I've ever been to.  From the moment you enter, they're friendly and attentive, to the moment you sit down to eat, they're made well and fresh as can be.  

The manager and staff was extremely nice, the restaurant was immaculately clean and the food was truly fresh!  A++

Well worth the extra money to eat here over Subway.  And I love Subway as well!

P.S. - My 2.5 year old daughter cried when we left!  They were extremely nice to her!

text: I always like to try new places and especially new sub shops. I use East Coast Subs as the bench mark for steak and cheese subs. The FH steak and cheese does not hold a candle to ECS. I had it with grilled mushrooms and onions. The mushrooms are canned and not grilled, the onions were cooked but not grilled. The steak was torn up roast beef or similar. It was not steak, it was tough and dry. The store is cute and clean and the crew was friendly and attentive. I will give them one more try to see how the Italian compares to Sausage Deli.

text: At a time when so many businesses are struggling and not a lot of people are dining in, it is sad to walk into an establishment and be treated like a burden. This is the second time we had a negative experience at this location. The (manager?) Ariel had a negative attitude and when my husband asked some questions about the combos she was visibly irritated and annoyed which made the experience uncomfortable. We realized that the small sandwiches were too small even for a little kids so my husband went back up to the counter to order another one and I heard her say a smart remark which I will not repeat. Probably won't return.

text: decided to try firehouse subs as they are close and were on my way home.  i ordered the club on the sub and i made 2 customizations.  one of the reasons i ordered that sub, was i wanted a hot sub and it is listed as such.  i got there are the exact time my order was to be ready.  got it home and the sub was stone cold; there was not a hint of heat anywhere.  there was way too much turkey and mayo and the bacon, well i couldn't even taste it.  i looked and there was half a slice.  so technically i got a turkey sub with a half piece of bacon as the ham was minimal as well and the mayo really overwhelmed the sub.  to say it was a disappointment would be an understatement.  the girls who were working the counter could also work on their customer service skills.  not especially friendly or courteous.  won't be recommending anyone go there soon.

text: I enjoyed my first time at Firehouse Subs! They made sure to enforce safety measures by enforcing masks and social distancing while inside the restaurant. There was inside seating, but tables and chairs were separated at a healthy distance. The customer service was great and my sub was absolutely delicious. 10/10 I highly recommend and will definitely be back! My sub also came with a pickle which was a nice surprise!

text:
Friendly staff, place was clean and the sandwiches tasted great. Unlike the other location in Tucson this one knows how to use the proper amount of condiments to make the food taste well and not soggy. 

The only negative I saw is the guy wiping tables used the same rag the whole time and never rinsed it.

text: First time we ordered from here ,sad to say you blew it!! Ordered mayo and lettuce only on my sub and got the works was able to pick off the onion and the tomato but the brown mustard not so much... who the hell puts brown mustard on a sub anyway?? So shout out to any one else who doesn't like brown mustard don't eat here because even if you don't order it your going to get it!!

text:
Was it the mood for something maybe a little bit healthier and so we went past firehouse subs and decided to give it a whirl. It was not a normal time to get food for there was virtually nobody in the place. It was nice and clean though. I liked the patio area. 

I tried the spicy Cajun chicken with the loaded soup. It was pretty good. The service was professional and nice. Price was alright. I like the idea of supporting emergency services. Overall it was good and I'd have it again. Not my top for sandwich places.

text: I'm a frequent customer. Now probably not for awhile, if ever again. Called in a one sandwich order. I spoke clearly as to what I wanted. I live 5 minutes away.  The sandwich was made wrong and cold. I asked for no onions and  no lettuce. I got no tomatoes and big onions. And It was cold. I called to let the manager know. How convenient, he was busy. The receipt clearly says no onions and no lettuce.

text: My husband and I love firehouse subs and since we moved to Delaware we have been missing them greatly! We have visited the Brookhaven store multiple times when we get a craving. The staff there is friendly and the owner is very personable. He stops by every table to check on the guests. We will be back many times!

text: Basically a Subway with fewer options. Sandwich was good but nothing special. Partner's order was messed up twice. The second time he just let it go because he was hungry. They were really nice about it but how hard is it to make a sandwich?

text: I walked in the door with my family and was greeted with a giant welcome. The rolls were so soft they melted in your mouth and a welcomed surprise. I ordered the meatball sub and it was phenomenal. Other members of my family were raving about the hook and ladder sub. I'll definitely be coming back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text:
Really disappointed I couldn't read any of the reviews on Yelp. This was the first time I ate at firehouse subs, I loved it. Every ingredient was fresh, and the meat had no freezer burnt taste. I know it is odd to tout that in a review but that is my pet peeve with all the sub places. Also the chicken I had was perfect and the meatball the boyfriendhad was apparently ummummmummm - since he was too busy stuffing his mouth to stop and chat. Lol!!

And they have a host of hot sauces to add to your sub. I tried a 7, 8 and 9.

text:
The food was good and the staff was pleasant. The owner is very rude and condescending to his staff. He barked at the cashier for not explaining the menu fast enough, even though we tried to explain that we were just looking over the selections. 
I will never patronage this business again until the owner learns how to treat his staff

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: Stopped by on a Saturday afternoon because we were in the area driving by. We ordered a make your own veggie. We were new, but they were friendly helping us order. We did have to wait a few minutes, but when we got our subs we could tell why. The cheese was melted into and sauted with chopped onions and the bread was soft and warm. The jalapeos were spice like we like them, and they had maybe about forty hot sauce bottles to choose from! We were very satisfied with the meal. The staff was extremely friendly, too; we were thanked for waiting and asked several times if our meals were ok. GREAT service! Would stop by if in the area again.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'"}
text: I love this place! The business motto is awesome. I thought it was just called firehouse subs because of the decor but I'm happy to support business that give back. You can tell they put a lot of work behind the ingredients they use. Best subs in town! Can't even think about subway anymore...there's no going back after you go to firehouse.

text:
When I ordered my 1 medium steamer he asked me if I wanted to make it a combo. I replied " no thank you". Whereupon he said "are you sure you don't want chips and something to drink?"  
Uhhhhhh, I politely already said no thank you. 
When I gave him a 50 to pay for just my sand which. He could not change a $50 bill at lunchtime (12:10) PM. How can you not have money in the til to do business? 
That's standard operating. 
When returning my 50 to He frankly acted like I was the problem. 

In addition to my steamer I was going to order 4 subs as combos for my visiting family so he lost $40 in one lunchtime check !
***** Rude  service!!!!!        I went across the street to BK and they took my $50 with a smile.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Ok, let me preface this review by saying that I generally love this place. However we got there about 30 minutes before closing, and the Manager, Tim, told us they close at 9. We figured we could wolf down the sandwiches and be out a little after closing.

Well, it took them about 12 minutes to make the sandwhiches. When they were ready, a kid care over and asked if we would mind taking our sandwiches to go. We asked if we had a choice and as politely negative as he could, he said they were really behind tonight.

I HAVE NEVER, EVER, BEEN ASKED TO LEAVE A DINING ESTABLISHMENT AT EXACTLY CLOSING TIME, LET ALONE A FEW MINUTES BEFORE!!! 

I realize these guys are hourly and it was Friday night, but come on. This is your idea of customer service? Faced with the possibility of having to try to eat rather juicy subs in the car, we abandoned the rest of our planned shopping trip and took the food home.

I can't really blame Tim, the manager. Hopefully he has no aspirations toward a successful career in restaurant management. I have to blame the person who gave him permission to bar the doors at 9, or the person who gave him the authority to make the decision on his own.

Next time we're in that neighborhood after 8 PM, we're probably not going to chance stopping in at Firehouse. We'll go to Cane's (in the same parking lot) for some very good chicken tenders. The don't close until 10 or 11.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
We stopped here for lunch today --- it was satisfying and good, but overall we weren't too impressed. 

We say 3.5 overall, we bumped to a 4 instead because of the extensive add ons you can put on your sandwiches (above and beyond the normal LTO, they had a variety of hot peppers and other veggies you could add, free of charge). We are big time hot sauce lovers, so we were excited to see the selection of over 30 different sauces to mix and match. 

I got brisket, it was good --- but lacked the smokey brisket taste I was hoping for. Also, at the last minute the soda machine broke and only offered diet drinks which bums be out because I don't drink (nor like)diet! This left me with only water and iced tea to drink. The staff was rather unfriendly, but that wasn't a huge deal since you order at the register and they aren't serving us.

We will come back, but I wouldn't make a special trip for the food here.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I am so glad we finally have a Firehouse in STL! I know this location has been open for a few months, but I finally made it this past weekend and I am so glad it's here! 

I used to order from Firehouse all the time when I was living in Florida; it was my favorite sandwich shop! I told a friend of mine (also from FL) about this location and so we had to go! I arrived on a Saturday afternoon around 2 pm and the place was pretty steady with customers. I already knew what I was going to order and my friend was ready too! 

The girl at the register was friendly and took our orders quickly. The guys making the sandwiches were working fast and seemed to have a good system down. I was so excited for my sandwich. We also ordered some chips and a drink. The drink machine is that really cool one where you can create flavors for your soda; lots of fun! 

The restaurant itself had a good vibe and looked clean. I didn't stay to eat since I had to be somewhere, but when I finally ate my sandwich it was still warm and delicious. 

I can't wait to go back!

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Usually I'm not one to rave about a business unless it's made a very good first impression,  this is going to be one of those kinds of reviews.

Firehouse Subs was awesome, and thats good coming from me when it comes to hot sandwich shops as I'm not a big fan of hot subs.  I'm one of the pickiest eaters around, so finding something on the menu to satisfy my tastes was a delight.

They have a nice selections of sandwiches to satisfy everyone's tastes, and they come in a few different sizes and prices.   I ended up ordering the beef and cheddar brisket sandwich.

I got the combo that included chips and a drink and the price was comparable to other sub shops.
The sandwich was ready fairly quick and i was ready to indulge.

The sandwich was hot and delicious as it could be,  and each bite was as satisfying as the one before, topping off my good experience with flying colors.

The counter service was friendly, and i wasn't rushed when looking over the menu to order,  which is always a nice touch.  Will most definitely return, for hopefully another satisfying experience..

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
We were at Target and decided to check this place out. I had read a little bit about it and knew that it was founded by 2 firefighters in Florida. I knew going in I would be limited with food options because I just recently decided to try to be gluten free and pescatarian.

Anyhoo, the staff was super friendly and informative and the place was clean.

As for food, I would say this place is VERY limited for non meat eating and/or gluten free people. Which is not their fault or their problem. I was only here to check it out with the bf. The bf had The Engineer: smoked turkey breast, melted Swiss, and sauted mushrooms, served Fully Involved (which means mustard, mayo, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a pickle on the side). He said it was good but  not great and he didn't seem too impressed. However, I think he is bitter about his recently gained food allergy to red meat and pork. I was stuck with a salad which was fine but nothing to write home about. It was a Chef Salad minus the meat (they did charge a little less for no meat, which is cool): Fresh romaine, iceberg, bell pepper, cucumber, red onion, tomato, provolone, sliced egg, and your choice of: Virginia honey ham, sliced chicken, tuna salad, chicken salad, or smoked turkey breast. It was mostly iceberg. 

They do have a nice selection of hot sauces in varying degrees of heat level.

So this place is fine for a quick and easy bite and definitely worth checking out but with my current dietary choices I will not be seeking it out anytime soon.

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
SOMEONE CALL THE FIRE DEPARTMENT !!!

Firehouse Subs delivers the goods. All the meat tastes so fresh. Standing out most has to be cool theme on-site, including an ENCYCLOPEDIA of SAUCES, for customer leisure. Inside shop appearance clean with attentive sandwich artists.

New York Steamer(Large) on wheat, sending me to the Tastebud Palace. Standard dressed and just phenomenal. No questions or concerns, arguably my favorite sandwich here. 

Instead of the normal styrofoam, TO-GO box procedures are cutting edge. A cardboard-type encasement houses the sub blissfully. Form fitting with room to breathe, stopping the soggy-sandwich effect in its TRACKS ! 

***Firehouse puts the SMOKE out in your appetite. Timely results and final product justifies the inflated pricing. A franchise in its infancy, my first choice for a quick lunch***

text: Gf orders us both subs (I am not there) I just want lettuce meat and cheese.  She comes homes with a sub full of mayo.  So she calls this Hampton village firehouse and tells them the issue and they say come back.  So we come right back and give them the defective sub and tell them just lettuce meat and cheese (very simple) on the sub.  Well, low and behold we receive another sub with sauce on it as I opened the wrapper before we left.  Lemay counter girl says "oh you want it dry you did not say that"  I am truly amazed at this point and told her ma'am I said lettuce, meat and cheese only.  The entire time she gave me an attitude. I asked for the owner/manager to contact me but that never happened.  Stick to fighting fires instead of making subs. Fellow sub lovers, Avoid this location!!! I wish I could give negative stars.  And way too much bread add more meat!

attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I was hesitant to try this place, as the pictures of the sandwiches on the website didn't appeal to me for one reason or another. I sort of thought it was going to be another Quizno's or something. Too much meat, too much seasonings, ech, no thank you. I am also not the biggest fan of hot sandwiches. They kinda skeeve me out. 

GUYS. This place is freaking awesome. We've (embarassingly) come here 3x in the last 5 weeks - don't judge us, we just had a baby and don't have much time to make food. I have only ordered the pastrami sandwich because I can't get it out of my head it is so yummmmm. The quality of the meat is top notch - this is coming from a deli meat snob face. 
Hubs has gotten the philly, which was superb, and now the club on a sub, which was also great.

Also - yeah, the beverage machine is definitely from the future. And let me tell you, the future has limitless soda flavor options. Which I think we can all agree is something that has been seriously lacking in the present.

text:
I will start out with 4 stars after my first visit.The staff recommended the brisket and I took their advice.I really enjoyed their branded barbecue sauce.
I found it very strange that they had about 50 different types of hot sauces.I am not sure what menu items one would put hot sauces on as there entire menu is "subs".I guess that this is their differentiation from other sub shops. 
I will be back to try other items , it looks like they have steam machines and call the steamed subs " hot subs".They also have some salad options that I am looking forward to trying.
I am classifying this new place in the subway category, may not be fair because I have not tried the lunch meats yet but the brisket was along the quality of Arby's.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
After trying to eat at the location in Audubon (which seems to be closed permanently now, given the "thanks for your patronage" sign I saw on the other side of the locked door), we decided to make the trip to the one in Montgomeryville. A bit out of the way for us, but we will make the trip of a place is worth it. 

Well, let me say that Firehouse Subs blew my expectations out of the water! The two young guys working were very polite and helpful, and once we took our toasted subs home, that's when the magic happened. 

I wasn't expecting to look in the bag and not see your typical paper-wrapped hoagie. They were set in individual containers, which kept the sandwich neat and together. It was sliced in half, diagonally (you wouldn't believe how hard it is for some places to slice a sandwich in half!) and everything looked really, really fresh. Upon first bite, I realized it wasn't just for show. This was an AMAZING sub! The roll was perfectly soft, all ingredients fresh, and just the right amount of everything. Even a pickle spear individually bagged! It may sound silly, but I didn't want the eating experience to end. 

I'm so glad we made the trip here to give this place a try. If we're ever up this way (or just have a hankering for a really good sub), we'll be back here!

text:
09/23/2018
Went back today. What a wonderful experience.
Food and staff were great. We will be back.


Worst service ever. The pictures on the board of the sandwiches look like nothing what they serve. Almost false advertising.I saw a picture of their bistro sandwich on their entrance door.  It looked great so I ordered one. 
It was awful. Half the size and not not very appealing. When I mentioned it to the staff. They said that is the way it is.   I don't think they even cared. Back to Jersey Mike's I go.

04/04/2017
What a difference from a year ago.
Wife talked me into going back. She wanted to try a Brixit sandwich she had heard about.
I reluctantly have in.  The place was clean. The girls behind the counter were friendly and made us very nice sandwiches.
Because of this I will raise my review by two stars. I look forward to my next visit. Maybe I will not wait a year to come back.
10/07/17 Went back today because my wife had a coupon. One sandwich with chips and drink. It was $9.87 with a $2 off coupon. Wow! 
Firehouse sure is expensive.

text:
Came in @ 11:30, no lines no wait - I felt like a boss.  Restaurant is very clean and service is friendly as always.  Parking can be tough because its on a busy shopping plaza.

Ordered the "Italian" sub and asked for NO ONIONS.  But guess what?  I took my order and ate it in my car.  It was delicious, but sure enough they forgot that I said no onions... I was able to calm myself down and I pulled them out.  Overall, it took about 10 minutes to get the sandwich at the counter (expected). 

Despite this I still give them 5 stars, we all make mistakes.  It was a very delicious sandwich and they seem to be very consistent with their food quality standards.

Now if I go there again and they mess up with the onions again, im just gonna have to pull a star away LOL.

We'd never been to this chain before - but we totally loved it...

I had the club and loved it - and "fully involved" (meaning with everything on it) was just fun to say.

Great alternative to Quiznos or Subway. And they give you a dill pickle spear with your combo - bonus!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Have eaten here before and thought it was OK. Tonight though I ordered the same meatball sandwich and before I got the sandwich I heard the 'cooks' talking to another customer about how sorry they were that the frozen bread was burning on the ends and that they would give a full refund. I guess it must've been delivered or something I don't now. But I keep hearing oh shit I can't believe that dam it, that frozen bread keeps burning. And I could hear this as I'm waiting for my sandwich. So I figured they would say sorry heres a refund. But now I get my sandwich get home and the ends are burned, and the sandwich actually is not that good. If the bread is frozen meats frozen everything is frozen, that sucks. And the little jar the collects the donations, I kind of question that too but I don't want to get ahead of myself. bye bye.

text: I love me a my firehouse subs, great hot sub sandwiches steamed to perfection, not soggy and a little crusty.  You have to try the ketchupy hot sauce they have available, fantastic!  I wish I could have a Firehouse Subs in my house.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I've een here a few times.  However, it's been a few years since the last time I visited.  I now remember why I loved it so much.  In the past I would get the Engine Company sub which is not on the menu anymore but they will still make it if you ask for it.  The lunch rush can be  a little busy, but that happens almost everywhere.  The bread was hot and fresh, the meat was good and everything tasted delicious.  To top it off, I tried one of the hot sauces and added it to the sandwich which took it over the top.

text:
Crusty bread, delicious and high quality meat, cool little firehouse gimmick...

Only gripe is that the selection is a bit thin. That said, though, what they do they do very well. The sub I had was pastrami and brisket with swiss cheese, italian dressing, mayo, some other delicious condiments.

Would have liked to see more chicken selections, more cheese selections, but hey--- it was good. Worth the trip for sure.

Love their subs!  They warm them up, and the ingredients are fresh.  I say "mayo only" but they still add ranch too.  So if you're a picky eater like I am, you'll need to be very specific when ordering.  But it's a good sub!

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Went to Firehouse Subs the other day before movies and tried a new sub. Usually,  I get either the meatball sub or the Italian sub. I decided to try the Turkey ranch bacon club sub and boy am I glad that I did. It was delicious. I love this place. Their rolls are so soft and they give you plenty of meat, cheese, and toppings. Unlike some sub places , their subs are pretty thick. There's nothing worse than a skimpy sub.

Also, if you have their Firehouse Subs app and you get points towards double meat subs and sometimes free Subs. On your birthday they will give you a free sub. Also, I think the decor is really cute here. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars is because the subs or a little bit small for the price you pay.  But, they are very tasty and it is definitely worth going here if you love subs.  I definitely recommend this particular Firehouse Subs because the employees are really friendly too.

text:
"Welcome to Firehouse!" is the standard greeting you'll here as soon as you enter. At least it's supposed to be. Some staff members are more welcoming than others. 

Anyway, this Firehouse Subs location deserves more yelp reviews (positive ones, hopefully). I always get turkey. Meat is of great quality and tastes fresh. I almost always get my sub "fully involved" minus the lettuce. Full involved = lettuce, tomatoes, onions, mayo, mustard and a dill spear. Toppings/condiments are always fresh too. Also, for you sauce lovers, there are a number of different mild-hot sauces available on the counter to add some kick to your sandwich. This is complimentary. 

Again, I like their deli meat. Turkey is smoked! Not sure whether I enjoy it or boars head more, but that tells you how serious they are about delivering great, quality sandwiches. 

A large sub (combo w/ drink and chips) cost me $11. Pricey, but yummy.
