text: Every time I walk into this Firehouse I'm quickly greated by a friendly employee who wiggly meets me at the register to take my order. My favorite sandwich is the number#1, hook and ladder- fully involved, meaning fully loaded.  Their bread is always sift and fresh and I love the flavor of the ham they use. It comes with a pickle. They also have one of those great, large, coke machines that make a millions current choices of sodas. I come here every time I have a class after work, which is a few times a month

text:
We ordered a 12" Hot Sub, the Premium Roast Beef on white bread all the way.

David's Take: A great tasting sub! Nice and warm, the roast beef was tasty nothing over powering. The vegs were fresh and crisp even the last 35 minutes of the night when we came in. 
Mom's Take: I really liked the sub, it had a nice overall pleasant favor. Next time I want to try the smoked turkey breast.

The location was clean well lighted,. The employees were very nice while working together cleaning and wrapping up for the night. Good to see!

Thank David Driggers

text: Today we were out and decided to stop in for a hot sandwich. When we entered we were very nicely greeted. The staff is so friendly. The restaurant was clean and it is open so you don't feel crowded. I was feeling a little under the weather and Gabby recommended the chicken dumpling soup. I ordered a small size which was perfect. My husband had an Italian Sandwhich that was toasted. They shave the meat nice and thin but stack it high. The food came out hot and my soup was steamy. We really enjoyed lunch and the kindness and cheerfulness of the staff. Definitely going back soon.

text: Was a little disappointed today. I come here quite often and. normally never have problems.  Ordered a hook and ladder combo with a split tray and a mac and cheese. The hook and ladder was half all the way and half no veggies.  We sat after ordering and got our sandwiches like normal. While eating we realized we had not received the mac and cheese. For some reason mac and cheese has always come out a little later than the sandwiches though I'm told it only takes less than 3 minutes to make. This time, it never came out. We were done with our sandwiches by then so I asked for a refund. The manager did offer to make the mac and cheese for us, but we were ready to go. He advises he would do a refund.  Interestingly, appears if you pay via ApplePay or Android you cannot get a refund on your card so he had to give it back to me in cash.  I normally wouldn't bat an eye at this,  but after the super annoying day I've had this was another point of stress I didn't want to deal with.  At this point, the issue was taken care of.  Sandwich still tasted good like always, but I'll need to keep a closer eye on making sure we get our ordered food.

text:
Man, what happened at this location?  This used to be my go to for a good sub.  I don't know if there has been a change in staff, management, philosophy, or all the above, but there has been a sudden and recent drop in quality.

My cheese steak was skimpy with more bread than meat, hardly any peppers, way too much mayo, etc.  See attached pic.  They used to be loaded every time, but no more.  My wife said her tuna sub didn't taste right, either.  Like the mixture was off or something.

So, looks like I might be on the hunt for another good sub shop.  Good ones are getting hard to find. Too bad, because this place used to rock.  And I don't want to hear Covid-19 excuses. You blew it.

text: UNSAFE BEWARE - I come to this location today 11/11 between 1230-1245p to grab sandwich. What was a simple lunch run became a very unsafe situation. As I walked in there a guy seating at the table closes to the door and as soon as he saw me he immediately begin to be inappropriate and giving uncomfortable compliments. I thanked him which was the worst idea ever because thereafter he continue to make inappropriate comments about me. I ask him to leave me alone. After I placed my order,  while I was waiting he begin to talk to me again but I ignored him & left the restaurant. When came back in my order wasn't ready so he still continued but at this point he was harassing me but very inappropriate and being extremely disrespectful. So I went to the counter to ask when my sandwich would be finished. Then the situation went left and he called me a b**** because I rejected his advances. He had no food, no order. Just in there loitering In the restaurant. That was a very scary experience and I will never visit this location again as I feel unsafe.

text:
Firehouse Subs is a great alternative to Subway, Quiznos, Jimmy Johns, and all the other sandwich joints! Firehouse Subs was started by firemen, and the chain has grown to 600+ restaurants around the US.

The gimmick is that all of their sandwiches are named after firefighting apparatus and job types, and this playful take gives you selections such as the "Hook and Ladder" and the "Engineer". Be sure to order your subs "fully involved" meaning served with mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a kosher dill pickle on the side. The decorations inside the restaurant are photos and memorabilia from firefighters, and the restaurant offers a nice discount for firefighters, police, and military personnel.

Firehouse Subs started a Public Safety Foundation in each city and makes a point of helping the hometown heroes. It's a nice touch that offers funding, life-saving equipment, disaster assistance and educational opportunities for first responders and public safety organizations.

You order your sandwich at the counter -- they have about a dozen different types to choose from. Some may say that's too small of a selection, but I've never found it a problem. Firehouse also offers sandwiches on rolls and a Chef's salad, and a couple of combos for the kiddies. On the front counter you'll see a vast array of hot sauces, and you're encouraged to splash on the heat after you receive your sub.

For dinner tonight I ordered an Italian sub on whole wheat, and of course I asked for it "Fully Involved". The sandwich came on a toasted sub roll with Genoa salami, pepperoni, ham, melted provolone, Italian dressing, and seasonings. The bread was toasted and crusty on the outside, and still soft on the inside. Add to that a bag of Miss Vickie's kettle-cooked potato chips and a trip to the always-enjoyable Coca-Cola Freestyle soda machine to mix up the tonic-du-jour, and I was a happy firefighter!

Great place to try something a little different, and donate some extra change to their Public Safety Foundation.

text: I ordered 2 hook and ladders in a tub and not on bread as my family is not eating carbs for heath reasons. Placed notes on the order to have as such and didn't indicate to place anything on the side or leave off any condiments. The item I picked up didn't have any cheese or condiments. Tomatoes and onions were in a separate container along with a small container of what appeared to be Italian dressing. All of this for 2 subs. Just lettuce and barely any meat and was not warm similar to how the hook and ladder typically is. I think I'll stick with Jersey Mike's as they beat you out of the ballpark with their sub in a tub. So disappointed being that one of these was my birthday sub and the other I paid for double meat.

text: Wow terrible is all I have to say about today's experience! Decided to come here for lunch...place wasn't that crowded but began to get a crowd after we ordered.  As we were walking in there was an older man at the counter complaining over something but I totally ignored it and went to the register to place our order.  Ordered 2 hook and ladder combos with a side of Mac and cheese for my daughter.  After we placed our order, we found a table and sat down.  After sitting there for a bit I knew it felt like an awful long time so I looked at my phone compared to the time stamp on the receipt and 18 minutes had already passed! Say what!?  I also happened to notice that there were about 4 people standing around also waiting for their to go orders, as well as a lot of the tables being full.  Sitting there a bit longer, I'm seeing the people behind the cook area sort of arguing and seem confused about orders or something, then the guy comes out and delivers food at the table next to ours which those people were after us in line! I can't believe what I am seeing -- and we are starving at this point along with our frustration as now its been over 20 minutes and no food!  My husband went up to the register to ask how much longer for our food and the clerks all looked puzzled, then tell him that they haven't even started our order yet!!  Are you freaking kidding me.  WOW.  He is beyond frustrated at this point and asks for a refund -- we will go somewhere else to have lunch.  He has to wait for another individual to come over to process the refund then we end up leaving.  I don't know what is happening to this location but although this has been the worse experience here, it's definitely not the only complaint or lack of quality service we've experienced here.  Management definitely needs to look at the reviews and take some action to improve the customer experience.  They are definitely in need of some organization and perhaps some additional training otherwise you're going to lose good customers due to experiences like this.

text: Poor job done. It was about 1:30 PM on a Saturday there were about 5 people waiting for food so I understood it might take a little while. I placed an order for a large New York Steamer fully involved with no dressing. I saw on the order screen that the order was not correct and asked about it . I was told it would be corrected. I sat down to wait for my food. 18 minutes later my name is called . I take my food to my car and open the box. What I got was meat, mustard ,and mayo so thick it's dripping out of the sides and nothing else. I went back in and was asked what I wanted them to do. I asked them to just put the toppings on . I go home and open the box . A little lettuce and one tomato slice for the whole large sandwich is what I received. No more dissatisfying soggy $10.00 sandwiches for me .

text:
My favorite sub place! Gotta go with the hook and ladder fully involved! We tried the Pastrami Ruben and wow that was good....hot meat with the cold slaw on it. Firehouse always does it right. A regular sub is about $6 then you can make it a combo for $2.89 more.  The medium size sub is big enough for me and my daughter to share. 

They have a deal for every day of the week now where you get a sub, chip, and drink for $5.55. Now that they do that they really compete with the other guys that offer deals of the day. 

Firehouse has seating inside available or you can take your order to go. They also have a reward program. You can order online as well. They have subs, salads, soups, chili. Their cookies are also good.

text: So I had a not so great experience the last review I left. Today's was not great either.  2 times in a row I've run into an issue. This time, We ordered food and all that, which was fine, but we sat and we sat for 20 minutes before I decided to go up to the register to find out what was happening. Lo and behold the girl at the counter writes my order down to put it in queue to make! They hadn't even started our order after other parties after us had received their food. I tell her to stop and ask for a refund.  The manager comes over, apologizes,  and says it's a problem with their order system.  I ask if it is corporate or franchise responsibility, which she says is a franchise responsibility and that corporate had not yet sent a tech to identify and fix the problem yet, though they had already notified corporate.  BIG fail on both sides.  Franchise should put in a manual process if they know something like this is broken.  Corporate should help their franchisee immediately if this was truly part of the process. Either way, if I hadn't checked we'd still be waiting.  I think im done with Firehouse for a while now. Moe's next door got our business today.  I'd love to hear a response from the franchisee and corporate to find out what happened.   We'll see if that happens.

text: We ordered food for pick up, when we arrived we noticed no food was on the Rapid pickup shelf so we took a seat and waited. About 15 minutes after our pick up time my boyfriend finally asked, to which the employee responded "we aren't putting food on that shelf, your food has been ready". No signage indicating that they weren't using the shelf and neither employee thought to ask us what order we were waiting for even though they had seen us waiting. Food was obviously room temperature by the time we ate and was really subpar beyond that. Disappointing considering Firehouse is typically good. Probably won't be going back to this location.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Subs is new to our area so I tried it for the first time after watching from my car as a guy waved a huge sign.  I decided to go in since it was nearly lunchtime.  The space is brand new and adjacent to Five Guys and other small eateries there.  It was clean and the employees were very welcoming.  I chose the most popular  sub---the Hook & Ladder--smoked turkey, Virginia honey ham, Monterey Jack with mustard, mayo, lettuce, tomato, onion with a  Kosher dill pickle on the side.  It was served on a toasted white roll.  I ordered a medium--nine inches which was totally shareable and ample for both my husband and me.

I also like that there are low calorie options listed.  Since this business was founded by a couple of firefighters, they also have a foundation that contributes to firefighting organizations in the way of equipment and also scholarships.  A very worthy cause besides getting a very delicious meal at a bargain price---$6.00!

text:
I frequent the other location on Milwaukee and Fairview. I'm a huge fan of this place since I found it a couple of months ago. 

This location is larger and had a much better dining room area. Great for families. The crew is friendly and the area is clean. Had the Italian today which was great. The large was 12" with over a half pound of meat!  Very shareable for me and my wife. The sub was $8 so with drink and chips we ate for around $5 each. Not bad!!

I highly recommend this place. Easily the best sub around. Only warning would be they are busy between 12-1 so plan accordingly!!

text: Ordered a salad to go and got 2 little cups full of dressing.  That is not a sufficient amount of dressing for a meal salad especially considering that the salads are lame at best.  Chopped lettuce with chopped tomatoes, cucumbers and green pepper as well as cheese cubes.  That is what is advertised and I'm fine with that, but at least provide enough dressing to wet all of the greens.  My son's sandwich was good.  The real reason for the 2 stars though is the staff.  They were far more interested in chit chat amongst themselves than helping customers.  We had to stand there and wait while they chatted about their day for 5 minutes instead of helping us.  The customer should always come first.  They can chit chat all they want when there are no customers in there.

attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
Went during lunch; had an Italian sandwich and got it to go. It was good...lots of food, and quality was fine. I'd recommend maybe a turkey or roast beef next time, since their version of the Italian sandwich was non-traditional; it had a sweeter oil & vinegar dressing and a sweeter ham. I would prefer a mortadella and capicolla on the sandwich, instead of pepperoni and (apparently) honey ham.

The filling was heated, which was nice...it melted the cheese and added flavor to the meat...but after taking it back to the office, the lettuce got a little warm. 
 Service was friendly and reasonably quick, took a little over 5m to make the sandwich, and it was at noon.

I could see going back if convenient, but it's not on my "top" list...Jimmy John's is closer to me and pretty comparable.

What's good: Friendly service, selection.

What needs work: Italian sandwich not to my taste; too sweet ham and dressing.

attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text: Would have gave this place 4 stars a week ago when we came but my experience last night will probably keep me from coming back. Tried it a week ago and it was very good. Last night I went through the drive thru and the boy taking my order was taking to me in a robot voice (on purpose) and I could hear him giggling with co-workers as he was doing it. It was so awkward for me. Then at the window he was trying to explain why he was talking in that voice. Just weird and unprofessional. When we got home with our food he had forgot the cookies and our sandwiches were made wrong. I looked at the receipt and they were punched in wrong. Probably because he was having more fun acting like a idiot through the speaker. Kinda sucks. My advice, hire more mature staff. Ordered through their drive thru and got a club on a sub and it's supposed to have bacon AND cheese. It came with neither of those things. attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
If I could give more than 5 stars, I WOULD!! This is my first time at this restaurant as I wanted to try out their gluten-free bread. Not many places offer that option. I ordered a sandwich and walked out to my car. After finding a place to park and eat, I opened the box. The wonderful aroma was driving me into a ravenous frenzy. I picked up the sandwich and quickly noticed that this was not like other gluten-free breads that often chew like shoe leather.With my first bite I could tell that this bread was different! So soft, so tasty, it was like an actual homemade roll! I had to force myself to eat slowly so that I could enjoy every mouthful, even though my stomach wanted me to gobble it all down!! I was in gluten-free sub heaven! This is now my favorite sub sandwich place! 

AND....I want to say thank you to them for not forcing the "MASK" issue. I am unable to wear one, but they made me feel like a valued customer, and for that I am now a repeat customer FOR LIFE!! I will recommend them to everyone I meet. If you're looking for an EPIC sub sandwich, then look no further than the Firehouse Sub shop on N. Eagle Rd in Meridian. 

P.S. Did I mention that they will round your purchase up (with your permission, of course) to the next full amount and donate that amount to First Responders? Well, they DO! And they have a rewards program for their customers, too!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
I have been coming to Firehouse subs every since they opened up here in Meridian. Their subs are very good. My mainstay is the brisket, so I will focus on this one.

If you like Brisket, you have to try it here. Forget about those other fast food places that claim they make the best Brisket sandwich. They don't. Trust me, Ive tried them. 

Arbys, for example, says "We have the meats". Well, they do have the meats, but in my opinion, they are not very good meats and their brisket is..well, lets just say based on the taste, its questionable if it actually is Brisket, and I will leave it at that. 

The brisket here is very smoky, but its not a strong smoke flavor like you get from Hickory. I am going to email them and try to find out a bit more about how they smoke their meet and where. 

There is only 1 issue, which is not big , but big enough to costs Firehouse 1 star.

Like I said, I have been going to Firehouse for a long time now. I have probably been here 50 times or maybe more. This has been a pattern that I dont understand. But it happens often enough as to cost them a star and raise concerns.

It would be like spending a dollar to save a nickel. In this case they do great with The Meats, but they skimp on other things, which I really dont get.

On 4 out of 5 carry out visits, they put little to no sauce on the sandwich and they give me few or no pickles, which are supposed to come with the Brisket. So I get lots of meat, which is great, but on a Brisket sub, sauce plays a huge role in the overall goodness of it.

If a Brisket sandwich is short sauce, its like taking a Ferrari, which is 12 cylinder, and making it so it only fires on 6 cylinders. Sure the Ferrari will still run and do a decent job, but its not going to perform near as well as it could if it was running on all 12.

Same goes for their brisket sub. Sure its still good, but its nowhere near as good is it could be because its either missing the sauce or has very little of it.

Its the weirdest thing in my mind. They give me lots of meat most times, but then they short me on the sauce and the pickle. 

I woke up at 3am this morning thinking on this. Weird right? To wake up at the crack of dawn and think about a review you have written and a restaurant you have visited, but as I tell my wife, Welcome to My Mind.

The problem is that on their Brisket sub, they put both Mayo and BBQ sauce. Why Mayo I have no idea. Being from Texas, I hate Mayo with a passion and the combo of the 2 is, in my opinion, even weirder. Even my wife hates it and she was born and raised here in Idaho.

When I order the Brisket sub, I always ask them to leave off the Mayo. When they do, they do not add more BBQ sauce to make up for this. They use what must be the very same ratio of BBQ sauce to Mayo, which is light on the sauce and heavy on the Mayo.

What I end up with is a very dry sub because they stuck to their formula of very light BBQ sauce. So mystery solved. If you like me, do not like Mayo, and order this sub without it, do yourself a favor and ask them to go heavier on the BBQ sauce.

Before I forget, speaking of the meat, they do sometimes have a nasty habit of shorting this as well. I usually order double meat just for that reason. When they do double meat, they usually do give you a ton of meat, but you pay for it. 

The foot-long Brisket is $10 then another $5 for the double meat so this is a bit of an expensive sandwich. But trust me, it is worth it if you are a carnivore like me.

Sometimes their bread is stale as well and a weird texture. Have you ever put bread in the microwave? When you do this, there is a weird reaction that happens at the molecular level of the bread. It becomes chewy, so I am wondering if they are putting their bread in a microwave to warm it up.

So when you go here, which I suggest everyone does, especially if you love Brisket, make sure you get your  sauce and a pickle.

text: Been so hungry for a big juicy meatball sandwich. You know the one that drips pasta sauce down your  hands??? I found it.... here. Reasonable price, great tasty sauce on a sub roll with a pickle. Yum yum yum!!! Of course this place also has salads, sides like Mac n cheese and chili... oh never ending selection of warm and cold subs. I will be back.

text:
First of all, none of the servers were masked. Upsetting. The pandemic is far from over.
Now about my sandwich: It didn't taste bad, because it taste at all. Pastrami should be spicy, salty. This was flavorless, dry and hard to swallow. And at over 9 dollars for a medium, way over priced. Won't be back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text: As much as I used to love Firehouse, lately their customer service has been pretty bad. I don't know if they have new employees or just don't care or what but they have messed up 3 times in a row in the past month or so. I've only had issues at this specific location. They don't listen in the drive thru it seems like and when I clarify and they confirm my order yet they dont give me something I specifically asked for or will add something I asked to not include. They continue to put Mayo on my sandwich, ask me 3-4x what kind of bread I want, never give me a total at the screen, and then give me either regular coke or Dr Pepper when I ask for Diet Coke and repeat myself multiple times. I asked for a cookie one of times I went last and they tell me to "choose at the window" and when they mentioned oatmeal I chose that. What did they do? They put a chocolate chip in the bag instead. The last time I tried my soda to make sure it was diet And it wasn't the girl rolled my eyes when I asked for a replacement. It's been shocking to me and I'm a huge fan of Firehouse. I can go on and on about the stupid little mistakes they have been making and I don't know why I continue to go there expecting a different outcome. I'm not one to complain and haven't even wanted make the effort to call and ask for some type of comp but actually hope they get it together and hire people who give a damn and take pride in their work. Sorry Meridian Firehouse but I know you can do better.

text: Love firehouse subs! I've been going to firehouse since 2012 in Virginia and it's always been a fave! My ultimate favorite sandwich is the Beef and Cheddar Brisket!! It is the best. Not to mention they use the BEST mayo (DUKES!). My husband got the Firehouse Hero and it was seriously delicious. When I want a sub this is the place I go! attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
Heard rave reviews and I was left very disappointed with an expensive meal. 
Ordered thru doordash and was missing one bowl of Mac n cheese which doordash gave me credit for. The bowl was the size of a cup at any other restaurant so not sure if this was also a mixup or if this was truly their bowl size.
The taste was nothing to be excited about. I've had better from a box as sad as that is.
I got the steak and cheese so like a philly. Tasted and looked like mayo on it, no flavor at all from the meat or veggies. VERY bland ate 6 bites and saving the rest. Will only eat because of the price which was double the price of subway.

Reason this gets 2 stars is because my husband also got a sandwich and he said it was good. His was the Italian and he liked it more than the Wendy's Italian.

Sad this wasn't a great experience as I've heard about and their rating seems to give them on doordash.

attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
We may have a new office fave after trying Firehouse Subs.  I placed an online order today around 12:10 pm and it was ready for pickup when I arrived at 12:25.  I found it very easy to place an order on their website.  They have a large variety of sandwiches that can be customized, you can save your orders, save payment method, etc.  They also have 3 different size options which I found to be rather helpful since a couple of us are light eaters but don't always like to order something to share.  FYI... you can pick up online orders through their drive thru.

I ordered a small white smoked turkey and found it to be the perfect size with a bag of chips a drink and a pickle spear.  It reminded me of the turkey I used to get at Schlotzkys back in the day.  Their meat is very thinly sliced just how I like it.  I ordered my husband a medium Italian fully loaded and he as only able to finish half of it but on a normal day it would be the perfect size. We also found it to be very affordable as we only paid $23.53 for 3 different sandwiches, chips and drinks.  This will definitely be a regular in our lunch rotation!

text:
UPDATED REVIEW: 
Ordered through their drive thru and got a club on a sub to try and it's supposed to have bacon AND cheese. It came with neither of those things. The sub was so sloppy once I got home, the bun on the bottom was so soggy it was hard to eat. If I ever want firehouse, I'll probably be eating in the restaurant rather than drive thru just to make sure they get it right.

attributes: {'DriveThru': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text: We stopped at this Firehouse Subs at 1:08 as we were traveling. I bought 2 turkey bacon subs. We were eating them & I was picking some turkey off to give to our dog. At one point I took the bread off to get more turkey for our dog only to find a dead fly in my sandwich. Thank God we had my dog with us otherwise I would have eaten that dead fly. What really irritated me was when I went in to give them the other half of the sandwich along with the part with the dead fly on it they actually said "oh we are sorry. We are having a problem with flies." Never ever again. We only eat fast food when we travel with our dog but you can believe we will never go to another Firehouse Subs. I own a business & I would hope my employers would never be that inconsiderate or dumb. I can not believe they did not see the fly because it was not buried in meat or lettuce but rather right on the edge.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Subs is a quick place to catch a quick meal! I would suggest order online and then having it delivered or picking it up! Once I order online, then it'll be ready by the time that I arrive! I can just grab and go! I love the convenience.

I ordered the Turkey Bacon sandwich on wheat with everything on it, paired it with Lay's Kettle Cooked Jalapeno Cheddar (suggested by one of the employees), and grabbed a Sprite as well!

My other go to order is the Italian Club on wheat with everything on it, so try that out next time!

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text: Just stopped in this location and won't be back to any other location. I entered and a guy in a irritated way said you need a mask. I waited to let him finish changing the channel on a tv and asked where they were at. He just rudely said "in your car". I get the mask mandates and I just got finished walking in the rain for 2 blocks and forgot mine. Many establishments provide masks so That's why I asked. So all you had to say was sorry we don't provide them but you want to be a smart a** that's fine. Go ahead a lose a $14 sale on a 25 cent mask and be a jerk to boot. I hold a grudge and won't return to any establishment.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True'}
text: Firehouse Subs opened a few weeks ago and I've already visited multiple times, from the convenience of coming down an elevator. I like the thematic significance of this restaurant in the 3949 Lindell building which had a history of a huge fire in 2012. They even have a few pictures and newspaper clippings on the wall from that fire. Their strength is the variety of meats, toppings and hot sauces available. I really think that the shelf with the huge variety of different hot sauces is the best part of the experience. The only negative is that their sandwiches can fall apart if loaded with toppings.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: Nice little addition to the city of Algiers. Very friendly staff all of which greets you as you walk in. Well staffed and not to mention, fast workers! I didn't wait no longer than 3-4 minutes and I received my order freshly made, straight to the table I was sitting at. That is great because they provide you with numbers so they can bring your order to you instead of getting up. I kept it simple and ordered the Club on a Sub with a bowl of baked potato soup. They both were very delicious and my soup came out steaming hot with a side of oyster crackers. I was offered the option of replacing my chips for a soup for the combo which also includes a drink with free refills when dining in. Overall, the staff kept this restaurant nice and tidy with a good, constant flow of customers throughout. I would definitely visit this location again to enjoy the pleasant hospitality and good sandwiches they offer!

text:
YUMMMMMYYYYYYY!!! I ordered the veggie sub because I'm trying the trying this plant based lifestyle, and it was pretty filling. The veggies were cooked before placed on the sub, so I enjoyed every bite. 

There's a parking lot in front of the restaurant, so you won't have trouble finding a place to Park your car. 

I also love how they have firefighters' gear hanging up inside the restaurant. The decorations are cute! 

Unlike most sub places, you can't see the ingredients as the sandwiches are made.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text: Many people say fire fighters spend most of their shift sleeping. During one of those glorious slumber sessions they dreampt up the perfect way to save us all from the monotony of cities littered with thousands of green and yellow Subway Sandwich Shops. There is something special about Firehouse subs. There is definitely more love per bite than your typical lackluster subway sandwich or greasy fast food quick fix. Whats even better is that you are supporting local first responders with every bite, so no need for it to be a guilty pleasure, it is a righteous cause. Many of the sandwiches are hot (duh, made by fire fighters) and they do not disappoint. A coke freestyle machine is available for almost limitless flavors to choose from to put out the fires on your plate should you choose to order your sandwich fully involved. It did take a bit over 10 minutes from order time to when the sandwich was received, but that can be forgiven, the firefighters still may have been a little bit sleepy.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text:
Well let's just say I was super excited that a Firehouse Subs was opened near my residence!  I couldn't wait to visit!  This place always have people that are very bubbly!  I was welcomed of course as soon as my hand touched the door.  This organization works as a well oiled machine!  

The best part of this place is the fact that your sub is handcrafted and served warm!!! Yum!! It's is not anything like the traditional NOLA poboy but oh my is it a flavor explosion on your tongue!  The ingredients are so fresh the tears begin to roll when you smell the veggies on the warm bread!  

I had the special which was a medium honey ham dressed partially involved without the onions... the only reason I didn't get the onions is because I am not a fan of white onions raw other than that I would have had those little igniters of tears all over that bad boy!!! I sat and ate at the Resturant there were a few people there but the store was super clean and neat!  I will be back sooner than I should!

text:
I've been hearing about Firehouse Subs and wanted to give it a try. I'm so glad I did! I love this place on Gen. DeGaulle Dr.  I don't eat fast food.  I don't do subway or any burger doodle place. Had to say bye to Taco Bell years ago because it made me sick one day. Found out they were using MSG and corn syrup in at least their sauces possibly other things too, I don't know.  I have to have real food and Firehouse Subs did not disappoint me at all! I had the New York steamer which is corn beef and it was the worst. Their bread is really good and I am ultra picky, especially about bread. I grew up on real French bread and do not eat supermarket (so French bread. I am disappointed to see that the Metairie store does not have five stars.  I live in Metairie so the place on Veterans Blvd., I hope is better than their reviews. 

NO IDEA WHAT THIS FUN AND GREAT PLACE IS DOING NOW. I AM THINKING ABOUT GOING THIS WEEK.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True'}
text:
Mmm, mmm, mmm. Wait, let me wipe my mouth. I just finished a philly steak and cheese sub. Finger-lickin', lip-smackin' good. I don't think I've ever tried the steak and cheese. I normally get their brisket sandwiches, whether the regular menu item or some limited-time version. I've also had the chicken, I think. It's a sandwich my wife normally gets. The steak and cheese sandwich had such a great flavor. I'm not sure if it was the brand of mayo or the combination of the mayo and peppers. And then the steak was chopped up nicely. I didn't have struggle with the meat. 

Anyway, I stopped in to redeem a b-day reward and boy, was I rewarded. My wife took a bite while it was warm and said it was delicious. I had to make a few more stops--Big EZ Seafood, Chipotle, Haydel's, Cupcake Factory--before I could sit and enjoy it. Yes, it was cold by that time and I put it in the microwave for a few seconds, but it was just as good as when I took my first bite earlier in the day. 

Service was good, but the wait was typical. Firehouse tends to be slower than other quick service restaurants, but it was worth the wait. Give me this over Subway any day. Subway who?

So food is very consistent and good. The game changer is the employees. Well trained, always nice and accommodating. In fact I was adding something to my sandwich ( bacon ) and I didn't realize that there already was a sandwich that had everything i wanted, the young lady rang it up as that sandwich because it was cheaper. 

I go out of my way to visit this location and will continue to do so.

text:
I used this location for a catering order, and  I was not disappointed. I used the online option to submit my order, which was super convenient. The order was ready by the time I requested, and I was in and out of the restaurant in 5-10 minutes. In addition to sandwiches, I also ordered a large salad and it came with a cute fire hydrant to hold the dressing. The sandwiches were tasty too- I ordered a platter of roast beef, turkey, ham, and veggie on either white or wheat bread (nothing too fancy). Overall, I was satisfied with this catering order and I would use them again. 

One thing to note was when I was picking up my order, I noticed that this location still does not do indoor dining. This didn't apply to me, but just good to know if you decide on eating here.

text: I ordered the Italian Sub and it was delicious. Their BBQ hot sauce has great flavor and just enough spice. Fun place for kids because their decor is all firefighter related. text: We came here for dinner for the first time the other night. The staff were very friendly and greeted us as we walked in the door. My husband ordered the Steak & Cheese, I had the Engineer, and our two boys ordered a Turkey and Cheese Kids Meal and a Grilled Cheese Kids Meal. I liked that the kid's meals came with a choice of either a bag of chips or a dessert, a drink, and a fireman's hat. Our boys really loved the Coke machine, which was one of the newer ones with over 100 variations of Coke products. Our food was ready quickly, and both sandwiches were delicious. I tried a couple bites of my husband's, and his was delicious, as was my Engineer. The restaurant itself was very clean, and we both loved the hot sauce bar, which had probably 40 different hot sauces. These were rated on a 1-10 scale based on hotness, which was very helpful. Overall, this was one of the best sub places in our area, and we will definitely be back!

text: Wife and I decided to give this a shot on Saturday.  We both thought the food was pretty awful.  She had a chicken salad sandwich.  The filling was pretty runny and just wasn't very enjoyable.  I had an Italian with Grilled Chicken Salad.  Some of the lettuce looked to be past its sell-by date.  The entire time I was eating it, I kept thinking it had kind of a slimy mouth feel to it.  Adding to the dining experience at 2 in the afternoon, the air conditioning system appeared to have given out.  There were two female employees diddling with the thermostat looking for the "cool" setting.  It was set to cool for 70 degrees Fahrenheit but the inside of the store was 83.  That may have been why the food seemed off.  We didn't get sick from it.  I also tried a sample of their datl pepper sauce.  It didn't have much oomph, so I decided not to buy a bottle to take home.

text:
While I didn't try a sub while i was here, i did have a bite of one!  The bread is fresh and delicious :)

I tried the chili, while it wasn't in my top favs for restaurants it was in the middle, it was just okay.  I will come back here to try out a sub, but i wasn't wowed like alot of people, i am a fan of jimmy johns.  Keep in mind i'm not a huge fan of spicey so that may be why im not a huge fan of this place.  I will update my review when i try out a sub.

Oh parking during lunch is HORRIBLE.  Be prepared to walk from the strip mall behind it.  No handicap available.  There may be 1-2 spots in the small strip mall but they def weren't available.

text: My wife and I were there on Friday 7/27 during the lunch hour. It was fairly crowded and the entire staff was busy on several large delivery/carry out/to go orders. The drink machine ran out of ice and we waited 20 minutes for our sandwich before we had to ask for carry out since we both had to be back at work.  Prior experiences were good until this one. Yet another example of a trend we see where more focus is on those not physically in the restaurant.

text:
Firehouse is Firehouse but it was great service from the gentleman that made this a really outstanding experience. My 3 year old and I grabbed lunch. The small sandwiches are perfect for her. So as our food was delivered she used her manners and thanked the young man. She really liked her sandwich and let him know. He brought her a mini rice krispie treat and encouraged her to continue to use her manners. It's little things like that, that will be the difference between where you stop for a quick lunch. 
I didn't get his name but he's a brown skin, African American male looked too be in his early 20s and had dreads. He was great.

text: Ordered 9 subs. Six of the 9 were incorrect. Some even missing basic ingredients. None of the subs were numbered and since they were wrong we had to pick them apart to determine which one belonged to which person.  Placed order 30+ minutes ahead of pickup time, but they were still 9 minutes late. Staff professionalism was abysmal. Manager hung up on us. We went to restaurant and were told they couldn't do anything for us as just advised that we call a phone number on the wall. Provided feedback via their survey and asked to be contacted. So far, no contact. If in Fairview Heights, I recommend eating elsewhere.

text: This place is awful, I have been here several times and on this day it made my stomach turn, the place is dirty full of flies, the workers never changed their gloves or washed there hands, one worker needed on a hair net, his pants were sagging, he placed an order on the door dash shelf for pickup, the receipt fell off the bag, he picked up the receipt off of the dirty floor and went back to the food prep line, he didn't change gloves or wash his hands, this place needs to shutdown! attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': False, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
Absolutely love this place! We ordered 2 subs. The Hook and Ladder (Monterrey Jack with Ham and Turkey) and the Beef and Cheddar Brisket. OH MY!! That Brisket sandwich was not only different than any other Metro-East sub place, but it made me drool. Seriously spilled hot sauce on my shirt. I'm looking forward to the Hawaiian pulled pork sandwich for next time. 

The service was quick, especially for being super busy. The manager was cashering and was really friendly. My favorite thing about this place is not only do they have a bar of hot sauces (like about 30-40 hot sauces) but they have their own on the side. This is a MUST TRY!!!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': False, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
Darling honey LOVES this place--- and before they brought FireHouse to this region
he would always eat at the one in Richmond--and he RAVED about them.
So coming home a couple weekends ago, I mentioned going to FH for lunch
and of course he was down.
My dad is a volunteer firefighter, and I immediately already loved the place.
I decided to order the Turkey Bacon Ranch, but with chicken---(i know, i know)
It took a little while for our sammys to come out, but it was WAY worth the wait..
THAT sandwich---- was DELICIOUS-------!!!
I know- i am a lover of deli sandwiches--but this one--- was so good!!!
And honestly, I cant wait to go back---
Not to mention---- get this--- when you walk in-- look in the corner--
It looks some drink machine from outter space--for riz.! 
They have something like over 220 different kinds of drinks you can make..
CRAZY-NESS..! but oh so cool ! 
THey also have a ton of different hot sauces and stuff you can choose from-
my sandwich was perfect, so i didnt need to add anything.
I can now see why my honey loves this place so much.
Beware- its a little hard to find, but its RIGHT next to Bread Co. there in the strip mall... so after a long hard day of shopping, or just out and about-
stop in! you wont be sorry! 
oh..and they even have little firehats, for little firemen...;)

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
Talking about top of the line customer service, I was blown away!

I literally haven't been in one in awhile because I had a bad experience, but on my lunch I decides to give this different location a shot and I'm glad I did.

Though they weren't busy, I was immediately greeted by the team with enthusiasm. The guy realized I hadn't been in many times and walked me through the entire menu. The staff was fun, conversational, and really didn't mind helping. Everybody just seemed happy and to be having a good day. After my order, they educated me in the different sauces I was thumbing through.. Giving me advice.. Sharing stories.. It was fun! I got my food.. Amazing... Great serving.. Hot.. An employee even checked in on me whine I was eating.. These guys definitely rectified the bad experience at the other location. Great experience for sure. Thanks guys! I really do appreciate y'all going the extra mile! It's appreciated!

(P.S. I did not proofread this, sorry!)

text: We usually enjoy this chain.  First time at this location.  Arrived at 7:45PM and finally got our food at 8:30, and the place was not busy. text: Our favorite sub place. Huge subs and they actually put a lot of meat and stuff on the sub unlike subway who barely puts anything on their subs. My fav sub at firehouse is the brisket! Yummmmmmm the bread is yummy and toasted and they have a drink machine with so many options of flavors. Customer service is excellence. The only negative is the price but we think it's worth it

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
Located in the shops at Indian Lake, I've never been to one, but Firehouse comes highly recommended.

When you walk in there's a great hot sauce bottle collection at the counter. That's really cool, I've not seen that and I looked thru all the bottles until my sandwich arrived. I like variety and this had lots of options from A1 to habanero based options, nice, very nice. They also rank them in order of heat 1-10, 10 being the hottest so that helps to take the guess work out of it. Offering this is a great idea and one that allows you to customize your sub and allows you to change it up every time if you'd like. 

I got the Italian, plenty of meat and fresh veggies.  Overall, a very tasty sub. The staff were all friendly and professional.  I'll be back again soon.

text:
ordered: 12" italian no mayo.

the tomatoes are flavorless mush. the italian dressing was some sort of concoction that had a ton of sugar and dijon/mustard seed. it overpowered the entire sandwhich. i could not taste anything else. the bread is sub par, the pickel was limp and slimy, and the cost was rather high for the forgettable experience.  the place reminds of of quiznos.

and why would you put a chip rack right smack dab in the middle of the walkway? being cramped like that as i was trying to figure out what i wanted... made me feel out of place and uncomfortable.

if you want great food for ten bucks, go to qdoba a block down the road.

attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text: Went there today, and it took 30 minutes to be two sandwiches! I could have had a steak dinner for as long as that took. Saw other unhappy people getting upset about how long they were taking. It's a sandwich, why in the world should I have to wait 30 minutes??? Talked to three people about it, including the manager and all just said they were understaffed. No refund, dessert, comp or anything was offered. If they were running that far behind why don't they tell you that before you place your order? Oh, and I was there and placed my order at 10:53am. That is the last time I will ever go back there.

text: My first time here had an Alice in Wonderland feel. The medium drink was huge, the straws were too short, and the sub  looked tiny. It was 8 inches, but skinnier than most. And cheaper. I had the Steamer sub, and it was delicious. Tasty, tender meat, crunchy roll, heated perfectly. And great service.

text: Everyone raves about how good this place is, so we decided to try it. Looked at the menu and decided to get the new sub with pulled pork and coleslaw, and of course they didn't have the supplies for it. So I settled on another sub. Overall both subs we got, Italian and Club were tasteless, soggy, and uninspired. We also got a kids meal and opted for the rice crispy treat, and got a very small 100 calorie package. Overall a very disappointing experience.  Lastly, the chip rack is in a ridiculous location. I will not be back!

text: Been there twice now. Italian is good. Steak and cheese is good, but needs double the meat. Service is pretty good, not as fast as other sub shops, but that is ok as the food is twice as good. It also has a very cool soda machine where you can mix different flavors with popular Coke brands. Huge selection of hot sauces too!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
I went here on a Sunday afternoon, restaurant was clean, food was great.  Negatives were the hot sauce varieties were lacking, normally they have 40 to 50 varieties, this location had 8 and four of them were rate 10/10 on the hot scale, seemed like an oversight from management.  Not a huge deal but if that's what your known I should expect a better variety.

Very over staffed, 8 employees in the store and 2 customers.  Staff was acting up, throwing things, on their phones, filling up drinks and drinking cokes in the service area behind the counter.  One employee made a reference to keeping it cold so the customers wouldn't stay long.  When I left I looked at the thermostat since it was next to the cash register.  It was set on 61 degrees.  

I feel like the management is not doing their job.  Hot sauce not stocked, staff acting up, cold environment and overflowing garbage cans.  This store is in a great location and has room to be very successful but it falls on the shoulders of good management.

text: Decent sandwich shop located near a few parks and the mall. Their food consist of steamed sandwiches. If you are looking for toasted subs there are none here. They do have a small selection of cold sandwiches but it is not a very vast menu. If you are looking for a really good sandwich in hendersonville I would give Sax Deli a shot before this chain

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text: My husband and I really like Firehouse Subs. We've been to the one on Thompson Lane and the one in Hermitage. Both have great food and service. We were super excited about getting one in Hendersonville. Granted it's only been open a few weeks. But, they are going to have to do better than the service we got last night. We walked in at 8:00 pm and ordered. There was one person who ordered before us and three that ordered after. 15 minutes later, we were literally the only people left in there and still had not received our food. There were four people behind the counter. It took everything I had not to get grumpy with them. And, they never said "sorry for the wait" or anything like that. If the place had been busy, I could understand. But, it wasn't. They also skimped on the sandwich in my opinion. Mine was all lettuce and bread and not at all the way the other locations do it. Hendersonville is a competitive sandwich market. We have Jimmy Johns, Jersey Mikes, and Subway all within a mile of each other. If they want to take a share of that market, improvement needs to come sooner rather than later.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
Well I should have known better after walking into Firehouse Subs on Indian Lake at 2 pm to find it filthy on first impression. Everything from food to mud all over the floors. If this was noon I could excuse it better. But the lunch over sometime ago and only two tables occupied with a total of three guests when I walked in. No reason it's not cleaner.  The young guy taking my order was inaudible speaking so low behind a mask. 
His ears must not work well either as he gave me a wheat bread sandwich instead of the white bread I asked for. 
Then their signature drink cherry limeade was out. Sandwich (steak n cheese) was mostly peppers and onions with very little meat. Plus I hate wheat bread. Entire meal sucked. I haven't been here in several months and it will be longer than that before I go back to this location.

text:
Stopped in today, a Tuesday, at lunchtime. After waiting for someone to wait on me for about 5 minutes, someone approached and asked, "Can I help you?"
I began to order, but he cut me off and said, "So you know, there's a 25 to 30 minute wait."
Meanwhile, it didn't appear that there was any "hustle" happening among the employees.
That's 100% unacceptable. The two stars are for telling me and not just taking my order without warning.
That being said, I likely will not be back.

text: Was so disappointed in fire house subs! Just moved to the area and I haven't been to a fire house in years... Used to be our favorite sub place. Ordered sandwiches to go. When we got home, we realized the bread was stale and after toasting, very hard. My son's sandwich actually had a hair in it. Although the lady who took our order was friendly, it took about 2 to 3 minutes to even be recognized that we walked into the place.   Unfortunately, will not be back!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text: This review hurts me to write. I believe that Firehouse has the best subs but my experience tonight was unacceptable. Since Crumb opened next door, the parking lot is always packed but thought it wasn't busy and I was looking forward to the smokehouse brisket sub.  I walked in and was greeted as usual and asked, "are you here for a pickup order? I answered I needed to order. I stood at the register for several minutes (up to 5 maybe) while 4 people made sandwiches. No one looked my way or said, "we will be with you shortly" It was if I was invisible. Someone walked in after me and they still didn't approach the register so I turned to the guy behind me and said, "good luck with getting waited on" and then I walked out. Just one more Hendersonville restaurant to mark off my list.

Only problem is that it wasn't big enough!! I also tried a bunch of BBQ and hot sauces which were all great! Staff was very friendly!

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
**DO NOT EAT HERE**
I visited the Largo mall location to try FireHouse Subs for the first time tonight. Sadly I was VERY DISAPPOINTED. I arrived shortly after 8pm and there were only 2 other customers in the building. The soda machine was flat, and not only was an employee aware of it but also completely ignored the problem. While waiting for my food, the female employee working behind the counter had a conversation with the other employees saying that they needed to get everything done fast so she could hurry up and get out. This conversation was occurring an hour before they were scheduled to close, and loud enough for customers to hear. She also stated that on previous nights she had turned customers away at the door before closing hours so she could get out. After all the fuss about the employees needing to get out early, it still took 10 minutes to get a single turkey sub. When all was said and done, there wasn't even a pickle with my sub which I specifically requested. Needless to say, I was extremely dissatisfied with my First and LAST visit to FireHouse Subs.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text: Firehouse is one of my favorite places to grab a quick bite, and when this location opened near my home I was thrilled.  After several visits, I had to write a review to say that while the food has been steadily good, the service at this particular location is consistently awful.  The employees are too busy talking and customers are made to feel an inconvenience.  Do yourself a favor and hit another nearby Firehouse where customer service is a priority.

My husband and I went here for dinner based on the previous excellent reviews. I'm happy to say that they were right. 
The restaurant was clean, spacious and well lit. The staff was enthusiastic, courteous and helpful with the menu selections.
Our food was delicious and came out in a timely manner. Staff wished us a great evening when we left.

text: Once I discovered the Jamaican Jerk Turkey sandwich I knew I would eat here regularly.  I have them add a little extra Jamaican sauce. Service is a bit slow at times but overall friendly and good service.  Having the freestyle coke machine is awesome and pair it all with some funyuns- enjoy. text:
We love firehouse subs much better than Publix, Subway, or Jimmy Johns.  I have tried most of their subs.  My favorites are the Smokehouse Beef and Cheddar Brisket and the Firehouse Meatball.  You can get the meatball Sweet and Spicy - gives it a great kick.  My son prefers the Engineer - he loves the sauted mushrooms.

The salads and chili are also very good.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text: One of my favorite sub places.  Bread very fresh. Been there about 6 or 7 times, always get the Firehouse Steak sub, steak is tender and great flavor & has never been dried out. Peppers & onions cooked perfectly. I'm picky about tea & the sweet tea is very good.  Always friendly staff.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
text:
Honestly, this place sucks. Slow service, sticky unclean dining area. I waited (no other customers)about 4-5 mins watching Brooke fumble on the register before taking my order, which was wrong but was too annoyed to complain. Then making my small sub was another 13 mins- so, NOW, I have 20-mins invested into this trip to a "fast food" place without the first hint of food. 

I filled up on soda waiting for my sub to be made & while I was waiting,  a little skinny "rough" looking brunette used the washroom, came out and went immediately back behind the line working alongside a younger man. I went into the single room bathroom to pee, from drinking so much soda, only to notice that the sink was bone dry. GROSS!!! 
The Mac & Cheese looks like watery soup with crunchy uncooked Stove Top Stuffing sprinkled on top. 
My lover made such a big deal about these subs and I'm grossly disappointed. 
Save the $ & go next door to Publix for a better sub!
