text:
So, yes, it's 2020 and I just tried Firehouse for the first time. The local Checkers closed down, not that I was a fan. But my grandmother liked to go there after doctor appointments. So today she decided she wanted Firehouse instead. 

She sent me in to do her bidding, and the nice peeps at Firehouse did a great job helping me pick out subs that we both liked. Very friendly service and the wait for my order was reasonable. My grandmother enjoyed her steak and cheese, and my cajun chicken was also good. Just half the medium sized sandwiches were all that either of us could eat. I would definitely get the small next time.

text: Good stuff. I had the roast beef saratcha with 480 calories. It was a good sandwich for a fair price, especially compared to the competitor chain that is about six doors down from this one.  The place was busy and it was hard to find a seat. The service was fast and efficient.  There was a food runner/dining room attendant that was attentive.  Picky, but I hate it when I say thank you and they reply "no problem".

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
What I don't get is, at noon this place is efficient and accurate. At 6pm it's terrible. At noon a busy order takes 5 minutes. At 6, with few customers it takes 10 minutes. I've had orders called out and then rung up wrong. When I get a Go order with 2 sandwiches, the paper is supposed to have #1 and 2. That would be a good thing...if you did your job. Your food is better than other sandwich places if you can just get it where it goes. My patience is thin from repeated errors.
Maybe better, if there is a next time.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: So, I go back to give the place a second chance. I wait for my sandwich and when my name is called I collect it and return home. There, I found that I had been given another person's order. I call and speak w/Warren, he apologizes for the mistake and asks I return to correct. Warren was very friendly, and apologetic. He replaces my order with a large rather than the regular I ordered. Assuming personnel like he will remain, I will return to sending my students there.  Food has always been savory, and, because of Warren, Firehouse has won back my business.

text: This was my first visit to Firehouse Subs and I must say it was a good one. It took me a while to look at the menu because there we're so many delicious looking subs to try. The cashier was friendly and pleasant and helped me decide on what to try. It was a little overpriced but absolutely delicious, so you get what you pay for. When I got to the drink station, I was very impressed with the fountain machine that offers over 120 flavors. I thought it was hard to decide on a sub but boy, it was a lot harder deciding on which flavors to try. :)   Would recommend and visit again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: This was a Perfectly acceptable firehouse sub location. Service is pretty friendly and fast orders come out quick. Ample parking. Like all firehouse subs they have a coke freestyle machine so you can get that Mello yellow with raspberry flavor you crave. (I kid, in reality I think these machines just slow down the line while folks figure out how to use them) food wise firehouse is like half Quiznos half subway. The subs are large and warm but not toasted. I like the pepper chicken sub on the light fare menu about 500 calories and still pretty filling. They also prepare a pretty solid salad. You will certainly be filled up by their full size options as they are generous with the meats. Alot of local sandwich places do a better meal in a similar price range. I would not drive past Phat Bites for Firehouse, but between here or subway this is usually your better option.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This is an excellent sandwich shop.  They have a great selection and I like how each sandwich comes with default toppings so I don't have to tell them (I'm lazy what can I say).  They also have amazingly good salads which surprised me.  I'm a big fan of spicy things also so I love their hot sauce selection.  I really love how they have the rating scale for how hot it is so you can find your perfect temperature.

The food is a little bit expensive for a sandwich place though.  And I found their new drink machine to be disappointing.  Nothing you can make from mix-and-match tastes as good as the real thing (like Coke+Cherry does not equal Cherry Coke).  It still provides a good selection though.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I haven't had a Firehouse this close to my home since I lived in Knoxville.  Thankfully, nowadays I'm going to grab dinner and not to relieve a hangover (most of the time.)  Anyway, we went in this past weekend, and I was very impressed.  The employees were really nice (although saying, "Welcome to Firehouse" each time someone walked in the door would cause me to impale someone with a jar of banana peppers.)  We got our food to-go and even after the 10-minute drive home, I still had to wait a little bit for my meatball sub to cool down so I could eat it.  YUM.  I've had a lot of meatballs in my life - like, so many it's not really ladylike - and I can say these are really well-seasoned and tasty as, well, something that you find really tasty.  Reasonable prices and clean atmosphere make this a place I will frequent, ummm, frequently.

text:
I've nothing but singing praise over how much better Firehouse Subs is than Subway is (not that this is saying much).  I've had Lenny's and Jersey Mike's also, but when Firehouse Subs opened about a two miles from my home, I just had to give it a try.

Verdict: pretty darn tasty.  They specialize in cooked meat subs, and the prices are reasonable.   So you've got as good as Jersey Mike's but not as expensive.  That's a recipe for success if I've ever seen one.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I've never had a bad experience in a Firehouse Sub Shop until today. When I got up to the register we exchanged a hello and then she literally walked away without a word to talk to an employee. She came back, I started talking again trying to order and then she did it again. Fianlly she comes back and actually pays attention to my order, all I wanted to get was an engineer sub, with no meat. Simple, easy. It becomes a delicious vegetarian swiss cheese mushroom sammich. At any other firehouse they have NO problem understanding this. She said the other Firehouse locations have no idea what they're doing. Just literally don't put any meat on it. No, she wanted to argue that it would just be a veggie sub. So that's what she rang it as. I got maybe 10-15 mushroom pieces, no swiss cheese, 70% shredded lettuce and a couple tomatoes. It was like eating 95% lettuce and bread, it was just sad. It took them 15 mins to make it even though there were more staff than customers present. In that time I listening to her push around/mock her staff like some kinda cranky sandwich overlord. Overall super negative vibes. I will not be spending money at this location again.

text: I generally like Firehouse subs but this one was a strange experience. I am wondering who the young lady and gentleman are who are not working here that are behind the counter. The girl is wearing sandals with no socks behind the counter and is distracting other employees enough they completely forgot to make a customer's order. Dancing around in front of the register for some reason acting like Miley Cyrus twerking.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I'm all in so far. At last, a sub shop with a concept that makes me at the very least, have cause for enjoying and even embracing the dysfunctional world we live in. Yes, it's another sub shop, but one that gives me a sense of childhood wonder that I haven't had in years. It's even given me a sense of being a real man...even after being raised by, and dangerously Wussified in the 1970s by a woman who would rather date me than her husband. Go to this place and git ya some sumbishin big sub sammishes and choice of hot sauces and watch some sports on the TV while yer there dammit...and no, it's not perfect, but yes...it's America.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I walked into firehouse around 2:45 PM on a Saturday. There was one table of customers seated and nobody else in the restaurant. I walked up to the register to place my order. There's one girl on her phone and one girl mopping as I stand and patiently wait for a couple minutes for one of them to take my order. The one mopping told the one on her phone to get off the phone and help me. She didn't put down her phone, clocked out, and then said I'm off clock. The girl mopping then stopped and took my order as she was laughing. I don't know of anyone else that would think poor customer service was humorous. Get it together, firehouse employees, and step up your customer service game. Otherwise, you won't be in business for long.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Every now and then I get on a sub kick and when I do it's hard for me to choose between Jersey Mike's, Penn Station, and Firehouse, especially since all 3 are right down the street from me. I guess the only thing that really stands out for me about Firehouse compared to the other 2 is that they offer a lower calorie option of a smaller sandwich. Same great fresh, sliced on the spot, meats and cheeses (if you choose) but it's on a smaller round bun vs. a larger sub roll. And less meat and cheese, of course. Customer service has always been great and the prices are comparable to the other mentioned sub shops. The local fire station dcor is pretty cool, too.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
You ever have a taste for something? That was me last week. I had to have the steak sandwich from Firehouse Subs. I placed my order. I asked for no cheese. I get home and my sandwich had cheese. Too tired to go back or call. 
Today I was determined to have my sandwich. I ordered before I left I asked the lady in the purple shirt who handed me my order if we could check my sandwich before I left. She turned to a gentleman who was preparing orders and asked if the sandwich had cheese. He looked confused another gentleman said he put cheese on both sandwiches. They began to mumble to each other. They all got busy filling orders. No one addressed me or apologized for the "mistake". After an additional 10 minutes she handed me my order with just a have a good day. Anyone can mistake, it's how you handle. So no not happy with Firehouse right not. I have a problem with bad customer service. Do better people please!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "'loud'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I would have to say that Firehouse subs serves up pretty bland sandwiches.  The turkey had very little taste to it and was on the mushy side.  Not good.  On a later second attempt, I tried the Ham and Turkey Sub Combo.  Again, very bland . . .(didn't suffer, though, because there was very little meat in the sandwich . . . mostly bread and lettuce).  The sub came with their version of a  "Deli Dill" - a quarter sliver of a dill pickle and some chips ... pretty weak offerings.   In the end, very corporate and soul-less stuff.  Definitely a case of style over substance!

text: I am giving Firehouse a one star for the four times I have been there. I am a big believer in giving most places a few chances before writing them off. There is nothing wrong with the service or cleanliness of any of the sites I have been too. I really just don't care for these subs. I have tried a different sub every time I have gone thinking it will be different. To me their meats do not have any flavor. The subs just seem very bland. My daughter absolutely loves the meatball sub that's why I have given it more try's. It takes a lot for me not to like a sub. Sorry Firehouse it's time to go to my favorite Jersey Mikes.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'DogsAllowed': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: First time @ this location & first time in a long time I've had Firehouse and just as good as I remember. Cashier, Spencer, was polite and helpful, as well as the two making sandwiches on Saturday night. I ordered the only sub I've ever tried here, the New York Steamer, which is absolutely amazing. The meat combination with cheese and Italian dressing, on soft white bread & then steamed.. perfection. If you've never tried Firehouse, or have never given this location a chance, I strongly suggest it. I really enjoy the Coca-Cola machine as well, which gives you options to make any soda & flavor combination which goes great with a hot sub. Thanks again!  5-stars.

text:
A bit pricey for your typical sandwich.  I ordered the New York Steamer and paid for it online.  When my co-worker took the receipt to pick it up, they said they never received the order.  Somehow only 3/5 orders went through, so there was a wait for two of the sandwiches to be made.  But that's not why the rating is low.

I just thought the sandwich was unimpressive and typical of what I could make at home.  The wheat bread was really disappointing.  It was hard and chewy.  This sentiment resonated with all of my other colleagues who also ordered a sandwich on wheat.  I can't complain about the quality of meat; it was good.  The veggies were fresh, but the Italian dressing was completely flavorless.  I will most likely pass given the choice to eat here again.

text:
I'm a little torn on the rating for this restaurant.  I'm not sure it rates a 3, but a 2 might be a little low.

On the plus side:  It's clean, the employees are friendly and helpful, and the atmosphere makes it just "fun".

On the minus side:  The sandwiches are just average, and the prices are high for what you get.

I would stop here again if I were with folks who wanted to eat here, but wouldn't make a point to go on my own.

text: Some of the best sandwiches in speedway. Large portions and a fair price. The Engineer on wheat fully involved is amazing! Glad they have healthy options like wheat instead white bread. text: Decided to stop in for lunch recently for the first time. I decided on the New York Steamer, my husband ordered the Steak and Cheese. Ordered a combo for my son, too, and didn't realize kids meals were only $.99 on Sunday (score!). My sandwich was OK. Not exactly piled high, and not much to it. On the other hand, my husband's was excellent, one of the best cheesesteaks I've had. My son enjoyed his turkey sub as well. The bread was nice and soft. The drinks were good- I enjoyed both the signature Cherry Limeade and fresh brewed iced tea. The service was great and attentive. In all, a satisfying lunch for 3 at just under $20.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': None, u'validated': None}", 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text: I looove Firehouse! However, my favorite sub sandwich, the Engine Company, is no longer available on the menu. Bummer, right? Well, yes and no. See the trick is, when ordering via Door Dash or Uber Eats, you should call the location, prayerfully get a kind, polite and helpful employee who will tell you what to put into said delivery app to achieve your desired "Engine Company" results. So, I spoke with the most amazing employee, can't remember his first name at the moment (blame last night's tequila), but his last name is Oliver, and he is working at this location today, 9/26/21 @12:46p. He informed me that I should order the hook and ladder and sub the ham for roast beef. See, there's always more than one way to skin a cat. Flexibility and nimbleness are key to growth. Being agile is the real flex, and today, Mr. Oliver understood the assignment. For this, on this fine Sunday, I am grateful!

text:
I know folks that RAVE about Firehouse Subs.  There's not one really close to where I live, but a group of friends were meeting for dinner, so that gave me the perfect opportunity to try them.

From the one experience I had, I'm not quite sure what all the fuss is about.  There was nothing outstanding about what I got, and the prices are a bit high for what you get.  I would not go out of my way to have a meal here.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Everyone in my family  (2 adults and 5 kids) really enjoy their sandwiches. My ten year old loves all the beverage options their cool soda fountain provides. It had became a regular quick dinner for us, 3 times in the past month. Our most recent visit may be our last. We were enjoyng our sandwiches with a friend who had tagged along (his first visit to Firehouse), when a group 3 intoxicated people came in puffing away on e-cigarettes. I thought for sure that they would be asked to "smoke" outside. But they were not. Before long there was a cloud of fumes filling the dining area as they stood at the end of the counter waiting for their order . No one working there said a word to them about it. We gathered up our kids and headed out. I mentioned to the girl behind the counter that we were leaving because they were allowing them to "smoke". She looked confused....so much for being "family friendly".

text: This place is fantastic. When you walk in the door you are promptly greeted by their friendly staff. This was my first time at any of the firehouse locations and the staff was more than willing to find out what my tastes were. They also have a really cool 'menu tour' which is very informative and gives a little bit of the history. They have a large selection of hot sauces from the weak to the fiery inferno and an even larger selection of drinks. I was not disappointed at all and I will definitely be returning for lunch many more times!

text: This was my first visit to any of the firehouse sub restaurants. I had heard that the meatball sub was top notch. Well it lived up to its billing. Excellent sauce and the meatballs were definitely not heated up in the microwave. The service was a little slow for as few people that they had in the store. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Sub's is a chain, so this location is much like every other store. Place your order at the counter, pay, and wait for your sandwich to be made and your name called out. While waiting you can grab a seat at a table and get your beverage, there is a Coca-Cola Freestyle machine here so can customize your soda to fit your personality. 

The food here is pretty good, a step up from Subway. The sandwiches are served on steamed bread. I usually prefer the Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket, its more than enough to fill even the biggest of appetites, if not you can always get a larger sandwich. Prices are reasonable, and service is usually however during peak times this location can get crowded especially during school as this is location seems to be popular with the Lindenwood crowd.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Thought it was going to be something like a Subway, but it's definitely not! I'd recommend trying the Smokehouse Beef and Cheddar Brisket for a delicious taste treat. Plenty of meat piled on a wheat bun. The BBQ sauce and mayo were a perfect balance for the cheddar cheese. Very filling sandwich, and a fair price for what you get. The restaurant was clean and the there was some cool local firefighter memorabilia on the walls. I'll definitely be back again to try some other sandwiches.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Very good subs and friendly customer service! FHS has always had great subs ever since they originated in FL, I couldn't wait to eat here, when I heard they were opening this location! The sub selection is very large and the theme of the restaurant is amazing, using local fire department equipment and pictures! The subs can sometimes be a bit lacking but that is only on rare occasion but the staff is also new and sometimes can be lacking in customer interaction skills. But overall this is one of the best sub shops in town by far and love to eat there every chance that I get!

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: During my first visit at this location, I was blown away by the kindness of, who I assumed to be, the owner. He was holding the door open for patrons and then took over a register when the line became three deep. He was so friendly and the staff was equally as kind and welcoming. During my second visit, he was not present and the staff's energy and welcoming attitudes were sub-par. However, the food was great and I would definitely recommend FHS for a quick meal.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Been going to this Firehouse for a little over a year now for lunch at work. Just recently I noticed a complete staff change including managers. Today, I called ahead at 12 and asked for my food to be ready at 1 as that's when my lunch would be. I get to Firehouse at 1:10 and am told my food will be ready in 10 minutes. This is the second time this has happened. An hour notice and food not ready on time- actually late. Not impressed with this. This did not happen with the previous staff. Otherwise good food, only reason why I came back after the first mix up. Not sure if I'll be back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Recently ordered online and found out the hard way that the Firehouse on Bass Pro was closed when picking up my order. Yelp showed that they closed at 10pm but the store's website showed they  close at 9pm. Why did they still take my money after it closed? The franchisee stated yelp goes out and checks that all the time, well how is the time wrong after so many months? Also, the 3rd party who handles the online transactions should not be able to take orders after the store closes!! This is a big issue!! The next day I called the store and stated the issue, but one of the owners was not helpful at all.... Larry was very condescending when speaking to me. He also seemed to just show me the door and take his food on his delivery than help me at all. No discount for driving to the store twice in 2 days, no coupons, no nothing for wasting my time.  I will not be going to Firehouse anymore after this shameful display by a franchise owner.

text: We love Firehouse Subs and have come to this location since it opened.  It has steadily declined since then though.  It is chronically slow, food isn't as tasty as it was and the cleanliness varies.  The slow service is just the worst.  It takes so long we started ordering online before we come. Even at that we will wait at least another 20 minutes past the time when the food is supposed to be ready. Every. Time.  They aren't understaffed so it makes no sense. attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text:
I found out about this place while at the St. Charles Chill hockey game. My family decided we would give it a try since we all hate subway.  We went there on a Sunday about 1p and the place was packed!  When we stepped the cashier, she was nice enough to explain their are different ways to order and she could tell by our concussion that we hadn't been there before. 

We ended up getting the meatball, which my son LOVED!!!  Especially since the sandwich is served open face and the provolone is melted onto the side of the bread. So he is under the impression that he's getting two items, a meatball sub and cheese bread. The cashier talked me into the New York Steamer, which I must say was outstanding!  Nothing makes me happier then a sandwich that falls apart and has juice dripping all over the place.  That to me is a sign of a GREAT sandwich. The messier the better. My wife got the smokehouse need and cheddar brisket, I'm assuming she loved it since she wouldn't let me have a bite. 

Also the crazy soda fountain. My son thought it was futuristic. So many ways to create your own soda, and loved that it was a touchscreen just like an iPad. 

This place is a top notch sub shop. The manager greasing you at the door, the cashiers and the food. All outstanding.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text:
I'm conflicted, being a police officer the age old hidden rivalry between us and the fire department tells me to stay away, but from what I have heard this place is supposed to be delicious, so I decided to give it a go.

I had a coupon...that also helped.

My wife and I walked in right before a HUGE lunch rush. We got in, ordered and sat down before the cattle drive moved in. I ordered TWO sandwiches because...well I was just plain hungry. Haha! The ambiance was entertaining, and the fire department lingo used in the order process made my laugh.

I had a brisket/cheddar sub and a turkey club sub. Both were top notch. I also had a bag of chips, nothing special there, but they are chips...who doesn't like chips. I see this as a cheaper, but more tasty, alternative to Quizno's. I am a long standing hater of Quizno's, mostly because the exuberant pricing and mediocre taste. I was kinda glad to see them go around St. Louis. This is better, but still more pricey than Subway or Mr. Goodcents. The subs are a bit small, I even ended up finishing my wife's and I was still a bit hungry after almost three medium subs. I probably won't go back often, since I am still partial to Subway, Goodscents and even the occasional Jimmy John's, but this is another option in the sandwich wars that I can recommend to anyone without regret.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text:
Turtles could probably build sandwiches more quickly. Honestly, some of the slowest service ever. Consistently. Not just today, but every time I've been here, it has taken an inordinate amount of time to get my food. 

I never order anything super complicated. There aren't typically a lot of customers there. 

Today, I was annoyed, as the man who came in after me and ordered a sub to go was given his food before me - by the only gal (out of at least four employees there) who was making the sandwiches.

It took TEN minutes to get my medium turkey sub. TEN. I checked in on Yelp when I arrived and it was literally ten minutes until my sandwich arrived. 

There was one couple sitting down when I walked in. They were almost finished eating. And literally no one ahead of me. I don't get it. 

I'll head to one in Maryland Heights next time. Or anywhere else, really. This place isn't worth the wait.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': True, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True'}
text: Don't waste your time at this location. The manager/franchise owner or whoever Larry is,  is as lost as they come. I tried giving the benefit of the doubt but it's every time I go. I won't be surprised if I get food poisoning. Yesterday  I placed an order online and when I got there, 20 minutes later, the ticket was literally still on the printer thing and the kids behind the counter said it just printed off. Jokes on them, it prints out the time when it comes through and you could blatantly see 513pm. There was no one in there and I got the privilege of listening to a job interview in there. After that, I am not surprised why the service is terrible here. Just drive to the one of Dorsett instead of here.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
I have ate here on a few occasions when in town. I have always enjoyed the food here. The briscuit melts in your mouth and the barbecue sauce was surprisingly unique. I usually stick to their promotional sub but the new york steamer is always good as well.

I tried their chili for the first time and was not impressed but I did finish it. 

The eating area is tigh at best and leaves you feeling a little cramped. Probably a better place to get a to go than eat in. 

All in all, I will keep a look out for Firehouse Subs when I am on the road.

text:
The sub was really amazing. I went with my friend. We got one No: 9 and 10 ( fire house hero sub and smoke house cheese & cheddar brisket) No: 10 was really juicy and No: 9 was a different taste. They have lot of sauces ranging from 1-10 depending upon their hotness.. Try all the sauces from no:7 those ho really well with the sub. We also tried Kings Hawaiian burger... Such an amazing and juicy one... The pork was well smoked and tasted really good.

We will go once again if we get a chance...

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
1st time at this location but definitely not a first at Firehouse.  When I walked in there were 4 employees working diligently behind the counter and all 4 looked up and greeted me, "Welcome to Firehouse." I had a fairly large order and when I came in 20 minutes earlier than what I had originally told them for pickup, they had all 7 orders ready in no time. Great service!

This location is almost spotless as well.  The food is always great at Firehouse. Fresh ingredients, meat and especially the bread. Great menu for those watching calories and for those who are not! They also have a great selection of hot sauces lined up ready for use and labeled 1-10 on the heat scale. I got the large Italian sub with chips and it was delicious. I will definitely be coming back to this location!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
I really like firehouse subs but this is not a place to go for a healthy sandwich.  I skip the mayo on all my subs but I have to draw the line when it comes to skipping the cheese.   The one exception I'll make to this is the Beef Brisket sub which is DELICIOUS and you can skip the cheese and the mayo and not be missing out.  Its' still almost 600 calories so I wouldn't recommend eating it everyday.  

They do have a pretty fancy coke machine there that allows you to make almost any drink you could possibly want (if you want orange flavored coke, you can get it).  I didn't actually love the machine because when I got my diet cherry coke, it had way to much cherry syrup in it. Now I know better and I'll adjust it accordingly for next time.  

If you're in a Quizno's rut, Firehouse would be a good place to try!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text: The NY Steamer is one of the best sandwiches I've had since I left New York.  Granted, I've been out of the US most of that time, so I didn't have a lot of opportunities.  Still, it was a great sandwich and relatively cheap.  I'll be going back again, and look forward to trying more of the menu.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
I'm just not a hot sandwich kind of girl but my meatball sub was okay.  It was gigantic and I only ordered a medium!  I was able to get two meals out of it.  The service was quick and the line moved along at a good pace.

After you order they ask you if you'd like to round up your order to the next dollar amount as a donation to whatever cause they're supporting.  When I was there it was for the victims of the November tornado outbreak in Illinois and Indiana.  I'm not quite sure how I feel about them asking.

In my ranking of sub places: Jimmy John's, Subway, Quiznos, Firehouse.  Eh...just not a fan.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
I was surprised at how good these subs are.  I thought that the food tasted fresh and the bread was excellent.

I had the chicken salad sandwhich and my husband had the italian sub.  Both were made well and in a timely manner.

 I would go here again.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text: We ordered online and when we arrived our order had not been received. No worries though as management comped us two drinks while they prepared the order. The soda machine is not to be missed as it blends any of the coke products with most every flavor you can imagine. I had coke zero raspberry. The Sammie's arrived hot and yummy. The hot sauces are an interesting twist. Tried one rated 4 on 1-10 hotness scale and it wasn't hot at all. Went to try the recommended sauce and it had been fermenting at room temperature so beware of bursting caps when you open. Will skip the hot sauces next time.

text:
I just had a firehouse steak sub delivered when it was pouring.  the sandwich was cold but I think maybe it may have waited for the driver to return from another run.   recommend, making sandwiches more closer to delivery time.

Subsequent orders through grubhub have been better.  Not sure who to blame:  firehouse or grubhub.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
This is a new restaurant by the Pyramids that opened probably a couple weeks ago.  At the office yesterday, we all decided to go try it out.  The place was packed out the door by 12pm, which is probably due to the place being new.  Everyone loves a new restaurant by the Pyramids!

It was hard to see the menu and wait in line to order for the food.  We waited for almost 30+ minutes before the food arrived at our table.  Based on observation, it appeared they were servicing all the to-go orders before any of the dining patrons first.  The server was very friendly and apologetic for the wait and try to do everything he could to make us feel at ease.

I ordered the Engineer Sub with a pickle on the side.  There was no pickle on the side.  There was supposed to be spicy mustard, but there was none on my sandwich either.  The presentation of the food was also not the most appealing; my turkey and tomatoes were not under the bread, but tossed on the plate.

Overall, there were kinks with our experience, and it's understandable due to it being a brand new restaurant.  The restaurant was opened by firefighters, so it seemed really cool to be able to provide support; therefore, I will try it again.  Hopefully, by then, the kinks will be ironed out, and there will be another great sub place to eat at for lunch.  However, based on my current experience, I can only give it 3 stars, but hopefully, my updated review will provide more stars.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text:
I have had a few subs from this location and they tasted fine but nothing outstanding to me. The prices seem expensive for what you get as the sandwiches don't seem to have that much meat on them, as there photos show on their menu. 

I have tried many varieties of their hot sauce which they have sitting out for anyone to use. They have all kinds of crazy names for the hot sauces and the employees tell you not to use more than a toothpick dip worth or it will burn your mouth. 

So with me liking very hot sauce I took their advice and tried some, and like most places there hot sauce failed my heat test. I had to use a lot of their hottest sauce in my chili to spice it up. But I understand for the average customer they can only make sauce so hot. 

So aficionados of extreme heat will not be satisfied with their sauces no matter how scary of a name they give them, lol. The sub sandwiches tasted better than the cheaper franchise subs but not as good as some of the other more top-of-the-line sub shops.

text: Average subs. It's a good substitute if you're in a hurry and don't want fast food. The reason I am writing this is because of the staff here. text: Visited today for the first time and had a very nice experience! My husband loves firehouse subs and has been trying to get me to go. Let me first start off by saying I'm not a big sub person....but I very much liked their Italian sub. So much so, I would go back and get it again! It had just the right amount of bread, meats, veggies and Italian dressing/Mayo combo oozing out. My husband had the New York sub which he loved and we share a side of Mac and Cheese which was also good! I can see us going back soon and I'm happy we have one close by on 86th street. The staff was very nice and helpful and it was easy to order. We were the only ones inside at the time so that made it nice with Covid but they also offer online ordering and curbside pickup to make it a breeze.

text: Grubhub completely screwed up and did not assign a driver. Candy at Firehouse called me, and after several unsuccessful attempts by both of us to reach Grubhub, it was determined that I would have to go without food and receive a refund from Grubhub the next day. text:
I hadn't heard about Firehouse Subs, well, ever...it's strange, I have a strong love for Jimmy Johns (as a cold sub) and, well, my loyalties lie with Subway in terms of hot subs and, just, subs in general.

Instead, I tried to give 'em a try one day- after all, there's no WRONG time for a grilled/toasted sub. I was pleasantly surprised to find that they have an abundance of veggies, sauce options, and they're pretty generous with the amount they put on there! As a vegetarian, we usually have issues getting enough substance into our subs - hence the loyalty to Subway, where they voluntarily load subs with a plethora of vegetables.

After having recently tried Jersey Mike's, I'd definitely go for Firehouse any day: I'm assuming it's the Italian dressing that makes it. At least, I'll stick with Firehouse until I make it out East for a really satisfying toasted sandwich.

text:
As with a visit to any Firehouse location, our food was great.  However, unlike visits to numerous other locations in various states, the service at this location was much different - and not in a good way.  The cashier was abrupt and almost rude, both when taking my order and then giving my order to me.  I realize that they appeared to be busy, but that really isn't justification for being short with your customers. 

UPDATE - upon a return visit to Indy this week, we did return to this location on two separate visits for dinner on 5/14 and 5/15.   On both occasions, the staff was incredibly friendly and provided great service.  We had VERY different experiences from our first one and will return to this location on future visits to Indy.

attributes: {'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'"}
text: I have been going to this Firehouse for about 10 years - give or take. I used to love the food here but lately it kind of makes me sick. It just does not taste as good as it did in the past. The employees here are extremely rude and when they are trying to be nice it is fake. The employees don't even treat each other well. On several occasions, I have seen them fighting/bickering amongst each other. I am guessing this comes from a manager or someone in charge. When you see this pattern it comes from the top. The employees see a manager acting a certain way and they emulate it good or bad and in this case it is bad. Also, last time I was there the bathroom was disgusting and the vegetables on my sandwich were slimy. They must not be holding cold foods at proper temperatures. Also, the prices are too high. I think I am done with this place - the main reason I ate here was because it was close to work but there are so many other good places to eat in Indianapolis where you are treated well and the food is good. It is too bad though because I used to like this place.

text:
Three times and I will not be back.   Waited to write my review until I knew for sure how I really felt.   Each time I have ordered take-out.  Each time there has been a service issue with basically an empty restaurant.  The bread does not hold up to the inside of the sandwiches.   Meats do not seem to be of high quality.  Only plus is the countless hot sauces, which can be taken in small to-go cups.  

You will find my at Viviano's across the street...

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
My rating should not be confused.  I am rating a sub shop, not  comparing  Firehouse  to Kemoll's, this is a sub sandwich shop to other sub sandwich shops I have been to review. That said, if I were a franchisee of Subway, I would start to worry if a Firehouse Sub is opening anywhere near.  While they don't serve hamburgers, if I owned an Arby's or Lion's Choice, I would be looking over my shoulder to see who is gaining on me.

There are currently 10 locations, and I have only been to the Chesterfield shop in the Forum Shopping center (at the northern terminus of Woods Mill was, before they rebuilt it).

Squeeky clean facility, but I don't understand the economics of building a one holer restroom in a brand new fast food restaurant.  Lion's Choice made the same mistake at their new shop on Clarkson.  The problem is if a gent forgets to lock the door, the second man in exposes the first guy hanging out......

Ok let's talk about sandwiches.  You name it they either have it as a standard offering with a cute fireman's lingo like "Hook & Ladder" or you can combine any meats and toppings you want, with a wide variety of meats.  They have a 500 calorie menu, a tuna option for non-meat eaters, and a vegan sandwich.

Here comes my only complaint....Don't call it a "New York Steamer" piled high with corned beef and pastrami, and then slather mayo on it.  Pull that trick in NYC and you will be out of business in a minute.  I did not think to order my "Steamer" with only mustard, although I could have.

Other than the mayo, my "New York Steamer" was hot, juicy, and had a lot of meat on it.  Unlike Subway which is spotty at best, they lavish on the ingredients.  

The young folks working there were friendly and nice to deal with.  They were patient with us, because as new customers on our first visit, the menu was enormous and making a selection difficult.  My wife had something with turkey on wheat, and really enjoyed it.

I honestly don't know what Kristen S. ate, but my meat was tender, juicy and favorable. The large sandwich is quite a handful.....They have a sauce bar if you want to add flavors to your meal, and they thankfully put a ranking number on the bottle so as a customer you don't get shocked by a habanero based product.

The Coke machine is worth going to this shop, to see what a really smart company does to demonstrate their product.  It was really interesting to see all of the various options.

Totally an enjoyable quick meal...We will return and are super pleased that they opened near our home.

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I've gone to this Firehouse Subs quite a few times now and every time I have gone, I have had a great experience. The people that work there are always friendly and they are ALWAYS doing something (working). No one is just sits there watching TV or attempting to text behind the counter. I've been here when it's very slow and when it was packed and they still give me a great sandwich with good customer service. They always greet you when you walk in so they know that you will be ordering. I ordered the Italian and it was delicious! The medium is a pretty good size and with a drink and chips, it's just the right amount if you're hungry. I have used their mobile app and ordered through there and the quality of the food is still good when I go to pick it up. I recommend this place over Jimmy Johns or even Subway which is close by because their food actually tastes good, the place is consistently clean. They also support local first responders which I think is admirable.

text:
No thank you. I paid $4.34 and donated my change to the firemen. I ordered a small turkey, bacon, and ranch sub. The piece of bread was enough alone to make me laugh out loud. The sandwich was too damn small to feed my 3 year old... not to mention they forgot half of my toppings.

text:
This review reflects my first visit.

I arrived around dinnertime.  There were several people already dining, but the line was nonexistent.  I ordered the King's Hawaiian special, which had 12 hour smoked pulled pork, cole slaw, pepperjack cheese all on a King's Hawaiian roll.

The sandwich was ready very quickly, and it came out hot and delicious.  The pulled pork was very flavorful.  This is a must try item.  I was able to finish it without any leftovers, so you may consider getting the combo or something additional to eat if you are extremely hungry.  

I will definitely be back.

text: This is now my go to place for a hot sub sandwich!! They have a good selection of subs! I really like their sweet 'n' spicy meatball sandwich! You can get your sandwich on either wheat or white bread. You can also order you sub fully involved which will load your sub with mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a kosher dill pickle on the side. They also have a pretty large selection of bbq & hot sauces that you can add to your sandwich.

text: I expect this to be better than Subway, but after one bite, give me a subway any day over this. First, there is no small size. The 8" and 5" cost the same, because you get the same amount of meat. Secondly, the meat tasted low quality. For the price I paid, I expect it to be better. After a few bites, I couldn't take it anymore. I paid as much for 3 subs as I could have a nice takeout at an Indian or Italian restaurant. Both of us had the Italian sub and we both did not feel well afterward. Our kid got something else so he was ok. I definitely will not come back. I want my money back.

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I was hungry and in a hurry, as I was going down highway 141.  I stopped at Firehouse, this was my second visit in about 2 months.

The line to order was short, and the young lady who took my order was super friendly, and courteous.  This was not an employee working just because she had too, she actually cared about me and was very thorough ensuring I got the right things.

They advertise the brisket as having been smoked 16 hours at a Texas smokehouse. I have been a judge for the Kansas City BBQ Society, and can tell you that the brisket was better than 95% of the contestants I have judged.

The coke machine is worth a visit in itself.  I don't want to spoil the secret, but it is more fun than the coin machines seen around, and gives you exactly what you want.

The sandwich was hot, and just as advertised on the radio.  It was hot, and the young man making the sandwich was fast and efficient, also just like the cashier, very courteous.  

Great service, a very good sandwich and impeccably clean.

text:
Food: 3 Stars
Service: 3 Stars

Conveniently located along Olive and near highway 141, Firehouse Subs can easily be seen from the main road. There's plenty of private parking in the shared lot in the front, and the venue is pretty quiet despite being near a busy street. 

I love the concept of Firehouse Subs and the charity it backs. The story behind the chain always tugs at my heart, which is why we make sure to visit from time to time. The subs are nothing out of the ordinary, but will for sure satisfy any hunger you had. Be sure to check out their collection of hot sauces and try a couple on your next sub! We have a good time rating the ones we like. :)

attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: An unfortunate  experience.  Let me start by saying I have eaten here many times and have always enjoyed it.  However, on my last visit which was 2 months ago, we had company over and I went in to place a to go order.  One of the sandwiches was a large "build your own" with specific ingredients for our guest.  I picked up the order about 30 minutes before closing time. When I got it home it had many extra ingredients that were not specified when I placed the "build your own" order.  Our guest did not take one bite out of his nearly $10 sandwich because it was not what he ordered.  We called back to the restaurant and spoke to the person who took the order (who we are on a first name basis with because of our many visits). She said they automatically make "build your own" sandwiches "fully involved" which includes mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato & onion. The order I placed was for a meat and cheese only sandwich. She then put the manager on the phone.  He said that he would "send us something in the mail" and took our address and we never heard from them again.  Because of that experience I have never returned.  It's too bad because I did like the restaurant but I don't like getting ripped off.
