text:
Super yummy subs!  Hard to choose because they all look so good.  I've tried the brisket & cheddar, turkey bacon ranch, and New York steamer so far, all of which have been delicious.  Their bread is soft and slightly chewy, toasted to match the hot meat and cheese so well!

All of the staff were very friendly, accommodating and enthusiastic.  The restaurant was very clean inside.

There are diaper-changing stations in both the men's and women's bathrooms!  Parenting win!

May have to make Firehouse Subs a new staple...

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I went today after errands. It was after 2 p.m., so there weren't too many people in the house.

They say, "Welcome to Firehouse Subs" to every patron who walks in the door. They're not looking at you; their eyes are down. It's kinda muttered and extremely unenthusiastic.

They should either stop doing it or do it much better.

The order-taker explained that all sandwiches are served hot. He told me the most popular sandwich overall (Hook and Ladder), and the most popular sandwich in St. Louis (Beef and Cheddar Brisket).

I asked specifically about the chicken salad sandwich, and he told me all the ingredients. I confirmed that there was no sugar in it. He said no, but there's black pepper and a little curry.

I ended up with a to-go Momma's Chicken salad sandwich ($6.26 with tax) from the "Under 500 Calorie" menu: small-diced chicken, pecans, green pepper, Swiss, tomato and light mayo on a light wheat roll (495 calories).

He asked if I wanted a pickle spear on the side. That was the most exciting question I was asked today.

When I got home, I found the pickle spear (dill) beautifully wrapped in a recyclable plastic bag that precluded pickle juice from getting to the sandwich. Brilliant. And it was delicious.

The sandwich was well-wrapped and secured with a little sticker.

 The light wheat roll had a great, nutty flavor. I think there were two tomato slices on the sandwich along with the other ingredients, but I didn't taste the pecans. And I didn't taste curry.

The bigger disappointment was the texture of the chicken salad. The chicken seemed nearly ground. It was too mushy and needed some gumption.

I would go here again, but I would not get the chicken salad in any form.

The hot sauce bar is filled with crusted over bottles and half are empty. Place looks clean and staff is friendly but the food is a travesty.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This is my close A-OK consistent quality sandwich shop.  (On my birthday I got a free sub w/o joining a club.)

It is great for a chain restaurant, but makes me miss the small 5 star delis on St Louis Hill like Eovaldi's.

The employees are nice & helpful.
They have the great make your own creation coke machine.
They warm up their meats in steamer trays to enhance the flavor vs Subways microwaves (NEVER MICROWAVE MEAT!).
I love the hot sauce rack & the included pickle slice.

I like the formula... I just can tell it is a formula vs heart.  I have never been disappointed.  However, I have never been amazed.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The food at this location is usually good. Unfortunately this time they brought out the wrong sandwich, and forgot part of another meal. I didn't really care for the Cajun chicken, I chalk that up to I just didn't care for the taste and no fault of the employees. My overall experience was terrible. The female taking our order seemed annoyed at my family's presence. The drink area was filthy, they were out of large lids, there was a sandwich maker wearing his hat around his neck. The individual, that I'm assuming is the manager, did apologize for not having the correct sized lids.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': True, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: So last weekend I didn't leave the house for a 36 hour stretch and about 24 hours in I decided to use DoorDash for the first time ever and settled on Firehouse Subs because it is extremely close to me and had the shortest delivery time. I ordered the Steak & Cheese Sub, a cup of Loaded Potato Soup, and a large Diet Coke. My order arrived promptly (about 30 minutes) and the food was satisfactory. Not amazing but satisfactory. All of my modifications to the sandwich were accommodated. I question the quality of the meat but perhaps its best I did not see it live in person. The Diet Coke had good carbonation! The pickle was crisp and had a good snap to it! The food was a little salty but I think that's to be expected somewhere like this, right?

text: I ate there for the first time on 6/21 in the afternoon. My sub was good, not great, and definitely overpriced. Service was fairly quick but the young ladies behind the counter seemed young and immature. I doubt I'll be back.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Fresh subs made while you wait. Love the combos of the sandwiches - things I'd never think of. My fave is New York Steamer which has Corn Beef, Pastrami, and melted Provolone. What makes it best is Italian dressing.  Yummy! 

Prices are a bit high but there are choice of sizes from small, medium and large. And let me tell you I'd choose this any day over Subway. 

Usually made quickly. Nice to hear a greeting from the staff and a smile. I've eaten here a few times and will be back again and again.

text: Today was my first time in a Firehouse Subs and I was very pleasantly surprised. I would definitely go back and look forward to doing so. My sandwich was delicious and so was my brownie. My only complaint is the restroom.. I walked in and walked right back out. Being 9 months pregnant and not being able to use the restroom is a bummer. Although I know the restroom probably wasn't their fault, they probably hadn't been notified about it and hadn't had a chance to clean it up.. so, not holding it against them.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The hook-and-ladder sandwich is halfway decent, but a little overpriced for what it is (fast food). Chips aren't even included with the meal. Publix has much better sandwiches, even if theirs take a little longer to prepare. Head across the street and grab food there if you can bring it home. The spicy sauces are nice, though.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Yesterday (9-2-16) was my 2nd visit...exactly the same as the first...wonderful. Their prices are slightly higher than Subway, but the amount of meat you get is at least doubled, if not tripled. The quality of their sandwiches are beyond reproach. Every order has been perfect. The staff friendly & professional. The restaurant completely clean. I love the fact that you can dine inside or out. I love that they have mushrooms (Subway doesn't), but the charge of .75 cents is a little ridiculous. Family of four, 3 combos & one just a sandwich-$40. At about $10 per person-that's a little pricey for a sandwich & chips. But, honestly, that is the only thing I can find that could use some attention. I really enjoy Subway, but when I'd like to take the sandwich up a notch, Firehouse is it.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'BikeParking': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Alright, I've had bad service before, but never have I actually been DISRESPECTED by a store manager...  Until tonight.

I live down in Tampa, but my son had a football game in Spring Hill, so after the game, we all saw the newly-opened Firehouse and decided to grub down on some sandwiches.  There is a Firehouse that we frequent in Tampa and the service and subs are always top-notch, so we were licking our chops as we pulled up to the store!

I guess the first mistake I made was not paying close enough attention to the time.  We walked in around 8:40 and placed our order at 8:45ish.  The store was surprisingly busy, so there were quite a few orders in front of ours.  We grabbed our chips and drinks, then sat down and waited for our order.  When they called my name, I went up to the counter to retrieve our vittles, which was packed up in bags.  I asked the guy, "Don't you usually serve these in baskets?"  "Oh, you have to take the order to go because we're closed now," was how he replied.  So I told the kid that I was from out of town and had no place to eat the sandwiches, so if I couldn't sit down and eat, I'd cancel the order and request a refund.  And this is where the magic happens.  The store manager, identifiable by his black shirt and name tag that read "manager," chimed in and said, "You can't have a refund because the order is already made."  I told the manger, "Had I been advised at the time I placed my order, I would have simply gone somewhere that I could eat."  His reply was, "That's not my problem."  At this point, I was flummoxed and at a loss for words.  So I went to grab the food, and he sighed heavily and said, "Go ahead and sit down to eat, but hurry it up."  So I turned around, looked at his name tag and said, "You're the manager?  Dave Harris?"  And he said, "Yeah that's right.  Do it!"  As if he was daring me to file a formal complaint.  As I was walking away, I heard him say to another employee, "What a jerk!" For real???? I seriously couldn't believe this guy.  I mean, where the HELL did Firehouse find this assclown?  Did he manage the soup nazi's joint on Seinfeld?  What store manager of a newly-opened location would speak to paying customers like that... with that tone? Wow.

After next week's football game, I can tell you where I'm *NOT* dropping $40 on food!

Side note, as we were rapidly scarfing down our sandwiches, one of the younger employees walked by and said, "Sorry about that."  He should be promoted to manager immediately.

text:
I've heard the subs at this location were the best (from a friend) so I had been dying to try Firehouse for months.  I got a meatball sub and it wasn't the best I've had.  In fact I won't go back for another sub as I was very disappointed on the taste.  I ate the meatballs as I paid for them but left the rest of the sub.  It took a  lot to finish the meatballs as I just didn't care for the taste, ...but like I said, I paid for them.

Perhaps it's great for other's tastes but for mine, I'd prefer almost anyone's subs than these.

I left without expressing my opinion to the staff.

attributes: {'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BYOB': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Corkage': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
My first visit to Firehouse Subs was at best disappointing. 
First, the online ordering via computer was clunky and getting the order submitted was difficult. If you did not set a pickup time far enough in advance, the system would tell it changed it but once you said OK, it still would not submit the order. And the hoops that you had to jump through to get the order in the cart was terrible. Clearly the ordering system for a computer was not thoroughly tested for ease of use.
But the Steak and Cheese Sub was the most disappointing. If you compare the pictures of what you were to receive and what you received, you would see how bad this sub was. Where was the onions, green peppers, steak, cheese and all of the other ingredients that was to be there? The only good thing was the roll. There was so little in the roll, I would not even call this a sub.

attributes: {'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BYOB': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Corkage': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text: Today was the first time I have been to a Firehouse. I waited because sandwich's I normally eat cold do not sound good to me hot. I didn't venture out of my comfort zone today though I was tempted. I ordered the pastrami. I'm serious it was outstanding. From the meat to the bread to the slaw. They should add that to their regular menu. I didn't like the soup, there was something that I don't care for, some ingredient I just didn't like. They have lots of options for low calorie, low sugar drinks, it was great. They also have a lot of chip options which is also great. The price is great too. The man at the counter was excited that it was my first time and he really had a wonderful attitude. The woman who made my sandwich and ran it to my table was so respectful and nice. I immediately liked the staff, warm, excited about their food and professional. I'm coming back!

text:
This was one of my favorite spots, to grab a quick bite, before it closed.

It's reopened! Under new management. The staff is friendly, professional and helpful.

Masks aren't required, but the staff is wearing masks. The tables are spaced per social distancing requirements.

The restaurant is neat, clean and tidy!

I had my usual, the large Hook & Ladder, it was really good!

You can dine in, order takeout. There is a pickup station for online orders. You can order through the major delivery services and have your order delivered to your home or work address.

Cash/Credit/Debit and Apple Pay are accepted forms of payment. I dont believe Samsung pay is accepted here.

Welcome back Firehouse Subs!!!!!

text:
You could do worse than a meatball sub at Firehouse. Normally I run screaming from the franchise hero market. Subway's soulless bread makes the average communion wafer taste like a nacho and their water soluble meats are sodium bombs disguised as turkey doppelgangers. 

Wawa will give you a fair hoagie for seven bucks but Firehouse is way above average. The bread is fresh and the meatballs are dense and flavorful. Although Grandma is in no danger of being displaced by their sauce, the red has a sweet tang that complements your lunch missle. It's all about expectations - I anticipated mediocrity and Firehouse delivered a four alarm favorite. An easy five stars.

This is a hidden gem, sandwiched between two slices of moldy ciabatta slices. I used to frequent this place a lot before it closed and now it's back! Under new management!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsBitcoin': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'BYOB': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Corkage': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True'}
text:
Looking for a change from the typical take out or delivery, especially during these Covid-times?  We were, and figured we'd try Firehouse.  It's local, and we pass it regularly, so what the heck.  Right?
They offer a variety of typical and not so typical subs in small, medium and large.
We got small cheese steaks and the small brisket and cheese.  We agreed they were tasty and enjoyed them.
Some caveats if you've never had Firehouse (and these are personal biases of things I'd like to see)- Cheese steaks offer a choice of provolone or no provolone.  Where's the whiz (or at least american)?  You want fries?  No fries.  Chips!  (see if anyone gets that LOL)  Fries or onion rings would be nice.
The biggest call out... small is... small.  Surprisingly small.  Like 4" petite small.  And I feel its a big price for a small sandwich.  So if you're a first timer, like we were... be prepared.  You may be stalking in the fridge afterwards.

text:
I haven't been to a Firehouse Subs in a long time. 
I had the Bacon Ranch on wheat bread and it was great! The bread is soft and the turkey was nice and warm. I got extra cheese with no onion. Perfect. A pickle comes on the side; I'm a pickle lover and the pickles here are mediocre. 
The service wasn't horrible... The cashier was nice. The manager said the "F" word right in front of me, and then one of the team members who brought my sub out, gave me a pick up line. 
I was hungry and the sub was awesome.
I will probably go to another location so I won't have to hear the employees curse ( which I do, a lot of people do, just not when I'm working, especially if there's a customer) and I won't have to hear pick up lines. 
I recommend the number 8.

text: I'm giving it two stars because I was really unhappy by the service. Came here on a Saturday afternoon,  excited because I love firehouse subs. Ordered a firehouse hero and they gave me the wrong sandwich. I didn't care though because the sandwich they gave me was delicious and I didn't even notice it was wrong until a lady working there came over and asked to see my sandwich after I have already eaten it half way. So good :( make me never want to go back to this one. Pretty bad service if you ask me. No one was really nice either in general. Such a shame.

attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse has definitely become my favorite "sub shop". I love that their meatball sub contains REAL meatballs and not nasty frozen manufactured meatballs like some other sub shops. You can order it regular or "spicy" and I alternate between the two. Sometimes the "spicy" sauce can be a bit much. I once asked for half and half and they obliged me. 

I also really enjoy the smokehouse beef & brisket sub. It has the perfect combination of bbq sauce and cheese. Yum. My Husband prefers the Hook and Ladder. Honestly, I haven't really had anything that I don't like at Firehouse. 

They are also the first restaurant that I experienced the many flavored soda machine at. I like to get either orange or grape diet sprite or lemonade. It makes me feel like a kid again getting flavored syrup added to my drink. It's even better that I get to do it myself and it is unlimited. 

This particular location is always very friendly and fast. They have a drive-thru that I have used a few times and they have a decent-enough sized dining room with an outdoor dining area. Needless to say, I'll be back.

text:
Serious lack of customer engagement. As a past food service employee, I know it can be hard to engage with customers when things are busy but when you have zero customers being helped, there is zero reason why all five of the staff behind the counter should look at the customer as they are walking in and make zero effort to say hi, welcome, etc. That's not really the problem in my case, my problem is as I approached the register to give my order, I greeted the staff member with a friendly "hello" and received an annoyed look the entire time. The staff who took my order acted as though he was completely high off his ass and couldn't use the register let alone understand my order. 

Then as I swiped my debit card because the chip reader is down, he explained that I was over my credit limit. That is not the case and I believe he automatically assumed I was using credit to complete my transaction and that is why my card wouldn't work. 

Honestly, this is the second time I've been in this location and if my boyfriend didn't like the food, I'd never eat at this place ever.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse subs is a good sandwich shop.  They always try to greet you with a cheery welcome. The dining room is clean although kind of small.  I think the only downside to the location is the placement of the 120 flavored soda machine (great idea with limits) which is located almost directly in a position that hinders the ordering line.  This is inconvenient and confusing since people wanting refills wind up in the ordering line or those getting refills block the ordering line.  Not to mention people seemed to find them confusing (almost like watching someone use an ATM for the first time) which takes more time and also backs up the line.  I am not sure what this location could do about it because as mentioned above it is small.

The good thing about Firehouse is their subs.  My two favorites are the Hook & Ladder and the Steak & Cheese.   The Hook & Ladder is a great sandwich that blends flavors that give a sweet and tangy sensation with its combination of smoked turkey, honey ham and cheese topped with mayo and deli mustard.  Which is good combination by itself but when the onion kicks it there is an explosion of flavors.  The Steak & Cheese has that meaty, sink your teeth in it sensation, topped with sauted onions and bell peppers.  This is a hearty sandwich that I find very satisfying.  One addition I like to do with this is add A-1 Steak Sauce which really adds a nice zing. 

One thing that Firehouse offers that is kind of an "in your face" secret is they have a multitude of sauces (hot sauces, steak sauces, etc.) that are readily available for your selection. 

Definitely give this place a try.  I think it is good for families and kids.

attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text:
Unfortunately this store is going to have to take the blame for poor service out of many others that I've seen. I signed up to firehouse subs for my birthday, currently I am waiting on the parking spot for drive thru only, but it has been roughly 15 minutes since I ordered my sandwich. I don't see many people inside, about 4 others. This is my very first time ordering from this establishment and I'm already given a long wait time for my first time, what a great impression right? While I'm I'm at the drive thru window, my order was a brisket & cheddar sub, but it took about 4 minutes just for the attendant to tell me they ran out of brisket, I asked for a recommendation & they told me steak & cheese would be the next best thing so I listened and substituted that instead. I'm currently still waiting for my sub as I've received no updates and during my drive thru, there was another car that received their order quicker than mine, I'm curious on what's taking so long. I also noticed an employee just casually walking back and forth with their cell phone taking a call, could the service be any better?

edit: I received my order after going inside after writing this review, there was 5 people working the counter and one shouting employee who I assumed to be the manager, he was really nice and generous, but the reason why my sub was not delivered earlier was because they had given it out to the wrong person, that same shouting person gave a speech on communication to his co-workers and how they should listen more, everyone who was a regular worker looked lifeless, and put to shame but didn't seem to care, once again, great manager, poor communication from team members, it took about 32 minutes roughly before receiving my order and finding out it was given to the wrong person, there was also another customer who came back in and returned their order, it was probably mine but they received the wrong order as well, they were in the drive thru I'm assuming, if management could work on this store, it could definitely be potentially a better store, with new staff members of course, I believe the manager was in the right of doing all the shaming and scolding, I appreciated that my patience didn't go to waste

attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text: Today was my first time ever at a Firehouse subs and I have to say what an experience. A few seconds after my friend and I placed our order the power went out. It seems that a transformer blew and knocked out the power In the area. You would think that this would fluster some people but not the staff at this store. Stephanie the manager kept her staff focused onn maintaining customer satisfaction. Even though certain things on the menu, that had been ordered could not be heated, she went above and beyond to accommodate all the customers in the store. We got our food, extras and ate with no rush In the restaurant. Stephanie and her staff did a great job In making what could have been a very tense situation pleasant. I look forward to going back and enjoying some more delicious Subs and soups.

text: The associates here are absolutely fantastic!  So helpful, understanding, and accommodating.  I am pregnant and have been CRAVING a delicious sub forever, but I also have Lupus with serious allergies to gluten, eggs, and dairy.  They worked with me as we figured out what alterations I needed and provided so much reassurance and help.  It's wild the amount of satisfaction a simple meal from a place with great customer service can give you!  Thank you, Firehouse Pinellas Park!

My sub was very good! 
My problem is cleanliness.  I cannot truly enjoy my food when the staff doesn't keep their hands clean. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text:
This review is for this location specifically. I've been to other Firehouses and they were great. This location seems to expect(and encourage) you to be a takeout order when you walk in. As soon as you walk in, they ask "togo order?" or even maybe guess a name based on orders that have been put in(as I observed while I was sitting and eating).

I like to eat in Firehouses(opposed to togo) since their sweet tea is amazing and can have the sub right when it's freshly made. I got to this location around 5pm and their tea urns were empty(sweet and unsweet). I asked if they could make more sweet and they said "aww man some guy just came in and took it all. Huge togo order" and I could hear snickering from the other coworkers.. guaranteed they were lying and just didn't feel like making it nor making me anymore. So they offered me some unsweet from the drivethru area and gave it to me in a cup packed full of ice and if you've ever tried to sweeten tea packed with ice, then you know where this is going... it was just blah. And at this point, if I asked them for a new cup with little or no ice, they would've likely shut down the store because what I was asking was just far too much.

A detail that I noticed: I've been to a few other FH's in the area and they're short-staffed, usually only 2 employees. There was a solid 5 or more employees so it's not like they were just slammed and couldn't help me; they all very clearly did not WANT to help me

And I sort of expected this last part, but even though they asked 'here or togo?' and I said here, they put it in a togo bag and when I said it was for here, they acted like it was this HUGE inconvenience for them to get me a basket to put it on

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text: This is slowly becoming my new favorite chain sub shop. Every sub I've had from here has been delicious and the meat is of good quality! I like the fact you can get any of the sandwiches that are all typically toasted served cold as well. They have a excellent selection of sandwiches and your sure to find one you like from all the choices. My favorite and usual go to is the hook and ladder, although lately I've been craving their meatball which is miles above subways meatball sub! Do you have all the customization options of Subway? No... But the quality is much better and at a very reasonable price!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'DriveThru': 'True'}
text: Have eaten at many Firehouse Subs and this location was near the top.  Bread was like it had just come out of the oven and my usual order Jamaican jerk turkey and my wife's Hook and Ladder was perfect. Staff was cordial and even checked on us as we were eating to make sure everything was good.  Only dinged them a star for the bathroom condition which needed some attention.  We will eat here again and if the restroom is in order will increase the review to a 5 Star.

text: Do not go inside to order your foods.  There are over 8 people inside all working drive thru and carry out and could care less about the people inside.  Shame on you.  You make the inside people wait forever.  At least give them the option.  Also tell them that they also cater to first responders.  I'm fine with that.  I had young children with me that would have preferred McDonald's which would have been much faster for two screaming children.  Let customers know the wait time. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
I love it when the guys behind the counter yell at me. In this case, they shouted a hearty welcome when we came through the door of this bustling Malvern toasted hero house. The staff was dressed in schticky shirts with labels like "Steamer Crew" on the back. Sort of like the Joker or Riddler's crew on a classic Batman episode. Holy Hoagie Hotspot, Caped Crusader!

I am a hard core hoagie biggot, so I was afraid I was bout to be hosed when I saw their Italian was served with Mustard and Mayo. I decided to jump without a net and order the combo, just the way they make it, with the House Special Cherry Limeade, served with real limes from a too cool for school soda dispenser. My buds all got the Hook and Ladder. A couple of us ventured into the signature hot sauce collection to turn up the heat.

Service was snappy, prices and just about everything else were about what you expect from a franchised toasted sub experience. I ate every bite of the sandwich, and while it was no Italian Hoagie, it was a pretty good lunch, and I will go back for sure, if nothing else, just to be yelled at when I walk through the door.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
3 buddies and I stopped here after playing golf at Play-A-Round which is in the same shopping center. We had no clue what to expect.

The greeting of "Welcome to Firehouse!" was fun but only just the beginning. The service was fast and the place was very clean.

The sandwiches that we got, were hands-down, THE BEST sandwiches that we have ever eaten. I really was pretty speechless about how good it was and so were my friends. I got the #10.

I rarely ever need to go out to Malvern for anything, but now I'm dreaming up reasons to make the trip and stop for lunch. 

I highly recommend this place. BTW - the drink sizes are out of control. Most people would be ok with a small - Trust me.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
The inside looks interesting and their computerized drink machine has 100 flavors.  That was a good start.  It's like a huge drink iPod.

At 2pm, service was slow. I expect to wait 15 minutes during a lunch rush for a sandwich but not in a nearly empty place. 

When I finally got the food, the corned beef sub on wheat was decent if not overwhelmingly good.  Definitely better than Subway but I can't expect them to compete with a local hoagie place. They load it up with mayo and cheese which satiates the part of the brain that enjoys saturated fat.  The steaming adds a nice touch to the overall texture.  The lineup of hot sauce bottles to choose from is a bonus. 

The chili was Wendy's quality, which is to say it tasted fine but really isn't worth more than 99 cents. So for $3.89 it's far from a bargain. A little too watery for my tastes, though flavor-wise it wasn't bad.  It probably could have benefited from a combination of 5 of the hot sauces.  

You have better choices in the shopping center to have a great sandwich. Dixie Picnic comes to mind  But this place is squarely in the "not too bad" category.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
My brother, his girlfriend and I were looking to get soup but the place was closed.  Lo and behold, we found Firehouse Subs to be having its grand opening.  They greeted us and we decided to check this place out.  All the firehouse items in the restaurant are authentic and have been donated by the local firehouse.

I've gone back to this restaurant a couple of times and have enjoyed several of their sandwiches.  Some of them are spicy for those with weak stomachs.  The absolute highlight of this restaurant is the soda machine.  It is one of two in the state of Pennsylvania.  You can mix and match the kind of soda that you want.  Fantastic.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
WOW. My favorite subs in the area, it beats out Primo, and then Wawa and Subway by far. The only problem is that it's very expensive comparatively, the menu obfuscates the prices so you wont know what it all costs until you order. Two large 12" subs for us was 17.50, you can get 5 or 6 dollar large subs at Wawa and Subway but they're  half the girth that Firehouse subs are. Firehouse subs taste way better than twice as much so it's worth it, but if I went here every day I'd go broke. I get the Turkey Bacon Ranch every time, I'm scared to buy a new sub cause then I would be missing out on getting my TBR again. :(

They also have the Coke Freestyle machine in there, so if you wanna go nuts trying out soda combinations then there you go. But really, a soda and a large sub there is gonna be 10 dollars so be ready.

text:
I love this place! The roasted chicken on wheat was amazing and the customer service was incredible. We asked for extra pickles and within one minute we were served a basket of pickles - at least 6 pickles!

The coolest thing about this restaurant is the Coke soda machine that offers 120 different soda options. I could have drank all the options but I had filled up on my hoagie. 

This place has become my new favorite quick lunch spot in the 'burbs. :)

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text: My new favorite sub shop! The cashier had perfect flair for the restaurant and recommended an outstanding sandwich for me. I will definitely be coming back. The pricing is cheap for most places you'd go for lunch but a little on the expensive side for a sub shop. The sandwiches are worth the extra buck though: meat which has been cooked until it is perfectly tender and fresh toppings (including a surprisingly nice balance between sauces and toppings) make for a lunch that will keep you salivating  even after your sandwich is gone.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
I've been here 3 times now, but I don't think I'll be back. The food and service are both decidedly mediocre.

As for the food, the cold hoagies are usually slathered in mayo and mustard to the point that the roll falls apart in your hand. Be sure to grab extra napkins if you get your sandwich "Fully Involved" (with everything on it) as they suggest. The rolls themselves are bland and doughy, a far cry from the traditional chewy, flaky Philadelphia hoagie roll. The hot hoagies I've tried suffer from the same over-slathering issue, with cheese and condiments rendering the bun soggy and limp. The taste? Just okay...about as good as any other hoagie after it sat in the fridge for a day.

As for the service, don't expect anything timely or efficient. I was the only person in the shop recently, and it still took 15 minutes from ordering to get my sandwich, that is, after the employees bickered over who was going to make it. If an employee has no interest in actually doing their job, he or she shouldn't be there. It is no wonder the employee who reluctantly made my sandwich got my order wrong while arguing with his coworkers over who was going to work the late shift. I was ignored while they complained about their hours and duties. Customer service was severely lacking, even with nobody else in there but me.

I won't be back again.

attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text: I have been here twice, and have mixed feelings about their food. The first time I ordered a BBQ Brisket sandwhich (not the exct title), and it was amazing, but completely full of sodium and the calories are out of the roof (over 1500 calories for the sandwhich). I know most people will say they don't care and it's delicious, which is true, but please keep that in mind when ordering most sandwhiches here. I decided to go with the Hot Pastrami sandwich the second time, which was around 1000 calories for the 12 inch, and it was a major dissappointment. I probably won't be returning as often unless I am looking to pig out that day, because it seems their best sandwhiches are the ones I wouldn't want to eat a couple of times a week for lunch. I am not a health nut by any means, I just don't like having to order a super unhealthy sandwhich to get the most flavor.

text:
Pretty decent place to get a good sandwich for lunch. 

I do a lot of things in the Main Line area but when I'm around Frazer I stop in and get a hot sub from Firehouse Subs. They have a large selection and reasonably priced. The building is clean and the staff is friendly. I gave it 4 stars because it's pretty good for a chain sandwich shop but definitely not the best. Just good for a quick easy lunch.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "u'quiet'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': True, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'None', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False'}
text:
So.....a sub shop born in Jacksonville, FL comes to Southeastern PA - basically the home of the hoagie. I'm skeptical, but my curiosity to try a new place so close to home quells the apprehension. 

The Good: My bf ordered the Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket - this was very good albeit a wee bit salty for my taste. I had two bites to be certain. 

The Bad: I ordered the Turkey Bacon Ranch on wheat. I'm really sorry, but they didn't really do any better than Subway. The bread was soggy, despite the fact they were economical with the Ranch dressing. The bread nor meat were of the best quality. The whole sandwich was the same texture. 

The Ugly: This place is competing with Primo's, Jimmy John's and every pizza shop from City to Shore. Unfortunately, I don't think they can compete in this dog fight. 

The bf reported that the decor was a lot like Jimmy John's discerned by the Firehouse theme (Dalmatian statue and gear on the walls) and a bar with an extensive array of hot sauce. 

For 2 large subs, a bag of chips and one drink, the bill came in slightly under $20. 

I really wanted this place to be great, so with much regret I post this 2 star review.

text:
Last time I was in the sammich line was moving slow and it took nearly twenty minutes to get 2 subs off a line backed up with only 5 other orders.  

I don't recommend for takeout as the toastiness turns into sogginess once the sub is wrapped up.  

Sammich quality is goodish - I'm unsure about the meat quality but the chesse steak doesn't taste fresh. I'd rather spend money on Primos or something with good MEATs!

This place seems more focused on the novelty aspect rather than food. 

PS the medium drink is LARGE and I've never wanted to see a large.

text: Absolutely LOVE their sandwiches and have never had a bad one yet. They are refreshingly different from your standard Wawa sandwiches, and have always tasted very fresh. text: This was my first experience at any Firehouse Sub, and I enjoyed both the sandwich (I had the Hook and Ladder) and the atmosphere (World Cup on the TVs).  The sandwich didn't seem to be anything to different from most of the grilled/toasted/yada yada sandwich shops that are popping up everywhere these days (Potbelly, Pickleman's, Which Wich, etc.).  It was a good sandwich, though, and there were many options that will keep me wanting to go back. It is also great to have a place like this in Oakville. Plus, they have the Coke Freestyle machine that can pretty well turn a run-of-the mill place into an amazing experience for me!

text:
This was my first experience at Firehouse Subs and the entire experience truly makes me want to go back.

The moment you walk in, every employee stops what they are doing and says, "Welcome to Firehouse".  The menu adorns both the ordering area and on the wall above.  They have many, many options to choose from.

I ordered the Turkey Bacon Ranch sub, with an order of chips and a soda.  The sub was big enough to share or to have as another meal.  It filled me up quite fast.  They have a Coke Freestyle machine that has an amazing array of drink choices.

This is a great addition to Oakville and I can't wait to go  back!

text:
Review is based on several visits for lunch in 2016, as well as a recent catering order in June 2016.

Bottom Line:
Friendly owner, Uncharacteristically Decent Chain Food, Clean Operation.

Overview:
Since March 2016, I have been sporadically visiting this location for lunch carry out orders. I typically order online and tailor my order specifically how I like it. That is part of the reason I order online. Anyway, I have never ordered from any other Firehouse Subs location, so I have nothing to compare this to as far as their other chain locations go. I do like the concept that they support first responders. 

Food:
My favorites here are:

Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket:
This is my go-to sandwich. The Sweet Baby Ray's BBQ sauce uses cheap High Fructose Corn Syrup versus sugar. Because of that, I request the BBQ sauce to be left off. Out of the roughly 10 visits this year, only one time have they sent me home with BBQ sauce on the sandwich. Otherwise, I add black olives and mushrooms (an upcharge). I should request onions to be added. That would help this sandwich out.

Hot Pastrami or Corned Beef Brisket:
There is not much to say on these two sandwiches. The meat is decent and something nice to pick when I am not "feeling" the Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket. 

The sandwiches do not stand out in any unique way. They do serve them "Fully Involved" which I think means you get tomato, lettuce, onion, mayonnaise, and mustard. Those are all fresh and help the sandwich.

Chili:
The chili is decent for a chain. It has "body" with beans and meat. It is a not a "liquidy" chili. The crackers they offer with it are not your typical cheap-o saltines. I need to find out if they would be willing to add cheddar or chopped onion. It would certainly help, along with maybe some jalapeno or some other additions.

Catering:
I ordered the "Sub Platter" for a recent charity bingo event. Of course, they tailored the order to how I wanted using both white and wheat bread. Some nice surprises for me were the inclusion of a gallon of their sweet tea, as well as a lemon cookie. After ordering the sweet tea, I will be getting that again! I did not get to sample the lemon cookie, but I hope to try it in the future.

As a side note, I found the owner, as well as the employee, Hailey (sp?), to be quite helpful during the catering ordering process. They helped me via email and by telephone.

Parking and Location:
This particular restaurant is located in a strip mall that has private lot parking. I have found it to be a very crowded lot, and you have to hunt somewhat for a spot.  

One day, I noticed a girl walking back from the Mobil station on the corner lot to where she worked (she was dressed in something formal) in the strip mall. I asked her who all these cars belong to. She said that the salon in that strip holds mostly their customers. Then in the evening, you have a total of three restaurants competing for space.

Online Ordering and Rewards Program:
The computer systems for customers at Firehouse Subs could use some help. The online ordering system is separate from their rewards system. Oh, and their rewards system has separate web and smartphone applications that are separate and do not share data. Perhaps these are results of growing pains. When I spoke with the owner of this particular franchise location about the issues I have experienced, I was told they are supposed to be making changes to their systems by year end.

One More Thing:
At this location, they have a Coca-Cola Freestyle machine. I rarely get to use it because most of my orders are "to go", and I am not a big fan of lugging a soda around. Regardless, it is a bonus in my mind, and just one more incentive for me to continue coming back.

Summary:
As much as I am not a fan of chain restaurants, the convenient location and the unique offerings at Firehouse Subs brings me back time and time again. Online ordering is a huge plus for me, as well.

text: I love Firehouse subs!  Usually the staff greets you when you arrive. The subs are served warm. And to top it off you get to put hot sauce(s) of your choice on your sub. I crave trying the hottest sauces they have. Each location chooses which hot sauces they'll carry. Tand waited for our subs. While waiting I went to pick out the hot sauces I was going to use that day. Unfortunately the pickings were very slim (at least 25% of the sauces were gone) (I took a pic, but can't see how to share it).  I asked a gal cleaning and she said they have been out for awhile. So for grins, I spoke to the manager (older, short woman) who told me they just ran out. Not a fan of being lied to.  Not sure if i'll go back to this location. May have to settle for Penn Station and Jimmy John's.

text:
If you like unsanitary practices and to wait 20 minutes for a sandwich, this is the place for you. 

This isnt my first or fifth time in and it's a literal shitshow with workers each and every time. There's one person who works and the rest goof off. 

I realize good workers are hard to find, but you can do better. 

While there I watched a gal making our sandwiches stop and leave the line and refill straws wearing the same gloves, leaving our sandwiches out on the line. The trash can was out and empty and other diners asked if there was another trash can to dispose of their trash from eating. 

If this how you run a business, this is precisely the way to run it to the ground. 

Seriously the most pathetic sight I've witnessed in a long time and that sucks because I like their sandwiches.

text: I love Firehouse and thankfully they have management like Rebecca who take ownership of a problem!  Thanks to her I will continue to be a weekly customer. Do Not Use Uber Eats for delivery. text:
I'm from Michigan, so when I moved to Tampa I had never heard of Firehouse Subs.  Most of my friends recommended it, so I gave it a try a little while back.

I went with the turkey bacon ranch.  While I appreciated the hot and toasted aspects of the sub, the taste was nowhere to be found.  Didn't taste like turkey, bacon, ranch, or anything really.  It just tasted like a bunch of stuff that fused together into a generic filling.  I was really disappointed because I am a huge fan of peppercorn ranch - but even if I could have tasted it, it wouldn't have saved this sub.

I'm not against giving Firehouse another try...but thus far I haven't.

text:
I usually took them to be an okay sub, with a good sauce, the Captain sauce. I didn't like the way some of the franchises served food, but this location by Plant High was pretty good. 

They went up to "notable", with the new line of under 500 calorie sandwiches. I got a beef sriracha sub that was good, meaty, less bread and met my diet goal. I was pretty happy with it. 

The only downer I would say is the bottled waters are tiny for $2.

text: Ordered a steak and cheese and had a horrible experience. They toasted the bread, steamed the already cooked steak then put the water filled steam steak on the bread. By time I got home the bread was a watery mush... They lost a customer.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': None, 'validated': None, 'lot': None, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Steamer! That's my favorite since it reminds me of what good deli want to be...

Is it the most awesome ever? Perhaps not 5-alarm but it definitely hits the spot when the bell rings. Kids love the meatball sub and don't question the wheat bread. Why? Because the soda machine is their fix! Whatever concoction you can think of...there is an option. So do I prefer Firehouse subs over the big M for a meal. You betcha...Sure do! 

There are lots more options and the great thing is that they are hot. Not your run-of-the-mill S-subs. The only hitch recently was that the made me the wrong sub (new staff) with turkey. But once notified, they made a a new one and bagged half of the large to-go, since I had ate part of the first one before realizing it.

text:
Unbelievable. I can't even review the food because i never got it! Came with my friend and both ordered medium subs. She got hers in about 15-20 min and after continuing to wait another 10 min, I went up and asked about it. They hadn't even started it so told me they would immediately. Another 10 minutes, with my friends long gone, I went back up and STILL NO ONE HAD STARTED IT. There were at minimum 15 people that came in after us that were served while I was waiting.....So, I get it that mistakes happen...but this is ridiculous. 
So, I was offered a refund...nothing more for wasting more than my entire lunch break! Will never, ever be back to this location!!!!!!!!

Ordered delivery***

Ordered the large wheat Italian an toasted.  Pretty good sandwich, although I felt it was a little greasy.  When I get a toasted sandwich I enjoy the various flavors dancing across your tastebuds.

This sandwich tended to blend into one flavor, which even the meats were a bit indiscernible from each other.

I'm going to try a different sub next time as I think this was just a bad fit for me.

text:
I was the only customer with four guys behind the counter. Ordered meal pretty quickly, and it was made pretty quickly. 
Cons: 
- Sandwich was sloppy and incomplete. Only vegetables on half. Bread was so soggy. Was not to the same standard as other Firehouse restaurants.
- Place was filthy, like they just had the lunch rush, despite no other customers being in the place. Out of straws until I asked, soda machine was out of several flavors.

text: Basically turning down customers (telling them 30 minute wait) because they are so backed up. This is the time to shut down online orders and take the walk-in customers. I patiently waited while they finished up all they online orders, they put a lone sub on the counter but never called out who's it was. categories: Delis, Fast Food, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches
text:
Really good subs. Hawaiian Bun sandwich was my favorite a couple months back at a different location, but that special sandwich is gone for now. nevertheless, I really like the BBQ sauce and they have a wide selection of sauces to choose from. I am reluctantly giving 4 stars because this location was very clean, well staffed, and since it was so new, it seemed everyone was in training and on their toes trying to go above and beyond.

Ultimately, firehouse is a bit pricey, they seem to go a bit skimpy on the meat, and the subs are not that big in the first place. Generally speaking, most Firehouse establishments probably do not deserve more than 3 stars, this place was so new, so clean, and working so hard to do everything perfect, that I was convinced they deserved an extra star. 

This location is conveniently located close to my work, unfortunately, unless they drop the price or load up the sandwiches and subs with more meat, I will probably continue to get my subs from Publix.

text: Firehouse Subs are always delicious and my veggie sub today was no exception! But I have to say I was pleasantly surprised by the excellent customer service and cleanliness at this location. Tim was outstanding behind the register and when there was no one in line, he was working hard making sure every surface was clean, all the paper goods were well stocked, and checking in with happy diners to see if they needed anything. What a wonderful overall experience! And no tip jar which is rare these days, and they would not take a tip either. If I was a Secret Shopper they would get a top score from me. Good job guys!!!

text: I've been a fan of Firehouse Subs for a long time.  Glad they finally made it to West Tampa!  If you are into hot subs this is a great alternative to the place that starts with a Q and ends with an o's.  The ingredients are fresh and there is plenty of meat on the sandwich.  Order it "fully involved" for everything or just name your toppings.  I like the Sorensen's hot sauce to give my sandwich a tasty zing (they also have about 25 other hot sauces available).  Also, they are one of the only places that has Cherry Limeade, I could drink gallons of that stuff.

text: I tried these guys out of days ago and I absolutely love their subs, the people are nice, the subs are fresh, and all around very clean environment. They have a plethora of drinks you can choose from but my favorite is their sweet and non sweet brewed iced tea made with cane sugar. They have fresh lemons and limes you can put in your tea which is a bonus for me and I absolutely love the freshness about this place. I suggested to a friend that we go back and try again. And as you can see the sandwiches are out of this world and they taste fantastic! If you're on a diet you can customize your sub anyway you want for your diet restrictions.  If you're in the area you have to check out this place. I highly recommend it!

attributes: {'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'WiFi': "'free'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}"}
categories: Delis, Fast Food, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches
text:
Great place if you are a sub sandwhich lover! Higher quality meats and cheeses than other places. I did not know it was a chain at first until I researched it online, no matter about that, a lot of store in Florida. 

Every-time someone walks in the staff says, " Welcome to Firehouse," which is nice and unexpected. You will wait a little longer to receive your sandwich because this is not Subway!

I only have experience with their meatball sub, (so far) which is outstanding and filling. I would rate their meatball sub better than Cosseta, and is little less (including tax) price wise for a 12" too. The only thing is the bread could be a little better, they should use more like a baguette. 

Plus, the Firehouse meatball sub puts a hearty helping of cheese on top and marinara sauce too and red pepper flakes can be requested. This is NOT a run-of-mill  'iffy quality shop like other sub shops, Firehouse is top notch in my book and very good. 

It has one of those Coke fusion machines if that is of interest to you,too. Overall, if you want good subs, don't mind paying a little more for better stuff, and are sick of Subway, Quiznos, and Jimmy Johns, then this a nice change of pace and will make you a regular because of their sheer choice in subs.!

text:
YUMMY!!

My fiance and I stopped by on our way to the mall and par my sugestion decided to split a meatball sub and boy and I glad he listened to me! The sub itself was so hot and the melted cheese made it look amazing! Not to mention the smell alone was heveanly! When it cooled down enought for us to eat it was perfect! We ended up splitting it because I don't usually eat that much but it was the perfect ammount!

The staff were super friendly and the store was clean :)

Keep up the great work with the yummy meatball subs!

text:
LOVED THE MEATBALL SUB!

Never tried the meatball sub till this visit. It was very good and hit the spot. The roll was not soggy and the sub was piping hot. I really enjoyed how this sub was presented and made. The cheese on top was bubbly and brown. This was a delightful attribute of the sandwich. The meatballs were moist, a good texture, and the sauce was flavorful.

The staff was engaging in conversation and funny. They helped pass the few minutes quickly it took for my sub to be made. 

You can never go wrong with a Firehouse sub and the hot sauce bar.

categories: Delis, Fast Food, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches
text:
Hook & Ladder, Hook & Ladder, Hook & Ladder! Firehouse was my go-to sandwich shop in college, but it has found a way back into my heart now that I live a mere half mile from the one on Kennedy. If you don't prefer hot mayo (I get it, everyone has their "things"), you can simply ask them to prepare a "cold" sub - but their hot subs are where it's at! 

My only qualm about this particular location is that they tend to be a little on the slow side. But to get around that issue, I just place my orders online ahead of time through Firehouse's corporate website, and voila - sandwich is ready upon my arrival (usually anyway)! 

I like that all of their subs are fully customizable, as I am incredibly picky. I despise spicy mustard and they never mind subbing it for yellow mustard. I also get my subs with light lettuce and light onion, and it's just perfect. 

You can get a large sub for under 10 bucks - and if you're thrifty like me, enjoy your chips and soda at home instead of opting for a combo meal... OR spend the extra couple bucks and enjoy a fountain soda from the giant self-service soda machine near the grab and go station. 

Dining in or taking out, Firehouse is a great spot for an affordable, delicious meal - and it is WAY tastier than other fast food sandwich chains such as Subway *blegh*.

text:
They make a genuinely good meatball sub. The wait for this fast-food sandwich shop is of course longer than Subway, but it's worth it. There were actually some complex flavor notes in the meatballs and I'm certainly not used to finding that at your average sandwich shop (or ever since the demise of my local Italian deli in Chester, NJ). 

Plus the employees were singing. A happy omen.

text:
Good location and all but one of my visits has produced a solid sandwich.

I've probably had about six different types of sandwiches here and I do like how many options I have to customize additional ingredients at no additional charge. 

While I usually come here at off hours when there is clearly not a lunch rush, the guys making my sandwich get to it and I don't mind waiting a few minutes for them to get it right...especially if I'm ordering something from the hot side of the menu.

The value of getting just the sandwich is very good considering every receipt seems to come with an online survey which produces a code that takes care of the medium drink on every subsequent visit. And I love the Cherry Lime Aid option at the machine.

I do wonder why so often my order is rung in by an employee who doesn't seem very good at doing it. Almost every time, the guy who ends up making my sandwich has to look over the shoulder of the employee taking my order and offer assistance. Sure, I could understand training somebody now and then, but my ordering experience almost always seems to have an awkward moment or two. 

However, the end results are usually tasty and the restaurant is consistenly very clean.
