text:
This was our favorite Firehouse Subs location.  We ordered take out from here once a week.  The workers and manager were super friendly and knew my husband's name, saying hi to him, every time he walked in the door.  The food was always consistently great and ready on time.  
We went in on Friday, 11/13 to pick up lunch and were told that it was their last day, they were closing this location.
Imagine our shock (as they were always busy) and sadness to lose such a great place.

categories: Delis, Fast Food, Restaurants, Hot Dogs, Sandwiches
text:
Firehouse subs is located off Kennedy in South Tampa. While I appreciate the unique fire fighter theme and donating money to local fire fighter stations, I have to agree with Yelp Elite Todd because I can't say I've ever had a decent sub sandwich here. The decor of firehouse subs is red brick with firefighter art all over the walls, with black and white dalmatian style counter-tops on all the tables. There is a covered patio for outdoor seating, a huge selection of hot sauces, a large indoor area with many tables, and 1 TV with the baseball game on. 

After placing my order at the register, it took 10 minutes to make my sub, which was surprising considering there was no line at the register, just people waiting for sandwiches, and a whopping 4 people making sandwiches. I got a $7 Philly cheese-steak sub and they forgot the cheese! It's in the name and they forgot it! The lady tells me there's cheese on the bottom. I ask her to point it out and she can't, so she puts a slice of cold un-melted cheese on top, and doesn't offer to heat the sub up so that the cheese is melted. First of all, who would put cheese on the bottom? Everyone knows cheese goes on top of meat. Have you ever seen a burger with cheese on the bottom or spaghetti with cheese on the bottom? Second, I notice they forgot to put mayo and mustard on the sandwich as I had asked. I have to get up again to get a side of sauce. Then I'm looking for the tomatoes and lettuce and finally notice it on the bottom of the sandwich instead of the top as it normally goes. Firehouse staff made my sandwich totally backwards! I then realize that Firehouse staff did not include peppercinni's on the side as I had asked, but I did not want to get up a 3rd time from my meal, so I didn't bother asking for them. With no melted cheese and my meal interrupted twice due to kitchen staff's mistakes, the Philly steak was quite lack luster. I really should've had them remake the sub with melted cheese but I didn't have that kind of time during lunch. 

On another occasion, I had the smokehouse beef and cheddar brisket which the lady highly recommended as Firehouse's best signature sandwich but it ended up having way too much sauce and turned into a fairly inedible soggy soup sandwich with chewy meat unfortunately. 

If anything tells you how sub-par the subs are, Subway is hands down far better than Firehouse and that's a real shame because Firehouse advertises themselves as a premium sandwich shop. In fact I can't name a sandwich shop that makes worse sandwiches than firehouse. If you are craving an awesome Philly cheese-steak, I recommend skipping this place and either going to Wawa's or Jersey Mike's!

text:
Hello there yelp!ers.

So I recently went to this location for the first time as it is on the route I take to get to work via MTA bus. I was deciding on the surrounding restaurants and I felt burned out from them. I noticed this nifty looking sub shop and decided "Why not? Been a while since I had SubWay."

But this place is so much better then SubWay by far. It's cleaner, the food is fresher, it's hot and they've got a good selection of product. One of the best things about this place is the Coca-Cola Freestyle drink machine, while it's a little bulky and not as streamlined as I'd like, it was still awesome. Over 120+ drink selections and a wide variety of flavorings you can add makes this machine worth checking out.

Now, as to the reasoning behind the 4 stars? Well, one of the associates there seemed like he could care less about the guest aside from just taking their order and moving on. He had no personal touch, it was almost as if he were robotic and programmed to just take orders. It's associates like that that really annoy me. Obviously if you want people to return they'd do it not only for the food but for the workers, too. It makes the experience that much better. Now the manager there (noticeable by the collared shirts they wear) was very nice, talkative just right, and attentive to my needs. The second time I went there (because it was such a great atmosphere) he remembered who I was, which always means a lot to me as a consumer.

But most certainly someplace to check out if you ever want great, hot food, several drink choices, and a cozy, hip atmosphere. Think twice about going to SubWay over Firehouse or you may regret the hesitation!

Happy yelp!ing!

text:
My mom and I grabbed a quick lunch here on her first day in town for a visit.  It was not a great first impression of Nashville for her. 

I'd never tried it before, but we were hungry on the way home from the airport and thought, how do you mess up a sandwich?  Well, let me tell you how... 

The flavor itself was alright, but in my mom's words, it was like "eating a sandwich that had already been chewed."  the bread was completely soggy on both of our sandwiches... we ended up eating the meat and veggies with a fork and even that was difficult.

I like the idea of the place and they have cute gimmicks to go along with the firehouse theme (ie fire hydrant shaped sauce bottles), but let's be honest, I don't care how good your cause is, your food needs to be edible. 

The service was also slow - we were the only two in the place and it took 20 mins to make 2 sandwiches.  It was also on the pricey side for a sub.

text:
If you like hot sauces and themed restaurants and subs this is your place. Are you reading this Tommy Gavin? 

I checked this place out for lunch. About 15 types of subs to chose from. The subs are steamed. Hmm, never had that before.. The smallest size you can order is a medium cause well all firefighters know smalls are for wimps.

As you're waiting for your sub to steam, you can choose your 'hot' sauce to put on your sub. There are about 100+ jars of hot sauce to chose from with numbers to indicate the hotness (#10 being holy hotness). That is the niche of this place. The Hot sauces. 

They bring your sub out to you and as i finished I said to myself, 'ah it was okay, i probably will never come back. I've checked it off the list" ... The place was clean, service was nice but i won't be telling you omg that place is on fire its so awesome.

it's just another sub shop with some hot sauce and super large sizes and that 'disney theme' feel.

text:
these are by dar the best sub sandwiches i have ever had!!!! A few of my friends and I were on vacation and wanted something a little lighter for lunch and found firehouse subs while driving. it was created by firefighters so the whole inside has helmets, jackets and artwork on the walls. there was about 15 different subs to chose from, but i wanted to make my own and the cashier said that would not be a problem, AWESOME!!! after they take your order they bring you your food at the table so you dont have to wait in a cluster of people to try and hear your name called out. the sandwich is HUGE!! I was only able to eat half of it for for the price of 7.50 i got to meals out of it!! the bread was thin and crispy and not doughy at all, which i loved! the meat was fresh and the pickles were amazing.
Also if your into hot sauces they have 100+ different types for you to try!!!

cant wait to go back!!!AWESOME SUBS!!!

text: Firehouse Subs is a  themed restaurant that serves submarine sandwiches.  Frankly, the restaurant is not much different from any other sandwich place such as Which Wich or Jimmy John's with one exception; it has a pretty nice hot sauce bar, where various local hot sauces are provided and ranked by order of spiciness.  I have enjoyed trying out various hot sauces here before purchasing them at a hot sauce shop.  The sandwiches are fairly large, and a meal with chips and drinks comes out to about $8-12.  All in all a reasonable place, but nothing out of the ordinary.

text: I just recently discovered Firehouse.  I really like the flavor of the New York Steamer.  And I recommend dipping it in the Firehouse house hot sauce for a little kick.  I've been to this location about 5 times as its not far from my work. Overall OK experience.  Bathroom toilet backed up one time, and staff doesn't seem highly trained on courtesy.  One day, I thought a teenage boy working the cash register was going to go asleep of boredom...management could tighten things up a little, but I have not had a complaint regarding the quality of the food.

attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I was introduced to Firehouse Subs in Knoxville, TN years ago while in college. I now work within minutes of the Charlotte Pike location and was more than thrilled to see it followed me back home to Nashville after graduation. Every time I enter the store I am greeted with a loud 'Welcome to Firehouse' which is a great feeling that you don't get at very many other places, actually Moe's is the only other place I know that does that. Above and beyond that many of the employees and managers have remembered my name, what I ordered and have even sat down with me and had a conversation, something I have never found at any other deli/sub style restaurant, ever.
I have had every sub on the menu and every one is as good as the other. The food and the staff are enough to keep me coming back, and I would recommend it to any one who has not tried it yet.
Overall, this place is a great addition to the West Nashville area and I hope it stays here as long as I do.

text: My son and I ate at this firehouse last Sunday July 29 at about 2 PM. The food was fine, service was reasonable as well.  Only complaint is the restaurant was quite dirty. There was a good bit of trash and crushed food on the floor.  The tables were also not clean and needed to be wiped off before we could use it. They weren't particularly busy, five or six of the eleven tables were occupied.  For whatever reason this crew had not cleaned the eating area in some time.  It made for kind of a gross experience.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Yeah, I'm a fan!

My husband was raving about this place because we have one around us.  We were visiting Nashville, and just wanted a quick bite to eat since we were going to have a big meal later.  This place really hit the spot!

I am not really much of a "sandwich" person, but these were pretty good!  The meat tasted fresh, the veggies were crisp and cold, and even the bread was good.  

Also, everything was clean and new-looking.  You can tell they really took care of the place!

I think I will let my husband take me to one of these again!

attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Great place just down the interstate from us. Never had a bad sandwich here and the staff is nice. One thing I don't like is those new Coke machines with the touchscreen. Lots of options but none taste mixed correctly (soda to syrup ratio is off). Also, these machines create a bottleneck and make it take longer to get your drink than to get your food.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: We had several of these back home in Mobile, AL so when I found this one I was ecstatic! If you've never eaten at a Firehouse what sets it apart from other sub shops is all of the different sauces that are available to put on your sandwich. I highly recommend their house sauce called Captain Sorensen's. This one also has the new Coke fountains that have hundreds of flavor combinations.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I guess if you like steamed sandwiches, this is the place to go.  But for those of us who the combination of 'wet' and 'bread' is less than appealing, I would say this is worth a skip.  
Subs don't have a lot of meat, there are no fries or other things that would separate them from Jersey Mike's.  The place is clean, I'll give them that!

text: I'm eating my first firehouse sub, NY steamer, steamed corned beef & pastrami, melted cheese, on rye... Freaking awesome!!!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I'm certainly a fan of Firehouse Subs.  While its probably not as good as Jimmy Johns in my opinion, it certainly eclipses the likes of Subway.

I'm thrilled to see one opening in my neck of the goods.

I have to agree with others that the bread does tend to be on the soggy side, which I have no doubt is because of the way they prepare the sub.  

If you are in the mood for a sub, they will definitely sub for Subway in a big way.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
For years, I've heard friends from Knoxville and Jacksonville, FL talk about Firehouse Subs and I was excited to finally get a location in Nashville to try it for myself. The stories I heard were definitely true - these sandwiches are fantastic! If you like hot, meaty, cheesy sandwich goodness, this is the place for your fix.

I'm really racking my brain here trying to come up with a negative, but nothing comes to mind. The bread is delicious and the meats... oh man, the meats. I've tried just about every one on the menu now and the story is the same across the board - they are all delicious and absolutely dripping with flavor - literally, dripping, I tell you. I guess that comes from the steaming process (And yes, I do realize how all this talk about dripping meats is probably opening up some gross sexual images in some people's minds). Though despite the juiciness, I've never had an experience with soggy bread like one other reviewer said... maybe because the sandwich is so delicious that I inhale it within minutes.

Penn Station, Jersey Mikes, Subway and any other sandwich competitor be darned - Firehouse, in my opinion, far outweighs the competition. OH and I should mention that I love the staff at this location - they are super friendly and attentive.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
i ordered a Smokehouse Beef & Brisket sub for my wife and i ordered an Italian for myself. we got our food quickly, and my wife loved her sub, as she usually does. mine was ok, and i ended up saving half for later. well, i came home from work and was planning on having the rest of my sub and was only two bites deep only to find a massive hair in it!

at first i thought it was a stringy piece of cheese, so i pulled on it only to see inches and inches of long blonde hair!!! i know that in the food industry things like this happen, but if your hair is this damn long, you ought to know better. prepare thyself to handle one's food, damn it! 

ridiculous. and gross. this has ruined Firehouse for me, because their subs are nothing compared to Publix (where they actually use hair nets) so i hope you found this review to be helpful (or at least funny) but i strongly urge you to choose somewhere else!

text:
There's really not much to say about Firehouse.  If you've been to one you've pretty much got it down how it's going to look and taste.  I went to this place for lunch and it was a solid good sandwich that was made quick.  

The service is on par and normal for a sub shop, but nothing over the top memorable.

I tried one of the new sandwiches and it was ok, I had wished I went with my normal chicken bacon ranch but it sufficed.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Incredible food, great selection, incredible hot sauces. I noticed they are very child friendly and look for situations to hand out their plastic fire hats to make someone happy. My favorite so far is the Smokehouse Briskett. Prices are a tad high but very much worth the service, consistency, food, and environment this place has to offer. Also, we order out at lunch quite a bit, and I've found firehouse to be the most organized so that you are not digging through other people's food finding which is yours.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I had my first experience at this establishment today and I will not be going back. It took about 15 minutes to get my sandwiches and they were cold when I got them. The staff was extremely rude and did not care one bit about customer satisfaction. They also failed to let us know that they had no lettuce until we had completely finished our order (we got there as soon as they opened). Let's just say it's a good thing they're not working for tips.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: This was a second trip to this location and to Firehouse. We enjoyed it the first time; this time not so much. Because we usually get subs elsewhere, I was uncertain about how to order. The guy at the register was not a great help in ensuring that I got the subs the way I wanted them. When I said I wanted a turkey with just lettuce and tomato, he said, "That comes fully loaded with mayo, etc etc". Um, I just said I wanted lettuce and tomato only. The worst part was that I only wanted a veggie sandwich to fit my vegan diet - no mayo and no cheese and no mushrooms (I did my homework beforehand so that I would know what "veggie" items to avoid). I don't know how many times I told him I just wanted veggies - no mayo, no cheese, no mushrooms. Got home with our subs, and had mayo, cheese and mushrooms. Thanks for not listening at all. At least the other subs were correct. I won't eat here again. On an aside, while it's nice that you are wearing gloves, I don't like to see you wiping your nose or forehead with your wrist and continuing to touch food. That was just gross.

text:
Came here with one customer in the whole place. Ordered two subs. A few people started to come in to also eat. 20 minutes later, after watching 3 groups of people who came in after me get their food and leave, I asked how much longer for my subs. All three of the employees looked at me so confused. They had completely forgotten about my order. 10 minutes later I was told they ran out of ingredients for my sub and it would be a longer wait. 

Won't be coming back if I'm going to be forgotten about. More than a half hour wait for two sandwiches??? No thank you.

text: Did an online order, was given the time it would be ready. Upon arrival there where 4 employees and 3 customers, but you could see a long line of orders on the board. My order was not ready, but I know it gets busy. After 25 minutes of waiting and other customers coming in and being taken care of o asked about my order. I was still in the cue to be made????? Sorry, no. I did a refund and walked out. Only one e person was really working hard, the others didnt care.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Walked into this location being two of three customers in the building without being greeted or acknowledged. JD (only known by our receipt due to lack of name tag or introduction) without looking up from the computer mumbled, "What do you want?" and "What else?" then walked away without cups and before pointing to the cups sitting in the back of the room by the drink machine. The service wasn't just disappointing for us but for the rest of the people who entered after us. Two of the employees had  AirPods in their ears, several of them cussing loudly  and everyone ignoring the customers standing in front of them. 

We specifically had to ask for pickles and then run we're still left out of the order.  We were told they did not have a manager in house and that if we had complaints to fill out the receipt survey. 


Very rude staff that didn't seem to care about doing the smallest aspects of their job.

text: My boyfriend and I decided to eat lunch at Firehouse Subs while we are in Nashville, since we are not fortunate enough to have a location in our hometown. At the ripe old age of 25, my mind must be going because I left my purse hanging on the chair I sat in to indulge on my delicious sub. Without even realizing I had forgotten my purse, we saw a Firehouse Sub hero, named Thor (seriously his name is Thor), running through the parking lot and across the street to get our attention. We tried tipping him for his gracious act, but he refused to accept. What a stand up guy. I just thought he deserves a glowing review at the least.

Clean store in a busy location.

text: Place is in desperate need of new management. Went today for a sub. Got there at 10:29. They were supposed to open at 10:30 by 10:33 employees saw us at door and didn't open it or acknowledge us. At 10:35 we called the store and the manager answered. We asked if they planned to open and she said "oh it's 1035 guess I'm late".  We ordered our food. I got a "small sub" which is literally only 1/2 a sandwich. They should be embarrassed to call it that. The women's bathroom was filthy and out of paper towels. Remember this was at opening! I told the girl at the register and she couldn't care less. They had a crew of 5 so there is no excuse for this really except for what I said before.....lack of real management. No desire to return.

text:
Decided to give this place another try. BIG MISTAKE! Got there at 10:35AM 4/17/18 and 3 young guys working (if you can call it that). Not one looked up when we walked in. No "welcome to Firehouse", nothing. The guy at the register finally made eye contact  with me and turned away. I said "hello?"....no response or acknowledgement. I looked at my husband and said @why did we do this again?". So after 4min we decided to leave. I turned around to look and 2 of them were LAUGHING at us! I just loudly said "bad customer service still. You all will cause this place to close with those attitudes". 
ATTENTION STORE OWNER.....GET NEW MANAGEMENT!! This location is horrible! The absolute worst service! I will be reporting this to FHS corporate. If I could get zero or negative scores I would.




Place is in desperate need of new management. Went today for a sub. Got there at 10:29. They were supposed to open at 10:30 by 10:33 employees saw us at door and didn't open it or acknowledge us. At 10:35 we called the store and the manager answered. We asked if they planned to open and she said "oh it's 1035 guess I'm late".  We ordered our food. I got a "small sub" which is literally only 1/2 a sandwich. They should be embarrassed to call it that. The women's bathroom was filthy and out of paper towels. Remember this was at opening! I told the girl at the register and she couldn't care less. They had a crew of 5 so there is no excuse for this really except for what I said before.....lack of real management. No desire to return.

text: Drove up at 8:15pm.  Open sign was off even though they close at 9pm.  Quickly realized why the sign was off.  They had no interest in selling any more subs and they looked quite frustrated that I walked in to their business. I've been a fan of Firehouse Subs for quite some time, but everyone once in awhile a location disappoints me.  The biggest issue is they don't keep a manager on site and they rely on young employees that don't really care to close up shop.  Got food to go.  Neither kids meals were given the treat or hat.  Poor service.  Food was decent.  Just another poor showing at what could be a great franchise location.

categories: Sandwiches, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Fast Food
text:
Sigh...so many restaurants and so many places we could have grabbed a bite to celebrate after grandson's winning playoff game. But, we chose Firehouse...and that celebration was short-lived.

Plenty of help on hand behind the counter. Polite enough....and that's as far as it went.

The following interchange is very close to verbatim...

Me: "I'll have the Special Pastrami. The one on the advertisement behind you that says, for a limited time only."

Staff: "Sorry, we don't have that. The truck didn't arrive."

(Me to self: Uh...then why you still advertising it?")

Other person in our group: Ok, I'd like to try the __soup."

Staff: "Sorry, we don't have that either. The truck broke down."

Finally, after nearly a 20 minute wait our sandwiches and chili arrive.

EXCEPT: 2 of the 4 sandwiches are wrong! Sandwich details (salami and lettuce only!) was marked/printed clearly on receipt. Instead, got ham, cheese, mayo, and stuff....???

Took one of them back and waited another 10 minutes (not crowded at 8:00 pm....) 

Service ... like the old "limbo song" was about as low as you could go.

Obviously, not worth going back again.

text:
This was our go to place last year, went last night for the first time and every single worker had their noses out of the mask..then pulled all the way down when calling out a name over the line food. We couldn't and left. Bummer, they were working hard but it just comes down to leadership. If your lead is pulling the mask down then everyone will follow. I'll go back if I get word it's corrected. MToo important right now. 
-There is no CDC or social guideline that says masks with nose exposed is cool. We do have a full public mask ordinance, so food workers should know to be covered.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Let me tell you the service and the food quality are top notch for a sandwich shop.  The King's  Hawaiian pork & slaw sandwich is the best BBQ sandwich I have ever had.  They need to make this a permanent item on their menu.  :)  Also very good is the smokehouse beef & cheddar brisket sandwich.  Now this is a permanent item on the menu and can be had year around.  
Firehouse is a little more pricey than subway and other subs shops but it is so much better.  A reg size sub w/ chips & drink will run you about $9.00.  Speaking of drinks the freestyle soda machine is very cool and gives you a ton of choices to choose from.

attributes: {'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2', 'NoiseLevel': "u'loud'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
There are so many sandwich shops to choose from on S. Mt Juliet Road, in fact kind of a ridiculous amount. In the area you could get Firehouse Subs, Subway, Penn Station East Coast Subs or Jimmy's John's. For me Firehouse Subs is at the top of all of these places! 

This location is clean and the employees greeted me and were very friendly. I hadn't been to this location before but for your birthday they give you a free medium sub when you subscribe to their e-mail list so I went to go get my sandwich. I got the Italian which comes with Genoa salami, pepperoni, Virginia honey ham, melted provolone, Italian dressing, and seasonings. I got the "fully involved" which is the works including mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a kosher dill pickle on the side. This sandwich was yummy and I would order it again.

I appreciated the quick and friendly service and the birthday benefit is a great deal--keep it up Firehouse!

name: Firehouse Subs
text: How is this sub shop not abundant in New Jersey is mind blowing. The subs are delicious compared to other subs.

name: Firehouse Subs
text: They make great sandwiches. It's definitely a place to stop by if you have time to spare, if not-call ahead.  The hours posted must be wrong because they were closed tonight 20min to 9:00pm.

name: Firehouse Subs
text: This place opened up by my job not too long ago and I've heard mixed reviews from colleagues but decided to try it today and I was pleasantly surprised. I'm pretty simple so I got a small turkey sandwich with provolone cheese fully loaded which means it comes with mayo, mustard, onions, tomatoes and a pickle on the side. Choice of white or wheat bread. I got white. You can choose to have the sandwich cold or steamed. I got steamed and the bread wasn't wet or soggy. It was actually very soft. Honey mustard is a delicious side. The service was good which is always a plus. I'll be back to try the meatball sandwich

name: Firehouse Subs
text: I was so looking forward to trying this place. Friendly staff and very helpful. Sandwich I selected was not good I chose the Italian on a wheat roll. More ham than any other meat. On top of that, the ham was sweet like honey ham.  I am not sure if it is because this place is relatively new but I was very disappointed. I would compare to Jimmy Johns. Primos definitely a better option.

name: Firehouse Subs
text: I got a turkey and cheddar sub, paired with a mac cheese and a loaded potato soup. Average at best, barely any meat on the roll, and with my luck a bug flew into the only good part of the meal, the potato soup. The mac and cheese literally has crotons on top and is very runny. (Taste like microwaveable lean cuisine mac and cheese) Not worth your money, just go to wawa across the street.

name: Firehouse Subs
text: The subs here are delicious and spot on. However, I've been here 3 times since they opened and every time, they miss an ingredient in my sandwich. For example, my Italian was supposed to have lettuce and I didn't get any. And then my hook and ladder was supposed to have cheese but didn't. And then my husband ordered the brisket sub which was supposed to have BBQ sauce but didn't. We will continue to give this place chances since the prices are good and so is the food, but I have to start checking my food to make sure it's correct. Sad but true

name: Firehouse Subs
text: Bread was so bad....no taste. The meat was piled on in a thick brick. I threw the sandwich away after a few bites.

name: Firehouse Subs
text:
Being served a frozen pickle doesn't help initially does not help with this review but I will try to be honest here with my following thoughts.


1. Sub was tasty and reminds me of Quiznos.
1. Price point is still high and there is a lot of local competition even as a fast casual. Because the price point is high it reminds me a lot of Subway's business model for franchise owners.  Most of the gains will come through the sale of chips and a drink.
3.Part of the profits go towards Firefighter causes unlike others business like Wawa that just collect cash from hoagie fest, gas and cigarettes.
4. It's new, give them a shot if you have a coupon.

text:
Used to go to this location 2 or 3 times a week, it was that good.  What a difference a crew makes.  One of the good managers bailed, tired of the long hours for no pay, and it's since gone wayyyy down hill.  I stood in line for 20 minutes (behind two whole people) and finally gave up to get Taco Bell.  Gonna miss the ole Firehouse.

Incidentally, this review somehow was posted to Fitlife Foods originally, and I have no idea how that occurred, but I posted the correction and an apology to the owner of that business.

text: First time ever and right now Im not sure if I will return. Young lady took my order, very friendly and clearly explained the menu. Took my order, confirmed my request. Got my order quickly and returned to work. Opened my sandwich and first thing I see are the onions I asked be left off my sandwich!!! The nice young lady even repeated my request. name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Firehouse subs is a great place to get different hot subs.  My personal favorite is the roast beef and melted cheddar sub.  This is pretty much why I come to Firehouse subs, it is hard to resist.  They have a good selection of other hot subs, although it is hard for me to order anything but the roast beef and cheddar.  They also have several chopped salads which my wife enjoys.  They also have a kids menu which includes a drink, treat and a fireman's hat, all for a fairly affordable price (under $5 i believe).

They make sandwiches fairly quick and I have never had a problem with order accuracy on what is delivered.  The serving staff are nice enough as well.

On my last visit they were somewhat forgetful on an item which accompanies the kids meal - mainly the fire hat.  The server who brought out the food informed me that I was supposed to get this from the person taking orders and payment however she promptly brought this to our table after we complained of not receiving it.

text: This is the spot to go when you're in the mood for a sub. I usually order the hot Italian it's delicious ! The service is good, place is clean and the subs are great....can't ask for more. Definitely better quality than Subways and Quiznos, don't forget to check for specials they usually have deals.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Firehouse Subs is a step above Quiznos and Subway but a step below any actual sit-down sub shop (RE: Lenny's)

Their sandwiches are standard fare: ham and turkey, meatball, corned beef and pastrami, tuna, etc... All sandwiches come with lettuce, tomato, white onion, mayo and spicy mustard, as well as a pickle. White or wheat bread are their standards. A medium combo with chips and a drink will run you just under $10. Sandwiches don't come out especially fast and I do recommend calling ahead if you're in a hurry. I really like their hot sauce bar. Customer service is average. Not a bad place for a good, quick lunch.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Alright, Firehouse doesn't have the world's best subs, but they do have one item that most of the chain sandwich spots don't--THE NEW YORK STEAMER.  This is a hot, toasted sub with corned beef brisket, pastrami, melted provolone, mustard, mayo, and Italian dressing.  And since I'm a fan of lettuce and tomatoes, I add those to this masterpiece of a sandwich.  And when I'm feeling frisky, I slather on the Captain Sorensen's Datil Pepper Hot Sauce, which ironically is not hot at all, but curiously tasty.

Overall, good place to grub down with reasonable prices, common chip selections and a plethora of hot sauces to dump on their subs.  Oh, and the chili is pretty solid too.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text: Ok, so I got the best sammich EVAR at Firehouse. I've never been an absolute fan of this place, just preferred feeding here rather than be left at home. Then I had the King Hawaiian bun pork sammich with coleslaw in it, and was in hog heaven. So much so, that there is no picture to attest to this. I musta downed it in a few minutes flat with peach Mello Yello as lubricant. So why not five stars? Before eating the sandwich I had to search for hand soap in the men's room. After eating this sloppy piece of heaven I was in dire need of hand soap, but there was some kid in the pisser just hanging out. I'd say I was pissed, but to avoid a bad pun, I'll say bring your own soap. The sandwich is great, but no amount of shitty brown napkins is going to clean up the sopping mess this flavorful pork leaves behind.

text: Nothing like any other firehouse I've been too. The place is ran by mindless dope-heads. Waited 20 minutes in an empty restaurant for the wrong sub and they made it sound like I was wrong when I told them what I ordered. Find somewhere else.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
As far as my sandwiches were... they were fair to good... I had one of my sandwiches with double meat, and it looked like it was normal meat.  Could not tell that it was doubled or not.  

What was my biggest problem with going into this location... This is only my 3rd time coming into this location.  I have been going to Firehouse Subs for the last few years because of its ties to the local community and its love for the men in women in uniform. (Fire, Police, and Military)  This was the first location that I went to that did not honor the Military.  I have probably eaten at a dozen different Firehouse subs over the years.  As a retiree, I enjoy giving companies my money that show that little bit of love to the members of our services...  It was very surprising to hear that this Firehouse does not honor that.  

When I was talking with the lady at the register, she seemed to be limited with her English and was not able to answer questions with logic or confidence.  

For these reasons, I will not be coming back to this location.  The food is ok.  But, I will drive to another location that has better service and shows respect to all uniforms.

text: First time at a Firehouse Subs...I didn't look at Yelp prior to see the other reviews. I placed my order then looked around...was busy with people sitting...none of them had food.  It's that moment I realized how long it was going to take.  20 minutes for a sub is way too long. Order ahead was keeping folks in the store from being served. text: Generally when you ask for a hot sauce they are low, near empty bottle, they will go back and get a new one. I asked when you usually get new orders she said "couple months"  it wasn't busy, her customer service was poor and unfriendly. Food was ok and I won't stop going to firehouse.. maybe this one.

text:
'Welcome to Firehouse Subs' can be heard every time you walk in by the friendly staff.  Let's start with the bread.  It's better here than their more famous competitor by far.  

Next, the hot Italian is my favorite and make sure you get it 'fully involved'.  Salas's are good here too.  I prefer them chopped which is a good option they have.

Finally, I like the Coke freestyle machine which gives you more drink and flavor options to choose from then you could ever try!

text: I love Firehouse. But this location has gotten worse. I ordered my food at 12:10 according to my receipt. It's now 12:31 and I still don't have my food. Way understaffed. text: I usually have a good experience going here. This time was not the best.  We were the only ones in line and maybe 3 people eating inside and one grub hub order waiting. When we first cane in the workers were more interested in something they were watching on a cell phone, had to wait to order and repeat what one of the sandwiches wanted on it. One sandwich was made wrong and had to wait to have it redone.  The drink station was dirty, the lemon and lime containers were open and had one old lemon in it and two dried looking limes. The lobby wasn't the cleanest.  Disappointing this day and not the best service. Hope to have better service next time and lemons to put in my tea.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
I only give this firehouse subs 3 stars because of how good their sandwiches are.

You walk in and it doesn't look that appealing to the eye. The wait is also always way too long! I tried ordering via grub hub to hopefully speed up the process, but it takes just as long and they leave it sitting there in the back until I lose my patience and have to go ask for it. One time I literally waited my whole lunch break for a sandwich! 

Honestly though , it is well worth the wait because it's just so good! 
I always order the hook and ladder combo which is ham and turkey and tomato , onions, lettuce , and mayo and mustard. It never disappoints! It is a little bit pricey for a combo. The total is usually a little over $10.

Even though the wait is long, I usually always get this for lunch.

text:
AVOID this Firehouse Subs like the plague.

Night after night - either does not "confirm" orders via DoorDash or CANCELS orders 30-40 minutes after they're placed.  My orders have been inexplicably cancelled twice.

When they do confirm and actually prepare food, the quality has plummeted vs any other Firehouse Subs in the area.  Sloppy and/or wrong ingredients, cold, skimpy.

This store's ownership has major problems.  Looking at the other reviews before I added this one, they've had problems for a very long time.  DO NOT RECOMMEND.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}"}
text:
Today was my first firehouse sub experience it most likely will be my last. 

I just wasn't impressed with Firehouse. I found this location to have a weird setup and everything was all over the place. You order in the corner and when you go to get your drink you basically have to turn around and walk directly back into the line you were just in to get your drink. It can get very cluttered especially if multiple people are getting refills. 

I ordered the "hook n ladder" sub, which I'm assuming is their "specialty" sandwich. It's the first thing on the menu, its got a firefighter theme, and well, lets just say I'm assuming this is their specialty sandwich. You get the point...

I ordered that along with a medium combo for just over nine dollars. The medium drink was huge. Anywhere else it would be a large. So when I got my cup and saw how big it was, I was excited for my sub hoping it would be rather large. 

It took about 5 minutes for them to make my sub, which I found a little long to toast some bread and put some meat together but oh well. 

Finally my sub came out and it was a lot smaller than I imagined. I don't know if I got unlucky or that's just how small their subs are, but it made a foot long from Subway look big and that's not saying much.  

My next thought is that maybe they are going for quality over quantity. Nope. It was warm at best. My sub had no flavor and was one of the most plain tasting subs I have ever had. 

I appreciate everything they do for fire fighters and what they give back to the community but the food is average at best.

text: When I'm in the mood for a sandwich this is my favorite spot. My favorite sub is the hot turkey sub fully involved. They have a secret ingredient that holds them apart from all other sub shops. The secret is the fire house hot sauce. It's on the wall with all the other hot sauces. It is so good. It's hot but not to hot. It is also sweet. It brings out the flavors in the sandwich for a perfect marriage! The restaurant is always clean and the staff is very friendly.

text:
I'm not necessarily a sub connoisseur by any means, but I do like certain toppings.   Growing up in the subway generation has certainly tainted my expectation of how a sub shop should function. They only offer two types of bread! What?! No rosemary crusted whole wheat Parmesan bread? 

In all seriousness though, I was happy to get back to basics and the subs were quite good. The ingredients were fresh and there was a myriad of hot sauces for your sub-eating pleasure.

text:
Actually a very good sub place.  They have mostly hot subs.  Fire dept. theme is kinda fun.  All of the staff is always very nice.

They just got a new coke machine that has a computer touch screen on it.  You make your selections on the touch screen.  There is something like 150 combinations.  I really like the orange lemonade and the orange coke.  They will probably have this type of thing everywhere before long.

Me and a friend make it a tradition to come to Firehouse when home from college. I love the brisket and the variety of hot sauces. Firehouse is a chain but this one does it right. 

They also have coke freestyle which is enjoyable. 
The atmosphere is kinda fun. 
Outdoor seating when it is nice.

text: I tried Firehouse Subs and I was impressed. I'm not a fan of Subway and this is no Subway. The biggest difference between the two is there is meat on the Firehouse Subs and are of a higher quality. The restaurant was clean, the service was good and friendly. The prices were what you would expect. I had the steak and cheese and it was tasty.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I'm sorry, but yelling "Welcome to Firehouse Subs" whenever a customer walks in, giving us a free sub because they made our order incorrectly, giving me a free drink and cleaning my table... all of the above does not make up for a sub-standard (no joke intended) product. 

First, the girl at the order desk kept taking phone calls instead of taking my order. Sorry, but in this day and age, a REAL LIVE HUMAN standing there takes precedent over a phone order. Every time I tried to order, the phone would ring again and she'd stop me. This is horrible service.

The price for this "sub" is way too high. I can get double meet at Subway and pay the same price and get a MUCH better sandwich. Very little meat, a ton of iceberg lettuce and that's it???  They didn't even ask if I wanted anything else on the sandwich, a standard at almost every sub shop. 

Sorry, I won't be back, I can't figure out why this place is popular, they have the people of Plainfield completely fooled. I'd rather go to Subway any time, much better food and you don't have to wait for a phone order.

attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This place has slid dreadfully downhill.  At first, they had a mature staff and everything was impeccable.

Now it's impossible to pick up a correct order.  Impossible.

After one particularly bad situation, I contacted the mgmt and was just given excuse after excuse.  Apparently, if you enter an order correct online and they screw it up, it's slightly more your your fault than theirs.

Today, we were out and about.  Since we were nearby, I ordered from the mobile app.  We had to wait 15 minutes past our pick up time (35 mins total) and they jacked up both sandwiches.  It was comical because as we were eating, I looked at P and said,  "I think I have your bread and toppings."

... and he had mine.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Great sandwiches and a nice alternative to other places.  You're not going to get a $5 footlong here, but  you're going to get a really delicious hot sandwich.  

They mostly feature hot subs and that's all I've ever ordered.  I love the NY Steamer, which is not to be confused with any other type of steamer that you may have heard about named after a city in Ohio.

The Firehouse Hero is also really good and served "Fully Involved," which means mayo, mustard, lettuce, onion and tomato.  

You know what else is really good here?  The salads!  Yes, I know.  They are very fresh and served with crisp green pepper, red onion and hard boiled egg.  They're very good and they'll throw some meat on them, too.  

I'm also a sucker for any place that throws a dill spear my way.  I know, I know, I can buy a whole jar of them... but it's NOT THE SAME!

attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: We came to firehouse for dinner after being on the road all day. The food was fine, but the staff was only concerned with leaving right at 9pm. The website says that the restaurant closes at 10pm and the door says 9pm, so when a family came at 8:55 they told them "no we can't serve you, we close in 5 min." They called a customer with an online order and told them if they didn't arrive by 9 instead of the pickup time of 9:03 then they wouldn't serve them. To top things off, they turned the lights off while we were still sitting there eating. We normally enjoy their sandwiches but this customer service experience was less than pleasant.

text: Tried this place for the first time and it was terrible!  I ordered a vegetarian hot sub online and asked for no mayo.   What I got was a soggy sub drowning in mayo, with no mustard on it and little to no cheese (the menu says there should be three kinds).   I even found a piece of ham on it (I don't eat meat). name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Hit or miss on quality. Poor customer service. The Plainfield Firehouse Subs used to be my favorite. The last two trips have resulted in errors with the food and showed a lack of quality. Customers are supposed to be greeted upon entrance - no greeting today. While they were steady on business, there was not a line. We got our order to go. I ordered the New York Steamer described as: USDA Choice Corned beef brisket, pastrami melted provolone, deli mustard, mayo, and Italian dressing. The sub only had pastrami on it which included a giant layer of fat. It had very little mayo, no mustard and no Italian dressing. I took the sub back in. I was asked, "what's wrong?" I told them the sub only had pastrami on it, and it had a large layer of fat. I showed the sandwich to the order taker. She then told me that it is one meat and that it is corn beef brisket pastrami, and it always has fat. it was clear that there was not going to be any customer service; no offer to make it right whatsoever. I started to order another sandwich and decided not to as i sure didn't want to give them more business when they couldn't be bothered to assist. Very disappointing and very poor customer service.

text:
When they first opened, it was great.  Then they took a dive and we stopped coming.  We have ventured back a few times and have mostly been pleased. 

I think my primary frustration is that the workers have zero attention to detail.  They can mostly make a sandwich correctly.  Mostly.  

Sitting here now, I was requested to pay.   I had to tell them I had paid online.  When bringing my drinks to the window, the server asked if I had my food.  I said that I did not and his reply was, "You don't?" No, I don't. I promise I'm not harboring fugitive sandwiches.  

When made correctly, it's a slightly above average sandwich.  The service just never seems quite right.  Q

text: We arrived around 7:50pm, the door shows hours of daily 10:30am-9:00pm. No one greeted us. We placed our order...asked if they give a firefighter discount and the girl ringing us up stated she wasn't sure....nor was she willing to ask anyone. No one spoke to us other than to place the order. As soon as we ordered a different girl locked all the doors. Yet according to the door they had another hour. No sign asking people to wear masks was visible anywhere. The food was exceptional but the experience was pathetic.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I stopped at fire house subs as I hadn't eaten at one in a very long time. I remembered they have a few unique options like the steamer. I saw that they had chili as well as the subs. As it was around 20 degrees the sub and chili sounded good. I ordered a small engineer which is smoked turkey sub with mushrooms and most of the other standard ingredients. I like the warm subs here. Also they have the coke freestyle which is a big plus. I have a theory with sub shops that I followed never go through the drive through. It's way to complicated to get what you want even being inside. They do offer on line ordering with pickup too. Inside was very clean and well adorned with appropriate fire house theming. Another big plus is they actively donate to help fire fighters. Always good to feel like your helping out while you eat. The sandwich was great my only drawback is I realized I should have ordered a larger one. The chili is not spicy at all but still tasted good. I also got a cookie to eat as they had chocolate with mint chips which was good to. I didn't have any issues during my visit and the speed of getting my sandwich seemed appropriate.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Ordered on the app, one of the few options available given current circumstances. That was fine but I pull up to the window and was completely ignored by the 3 employees that I can clearly see. Finally, someone comes over and asks the name. I told him and he replied that he didn't have an order for that name, then I told him that I've already paid for it. He walks away but says nothing. A few more minutes pass and finally another man comes over and asks what the name on the order was. I told him and proceeded to ask him if that was in fact FHS #584, followed by showing him the order on my phone. He said he didn't know what happened (HOW CAN YOU NOT???)but that he'd make the order and bring it out to me if I'd just pull up. I started to but then he yelled to wait.  Of corse there was another vehicle right on my bumper hindering me from backing up. So I opened the door and the guy hands me a bag and says "it's been sitting next to the window this whole time." I took it and left then when I got home, my order wasn't right and was cold. Thanks for the sorry excuse for service and food.

text:
WOW!! I have heard so much about fire house subs. I actually went out my way to eat lunch there today. The parking is not bad and the establishment is clean, and has  an appeal to the eyes. From there it goes south. I ordered the Italian sub, with chili as a side. The Italian club is the worst sandwich I have had to date, and at a whopping 10$ with tax for a footlong is way over priced. The chili on the other hand was (the worst chili I have ever had). I thought I was eating warm apple sauce with Tabasco. So all in all the establishment is nice. The food and pricing of the food is outrageous. This will be my first and last time here. 
Ps. There's a subway down the street.

text: I go to this place frequently because I really enjoy the Cheddar Brisket sandwich. Few buddies and I used to drive all the way to Covington (25 minutes) just to grab some of these sandwiches! This particular location seems to be still transitioning to a full functioning team as I would always see a change up in staff with a person always in training. With this constant change over the course of 8 months (?), the consistency of sandwiches are ever changing... As I would get a fraction of the meats- stingy portions of sauce- and getting a 'normal' amount of meat when I clearly paid for double meat. All in all, when you catch this place on a good day then you'll be happy you came here.

text:

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': None, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': None}"}
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New), Delis
text:
If you've ever been to a Firehouse Subs, this place is par for the course.  If you haven't, you're in for a treat.  Keep in mind that these aren't poboys.  They aren't less tasty, they're just different.

The bread isn't as good as Jimmy John's or Panera Bread, but it's a lot better than Subway and Quizno's.  They do a lot of sandwiches well, and you can always custom build your own, but as far as I'm concerned, the Firehouse Hero is where it's at--roast beef, smoked turkey, Virginia ham, and provolone melted on top.  I get it "Fully Involved" (fully dressed, plus mustard and onion), slather some Captain Sorensen's Datil Pepper Sauce on that baby, and drift off to seventh heaven.

Pickle comes on the side and it's tasty.  If you're going Large, and you like pickle, order an extra pickle.  The combo is of questionable value in my book, but if you're gonna get a drink anyway, just get the combo.  I like Doritos, but they have all the national brands of small-bag chips, and their baked goodies are as good as Subway (or better, depending on the item).

I go here about once a month, and I've noticed that the tables can be a little dirty AFTER the lunch rush.  I think the employees are tired and a little off their game after the rush, so as the volume drops off, they aren't as good about the wipe-down and refresh.  That means I prefer to go before 1pm or after 4pm.

categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New), Delis
text:
Guys, I am really REALLY disappointed with how absolutely terrible the service and food quality was here today. It was so bad that honestly I am never coming back and I have no doubt in my mind that this place is going to go under in near future if things continue on their current path. 

We came in as soon as they opened, so 10:30 am.  No one welcomed us, we were just met with blank stares. Whatever, we ordered two large sandwiches, one Steak and Cheese and the other was Brisket and Cheddar. It took them over 20 minutes to prepare two sandwiches. There was only one person who had ordered ahead of us, so I have no clue why it took that long to make two subs. There were at least six employees there, so staffing was not the issue. We eventually get our sandwiches, and they were terrible. They did not toast the bread, our sandwiches were made incorrectly and the quality of the meat was poor. To make a bad situation worse, both my husband and I experienced stomach pains within an hour after leaving. This was literally our first meal of the day, so there is no question as to what could have caused our discomfort. I'm just happy our toddler did not eat anything while we were here, so at least he was spared feeling ill. 

Believe me when I say that you're better off going to Subway or any place that serves sandwiches for that matter. I would avoid this place like the plague, unless you enjoy bad food prepared by poorly trained employees. Eat here at your own risk!

I was in the mood for a hot sandwich and had never tried firehouse subs do decided to stop by and try it.  I looked at the menu online and noticed they had a pairing of half a veggie sandwich + salad so i went to the store to order that.  

The foot itself was good - a decent size, good flavor and overall tasty.  The salad was a good side salad and had lots of veggies - same for the veggie sub which was also good

The thing that was bad was the service - when i went inside the manager and an associate were talking loudly to each other and just continued as if i was not there.  only after about 5 minutes did someone actually take the order - and the other associates didn't look nor act professionally or customer friendly

overall decent food but poor service

text:
So my first visit here left me with mixed feelings. On the one hand, my sandwich was delicious. On the other, the chick at the register was kinda rude. Not so much in what she said, but in her attitude. Very brusk, no thank you, no smiles. I mean, I take my sandwiches seriously, but this was dedication to a bad mood gone awry.

Still, the Steak and Cheese sandwich was delicious and prepared perfectly; heavy with meat and fresh veggies, with a fresh and crispy roll. I haven't had one of these in quite some time and I will be back for this one! It reminds me of the steak sandwiches I used to be able to get on the Westbank many, many moons ago. So, could there be some sense of nostalgia when I'm biting into this fluffy pillow of yum? Of course! Doesn't the best food do that to you? For you?

So while the customer service was a little off, it was still fast and delicious and super filling. I'll totally be back!
