categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New), Delis
text:
Give me Firehouse over Subway any day. It's bittersweet because Firehouse reminds me of Quiznos in its prime; although, I think Quiznos was superior in quality to both of these delis. Tsk, tsk. 

I love Firehouse's steak and cheese sub. It is my go-to sammich. It amazes me how they put the right amount of mayo every time and I love me some mayo. Now, on this most recent outing, my sandwich was lukewarm and I don't understand why. I picked up my free medium sandwich, by the way, thanks to T-mobile Tuesdays, drove to the nearby mall and parked. That took all of...two minutes? My sandwich had the temperature of a sandwich that had been sitting for 10 minutes. Temp aside, the bread was pillowy soft, the steak was well seasoned and the peppers were on point. The medium is pretty filling too.

Service was great and fast. Of course, there weren't many customers because of Covid, I imagine. But it was another opportunity to support a small business.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'WheelchairAccessible': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': None, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': None}"}
categories: Restaurants, Sandwiches, Fast Food, American (New), Delis
text:
Our first visit to Firehouse Subs was a fantastic one!

We didn't have time to dine in, since we had a sleeping baby and cold food in the truck- so this review is based on our take out experience. 

Matt ran in and ordered a large Firehouse Steak and Cheese for us to share, although they had lots of tasty options on the menu (I'm talking about you, Firehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket). While he was inside, I noticed that if you check-in on Yelp you can get a free cookie! I called Matt in a hurry and to fill him in on the Yelp swag and he managed to check-in and snag one before they finished making our sandwich. I'm so glad he did because their cookies are absolutely delicious! Not too hard, not too soft and filled with lots of chocolate chunks- what's not to love? We devoured our cookie on the ride home, and couldn't wait to dig into our sandwich. Well let me tell you, the Steak and Cheese did not disappoint. The bread was perfectly toasted, and the steak was thin and well seasoned. It also had an excellent ratio of steak to bell pepper. It held up extremely well on our 10 minute drive home, so I can only imagine it would be even better if we had the chance to dine in. 

Matt reported that the service he received was very friendly and that all of the employees greeted him when he arrived. One of my favorite reasons for giving this chain our business is that a portion of their proceeds goes towards first responders! This is  such a wonderful cause, and one that is close to my heart as my grandfather was a firefighter. These individuals put their lives on the line everyday to help other families in need, so I love contributing to organizations that give back to those who serve our communities. 

I encourage you to give Firehouse Subs your business if you're in the area. There is also a special they are currently running- $4.99 for a medium sub! So there is no better time than the present to try them out!

text:
Why 4 stars?

text:
I've been waiting for Firehouse to finally land in my area and I'm glad to see they did. The Plaza that it resides in is easy to access and a very nice location. The store is new and clean and the staff are friendly and attentive.

Purchased 3 subs, Large Steamer, Large Meatball and a small Turkey sandwich. Total bill was $24. Plus tax. Not a bad value. Ordered online and my items were ready for pickup when I arrived. 

When I got home I was happy with how my food was prepared. Very well made and how the photo looks for the items. They were very well prepared and tasted great! I'm very happy with my first visit and plan on going again to sample other items they have up for sale. Give it a shot, you won't be sorry!

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
This place is quite the trek for us, but I'm glad we finally made our way to it!  For a chain sandwich shop, Firehouse Subs is actually really good!

Upon entering, you see a very, very clean space.  All the tables were clean, the floors were clean.  The decor was decent, the lighting was good.  Overall, it's a very inviting space.  They have the ordering and pick-up lines clearly labelled, so understanding where to go was simple.  It was made even easier by the very friendly employee that greeted us at the door.  She explained some of the sandwiches and pricing, and gave us some of her favorites as recommendations.  

The sandwiches we chose were the Hero and the steak and cheese, both on the white bread sub roll.  The Hero has roast beef, turkey, and Virginia ham, and all were extremely moist and tasty.  And the sandwich had a lot of all three, making it a pretty substantial sandwich.  The cheese didn't have a ton of flavor, but the rest of the sandwich was so juicy and the bread was so soft and fresh, that I didn't mind.  The steak and cheese sandwich was great!  The steak was the shaved type typical in Philly cheese steak sandwiches.  It was quite flavorful and good.  The peppers still had a bit of a crunch, adding to the texture of the sandwich.  Surprisingly, the mustard that comes on the sandwich was also very good.  I'm from the tri-state area and have had quite a lot of cheese steaks in my time.  The idea of mustard on one was a little odd for me, but we tried it anyway, and it worked!  Overall, these were two very good sandwiches.

Also kinda cool, Firehouse has a Coca-Cola freestyle machine.  Oh my!  The amount of fountain drink options in that thing is mind boggling!  We tried their cherry limeade, which was basically very sugary cherry flavored stuff, but it was ok in small quantities.  You have to squeeze a lot of limes in it, though, and I added some water in mine to cut the sweetness.

Our table was cleaned up for us very quickly by the nice lady that greeted us upon entering.  They really cared about cleanliness and making customers comfortable!

The pricing was about average.  I'd much rather give them a couple of bucks more for what they're serving than pay less at Subway and eat "food" that has no flavor and looks to be the consistency of wax and plastic.

Hopefully Firehouse Subs opens a location on the east side now!

text: Hot subs that are actually hot, unlike Subway's "toasted" subs.  One of the kids got a grilled cheese on bread that Subway can't do so if you are looking for a sub, hot or cold, this place beats Subway hands down.  We came at high noon and the parking lot was packed and I feared a mob scene but the line moved very fast (3 cashiers) and there were still places to sit because its pretty big for a sandwich shop.  They could use a second drink dispenser only because a few people are unfamiliar (me) with all the billions of choices and we slow the line down.  But an employee was right there to help me solve my dilemma.  The food quality was great with plenty of chips selections. We'll be coming back often.

text: At first it kinda smelled funny when I walked in so I didn't want to eat there. They were friendly and helpful from start to finish. We had never been there so we probably did look a little lost but they were quick to explain how everything worked. We decided to give it a try. I got the Turkey Bacon Ranch. I'd say it's a little expensive, but worth it. I've been back once since, and will be returning to try new things. text:
Soooo happy that Firehouse finally came to Tucson. Decent sized subs, great bread and good quality meat. The option may be pretty "basic" but there is still something about them that just tastes great. What really makes this place is the wall of hot sauces. Anywhere from something sweet and spicy, garlic or melt your face right off. Been to a couple across the country and that was what got me. 
Gotta love the story behind the place also, company started by fire fighters. 
Be ready to be welcomed with a "WELCOME TO FIREHOUSE" whenever you walk through the door.

text:
The Firehouse gig is certainly fresh and fun, but I suspect after the newness wears off it won't be as popular as it is now. Founded (not owned) by firefighters but still a big chain franchise restaurant. 

Forget the Sweet and Spicy Meatball sub. In fact, forget the meatball sub any way. The meat just lacks flavor and is too bland no matter what sauce you put on it. 

The Italian is good as long as it is hot but the flavors fathers when it cools. It could be served hotter to prevent that. The of the other subs are tasty as well but they could use more meat and cheese. The variety of meats and cheeses are certainly a plus.

There are two real downers. First, the Jimmy's-John's-style doorway greeting called out to every entrant: "Welcome to Fire...House!" There is usually a drawl on the vowels. The first time or two is cute but anything more becomes as annoying distraction from the meal. Second, the Coca Cola Freestyle machine with more than 120 brands and choices. Great idea and way cool, but not practical or efficient in a fast serve place. Everyone has to use the single user machine. Ridiculously long drink lines every time all the time. Even for water. No bueno.

text: So we stopped here for a quick bite....let me just say, taking 30 minutes to make a sandwich...and asking repeatedly during those 30 minutes what was taking so long...is unacceptable.  This type of restaurant is known as a "Quick service restaurant", not fast food, however 30 minutes is just not ok when people are on a lunch break.  The food is decent but not worth waiting that long.  We called the owner...haven't heard back.  Not a shock.  The kids behind the counter (and I mean kids, no one over 25) were overwhelmed and it's not their fault they were mismanaged.  Not going back, and it's too bad, the food and philanthropic efforts are worthy.

Absolutely amazing food and service... Yes I'm talking about a fast food sub shop I took my dad here for his first time and he is still raving about it 7 hours later. The subs are simple and very tasty. They will adjust any sub on the menu I highly recommend the pulled pork sandwich.

text:
I used to frequent Firehouse Subs in Orlando, Florida while going to college and thankfully the Firehouse here in Tucson is just as delicious as I remember. For the uninitiated, Firehouse offers a variety of subs and every single one of them is mouth-wateringly good. Try the Meatball sub for starters. You'll be glad you did.

As a side note, this particular location has some fantastic staff. My wife and I waited for our sandwiches and when the lady brought them over, she apologized profusely for the "wait." I think the wait was about five minutes tops. I then apologized for drooling all over the table because my sub was so good. True story.

There's also the most wicked Coke machine I've ever seen in my life there. It offers about a thousand choices in soda.

text:
Great service. Great food. 

I don't typically review fast dine in places, but Firehouse Subs deserves it. Their food was out of sight, but the level of service they provide makes the difference. 

We had a large group order and it was prepared correctly, and made promptly in time for me to pick it up on time, but for the hot sandwiches to still be warm and not soggy. Their online ordering made it easy for the whole group to put their order in. 

I highly recommend them for a quick bite or a lunch carry out for the office.

text: Hubs likes firehouse more than I do. To me, they're a step above a Subway or Quiznos-style sandwich place, but it's not like they're anything crazy special. They are very family friendly (and even give out little plastic firemen hats for kids) which earns them an extra tip of the hat because I've got twin 3-year-olds and I never have a problem eating here (some restaurants are just out of the question when you're wrangling twin 3-year-olds). But the kids love Firehouse and the parents like it, too. Plus, they have a drive-through lane so you can call in your order ahead of time and drive through to pick it up. I literally just changed my rating from 3-star to 4-star for that feature, alone (again, a very nice feature for a family with young kids that can be challenging to get in & out of the car). So maybe not the best/most gourmet sandwich of your life. But it's a very decent sandwich at a good price and they are great at accommodating families. 4 stars from me! : )

text:
This is a new place on this side of town so I thought I would pick up a quick sandwich after going shopping.

Total bill was $8.93. I had the "engineer" (turkey). It's an 8-inch hot sandwich loaded with tomatoes, lettuce, and other goodies. Bag of chips and a medium drink come with the meal. The sandwich was much better than what you would get at Subway for just a little more cost. 

Friendly staff!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Firehouse Subs is a solidly great grinder option.  Yup, I said grinder (East Coast girl and proud of it!) and I was impressed by my two visits.  

The space itself is clean and bright, and they offer one of those drink dispensers that have 20934820358 options of soda.  They also have an iced tea station - both sweet and unsweet teas.  I did a mixture - 70% unsweet and 30% sweetened for a perfect (for me) ratio.

Both times I got the Engineer with chopped pickles added.  I chose to get the wheat bread option, and it was delicious.  Great chew, fluffy, and light all at the same time, and sturdy enough to hold up all of the meat and toppings that they pile onto the grinder.  The toppings (tomatoes, lettuce, etc) are fresher and a higher standard than what Subway uses.

The first time we ate in the restaurant itself, the second time we did take out to eat at home.  The sandwiches definitely hold up better if you can eat them in the restaurant, mainly because when you take a hot sub to go it is bound to get a little soggy in the wrapper.

I'm intrigued to try their online ordering system - if it works well I will definitely utilize it as the subs do take a little longer than the average grinder place to come out.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
The staff at Firehouse Subs are some of the nicest people I have ever met.  Almost all the sub sandwiches (with the exception of a few sandwiches) are hot subs.  You can get 8" or 12" sandwiches.  Most combos are about $8.20 which includes chips and a drink (from the Coca-Cola freestyle machine).  I loved the sweet and smoky barbecue Ruffles chips. 
 My favorite sandwich is the Italian on honey wheat.  The deli meat is hot, and the toppings are cold.  It is recommended to eat the sandwich right away or else it will get mushy even with the thick bread.  I know some Italian sandwiches are too sour from the vinegar, but it has a great taste with the Italian dressing and spicy mustard.  I highly recommend Firehouse Subs.
If you need your sandwich made in less than 10 minutes, I would say to call your order in and take your car to the pick-up window.

We also enjoyed the siracha beef sandwhich.  Sometimes service is a little slow but the sandwiches are always put together nicely and not thrown together!

text: They have about 7 people working in there and maybe four customers at a time and still can't get an order correct I had to walk out after waiting 10 minutes for a sub being the only person in the restaurant. Just horrible.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: It was my first time experiencing Firehouse Subs, and I will never go back. To begin with, they had three employees and none of them greeted us. It would be excusable if it was busy, however we were one of three couples in the place. I had never been and spent a good amount of time scanning the menu, in that time I wasn't asked if I had any questions about the menu or shown how it generally works. My girlfriend wondered aloud about the sizing, and all three employees ignored us until I explicitly asked. Our food didn't take much time, though I would have waited longer for a meal with more care. Our sandwiches were haphazardly thrown in the bag. I had the club, which looked good, but all I could taste was mayo and sweetness. The honey ham overpowered the entire sandwich. The bacon was wet and limp. It seemed microwaved. My girlfriend's New York Steamer was a mushy disaster. It tasted like a microwaved gas station sandwich. We are pretty easy going in regards to food and typically give restaurants more than one try but this experience was awful all around.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Update!!! Another good review. I think the sandwich I got this time was even better than the first, if that's possible. I went to Firehouse Subs over the weekend with my daughter and mother. I ordered the new pulled pork sub with the Hawaiian roll. OMG! It was so good! It was meaty and juicy. It had the cole slaw on it. The roll was soft and fresh.

It wasn't as loud and crazy as the first time I went but it was busy and we got the last table inside that wasn't occupied. We will be back next time we are in Tucson.

Too expensive for what it is. 

I have been here about 3 times, I've tried a few sandwiches but the only one I'd reorder is the brisket and BBQ. It's a good sandwich, but the combo is over $10. The sandwich has really good, tender beef with good BBQ on it. The problem is, it's not big at all. I could probably eat 2 honestly.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I went there yesterday between lunch and dinner time thinking it was going to be not as crowded. This place was crowded busy and very loud! The line went pretty quick. They do have a tea/water/ice station which I see from other reviews that they added. I can see why it was necessary. The coke freestyle machine is awesome but that place was too buy to just have one machine, even if they did have another machine I'm not sure where they would put it. If you have an undecided person or a newbie to the coke freestyle machine, you might be there for a while.

I didn't get the welcome to the firehouse like other people have said. I ordered the hook and ladder with chips and a drink. My daughter ordered the salad with the sliced chicken on top. It was sliced lunch meat not a sliced chicken breast like I thought it was going to be. My daughter and I shared the sandwich and salad. Make sure to ask for a cold sub if you want that, they are all served warm. The hook and ladder was better than expected and the chopped salad was good too. My ice tea was very good. My daughter got a vanilla coke and she said it was good. 

Oh, they do have an employee to bring your sandwich out to your table. They have firemen hats for the kids. If I'm in Tucson again visiting family I would definitely go again.

The ladies restroom was clean but my brother said the men's restroom was dirty.

text:
Wonderful for what it is. The subs are expensive but delicious and high quality. The staff is helpful and friendly and the store is new so still very clean. 

The real draw, though, is the soda machine. I'm not even sure what to call them still but if you've used one you probably know what I'm talking about; touch screen, over a hundred choices. 

Highly recommend this place. Just be ready to shell out $10 per person.

text:
Welcome to Firehouse!!!!

Those are the words you will be greeted with when you walk in the door.  I am a fan of Firehouse from when I lived in Florida.  The sandwiches are now your ordinary sandwiches.  They have some really great flavor combinations.  

For your first visit I would recommend the Club on a Sub or the NY Steamer.  These are two of their best but won't got wrong with any item on the menu.  I have had them all.  Not all at once!!

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Can't believe I waited so long to try Firehouse... wonderful varied menu, fresh meats and the bread is delicious.  A bit of a challenge for my kids, since everything has so much flavor... :D  But even they raved about the bread and the flavor of the meats. Went to this location on a road trip, so likely I won't be back anytime soon, but I'm going to try the Firehouse subs when it opens in Surprise, for sure!

text: I have gone over here many times on the way home from work. They have meatball subs which my husband loves, CHerry limeade which I could drink a gallon of and it's a hot sub place with a firehouse theme. The staff have always been attentive and it's consistently a good meal. A bit on the pricey side for subs, twice what i'd pay for Eegee's. Yet it's got some really mouthwatering hot subs.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Their subs are awesome! You can get hot or cold and there are many options for meat, including brisket and meatballs. Better go hungry, their subs are pretty good sized. They have one of those fancy new computerized Coca Cola machines. They have a custom drink too--cherry limeaid, very yummy. You have to try the King's Hawaiian Pork & Slaw sandwich while it is still around!

There were 4 people work, all just standing around talking. It shouldn't take 30 mins to make two sandwiches. This is the second time this has happened to me in the last month

text:
Normally, the food and service here are pretty good.

Not yesterday, though. We waited over 30 minutes just for 2 subs to go when only one family was in the restaurant.  To make matters even more interesting, one person walked in about 10 minutes after we were waiting, and his sandwich was ready to go in about 7 minutes while we still waited.  4 people were working at the counter, so you would think it wouldn't take too long..

When we got home, one of the sandwiches was wrong, so I contacted the website but have not heard anything back yet.  

We still want to like this place, but after yesterday, we might not be going back so soon

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
11:30 on Saturday morning and they are OUT of Chili. Not well managed.  Very young argumentative manager.   

With his sub my husband wanted the chili. $3.69 for a cup is not bad, but not great either. The cup was half empty. I noticed a man one table over eating his chili and his cup  was full. The server said they were "rationing" it  as they were low. I asked for the manager. The manager came over, told me the half cup was acceptable to her but would bring us more "when it was done". Never came. Needless to say we just ate and left. Chili was mediocre anyway.

They should have refunded our money if they could not fill the order.   My husband loved his Meatball Sub. My Chicken Club sub was nice but bland. No spice, no sauce....bland. So we will not rush back any time soon.

Read a big article in the paper a few weeks ago so we went out of your way to try it. Expected it to be great.

text: This is my free favorite sandwich shop in town. They have the best subs, especially the Italian. Every time I go in here they are very friendly and fast. I love that they employ people with special needs. Everyone wants to feel valued and of worth. What a great example to the community!

name: Firehouse Subs

text:
This place is great.  Each time I've been there the place was packed, the service was quick, and the food was delicious. I love the corned beef sandwich, and their BBQ sauce is to die for.  They also have a really cool soda machine that will vend different flavors of soda, I'm assuming with some sort of syrup to mix in.

All in all this is a great place for a great lunch at just under $10 for the whole kit and caboodle.

text: The subs are not bad.  But it takes forever to get your order.  I've been here numerous time and it doesn't matter if they they are busy or not, plan on waiting for your order.  Today's order was wrong...i got home and after waiting 13 minutes for two subs, one of the had an item I requested be removed, and was missing an item I requested be added.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I've always liked Firehouse ever since I first experienced them 6 years ago. However lately the River Rd location seems to be slipping. One time I wanted 10 minutes for a sandwich with the place near dead as far as customers. I actually had to talk to someone to get my sub to my table.  In my opinion the onions should be diced or chopped and not put on the sandwich as a whole circle, it's difficult to eat trying to chop apart the onion with your teeth.  And the last time I went I got the Italian sandwich and it arrived with no Italian dressing or brown mustard at all. These items are supposed to be on the sandwich by default. I really can't see myself returning to this location without proof they've improved.

text: This is our go to place for great subs. I've tried a few different ones now. I really liked that the meatball sub did not get soggy at all and it tasted great.  We've never been disappointed with the food or the service here. They also the Coca-Cola Freestyle drink machine with a wide variety of soft drink options.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: This place is very clean and the BBQ cheddar brisket sub is quite tasty. The big problem we had was that it took forever to get our food, and my husband's sub was wrong. When he pointed it out to the staff member, he was given an attitude and told that was what he ordered. He then spoke with the manager to explain it was wrong, and then she told him they would fix it but told him next time he needed to be more specific. She was quite argumentative and rude so I can see how the staff would follow suit. Place is overpriced and service was lousy. Very disappointing.

text: The sandwiches are so good here! I got a pastrami sandwich. Definitely planning on going back and trying their other sandwiches soon.They offer combos with speciality sandwiches, but they also offer simple sandwiches. The small sandwich was a decent size and the prices are reasonable.

text:
Turkey bacon ranch... I can say without a doubt this was gawd damned amazing! I loved it! I recommend wheat bread. So tasty! I also got the large size. The only reason I gave this a 4 star is because my wife got a small veggie and for almost $6 it was really lacking. I'm stuffed and she is starving. 

Pro tip: Even if you are a light eater go medium and not small. Small price increase for much more food.

text:
(3.5 stars)

Firehouse is my favorite chain sub shop in Tucson. The large sub is huge and meaty! They're very clean and the product is consistently tasty. I wish the meat were a little less like the thin, salty, grocery-store style slices. But for hot subs they beat Quiznos any day. Ooh, and you can order online. It's a great place for a quick stop-off at the start of a northbound trip.

text:
Firehouse is one of my favorites and I have gone many times and will continue to go back often. The food here is always great and the staff is super friendly with quick service.  Plus, who can resist rounding up your bill to help with such a great cause?

I have noticed, however, a slow shrinkage in the size of the sandwich with a opposite growth in the size of the bill. If these two things continue to move in the wrong directions then I may need to rethink my choices.

text: Firehouse is crazy busy. The reason they are crazy busy is because they are crazy good. The reason they are crazy good is because their sandwiches contain a whole days worth of sodium. Their soft drink machine is pretty crazy too.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: First, I love the commitment of Firehouse Subs to First Responders. It is enough to make me want to stop in when someone suggests going. As for the food, it is a little pricy for what you get. Nothing seems to be overly fresh or great. The subs are standard but service is quick.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I love this Firehouse location. The employees are always so nice, my order is always correct (always to-go), and the food always tastes great! 
I have eaten at another location in town... the food is good but it always seems like a huge struggle for the employees to figure out what's going not. Never the case here. There is a long-haired (tied back) guy working here- I'm not sure if he is a manager or not, but he is always extra pleasant and seems to be training the other employees. The whole experience is just really refreshing, especially for a fast food restaurant. Plus, who doesn't love yummy food?!?

text:
I pass by this sub franchise daily on my way to work and school.  I have never tried it until yesterday.  I must say I was impressed with the food.  I had a steak-and-cheese sub (hold the mustard) and it was a decent take on a Philly cheese-steak.

The atmosphere of the restaurant is a little less than inviting, has the total franchise feel to it, but the deliciousness of the food makes it easy to see past the gaudy decor.

One complaint, a little pricey for what you get.

text: I ordered a hot club on a sub. This sub was absolutely delicious. I only ordered a medium sub and it was more than enough for me. It was packed with meats. The combination of the meats with the bacon was just the best. I have eaten at Jimmy Johns, Eegees's, Jersey Mikes and Subway. This place beats them all.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Drove over from the Eastside, it was completely worth it! We decided to check it out because they generously give away a free bday sub, no coupon needed. We got the Kings Hawaiian pork and slaw. It was fantastic. A perfect ratio of meat to slaw on a super pillowy roll. We also bought the Brisket and Cheddar and the NY Steamer which is corned beef and pastrami. Both of these were amazing. All had an ample amount of meat, which made my hubby very happy.The facility was very clean and bright and the cashier sweet, competent and quick. I really hope someone opens a Firehouse subs on my side of town but in the meantime we will take the occasional 'road trip'. Yes, it is that good! Oh, and can't wait to try the under 500 cal menu, looks great! :)

text: I've been here a few times. The sandwiches are huge and have all the toppings, they call it "fully involved".  The ingedinents are primo Sandwich recipes come from their own family favs. These do not disapoint. When you walk in you're entering a themed red and white firehouse. It is decorated with all the equipment and uniforms firefighters use.  I think this place is great. I forgot my stresses for a minute and took in all the cool things this place has on display.  You can customize anything about the sandwich to fit your tastebuds. My 7yr old gives a thumbs up too, they give kids lil red fire hats!

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: The Captain Sorensen's sauce is amazing, love it on all their sandwiches.  The smokehouse and steamer are my favorite and my son loves the ham or meatball on the kids menu. Always made fresh and not too long of a wait

text:
Before anyone starts hating on my review please know that I 100% absolutely love Love LOVE Firehouse subs!! HOWEVER I am E X T R E M E L Y disappointed I this store tonight!!! I paid for my 8 inch Sub On A Club and for extra bacon. This is all I ordered. After waiting over 25 minutes I was given a way less than par sandwich. 

NOTE: On the way into this store there was a couple who had never tried Firehouse and I was selling them on this place and now I look like a fool!

I am extremely upset and disappointed that the guy before me who was dining in had to wait for a second sandwich to be made because his was screwed up. I get home and as you can see by my proof of purchase I paid for extra bacon and no onions and this clearly is not what I paid for! 

Some places are hit and miss but I truly dos not know that the place I love would become one of them!

text: Absolutely terrible service. DO NOT order the "salad" as it looks NOTHING like the image. Who made my salad, a 3rd grader? The photo has veggies, peppers, and other items included. I received nothing other than plain chopped lettuce. This is twice in two weeks, and previous salads we ordered looked way better. Awful. Dont even deserve one star. See photo of 3rd graders salad. When I called, I was told "Go right ahead" after I was denied a refund and told them I would write this review.

text: Their sandwiches are repulsive, the tuna was okay, I didn't like how the tuna had these  big chunks of onions in it, but it was a 5 out of 10. I ordered the regular club and it looked repulsive all greasy and slimy. I looked on the inside and it looked like someone just slopped it together, the turkey looked awful bad, the whole sandwich  looked like it was dropped on the floor. Worst sandwich I've ever tasted and seen in my life.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I've had great sandwiches here before. Always the hook and Ladder. Always delicious. Yesterday, first time I used the drive thru order pick up. Sandwich was still piping hot and staff pleasant. problem was the veggies.  There was old lettuce in it and the tomato and onion had no taste nor scent. The lettuce is what destroyed the sandwich, because even after taking the wilted stuff out the whole sandwich, it was left with that gross aftertaste of old lettuce. That rancidness. The meat was beautiful, full of flavor and aromatic. the cheese I couldn't find. My previous hook and Ladders were made with delicious aromatic bread. The bread yesterday was edible,  but I am not sure it was any better than store bought off the shelf with a fast approaching shelf life.  I know the quality the company prides itself on and for an $8.00 sandwich with no drink and no chips I think it's important to share this.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: I patronize Firehouse because they support first responders. I have terminal multiple myeloma as a result of my time in the fire service.  Unfortunately, I've now have had TWO occasions where I ordered a "Plain Salad" via Grub Hub, but what I got was nothing like the description/photo on the Firehouse menu. None of the items described in menu were there - they literally sent me a bowl of lettuce. The first time I didn't complain because I assumed it was a one time mistake. This time, I was tired and had been at the hospital all day. I just wanted my Firehouse salad and sub.  When I got the salad, I immediately called the store.  The Firehouse employee was familiar with my order & said he actually made the salad himself. He said he saw "Plain Salad" and thought that's what it meant. When I referred him to the menu (you know, the menu where you work...) description of a Plain Salad, he acknowledged that it should have tomatoes, cheese, peppers, cucumbers, etc. He apologized & said he can't fix it because he can't contact the Grub Hub driver. That isn't true! While we were reviewing the order, I noted that the contact for the driver was right there. He didn't want to do that. When I requested a refund of the $6.99, he said talk to Grub Hub.  I told him that is horrible customer service; it would take several days to get my money back. I suggested they re-make the salad & deliver it to me, even if he had to send an employee.  All I got was a sorry, after being repeatedly told there is nothing he can do to fix it. I have enjoyed Firehouse in the past & I appreciate their mission to support first responders. However, clearly this store has a training issue if I have to educate their employee about the menu. The bowl of lettuce was bad, but the response is what made it horrible.

text:
Firehouse knows how to do sandwiches. I love that Firehouse really packs on the meats, cheeses, and other sandwich fillings. 

This is not a hate post about Subway- I love Subway. But at times I feel like they miss their mark on the actual quality of meats and cheeses. 

These sandwiches are moderately priced. It ends up being a lot of food. Got the large Turkey Bacon Ranch combo meal, and it was around $16. It was definitely enough for two people!

text: We went to the Firehouse Subs near Orange Grove and River Rd near Tucson.  I truly wouldn't even give this place a 1 star review.  We ordered two subs that were supposed to be hot.  The only thing they did was today the bread.  Sandwich meat and cheese was cold...directly out of the fridge.  We would have sent it back, but we waited more than 20 minutes for this poor imitation of a sandwich.  We used to eat at Firehouse often when we lived in the DC area.  I'm not sure we will ever eat here again.  Don't waste your time.  Jersey Mike's and Baggins are much better.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
On both of my visits I had a sandwich featuring pastrami. The first time was straight pastrami "fully involved'... more on this in a minute. The second time was the New York Steamer with pastrami, corned beef, provolone, mayo and Italian dressing. Both sandwiches were very much to my liking. My wife tried their meatball sandwich , which their radio advertisements brag about. Her base comment was that it lacked flavor, but we agreed that their bread is among the best of the sandwich shops.

Now back to... pastrami. I recommend getting "fully involved" with your pastrami sandwich here. Which is to say it would be the aforementioned pastrami tucked in that nice, soft, fresh bun underneath a blanket of provolone decorated with mayo, mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion and a pickle spear on the side.  Of course, you can always get your sandwich as stripped down as you want, but if you are going to build a relationship with a sandwich this good, you need to get fully involved.

attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I'm still unsure if I like this place. I want to be impressed with a good sub, but overall-- I'm not. Last time they messed up my order. This time, they just didn't ask anything. They just lack pure service. No question of what sauce. No question on white or wheat.  How about the size. Nope. Nada. Not even  offers for free add ons (that I saw after I ordered on a cardboard menu. Not even a drink offer. I'm like... huh? So just letting you know: (1) check your sandwich before heading out the door to home & (2) Ask for extras -- they are on a cardboard sign on top of the counter-- & (3) don't forget thee drink!  

Oh... if you take it to go, ask for any wet sauces like Italian in a plastic cup to go so your bread doesn't get S-o-g-g-eeeeeee.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
After reading the great reviews, a friend and I decided to finally check out Firehouse Subs. We were both hungry enough to chew on our wallets that day, so we were looking forward to some great sandwiches.

We ordered the smokehouse beef and cheddar and the chicken salad sandwiches to go. After seeing the pictures, and again reading reviews, we were drooling on our way back home (less than a 5 minute drive). We got home, opened up our sandwiches. We each tried both sandwiches. After two bites, we stopped, looked at each other and said "What?" The bread was dry. I don't mean toasted, crunchy. I'm talking multi day old bread that was dryer than the Rillito River bed outside of monsoon season. And this was on both sandwiches. We've both been to Subway and Eegees (okay sandwiches, nothing to write home about), but compared to those places, these Firehouse subs were sandpaper. Okay, maybe it was a bad day. We'll try again.

Fast forward two weeks later, we tried it again. This time, we tried the smoked turkey and the premium roast beef. Same issue. Bread as dry as California's drought. I don't understand. This place has amazing reviews. What am I missing? I talked to a neighbor who swears by the place and he informed me "you're doing it wrong." Apparently, we needed to take our sandwiches around the corner from the pick up and douse them in the selection of hot sauces. Otherwise, as my friend said, "you get a dry, bland, pretty lousy sandwich." So, the claim to fame is the hot sauce selection?

I know others on here have had great experiences with Firehouse Subs. Good for them. And please, don't take my word for it. Try them yourself. I may have the palette of a goat.

text: Firehouse offers a variety of hot subs. Since the last time I visited they now offer a smaller sub, same great taste and perfect portion without over eating. The hook and ladder is my original favorite and a much try if you haven't. This location was very clean and the staff was very friendly. This place reopened when it moved from the 199 W Bloomingdale location.  It seems like the place was reborn, because it has new management.  The service is ultra-fast and super friendly.  Also the traffic is more easy to get in and out and also to find parking compared to the old location.  Also if you want a landmark it is close to the intersection of Bloomingdale and Bell Shoals next to the Walgreen's.

This is one of the best Firehouse Subs in the franchise.  If you want to get in and out without a lot of bother then this place is for you.

text:
I love Firehouse, and this is my favorite of the ones in my area. It's actually closest to my home, but is in a direction I almost never go, so I never frequented this location until very recently. I had my "last straw" experience at the Brandon Blvd. location recently and just do not want to go back there for my Firehouse fix if I can at all help it.

This location is the opposite of everything that is wrong with Brandon Blvd. Service is friendly. Food comes up FAST - 5 minutes as opposed to 20. The store is neat and tidy. They get my order right. They give me time to punch in my phone number for the rewards, instead of racing to try and beat me, forcing me to submit my receipt via the app. Staff members come out to check and see if everything is okay, if you need anything, or see if they can take your tray for you.

Excellent all around.

text:
I'm giving 2 stars because of other reviews saying the food is great. I tried...

Tonight at 826 I placed an order thru a delivery service. Waiting waiting waiting. I know they close at 9. It takes 8 minutes to make a sandwich says another yelper. I'm thinking hoping they can throw it together throw it at the uber. But here is where 1 star comes from. If it's too close to closing, call me and say sorry it's too close to closing which I understand. But no call or email or text. Nothing. I finally checked the app to find my order cancelled. So no food. Really wanted to try the Philly CS being from Philly we are always looking. Someday maybe I'll try you again fs.  Maybe put on the delivery app no orders after 8.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'average'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': None, u'lot': True, u'validated': None}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'True', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I have absolutely no complaints! Firehouse subs is where it's at!!! 

My first introduction to FS was the free medium sub that they give for your birthday. (Keep that in mind when your bday comes along). I got the beef and cheese (Philly cheese steak)sub. It was great! Amazing flavors! 

A couple of weeks later and I've been here 2 days in a row during my lunch break. I only have 30min lunch break so if I didn't bring lunch I would go to tacobell, wawa, even order in for a pasta bowl at dominos. But I was sick of those places. Then I remember firehouse subs was right there! My break is usually at the time it opens (10:30) I come in at 11. With only 30min, I need a quick meal. FS is efficient and quick. They are not sloppy when making my sub. Importantly, QUICK! The wait is no longer than 8min.

 I'm greeted by the employees welcoming me with bright smiles! 
The menu is just mouth watering. From meatball subs to their moist chocolate chip cookies. 

I'm usually just staring at the menu. I have yet to try a sub that disappointed. The average medium sub meal that comes with a drink and your choice of chips, cookie, or Brownie. Is $9.40! Not too bad in my book! 

They have the coke variety machine so mix and match your favorite drinks and flavors with your meal. This is my new favorite lunch spot. Forget the rest and take a chance at FIREHOUSE SUBS!

I'm pretty easy to please and rarely share an opinion unless it was stellar experience or a complete dud. Unfortunately, this take out trip was pretty bad. 

First, they were out of meatballs. Bummer..but okay I'll order something else. I get the hook and ladder with a side of Mac n cheese. The Mac n cheese was terrible--very soupy and no flavor (also no breadcrumbs). The sandwich was pretty good until I pulled out a long piece of hair (not my hair color). Ugh. Staff weren't very friendly or motivated either. I don't think we'll be going back.

text: My business and home are in the immediate area of this restaurant.  I am a regular at other sub shops and had not yet tried Firehouse.  I ordered a NY Steamer to go and asked it to be "fully involved" which means lettuce, tomato, onion, pickle and brown mustard.  It took over 15 minutes before it was handed to me.  Once at home I opened it to find basically a bread sandwich with a small handful of meat - that's all.  It was pitiful.  For almost $7 this was an embarrassment.  I can see no reason to ever return to Firehouse.  Yes, I completed their survey while I ate the sad sandwich.

text:
Considering how busy this location gets at lunchtime, I have to admit they did turn my order around pretty quickly.
I'm a big fan of Firehouse Subs overall and the sub (The Fully Involved Italian) did not disappoint

Having said that, however there are a few things working against this Firehouse:

First, the parking is absurd. It shares with several business and at least one of them has an angry sign telling you not to park there for Firehouse. It's not a big lot either, so it is not easy to find a spot.

Second, the woman who took my order looked at me, and everyone else exactly like she'd be much happier if we all went to some other location for lunch. I don't expect to be greeted like I'm the greatest customer of all time, but looking like you wish I was dead is a big turnoff.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
Hello again yelpers!

I find it hard to believe that I've not reviewed Firehouse subs before. It's absolutely THE best place for hot sub sandwiches. My personal favourite is the Firehouse Meatball because it's got a great flavour and is, without fail, always hot and fresh. I should give it a 5-star rating but I don't pass those out easily unless a place really hits home and does a fantastic job. Another great thing about Firehouse is that it has really fast service 9 times out of 10 (barring any busy hours). I also really like the wide variety of sodas because they have the Coke Freestyle machine which, surprisingly, offers Pepsi products as well.

At any rate, I digress. This place was great, hot, fresh, fast, and fairly convenient and my only wish is that there was one closer to my house but still, taking a trip out that way is worth it. Beats Jimmy Johns, beats Subway by far, and beats Jersey Mike's.

Happy yelping!

text:
I've just checked out the new Firehouse Subs in my neighborhood. I can't decide what my final opinion is. The decor is cute and prices are reasonable as compared to the nearby Jersey Mikes - which is a regular stop for me. 

My husband had a cheddar/brisket sub with bbq sauce. It tasted WONDERFUL but the meat portion was far too small. I had the chicken salad sub which was only okay taste-wise. It was bland, but the meat portion was really generous. I can say that I really did like the texture of the whole-wheat bread. 

I will definitely try Firehouse again and report back. I see on their menu that they specialize in Cherry Limeade like Sonic (love!). Somehow I missed this, but I will be trying that next time fo' sho'.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
I love eating at Firehouse subs; just not this location. There were three gals behind the cashier and not one of them acknowledged me! My wife and I stood there for a few seconds before I went and said, "Hi. Can I place an order?"

Sorry to bring your review score down FH Subs on Thompson, but dude, the service was deplorable. 

I think they were bugged at some lady who was before me, but c'mon dudettes, let it go. Don't take it out on the rest of us.

When my order was finally taken, it was as if I was bothering them just speaking to them. At one point I began to wonder if they were being robbed and the assailant was hiding in the kitchen. They all seemed so morose.

Food was great, though. Better than Subway, waaay better than Jersey Mikes. That's where the one star comes from. Minus four stars for the service. The guy who made my sandwich was nice, soooo, okay, one more star. But that's it.

Well, I did notice they treated the guy after me with the same contempt. So let's go back down to one star. 

The lesson here, dear manager, is don't just hire pretty faces. Let's get someone of depth and character.

My first time eating there was today. Only reason I've never tried it in the past was because I don't eat beef, pork, or chicken and I didn't know they had tuna.

A basic Firehouse sub place.

text: Sweet & hot Captain Sorensen's Datil Pepper Sauce is not 4-alarm hot but still gave a good burn to my Hook & Ladder sub. It complimented the turkey and ham. Hank Williams Jr. Family Tradition hot sauce was another among the many bottled sauces available to add to sandwich meats. I wasn't surprised its decorated inside with a firehouse decor. It fits. My white roll sub was heated warm and moist with hot steam. Not the cheapest sub sandwichs in Berry Hill but Firehouse is the sub spot that is the most meatnificent.

text:
I got the club, and it was really good. The bread is fresh, the meat is tasty and is more like deli meat than Subway type meat. 

If you are looking for a good sub, this is a great spot. 

Also, they have the best hot sauce collection in Nashville. I would say there are 40 different types of hot sauce from all over the country, and at least 10 from Nashville that I have never heard of.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text: Well, I was a little bummed about not being greeted with "Welcome to Firehouse!", but my overall experience was incredibly mediocre. It started in uneventful fashion as the lady at the register misunderstood my name, which resulted in me getting my food a little later because they were calling out the wrong name. The major highlight of my experience was the zoo of people that accumulated as several of the bottlenecks that most chains have worked out were very apparent. Firehouse elected to use only one person at the register (who seemed inseparable with her phone) and also chose a myriad of inexperienced people who blankly stared into the distance, hoping the clock would tick faster. I cannot blame those who do not enjoy sandwich making and I will note that there was a young lady with glasses who took extreme pride in her work and was definitely the difference maker in Firehouse getting double the stars they deserve. I will do some follow up research and give them another shot, but I do not suggest going during lunch time as this location cannot seem to handle the traffic flow better than a class of first graders.

text: This is a great place to have lunch as I work right around the corner. Always greeted with "Welcome to Firehouse". I wanted to commend one of their employees by the name of Lolita. She was very efficient, conscientious, friendly, accommodating and her attention to the littlest details in regard to her work and the customers was simply phenomenal. I love to watch people to see their reactions to certain things and situations and this young lady is on top of it. Firehouse if you get this review give that girl a raise, or some kind of appreciation for a job very well done!

text: I've been here a few times in the last year, or so. Always had great service and great food! On October 29th, 2015 these guys were having some serious power issues during the lunch rush. The cash registers, toasters, steamers, microwaves, drink machines, and the meat coolers were all affected; they were going wonky!  The manager was soooo professional in explaining the situation, and getting everybody taken care of.  They had to make cold sandwiches, but they were still pretty good.  I applaud that manager and his employees for their professionalism and awesome service!  Thank you Firehouse, my all-time favorite Sub restaurant!

text:
Outstanding.

I have written, rewritten, and started over this review a few times. Good grief! All you need to know, the sandwiches here are better than any other quick serve sandwich places in town.

The bread is great, the meats are tasty, the toppings are fresh...but, what really makes the difference is the way they steam the sandwiches. 

The huge selection of hot sauces are fun and the Coke dispenser is fun for all ages.

text:
I am a fan!!! We wanted a good sub so we headed to "Firehouse" Subs on Thompson Lane. We opted to get two separate subs and to try something new..We usually get the Hook and Ladder or the Italian..but tonight we opted for the "New York Steamer Sub" : Corned Beef Brisket, Pastrami, melted Provolone, mustard, mayo and Italian dressing..we had them Fully involved to include Jalapeno, lettuce, tomato and onions...we got the 8" sub for $5.89 
and we also got the " Firehouse Hero Sub" :  Premium Roast Beef, Smoked Turkey Breast, Virginia Honey Ham, melted Provolone, served fully involved with onions, tomato, lettuce, mayo, mustard, italian dressing and Jalapeno peppers..
both were very good...but we both said that the Firehouse Hero was our favorite of the two tonight..
what is your favorites?

text:
Summary:  Of the fast food sub places, this place smokes everyone else.

Sometimes, you just need a good sandwich.

I've made that statement many times over my 47 years of life.  

When I need that sandwich, and I'm not home in Philadelphia to get a cheesesteak, I go to Firehouse Subs.

Why?  These are real sandwiches.  Not that so called "sub" from that the place that puts sub in their name.

My go to is the BBQ Steak and Cheddar which is freaking delicious.  But you can't really go wrong with the other subs which have real quality meats.  The fact they're heated just adds to the quality.

Bottom line:  They're the kings of the fast food sub arena.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
This restaurant has the worst customer service. I have never been to a Firehouse subs. A coworker ordered online and asked me to pick it up. I again had never been there or ordered online. When I walked in the door I saw a sign for "to go" orders so I went there. I waited several minutes and no one greeted me so I waved my hand and said hello to get someones attention. An employee looked up and walked over like I was annoying him. I explained I was there for an online order. He pointed to the bag and rolled his eyes and said its right there. I said is that everything he said yes. I grabbed the bag and began to walk out when another man said "HEY HEY HEY you need to sign the receipt". I said OK and signed it. I walked out and drove back to the office. When I get there my coworker noticed that chips and cookies were not in the bag. I called the store to tell them and they said you were supposed to grab them. I told him I asked if the bag I had was everything and you said yes. He replied yes that was all your sandwiches. You are supposed to pick them out yourself. I said why dint you tell me that when I asked if this was everything? He said you should have known. I said I wouldn't know cause I am a new customer. He repeats to me several times that everyone knows and I should have known. When I get back to the store I ask where do I get the chips and cookies and he point to the rack and says over there. I say OK what do I put them in? He huffs and turns around and grabs a bag and flings it at me. I gather my chips and cookies and leave. Just know, I will never eat at a Firehouse Subs again. I called corporate and they are informing the owner (which by the way manager refused to give me contact information for). The food was even that great. I only ate it because work paid for it and by now I was starving from driving around for over an hour back and forth to their location.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
It's SUB TIME again!

This particular day took me over to the Berry Hill area.  My sub sensors zeroed in on Firehouse Subs as a lunch stop and an opportunity to appraise another sub machine shop!.

Well, from my point of entry, the staff smiled and greeted me, despite their obvious  focus on preparing sandwiches. (Score #1.)  Fun decor with a great soda fountain and reasonable table layout.

They permitted me a minute to focus on the menu  (Score #2) - which offered multiple enticing and commonsense selections and combinations,

They offered good insight and suggestions on the sandwich choices, without over selling (Score #3).  I selected The Engineer Sub (smoked turkey, melted Swiss and sauted mushrooms).    Good choice of fresh breads, too.

I was able to directly observe their preparation and steaming of my sandwich.  Refreshingly, I didn't have the uneasy feeling that I get when watching my Subway sandwich being thrown together...nice!  (Score #4).  I was also pleased at the numerous choices of sauces, ranging from mild to "Shut the Front Door, that's HOT!"  I sampled several and all were very good (Score #5).

Finally, the noise level in the place was not unbearable, making the dine-in experience pleasant.  I did not feel in a hurry to get outta there (Score #6).

Let's face it:  the Firehouse scored all over my card!  I have yet to experience better.
I highly recommend this place!

text: Customer service at this location is AWFUL. I ordered the Spicy Cajun Chicken Sandwich online and wanted it on wheat bread but did not see the option online. I kindly asked if I could have a wheat bun when I got there to pick the food up and was told by the general manager, Coleton that he wouldn't just give me a bun and said I would have to pay for it.
