text:
I came in to grab a sandwich and felt kind of awkward ordering, since the cashier had no desire to serve me, and I was the one providing him with courteousness. I ordered "medium turkey sandwich on wheat, with hot peppers, green peppers, olives, and cucumbers." I got a medium turkey sandwich on wheat with hot peppers, green peppers, olives, cucumbers, and also cheese, onions, mayo, and tomato. I was too hungry to wait for another sandwich, so I ate it anyway and picked off some of the toppings I hadn't ordered, and it was a good sandwich regardless of the fact it wasn't what I wanted. While I was eating, a couple ordered a Club on a Sub and an Italian without mayo. Both of their sandwiches got messed up. I understand if maybe you put one ingredient on accident or leave one out, but to mess up my custom sandwich so much and then also two signature sandwiches is pretty bad.

Moral of the story: come here for a tasty sandwich, but don't expect it to be the sandwich you ordered. I'll come back to Firehouse Subs, but just not this location.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
The base sub of Firehouse is good. There's not too much that sets the sandwiches apart from the other sub shops I've been to (keeping in mind I am a veggie). However, the two things that do pop out and make you wonder why this isn't sub-store-standard is the metric ton of condiments.

If you're a condiment whore, this is the *only* sub shop for you. Especially if you like actually spicy condiments. They have about 80 different sauces up there, if I'm remembering correctly, that you can grab and sprinkle to taste on your sandwich.

They have a mix-your-own-Coke machine, in which you can create many different flavors of beverage off of a touchscreen. When I looked up that machine, it appeared there were only 3 within a 25 mile radius, Eh, I'm a sucker for gadgets that make flavors of yum.

I would probably be a fan if not for an exchange with an employee that left me uncertain whether I had been insulted or if he was not understanding the question or if he was just high and that's why it required 3 people to get the wrong answer.

Eh, it's a sub shop, it's good, it's more expensive than it should be but if you want condiments selection galore, it's where you have to go.

attributes: {'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'HasTV': 'True', 'WiFi': "u'no'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{u'valet': False, u'garage': False, u'street': False, u'lot': True, u'validated': False}"}
text:
Despite the fact this place is a chain, it has won me over rather quickly. My "go-to" is their smoked turkey and provolone hot sub, since it reminds me of a local deli sub I used to eat on the reg in college. Yum!

The medium is more than enough for me. A large sub would just be ridiculous.

My fave kettle chips are offered here too - WIN! The futuristic Coke machine is highly entertaining with over 200 flavored drinks offered. #fancy

This location is crazy busy during lunch rush, so it's ultra convenient to order ahead online and pick up 20ish minutes later. Only once was my order not ready, and when I arrived, the staff was less than friendly. All other encounters with this approach have been flawless.

Parking is very limited out front, but there is additional parking in the gravel lot out back.

attributes: {'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "'quiet'", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}"}
categories: Food, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Beverage Store, Fast Food, Delis
text: Don't get me wrong, I love firehouse subs! However, I was SO disappointed with how they treated me. I went to this one back in April, and when I got my to-go order, I thought it tasted wretched. The tomatoes were mushy and I could tell they'd been previously frozen. The bread wasn't toast enough and therefore was too soggy once I took it home (though I only live three mins away). It was just miserable, and disappointing. I emailed corporate and they apologized and sent me a free sub voucher. When I went back to this firehouse, the supervisor on duty was extremely rude and wouldn't accept my voucher, even implying that I was giving him a forgery. I emailed corporate again, fuming. I will say that the manager sent me quite a lengthy reply telling me the supervisor I had dealt with was new and that all her cashiers were told to accept those vouchers. When. I finally got to use my coupon yesterday (5 months after the original incident, mind you), the food was just alright. I still feel like they didn't toast my bread enough or put enough dressing on my Italian (which, if you go to ANY other firehouse, the Italian is the way to go!). Pick a different firehouse, really, any other one.

It is so smokey in that place I have no idea how the fire alarms don't go off. The staff is ok but the real score is for how terrible the set up inside is. It is the most difficult restaurant to maneuver. 

The first and last time at Firehouse Sub there were two gentlemen in automatic wheel chairs. There was absolutely no room for either of them nor the amount of people in the restaurant. Two gentlemen lifted a couple tables and moved some chairs to help clear a proper walk walk. The set up is so inconvenient from the ordering process to waiting for the food. My one visit was enough. Mediocre sandwich and a major headache after walking out of there.

categories: Food, Restaurants, Sandwiches, Beverage Store, Fast Food, Delis
text:
Not bad, not great.  Definitely not fast.

I thought that this place would be a good, healthy and fast lunch option.  I was wrong on at least one count.

I tried the turkey bacon ranch sub combo.  I asked for it with lettuce and tomato, no mayo or mustard.  Sounds pretty simple, right?  Apparently not, as the cashier did not hand me a cup for my drink until I asked.

After about 15 minutes of waiting, I finally received my sandwich.  It was fine.  Someone forgot to add the ranch dressing, which did make the sandwich more healthful, but also made it rather dry.  There was nothing especially memorable about my sandwich.  The turkey tasted like all fast food lunch meat, the bacon was like fast food bacon (thin, soggy, anemic), and the bread was only okay (I do like that it was toasted, though).  I will say that the pickle on the side was crisp and refreshing.

Add the 15 minutes waiting for the sandwich to the 5 minutes I waited to give my order, and this was hardly a fast meal.  I would have done better to go to the nearby Indian buffet or Panera or Jason's.  Additionally, the staff was rather slow about cleaning tables, so I had to search for a clean place to eat.

I'm not sure if I'd return.

attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches
text: I am sorry to say Do Not Go to Firehouse Subs!!!! This location is about to move to across from Wiregrass on SR 56. The reason is that on Sunday 11/4/12 we purchased a couple of subs. The one that my wife ordered, beef and cheddar brisket gave her food poisoning. And she had to stay home from work a couple of days to get over it. Tonight to give insult to injury I went there with the receipt in hand and asked for our money back! We wanted a return on just the one sandwich that made my wife sick and phone numbers to the general manager of the store and the regional manager for the area. The shift leader said no problem. And went into the back. She called the owner a Sarj Patel, who she stated owns that location. She gave the phone to me for when I asked about this situation he said that he would have to turn this over to the insurance company, that he couldn't give back our money!  The least he could do is return our money!  After all my wife went through, and  the work she missed he could have a least given our money back! Especially since two of his employees told us they would and  he never bothered calling us back like they told us he would!!!

text: Normally this is a quick place to grab a hot bite to eat with lots of choice and a good staff.  I was a bit shocked after ordering a combo meal and a cup for water that I was told that the best they could do for me was a kid's cup.  I was informed that the owner has a strict policy of not allowing people who want water with their meal a full size cup.  So the wife and I are and I made the necessary four trips to refill my miniscule water cup.  I think I might have used more napkins than I was supposed too...nice gooey sandwich.

text:
Finally, a firehouse in the area that is a real firehouse! 

After my dismal experience(s) with the firehouse by USF, firehouse has been off my radar for awhile. But, as I was in the immediate area for an interview, I decided that I can't hold a grudge against the entire franchise since I knew it was good. 

Just stop for a second and realize how awesome a hot, toasty sub is with melted cheese and all the fixins....mmmm. Now, imagine the normal amount of sliced meat and DOUBLE it. That's how much meat was n my Italian when I ordered it, even though they didn't charge me for so much. So delicious! Even though it was the lunch rush, the food came out fairly quickly and I was in and out in 20 minutes. Not too shabby at all. 

My only concern is that I live 20+ minutes away.... :( but seriously, if you love hot sandwiches, this is the place to experience firehouse subs!!!

text: I've never heard of Firehouse Subs but I was visting family in the area and this place is one of my sister-in-law's favorite. Both my wife and I had the Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket and we really enjoyed it. It takes longer to get your meal here than at a place like Subway but I liked my sub better too. There's also more seating here than at a traditional sub shop.

text:
I asked what the number one seller is, so I ordered the #10 Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar.  I switched out the cheddar cheese for provolone.

The sandwich looked nothing like the picture on the menu board.  Pitiful is the only way I can describe it.  

I could have gotten past that if it had flavor.  It was one of the blandest subs I've had in a long time.  I'm honestly not sure how you can mess up a sub.

This was a cheat meal that's leaving me wanting more.  I will have to pick up some macaroons from the mall to make up for this disappointment.

I gave it three stars for cleanliness, food was hot, and the staff was friendly.  I want to give it two but for those reasons, I bumped it up to 3.

text:
Looking at a menu photograph of what my Smokehouse Beef & Cheddar Brisket was supposed to look like you get Strike ONE.We ordered by phone and asked for BBQ Sauce on the side. I didn't receive sauce on the side. Strike TWO, I didn't see or taste that lovely looking cheese, that is so prominent in the photo. Strike THREE. Ordered a combo didn't receive chips, another STRIKE. The soda was great. One more thing. Compared to the on-line image my sandwich was so flat  that it looked like it was run over.
My husband's order was pretty much the same. Since my husband was the only customer at the time, how hard should it be for 2 sandwiches, 2 bags of chips, 1 cup of BBQ sauce and dumping cheese sauce on both sandwiches.

text:
The sub was great, but the cashier might have been new, or just needed more training. We came in with a coupon, and she had to ask someone if we were able to use it. Then she didn't know how to ring it up.

At our usual location, we are always asked about toppings and bread choices. I usually opt for wheat, but totally forgot to ask since it wasn't mentioned. So we ended up both getting white bread, which wasn't bad, I just prefer the wheat. 

The sub was still delicious, just don't expect the cashier to ask, so be prepared to tell them exactly what you want.

text:
My hubby and I had a firehouse sub and another sandwich from a nearby local sandwich shop. We tried both sandwiches side by side. Firehouse sub was the sandwich we liked better. We tried the pork and slaw sandwich on a Hawaiian bun. His first comment was oh that is small because it was the round hamburger bun. But how could a Hawaiian roll not win. No way, it will for sure, our sandwich had smokey pork and the cole slaw on top was perfect. We chose provolone cheese instead of Wisconsin jack. So much flavor and it was a perfect size.
It was his birthday. Make sure to sign up for your birthday sandwich that is free. They send u an email. On the email it shows, u don't have to print out the email. Just let them know either by showing on your phone, or possibly showing them that's it's your actual birthdate. Getting the opportunity to try the sandwich will definitely make me go back there. There r pictures at the restaurant as well, as it stating what each sandwich consists of. We will definitely be back.

text: I was happy with the taste and flavor of my sub, but I definitely wish there was a little bit more meat and it was a little bit more wholesome. What made the sub really good is the fact that they had so many different types of hot sauces. I'm a huge fan of hot sauce and if you are I highly recommend you grab a lot of the ones on the counter.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches
text: I am normally a firehouse LOVER. But the three times I have come to this location on my lunch break have not been very good. There was quite a few ppl in there today so I knew I would wait for my food which is fine but, I was not asked if I wanted my sub "fully involved" as they call it and was not offered a kind of bread either. My sub didn't come like I wanted it because I forgot it came with tomatoes which I usually so no to fully involved. Also when I got my sub the middle was cold which is pretty disappointing as it's supposed to be steamed. The cashier was also taking two orders on the phone which was causing a line at the cash register which wasted even more of my lunch break. Seems like they need to get some quality control going on, probably won't be back.

text:
If I've said it once I've said it a thousand times. If you don't want to serve customers past a certain time then you should close earlier. 
I maybe understand not making a new urn of tea in the last hour of business, but pouring out what's left before you lock the doors with patrons inside is unacceptable. I stopped going to Subway because the last two hours of business you can bet on the same behavior. Firehouse, I guess you're next. You're overpriced anyway.

Two stars because what we did receive was pretty tasty. Just really bummed about the customer service, so probably won't be going back.

categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches
text:
I've only had take-out from here and do not like anything I've tried.  The chili tastes sweet, the Italian Sub tastes sweet, the meatball sub tastes sweet, the Chef Salad came fresh, but with packaged Ken's dressing.  Packaged dressing went out of style ten years ago, especially for the prices here.  No one in my family who had the Steak and Cheese sandwich said they were as gross as the other sandwiches, but didn't rave about them.  The peach flavored Sprite wasn't bad.

Overall, I would suggest another place such as Larry's Deli or Panera Bread unless you're a big soda connoisseur.

text: Way to go Firehouse Subs Wesley Chapel for being a company who hires a special needs person then firing him for not meeting your expectations in two weeks. Fantastic job to management for actually taking the time to talk to your employee to figure out why he is taking longer to pick up on things. Would you really of given him a chance at the job if he told you in the interview he is special needs and has an iq around 73??? Did you notice and think it was a good idea to give him a task like the cash register and when he fails because he doesn't understand how ,you found your way to say hey, you're not picking up the job good enough so let's part ways. He left a job that was mistreating him to come to this place of business in high hopes of not being discriminated. Thanks Chris the GM for taking time out of your busy day to return my message I left for you to discuss this matter. I'll be in touch.

text:
I stopped in for lunch and while it was busy, it seemed like everything was going smoothly. The place is clean with friendly staff members. I stopped in for lunch and the service was efficient. My order was taken promptly with a smile. The countertops and tables were free of debris. As people left, a staff member would quickly clean it. The manager was on the floor as well assisting with customers, which isn't normally seen. 

I ordered the Jamaican Jerk Turkey with everything on it. It was delicious!

text: Friendly service, clean inside and good food. I love their bread - super soft. I also really appreciate having a choice in the size of the sub - small, medium or large. My daughter normally gets the kids meatball sub - yummy but tends to fall apart when that small. I'm an Italian fan - I love their Italian seasoning in it, it's got an ever so sweet taste to it when mixed with the mayo.

categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches
text: I just had a horrible experiencing at this location. We entered prior to the store being closed: prior to 8:30. I should note the website states they close at 9. The person taking our order was cordial; however, upon ordering there was someone in the back who yelled at extremely loud saying they were closed while our order was being taken. If it was indicated to us prior to our order being taken that the location was closed we would've left. While we were waiting for our order the same individual kept yelling profanities and was yelling about the location closing at 8:30. I want to emphasize this was after our order was taken .There was two customers that came in to pick up their orders and the same individual was making comments like: "I hope you're not placing an order because we're f***ing closed". And would say "sad f***ing story if they were placing an order". They were  overall very rude in demeanor and was cussing at the other employees in the store. If the store is closed indicate that prior to the order being taken instead of making your paying customers feel extremely uncomfortable. That is completely unacceptable. Treat your employees better and treat your customers better.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'HasTV': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'classy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': True}", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'WiFi': "u'free'", 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'True', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'Alcohol': "u'none'", 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}

text: Pretending to care.   So I have not been to Firehouse for a long time.  I think since Covid.  Food is still good, but their setup is a joke.  1st they have a mandatory mask rule. They're in Pasco County.  There is no mask order.  But if they're going to have a mask rule and limited seating, why did we have to wipe off our own table?  Bring disinfectant.  Bathroom same stupid setup. If mask order, why not a motion sensor light?  Why not a door that pushes out instead of pulls in?  Why a manual door lock that you have to touch?    Food still good.  Just need to either put all sanitation in place or stop pretending.

categories: Fast Food, Delis, Restaurants, Food, Sandwiches
text:
So, I am a big JJ fan and hubby & son #2 love this place. I was forced to go - full disclosure. 
We ordered our food and my bad, totally, I didn't realize there was cheese on the sub I ordered for two of the kids to split. One of which refuses to eat cheese (DNA test pending). Well, I sucked it up and paid for another sub. I asked for ONLY turkey and lettuce. It came out with turkey, lettuce and cheese. Argh!  My little one was trying to scrape the cheese off of the lunch meat and was miserable. My sub was good. I had the turkey/mushroom. Hubby loved his Italian sub and they do have a fun drink machine there. One detail I noticed that was off-putting was the pickle. Totally gross, neon green cheapie pickle. Not what I would expect from a good sub shop. I mentioned it to hubby and he said he tells them to leave it off the tray. He agrees they are gross. Oh well, I've tried this place 3 times. Not really impressed and will stick to Publix & JJ from now on.

text:
I had my first experience with Firehouse Subs yesterday. I was impressed by the professionalism and friendliness of all of the staff. Every time the door opened,  they all greeted the customer walking in. I also took note of how clean the location was. The dalmation print table tops, red and chrome accents nicely compliment the firemen theme of the restaurant. I also appreciated the local fire department pictures on the wall.  And of course, the option to donate to first responders by rounding to the next dollar with your purchase is really great.

I ordered a medium sized Italian sub, which was a perfect size for me. I was pleased with the amount of meat on the sandwich. It kind of had a sweet flavor which was different. It wasn't the best sandwich I've ever had,  but I'd like to go back to try a different sandwich.  I also like that they have a large variety of sauces available at the counter for customers to add their own flavors to their sandwiches. When i say large, i mean like 20 diiferent sauce bottles.

text:
Came in for my lunch break from trainings in the area. 

I came in and was greeted immediately. I ordered a Philly sub combo which was $10. 

The sandwich was delicious! They have a freestyle Coke machine which always makes me feel like a grandpa because of all the options and technology. I'm 25. But it is awesome to have options! The staff were very friendly and I had a great experience.

The sandwich was small for the price compared to other sub shops. I didn't mine to much since some of the money goes to first responders. 

Overall it was great. A tad expensive for the size sandwich you get but the food and staff were great!

attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I know, I know...it's a franchise.  Personally, I try to avoid Yelping about franchise restaurants...but I just can't help myself.  The sandwiches here are so damn good.

I love this sandwich shop--and that's saying a lot.  I have pretty high standards with sandwiches, and franchise stores usually fill the void of "I'm hungry, need food".  However, with Firehouse, I find myself looking forward to my next sandwich there.  So far, I have been here four times since they opened, and each visit is preceded by a 15-minute gaze at their online menu, trying to decide which one to take home.  There's probably something wrong with me...but I don't care.

Great sandwiches, excellent service, and a quick turnaround during a lunch hour.  Also, if you are a fan of hot sauces, Firehouse offers a terrific selection of bottled hot sauces, each one ranked 1-10 in order of spiciness.  

I also am a fan of their cool Coke machine which has dozens of flavor combinations.

CHOICES!  So many choices at Firehouse.  Eat here.  Judge for yourself.  But from one sandwich guy to another, it's a pretty tasty sandwich.

The ONLY drawback is location.  Leaving the parking lot of Firehouse to get on Dorsett can be a bitch turning left...but it hasn't deterred me yet!

Finally, kudos to their fundraising for First Responders.  Rounding up to the nearest dollar is a brilliant way to shake the cushions for a good cause.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'NoiseLevel': "u'average'", 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': None, 'street': False, 'validated': None, 'lot': True, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsTableService': 'False', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Employees bickered like siblings on this visit. Ugh. 

What I assumed were two female managers had a tiff in the middle of my order. It involved the order right before mine and a big deal was made over whether or not onion should be on someone's sub. 

Typically, service is hugely friendly and efficient, though the above drama (and tone of the woman taking my order while speaking to her co-worker) prompted me to ask her if they were siblings. 

She said they were not...I replied that the way they spoke to one another sounded like they were. 

A short time later, after my food arrived, a customer appeared and though greeted with the usual, "Welcome to Firehouse!" cheer, apparently no one was at the register. This prompted the aforementioned Faux Female Sibling #2 to call out, "Cashier...cashier...cashier..." until Faux Female Sibling #1 appeared. 

I've been here several times over the last few years and have never seen this type of behavior. Totally inappropriate to let whatever is between the two of them seep out not only in front of employees (what a morale booster), but in front of guests. 

The food is always delicious, however, if this pair is on stage next time I come in, I'll  turn right around and head for the St. Charles Firehouse locale or hit the new MOD Pizza down the block. 

As well, the iced tea machine needs a thorough scrub-down and/or that SCARY WATER SPOUT appears to need replacing (see pics). 

Food: always 5 stars
Service today: 0 stars
Uncomfortably charged sibling rivalry-esque atmosphere: unfortunate for everyone

Got here around 5pm. I was greeted by one if the three girls behind the counter. The cashier was Adreian, she had a bad attitude and this is why I'm giving this place a 3 stars. I asked her if the engineer sandwich came w jalapeos, she said a plain no... ok, so I asked if they could add jalapeos to my sub, she said yes and told me the total, she was rushing it... I got my sub with no jalapeos... lol 
The food was very good and fresh.

text:
I've visited firehouse subs today and ordered turkey sandwich. The food was very good however; they use way too much bread (too big) and not enough meat. The ratio is probably 35/65. 

This place kind of reminded me of Penn Station but just a bit better. The prices are definitely comparable to Penn station.

The inside of this place is much bigger than any subway or Penn station that I have visited. One thing I did like was they give children a plastic red fireman's hat which I thought was kind of cool.

A drink, sandwich and a bag of chips would roughly cost about $12 which in my opinion, is high for a sub sandwich. 

The place was very clean and the staff was friendly and fast. I think it is definitely worth checking out but I don't think I will be a regular here.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I enjoy their food here at the Smyrna Firehouse, however, the female manager lost a lot of respect tonight. 
We came in with our young daughter and while waiting in line to order, a guy started going off because he was told he couldn't get a cash refund on his card order for whatever reason.  Well, what really upset everyone in the restaurant is this guy was yelling and cussing very loud.  Well, not only did the employees call police, but this guy did to for whatever reason he thought necessitated the call.  Well, the manager was outside in her suv when the police pulled up and they all went outside to talk.  Well, the manager and officers came in and the guy got a sandwich with a smile...amd was able to eat there in the restaurant.  I'm sorry, but if you disrupt a place of business and are disrespectful, you should not be allowed to stay.  That manager didn't have her employees backs, and didn't care about the other customers allowing him to stay.  We got up and left.  Not cool lady!

For me that is part of what makes this place almost worth the price. For what these guys charge, they can't afford to cut any corners.

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
Ate here today for lunch.  Had the Capt. Sorensen's sandwich.  It was tasty.  I really liked the whole wheat bun they used on it.  Ordering was quick.  Service was quick.  This was the first time I used the Coke machine with all the different varieties of drink.  I got the diet root beer.  It was good.  The only criticism I have is that they may want to consider changing around seating.  It was a little awkward getting to the cashier to order.

I would recommend this place to friends and I expect to return again after another round of foot golf.

text: I came in here for dinner with the family and (bonus!) it was kids night as kids eat free with an adult! I love their subs. They are packed with lots of meat and full of flavor. My usual here is the Club on a Sub. Yum! My husband ordered the Steak and Cheese and it was good but not the best. Kids had meatball sun and turkey and provolone sub. They loved it! I would definitely recommend this great Sub restaurant and it will fill you up and won't leave you hungry!

text:
I have been to several Firehouse locations all around.  The quality of this store is by far the worst.  The sub I got yesterday was inedible.  The bread was under cooked and drenched in mayo.  I tried just eating the meat, but it was more fat than meat.  This location is dragging down the brand.

Also, be prepared to be shamed into donating your change upon check out.

text:
I love Firehouse and this is one of the best locations around.  The meats are always piled high and the wait time is always short.  I usually dine in since you can get in and out quickly for lunch. On nice days they have outside tables as well which are great.  

The restaurant is always very clean, which is amazing considering how busy they are, but they are obviously on top of things!

text: I ordered a sandwich and chips on Uber eats.  I opened my food bag and no chips.  I called Firehouse and explained what happened. The girl says hold on, I don't know what to do. I can hear discussing this with someone else, then she says there is nothing she can do.  I explain that this was unacceptable because I was charged for the chips (almost the cost of a full sized bag of chips) and I want to speak to a manager. She then tells me it is the Uber driver's job to make sure they have everything.  I don't think an Uber driver should be going through your food in the bag. That is not clean. That is the food preparer's job.  I did find on the Uber app that I could request a refund.  Just not a very good experience and the firehouse sub staff didn't do a very good job handling this.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text:
I haven't eaten here in years but it was one of the only places open on Labor Day this year so I stopped in for lunch. The lack of good veggie options ruined this visit for me. 

There is a veggie but it's weird. It is supposed to be three cheeses with sauteed onions and bell peppers. What it was, it looked like, was a bag of onion slices with cheese and a lot of liquid. The guy who took it out of the heater box drained the liquid for a good 5 seconds there was so much. Then just piled all the onions on to the bread. I asked for cucumbers and they came cubed. So what I got was a liquidy onion sandwich with odd chunks of cucumbers. What the heck is this!?

I ate the sandwich. I like onions so it didnt kill me. But I've never eaten that many onions at once and never without something else. It would have been better to just go with cold onions and peppers with veggies like Subway. There was no avocado either. 

I'm not a fan of the veggie and won't go here again for it. 

PS: look, I don't care if someone is cussing. But when you are like 2 feet from customers you ought to avoid "Motherf***er" etc. I'm not sure what the dude was struggling with when making the sandwiches but that was unprofessional. (And it wasnt a one time thing either.) No names because I'm not about getting someone fired or anything. But if management reads this maybe just a word to the team about appropriate language.

In my opinion the Health Department should make a pop in visit because this place has drastically changed and gone down. text:
Firehouse Subs is a unique place in that its founded by Firemen. I don't know what qualifies Firemen to make delicious submarine sandwiches, but they appear to succeed! 

Its not quite as good as Jimmy Johns to me, but its considerably better than Subway. My biggest complaint seems to come from the soft moist buns. They made my sub collapse under its own weight. But its a minor complaint. I would certainly return if I'm in the area. If its this or Subway, Firehouse wins in every category.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '1', 'HasTV': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'RestaurantsAttire': "u'casual'", 'BikeParking': 'False', 'OutdoorSeating': 'True', 'WiFi': "'no'", 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'romantic': False, 'intimate': False, 'classy': False, 'hipster': False, 'divey': False, 'touristy': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'casual': False}", 'Alcohol': "'none'", 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': True, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True'}
text: Not sure why I have not tried this place sooner. ALL of the Firehouse Sub establishments and never tried. I have been missing out on a good sub place. This one is extremely friendly, clean and quite inviting. I went on a Fall day when some people coming from working out, soccer games and shopping were getting their sub fix on. All the subs looked very good and I wanted to try all of them. Was not ready to be too adventurous so got the turkey bacon ranch which is Smoked turkey breast, Smithfield bacon, sharp cheddar cheese topped with peppercorn ranch, mayo, lettuce, tomato, and onion. The Italian Genoa salami, pepperoni, Virginia honey ham, melted provolone, Italian dressing, and seasonings and what they called Fully Involved. This means all in with with mayo, deli mustard, lettuce, tomato, onion, and a kosher dill pickle on the side. They wrap the pickle. Also had the Fire House hero, this had roast beef, smoked turkey breast, Virginia honey ham, and melted provolone and also had it fully Involved.. They were GOOD. So good, I wanted to eat 1/2 of each but they were for friends. I did get to sample theirs. Bread is warm and soft and easily hold-able. Meaning not to mushy and not too hard. Some places are proud of their breads that are really crunchy, but that can hurt the top of your mouth if your not careful. The meats are tasty, not like others that have NO flavor. These sandwiches have substantial taste. Easy parking, fun type of soda machine with different flavors. I drink tea, but it looked interesting. There was someone going around cleaning, so the place was well kept. Food took just a few minutes and I was off. Next time around I am going to try the Engineer. Smoked turkey breast, melted Swiss, and sauted mushrooms also fully involved. Wish I had a picture, we ate them too fast. Go get you some.

name: Firehouse Subs
attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
text:
I thought I'd try this place out since most of the restaurants in Alton would be busy today. Plus I'm always willing to try new sandwiches from wherever. I found this place located in the half-dead strip mall along Homer Adams Parkway in Alton. Very attractive name, so why not? The workers were friendly and very helpful in choosing what was most popular (the Hook and Ladder (#1) was most popular with all locations and the Smokehouse Brisket one (#10) was popular locally. I decided to go with the latter, and I took advantage of the add-ons. They have the same kind of chip selection as Jimmy John's, which wasn't too bad. They have the Coke Remix machine, but for some reason all the drinks came out tasting like crap (Alton flouride, anyone?). Even their exclusive drink, the Cherry Limeade tasted so weak. The sandwich was okay, nothing special. It didn't taste any different than all the other places. I do like the big hot sauce selection they offer for the patrons. As a hot sauce lover, I was digging it. But for some reason, I wasn't that impressed with the food. Especially for how much I paid. Oh well. 

This place gets extra points for paying tribute to a division of America's heroes, the firefighters. You'll get a great fireman theme throughout the place.

text: This place is a double dipper for me. You can get a great sandwich and donate to a non profit at the same time. The have about 10 featured sub sandwiches, and half of them come are offered in a lighter version. I like the Hook and Ladder light (which means mustard instead of mayo) which is tasty and filling. Chips and drinks are additional, bonus they have the fountain soda machine that dispenses every soda that man can imagine. Plus a part of your purchase goes to BackStoppers. It may seem a little heavy on the price, but I feel that it is a good bang for my buck. My sandwich is always over flowing with turkey and veggies. Give it a try...

attributes: {'RestaurantsTakeOut': 'True', 'Ambience': "{'touristy': False, 'hipster': False, 'romantic': False, 'divey': False, 'intimate': False, 'trendy': False, 'upscale': False, 'classy': False, 'casual': False}", 'GoodForKids': 'True', 'GoodForMeal': "{'dessert': False, 'latenight': False, 'lunch': False, 'dinner': False, 'brunch': False, 'breakfast': False}", 'RestaurantsDelivery': 'True', 'BikeParking': 'False', 'BusinessParking': "{'garage': False, 'street': False, 'validated': False, 'lot': False, 'valet': False}", 'DriveThru': 'False', 'RestaurantsGoodForGroups': 'True', 'BusinessAcceptsCreditCards': 'True', 'OutdoorSeating': 'False', 'RestaurantsAttire': "'casual'", 'HasTV': 'True', 'RestaurantsReservations': 'False', 'Caters': 'True', 'RestaurantsPriceRange2': '2'}
text: My husband and I ordered sandwiches for pickup today, which we do a couple times a month. His pastrami was well-made with a good portion of deli meat. My tuna... well at first I thought they entirely forgot the tuna! Pulled it apart to find a tiny spoonful on each half-- absolutely laughable amount of filling! I order this sandwich regularly and it's NEVER like that. He took it back and asked for a remake,l. The assistant managers said "it's our portion size", and never apologized or offered either a refund or a remake. So $7 for a teaspoon of tuna, and apathetic response from the employees... you ARE KIDDING ME!! Customer service standards and quality need an overhaul in this location.
